{"title_page": "Humam Tariq", "text_new": "{{Infobox football biography\n| fullname = Humam Tariq Faraj Naoush\n| image = Pre-Iran Iraq press conference 20190115 05.jpg\n| image_size = \n| caption = Humam Tariq in 2019\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1996|2|10}}\n| birth_place = [[Baghdad]], Iraq\n| height = 1.71 m\n| position = [[Midfielder#Winger|Winger]], [[Attacking midfielder]]\n| currentclub = [[Ismaily SC|Ismaily]]\n| clubnumber = 10\n| youthyears1 = 2006\u20132007\n| youthclubs1 = [[Al-Zawra'a SC|Al Zawraa]]\n| youthyears2 = 2007\u20132010\n| youthclubs2 = [[Al-Quwa Al-Jawiya]]\n| years1 = 2010\u20132014\n| years2 = 2014\u20132016\n| years3 = 2014\u20132015\n| years4 = 2015\u20132016\n| years5 = 2016\u20132018\n| years6 = 2018\u20132019\n| years7 = 2019\u2013\n| clubs1 = [[Al-Quwa Al-Jawiya]]\n| clubs2 = [[Al-Ahli Dubai F.C.|Al-Ahli]]\n| clubs3 = \u2192 [[Al Dhafra SCC|Al Dhafra]] (loan)\n| clubs4 = \u2192 [[Al-Quwa Al-Jawiya]] (loan)\n| clubs5 = [[Al-Quwa Al-Jawiya]]\n| clubs6 = [[Esteghlal F.C.|Esteghlal]]\n| clubs7 =  [[Ismaily SC|Ismaily]]\n| caps1 = 46\n| caps2 = 0\n| caps3 = 20\n| caps4 = 14\n| caps5 = 53\n| caps6 = 14\n| caps7 = 8\n| goals1 = 4\n| goals2 = 0\n| goals3 = 2\n| goals4 = 1\n| goals5 = 6\n| goals6 = 1\n| goals7 = 2\n| nationalyears1 = 2012\u20132013\n| nationalyears2 = 2012\u20132016\n| nationalyears3 = 2012\u2013\n| nationalteam1 = [[Iraq under-20 national football team|Iraq U20]]\n| nationalteam2 = [[Iraq under-23 national football team|Iraq U23]]\n| nationalteam3 = [[Iraq national football team|Iraq]]\n| nationalcaps1 = 13\n| nationalgoals1 = 0\n| nationalcaps2 = 15\n| nationalgoals2 = 5\n| nationalcaps3 = 63\n| nationalgoals3 = 3\n| medaltemplates = {{MedalCountry | {{IRQ}}}}\n{{MedalSport  | Men's [[Association football|football]]}}\n{{MedalCompetition | [[Asian Games]]}}\n{{MedalBronze  | [[2014 Asian Games|2014 Incheon]] | [[Football at the 2014 Asian Games|Team]]}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[AFC U-19 Championship]]}}\n{{Medal|RU|[[2012 AFC U-19 Championship]]|[[Iraq under-20 national football team|Team]]}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[AFC U-22 Championship]]}}\n{{Medal|1st|[[2013 AFC U-22 Championship]]|[[Iraq under-23 national football team|Team]]}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[Gulf Cup of Nations]]}}\n{{Medal|RU|[[2013 Gulf Cup of Nations]]|[[Iraq national football team|Team]]}}\n| ntupdate = 14 November 2019\n| club-update = 27 April 2019\n}}\n\n'''Humam Tariq Faraj Naoush''' ({{lang-ar|\u0647\u0645\u0627\u0645 \u0637\u0627\u0631\u0642 \u0641\u0631\u062c \u0646\u0639\u0648\u0634}}; born 10 February 1996 in [[Baghdad]]) is an [[Iraq]]i professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays for [[Ismaily SC|Ismaily]] and the [[Iraq national football team|Iraq national team]] as [[Midfielder#Winger|winger]]. Tariq has long been considered one of Iraq's most talented footballers. He has been nicknamed the \"Iraqi [[Lionel Messi|Messi]]\". He has represented Iraq at Under-19, Under-20, Under-22, Under-23 and full international level, making his debut for the national team at the age of 16, making him the youngest Iraqi in history to represent the senior team. Humam represented Iraq at the [[Football at the 2016 Summer Olympics|Rio Olympics]] in 2016, playing in all 3 of Iraq's matches against Denmark, Brazil and South Africa. Tariq has also played at the [[2013 FIFA U-20 World Cup|2013 FIFA Under-20 World Cup]], where he was one of Iraq's star players as the underdogs went on a run to the semi-final. At senior level, he has played at the [[2015 AFC Asian Cup]], where they beat the odds and reached the semi-final.\n\n==Club career==\n\n===Early career===\nTariq started playing football at a very young age and often participated in local matches and could regularly be seen playing as a child in public. This eventually caught the attention of Baghdad's biggest clubs. He decided he wanted to pursue a career in football, and from an early age he use to play with older kids at the local shaabiya football pitches near where he grew up before he joined the youth teams in the academy of Iraqi giants [[Al-Zawraa]]. He stayed with Al Zawraa for a few months but later decided that he wanted to play for his boyhood club [[Al-Quwa Al-Jawiya]], who he joined in 2007 at the age of 11.<ref name=ACUP>{{cite web|last1=Mubarak|first1=Hassanin|title=Profile of Iraq\u2019s 23-Man 2015 Asian Cup Squad|url=https://iraqsport.wordpress.com/2014/12/29/profiles-of-iraqs-23-man-2015-asian-cup-squad//}}</ref><ref name=\"Humam Tariq full scout report - Outside of the Boot\">{{cite web|last1=Mubarak|first1=Hassanin|title=Scout Report - Humam Tariq: Al Dhafra SCC and Iraq\u2019s talented youngster|url=http://outsideoftheboot.com/2015/04/29/scout-report-humam-tariq-al-dhafra-scc-and-iraqs-talented-youngster/|website=Outside of the Boot|date=April 29, 2015}}</ref>\n\n===Al-Quwa Al-Jawiya===\n====2009\u201310====\nAt a young age, Tariq started his football career, by joining [[Al-Quwa Al-Jawiya]]'s academy, where he kept getting promoted until, in 2010, he joined the senior team at the age of just 14.<ref name=\"Humam Tariq talks to Al-Bayyina\">{{cite web|title=Humam Tariq, the Olympic team and Al-Quwa Al-Jawiya player to Al-Bayyina|url=http://www.al-bayyna.com/modules.php?name=News&file=article&sid=52083|website=Al-Bayyina|language=Arabic}}</ref> He started playing for the senior team, in the [[2009\u201310 Iraqi Premier League]]. He made his debut with Al-Quwa Al-Jawiya, on 26 May 2010, in a match against [[Salahaddin FC]], where the match ended in a 2\u20130 win for Al-Jawiya.<ref name=\"Humam Tariq Jawiya debut - Goalzz\">{{cite web|title=All Soccer Matches on 26 May 2010|url=http://www.goalzz.com/?region=-1&area=0&dd=26&mm=5&yy=2010|website=Goalzz}}</ref>\n\n====2010\u201311====\nHe appeared every two or three matches as substitute. Al-Quwa Al-Jawiya finished in 2nd place in the groups stage, being qualified to the third place match, where they lost against [[Al-Sinaa SC]] 0\u20131.<ref name=\"Iraq 2010/11\">{{cite web|title=Iraq 2010/11|url=http://www.rsssf.com/tablesi/iraq2011.html|website=RSSSF}}</ref>\n\n====2011\u201312====\nTariq scored his first goal in his third season with [[Al-Quwa Al-Jawiya]], on 27 April 2012, in a match against [[Zakho FC]], three minutes after the beginning of the match, which ended in a 1\u20131 draw.<ref name=\"Soccerway (27 April 2012)\">{{cite web|title=Zakho vs. Al Quwa Al Jawiya - 27 April 2012|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2012/04/27/iraq/iraqi-league/zakho/al-quwa-al-jawiya/1221816/?ICID=PL_MS_25|website=Soccerway|language=Arabic}}</ref> Tariq scored his second goal in a match against [[Al-Sinaa SC|Al-Sinaa]], which ended in a 2\u20131 loss for [[Al-Quwa Al-Jawiya]].<ref name=\"Soccerway (12 July 2012)\">{{cite web|title=Al Sinaa vs. Al Quwa Al Jawiya - 12 July 2012|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2012/07/12/iraq/iraqi-league/al-sinaah/al-quwa-al-jawiya/1221835/|website=Soccerway|language=Arabic}}</ref> Tariq scored his third goal in a match against [[Arbil FC]], which ended in a 1\u20131 draw.<ref name=\"Soccerway (16 August 2012)\">{{cite web|title=Arbil vs. Al Quwa Al Jawiya|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2012/08/16/iraq/iraqi-league/arbil/al-quwa-al-jawiya/1221898/|website=Soccerway|language=Arabic}}</ref> Tariq scored only three goals in this season. [[Al-Quwa Al-Jawiya]] finished in 3rd place in the league table, at 74 points, while [[Arbil FC]] became the champions, at 83 points.<ref name=\"Iraq 2011/12\">{{cite web|title=Iraq 2011/12|url=http://www.rsssf.com/tablesi/iraq2012.html|website=RSSSF}}</ref>\n\n====2012\u201313====\nIn the [[2012\u201313 Iraqi Premier League]], Tariq scored only a single goal against [[Kirkuk FC]].<ref name=\"Soccerway (7 December 2012)\">{{cite web|title=Kirkuk vs. Al Quwa Al Jawiya - 7 December 2012|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2012/12/17/iraq/iraqi-league/kirkuk/al-quwa-al-jawiya/1421756/|website=Soccerway|language=Arabic}}</ref> [[Al-Quwa Al-Jawiya]] finished in 3rd place, at 69 points, while [[Al Shorta SC]] became the champions, at 72 points, with Tariq not finishing the league season.<ref name=\"Iraq 2012/13\">{{cite web|title=Iraq 2012/13|url=http://www.rsssf.com/tablesi/iraq2013.html|website=RSSSF}}</ref> In the [[2012\u201313 UAFA Club Cup]], Tariq scored a goal, in the first leg of the match, against [[Shabab Al-Dhahiriya SC]] from [[State of Palestine|Palestine]], which ended in a 3\u20130 victory for Al-Quwa Al-Jawiya.<ref name=\"2012/13 UAFA Club Cup - Round 1\">{{cite web|title=2012/13 UAFA Club Cup - Round 1|url=http://www.kooora.com/?c=6933&stage=2|website=Kooora|language=Arabic}}</ref> Tariq did not stay with Al-Quwa Al-Jawiya until the end of the tournament. Eventually, Al-Quwa Al-Jawiya was eliminated, in the quarterfinals, by [[Raja Casablanca]] from [[Morocco]].<ref name=\"2012/13 UAFA Club Cup - Quarterfinals\">{{cite web|title=2012/13 UAFA Club Cup - Quarterfinals|url=http://www.kooora.com/?c=6933&stage=3|website=Kooora|language=Arabic}}</ref> In Tariq's last days in the club, on 24 May 2014, he was fined with $10,000 by the club's management because Tariq missed his team's training camp in [[Sulaymaniyah]].<ref name=\"Humam Tariq fined with 10k from al-Jawiya - Hatha al-Youm\">{{cite news|title=Al-Quwa Al-Jawiya fine their player, Humam Tariq, with 10 million dinars|url=http://hathalyoum.net/sit/358983.htm|agency=Hatha al-Youm|date=May 25, 2014|language=Arabic|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150702102454/http://hathalyoum.net/sit/358983.htm|archivedate=July 2, 2015}}</ref>\n\n===Al Ahli===\nOn 29 January 2013, at the age of 16, Tariq signed a contract worth $9,582 per week with [[Al-Ahli Dubai F.C.|Al-Ahli]], who bought him for \u20ac600,000, to play for them for 5 years, with bonuses and good efforts income added. Al Ahli also provided an apartment for Tariq in [[Dubai]], a personal car and free transportation between Baghdad and Dubai for Tariq and his family.<ref name=\"Humam Tariq's contract\">{{cite web|title=Humam Tariq and Al-Ahli|url=http://forum.kooora.com/?t=32106250|website=Kooora|language=Arabic}}</ref> Although Tariq signed the contract in January 2013, he had to wait over a year to join the squad, because he wasn't going to be 18 years old until 10 February 2014, at which point he wasn't allowed to join up with his new club.<ref name=\"Humam Tariq's contract\" /> He was loaned to [[Al Dhafra SCC|Al Dhafra]] after playing only two friendly matches with Al Ahli.<ref name=\"Humam Tariq Dhafra loan\">{{cite news|title=Al Dhafra from UAE gets the services of Humam Tariq in a loan contract|url=http://www.alsumaria.tv/news/112436/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B8%D9%81%D8%B1%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A5%D9%85%D8%A7%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%AA%D9%8A-%D9%8A%D8%AD%D8%B5%D9%84-%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%89-%D8%AE%D8%AF%D9%85%D8%A7%D8%AA-%D9%87%D9%85%D8%A7%D9%85-%D8%B7%D8%A7%D8%B1/ar|agency=Al Sumaria|language=Arabic}}</ref>\n\n====Failed Transfers to Turkey====\nOn 14 June 2015, Al-Ahli received an official offer from an unnamed Turkish team to either buy or loan Tariq.<ref name=\"Turkish offer to sign the Iraqi Humam Tariq - :24\">{{cite news|title=Turkish offer to sign the Iraqi Humam Tariq|url=http://24.ae/article/165720/%D8%B9%D8%B1%D8%B6-%D8%AA%D8%B1%D9%83%D9%8A-%D9%84%D9%84%D8%AA%D8%B9%D8%A7%D9%82%D8%AF-%D9%85%D8%B9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B9%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%82%D9%8A-%D9%87%D9%85%D8%A7%D9%85-%D8%B7%D8%A7%D8%B1%D9%82.aspx|agency=:24|date=June 14, 2015|language=Arabic}}</ref> After five days, Tariq's agent, Najm Mohammed, stated that the negotiations between the unnamed Turkish side and Al-Ahli broke down after Al-Ahli demanded $400,000 for Humam but the team wasn't willing to pay more than $200,000.<ref name=\"Humam Tariq broke Turkish negotiations - Hamrin News\">{{cite news|title=Two Saudi clubs sign two Iraqi players and the negotiations of signing Humam Tariq for a Turkish team broke|url=http://hamrinnews.net/sport/3519.html|agency=Hamrin News|date=June 19, 2015|language=Arabic}}</ref> Al-Ahli received an offer from another team in the [[S\u00fcper Lig]] and it was [[Bursaspor]]. Al-Ahli initially accepted the offer.<ref name=\"Bursaspor offer - Al Bayan\">{{cite news|last1=Zahdi|first1=Ehab|title=Offer from Buraspor to buy Humam Tariq|url=http://www.albayan.ae/sports/emirates/2015-06-22-1.2400798|agency=Al Bayan|language=Arabic|date=June 22, 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"Humam Tariq Bursaspor - Bursa Hakimiyet\">{{cite news|title=Humam Tariq beklemede|url=http://www.bursahakimiyet.com.tr/haber/bursaspor/humam-tariq-beklemede-85841.html|agency=Bursa Hakimiyet|date=June 19, 2015|language=Turkish|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150627201636/http://www.bursahakimiyet.com.tr/haber/bursaspor/humam-tariq-beklemede-85841.html|archivedate=June 27, 2015}}</ref> But, again, on 30 June, Tariq's agent announced that the deal failed, in the last moments, because Bursaspor offered a low amount of money and the offer was rejected by Al-Ahli.<ref name=\"Bursaspor breaks down with Humam Tariq - Al-Mada Newspaper\">{{cite news|title=Deal of Humam Tariq transferring to Bursaspor breaks down|url=http://www.almadapaper.net/ar/news/490815/%D9%81%D8%B4%D9%84-%D8%B5%D9%81%D9%82%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%86%D8%AA%D9%82%D8%A7%D9%84-%D9%87%D9%85%D8%A7%D9%85--%D8%A5%D9%84%D9%89-%D8%A8%D9%88%D8%B1%D8%B5%D8%A7-%D8%B3%D8%A8%D9%88%D8%B1|agency=Al-Mada Newspaper|issue=3399|date=June 30, 2015|language=Arabic}}</ref> In July 2015, two teams from the [[Iraqi Premier League]] showed interest in signing Tariq, his last team, [[Al-Quwa Al-Jawiya]],<ref name=\"Tariq close to Al-Quwa Al-Jawiya - Al-Bayan Al-Riyadhi\">{{cite news|last1=Zahdi|first1=Ehab|title=Humam Tariq gets close to Al-Quwa Al-Jawiya|url=http://www.albayan.ae/sports/all-games/2015-07-07-1.2410877|agency=Al-Bayan Al-Riyadhi|date=July 7, 2015|language=Arabic}}</ref> and [[Al Shorta SC|Al Shorta]].<ref name=\"Hakeem Shakir calls Tariq to join Al Shorta - Iraq99\">{{cite news|last1=Jaloob|first1=Dhurgham Ismael|title=Hakeem Shakir calls Younis Mahmoud and Humam Tariq to join Al Shorta|url=http://www.iraq99.com/534439/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%A7%D8%B6%D8%A9-%D8%AD%D9%83%D9%8A%D9%85-%D8%B4%D8%A7%D9%83%D8%B1-%D9%8A%D8%AF%D8%B9%D9%88-%D9%8A%D9%88%D9%86%D8%B3-%D9%85%D8%AD%D9%85%D9%88%D8%AF-%D9%88%D9%87%D9%85%D8%A7.html|agency=Iraq99|date=July 15, 2015|language=Arabic|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924040339/http://www.iraq99.com/534439/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%A7%D8%B6%D8%A9-%D8%AD%D9%83%D9%8A%D9%85-%D8%B4%D8%A7%D9%83%D8%B1-%D9%8A%D8%AF%D8%B9%D9%88-%D9%8A%D9%88%D9%86%D8%B3-%D9%85%D8%AD%D9%85%D9%88%D8%AF-%D9%88%D9%87%D9%85%D8%A7.html|archivedate=September 24, 2015}}</ref>\n\n====Al Dhafra (loan)====\nOn 1 October 2014, Tariq was loaned to [[Al Dhafra FC|Al Dhafra]], without playing a single official game for [[Al-Ahli Dubai F.C.|Al-Ahli]]. His loan contract stated that Tariq will play for Al Dhafra for the [[2014\u201315 UAE Pro-League|2014\u201315]] season, which can be extended.<ref name=\"Humam Tariq Dhafra loan\" />\n\nTariq played his debut match, in the 2014\u201315 season, on 5 October, against [[Emirates Club]]. He played for 77 minutes and got subbed off for [[Ali Al-Hammadi]].<ref name=\"Al Dhafra vs. Emirates - 5 October 2014\">{{cite web|title=Al Dhafra vs. Emirates - 5 October 2014|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2014/10/05/united-arab-emirates/premier-league/al-dhafra/emirates-club-ras-al-khaimah/1714751/|website=Soccerway|language=Arabic}}</ref> Tariq scored his first goal with [[Al Dhafra SCC|Al Dhafra]] on 29 November, against [[Al-Ittihad Kalba SC|Al-Ittihad Kalba]], in the 19th minute,<ref name=\"Diop and Humam lead Al-Dhafra to the first win in the league over Ittihad Kalba\">{{cite news|title=Diop and Humam lead Al-Dhafra to the first win in the league over Ittihad Kalba|url=http://www.emaratalyoum.com/sports/local/2014-11-30-1.733251|agency=Emirates Today|date=29 November 2014|language=Arabic}}</ref> rocketing the ball from outside the penalty box into the right corner of the goal, from a pass by [[Makhete Diop]].<ref name=\"Debut Goal - Dhafra - Youtube\">{{cite web|title=Goal of Humam Tariq against Ittihad Kalba in the UAE Pro League (29/11/2014)|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-f4WWpN3a-s|website=Youtube|language=Arabic}}</ref> His second goal with Al Dhafra was one of the fastest goals in the [[UAE Arabian Gulf League]], on 10 May 2015, in the 4th minute, against [[Al-Shabab (UAE)|Al-Shabab]].<ref name=\"Arabian Gulf League: Al-Shabab trips over Al-Dhafra and loses 2nd place\">{{cite news|title=Arabian Gulf League: Al-Shabab trips over Al-Dhafra and loses 2nd place|url=http://24.ae/article/157680/%D8%AF%D9%88%D8%B1%D9%8A-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AE%D9%84%D9%8A%D8%AC-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B9%D8%B1%D8%A8%D9%8A-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B4%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%A8-%D9%8A%D8%AA%D8%B9%D8%AB%D8%B1-%D8%A3%D9%85%D8%A7%D9%85-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B8%D9%81%D8%B1%D8%A9-%D9%88%D9%8A%D9%81%D9%82%D8%AF-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%88%D8%B5%D8%A7%D9%81%D8%A9.aspx|agency=:24|date=10 May 2015|language=Arabic}}</ref> Tariq finished the league season with Al Dhafra in 12th place at 26 points, only one place away from relegation.<ref>{{Cite web|url = https://int.soccerway.com/national/united-arab-emirates/premier-league/20142015/regular-season/r26021/|title = 2014-15 UAE Arabian Gulf League|date = |accessdate = |website = Soccerway|publisher = |last = |first = |language = Arabic}}</ref>\n\nIn the [[UAE President's Cup]], Tariq played Al Dhafra's match in the Round of 16, on 15 May 2015. He had an assist in a goal for [[Bilal Najjarine]] from a free kick, crossed by Tariq to Bilal's head. Tariq was injured, in that match, with a muscle strain.<ref>{{Cite news|url = http://www.albayan.ae/sports/emirates/2015-05-23-1.2380050|title = Humam Tariq: I'm 90% fit|last = |first = |date = |work = |access-date = |via = |publisher = Al-Bayan Al-Riyadhi|language = Arabic}}</ref> Al Dhafra won 7\u20136 on penalties after a 1\u20131 draw.<ref>{{Cite web|url = https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2015/05/15/united-arab-emirates/presidents-cup/ahli-al-fujirah/al-dhafra/1699521/|title = Al-Fujerah vs. Al-Dhafra - 15 May 2015|date = |accessdate = |website = Soccerway|publisher = |last = |first = |language = Arabic}}</ref> In the quarterfinals, Tariq started the match against [[Ajman Club|Ajman]], where he had another assist in the first goal, by crossing the ball to [[Makhete Diop]]'s head and into the goal, in the 62nd minute.<ref>{{Cite web|url = https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KkrjxXFjR0s|title = Al Dhafra 2-0 Ajman - UAE President's Cup 2014-2015|date = |accessdate = |website = Youtube|publisher = |last = |first = }}</ref> The match ended in a 2\u20130 win for Al Dhafra. In the semifinals, against [[Al-Ahli Dubai F.C.|Al-Ahli]], Tariq wasn't allowed to play because of the friendly agreement between Al Dhafra and Al Ahli that doesn't allow him to play in a match against Al Ahli.<ref>{{Cite news|url = http://www.iraq99.com/237738/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%A7%D8%B6%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%8A%D9%88%D9%85-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B8%D9%81%D8%B1%D8%A9-%D9%8A%D8%B3%D8%B9%D9%89-%D9%84%D9%83%D8%AA%D8%A7%D8%A8%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AA%D8%A7.html|archive-url = https://archive.is/20151021035637/http://www.iraq99.com/237738/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%A7%D8%B6%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%8A%D9%88%D9%85-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B8%D9%81%D8%B1%D8%A9-%D9%8A%D8%B3%D8%B9%D9%89-%D9%84%D9%83%D8%AA%D8%A7%D8%A8%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AA%D8%A7.html|url-status = dead|archive-date = 21 October 2015|title = Al Dhafra looks forward for writing history... and Al Ahli's eyes on the most precious of cups|last = Jaloob|first = Dhirgam Ismael|date = 30 May 2015|language = Arabic}}</ref> Al Dhafra lost the match 0\u20132.<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://www.emaratalyoum.com/sports/local/2015-05-31-1.789131|title = Al-Ahli defeats Al-Dhafra and qualifies to the final|date = 31 May 2015|accessdate = |website = Emirates Today|publisher = |last = Mustafa|first = Sayyid|language = Arabic}}</ref> Tariq finished his season with his team that he was loaned to with a total of 22 appearances, that included 2 goals and 2 assists.<ref name=\"Humam Tariq - Soccerway\">{{cite web|title=Humam Tariq|url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/humam-tarek--/241430/|website=Soccerway|language=Arabic}}</ref> After the end of the season, Al Dhafra didn't show interest in extending Tariq's contract. Therefore, he returned to Al-Ahli.<ref name=\"Humam Tariq out of Al Dhafra\">{{cite news|title=Asia Angle: From Didier Drogba to Robinho - Players who could be moving in and out of Asia|url=http://sport360.com/article/football/38517/asia-angle-didier-drogba-robinho-players-who-could-be-moving-and-out-asia|agency=Sport 360|date=June 23, 2015}}</ref>\n\n====Al-Quwa Al-Jawiya====\nIn 2015, Tariq returned to Jawiya in a loan deal for the season and played in the league and [[Iraq FA Cup|FA Cup]], where he scored in the [[2016 Iraq FA Cup Final|FA Cup final]] which Jawiya won by two goals to win the cup. After a successful loan spell at Jawiya, Humam returned permanently in 2016 where he has consistently impressed for the Iraqi outfit, regaining him a call up to the national team and new rumours of a move abroad.\n\n===Esteghlal===\n[[File:Humam Tariq.jpg|thumb|Tariq playing for Esteghlal in 2017]] \nAfter failing to join [[Elaz\u0131\u011fspor]] in the [[TFF First League]],<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.elazighakimiyethaber.com/humam-tariq-olmadi/31092|title=Humam Tariq olmad\u0131!|language=tr-TR}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://gunisigigazetesi.net/humam-tariq-konusunda-olumsuz-rapor-vermedim/57604|title=Humam Tar\u0131q konusunda olumsuz rapor vermedim|last=Gazetesi|first=G\u00fcn\u0131\u015f\u0131\u011f\u0131|language=tr-TR}}</ref> Tariq officially joined [[Esteghlal F.C.|Esteghlal]] on a three-year contract on 1 August 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fcesteghlal.ir/news/item/2759/\u0628\u0627+\u0627\u0639\u0644\u0627\u0645+\u0641\u062a\u062d\u06cc\u061b+\u0637\u0627\u0631\u0642+\u0647\u0645\u0627\u0645+\u0627\u0633\u062a\u0642\u0644\u0627\u0644\u06cc+\u0634\u062f|title=\u0628\u0627\u0632\u06cc\u06a9\u0646 \u062a\u06cc\u0645 \u0645\u0644\u06cc \u0639\u0631\u0627\u0642 \u0628\u0627 \u0627\u0645\u0636\u0627\u06cc \u0642\u0631\u0627\u0631\u062f\u0627\u062f\u06cc 3 \u0633\u0627\u0644\u0647 \u0628\u0647 \u0627\u0633\u062a\u0642\u0644\u0627\u0644 \u067e\u06cc\u0648\u0633\u062a.|trans-title=Iraq international joined Esteghlal on a three-year contract|publisher=Esteghlal|language=Persian|date=1 August 2018|accessdate=1 August 2018}}</ref> He was assigned the number 17 shirt in Esteghlal.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://90tv.ir/news/\u0634\u0645\u0627\u0631\u0647-\u067e\u06cc\u0631\u0627\u0647\u0646-\u0628\u0627\u0632\u06cc\u06a9\u0646\u0627\u0646-\u0627\u0633\u062a\u0642\u0644\u0627\u0644-\u062f\u0631-\u0644\u06cc\u06af-\u0642\u0647\u0631\u0645\u0627\u0646\u0627\u0646-\u0622\u0633\u06cc\u0627-\u0645\u0634\u062e\u0635-\u0634\u062f|title=\u0634\u0645\u0627\u0631\u0647 \u067e\u06cc\u0631\u0627\u0647\u0646 \u0628\u0627\u0632\u06cc\u06a9\u0646\u0627\u0646 \u0627\u0633\u062a\u0642\u0644\u0627\u0644 \u062f\u0631 \u0644\u06cc\u06af \u0642\u0647\u0631\u0645\u0627\u0646\u0627\u0646 \u0622\u0633\u06cc\u0627 \u0645\u0634\u062e\u0635 \u0634\u062f|trans-title=The jersey numbers of Esteghlal players for AFC Champions league were revealed.|publisher=[[Navad]]|language=Persian|date=14 August 2018|accessdate=17 December 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn 16 August 2018, Tariq made his competitive debut for Esteghlal as a second-half substitute in a 1\u20130 away defeat against [[F.C. Pars Jonoubi Jam|Pars Jonoubi Jam]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tarafdari.com/node/1057600?page=3|title=\u067e\u0627\u0631\u0633 \u062c\u0646\u0648\u0628\u06cc \u062c\u0645 1-0 \u0627\u0633\u062a\u0642\u0644\u0627\u0644 \u062a\u0647\u0631\u0627\u0646|trans-title=Pars Jonoubi Jam 1-0 Esteghlal|publisher=Tarafdari|language=Persian|date=16 August 2018|accessdate=17 December 2018}}</ref> On 29 November 2018, he scored his first goal for the club in a 3\u20130 victory over [[Sanat Naft Abadan F.C.|Sanat Naft Abadan]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tarafdari.com/node/1160086|title=\u0627\u0633\u062a\u0642\u0644\u0627\u0644 3-0 \u0635\u0646\u0639\u062a \u0646\u0641\u062a \u0622\u0628\u0627\u062f\u0627\u0646\u061b \u062e\u06cc\u0632 \u0622\u0628\u06cc \u0647\u0627 \u0628\u0647 \u0633\u0645\u062a \u0628\u0627\u0644\u0627\u06cc \u062c\u062f\u0648\u0644 \u0628\u0627 \u062f\u0631\u062e\u0634\u0634 \u0641\u0631\u0634\u06cc\u062f \u0627\u0633\u0645\u0627\u0639\u06cc\u0644\u06cc|trans-title= Esteghlal 3-0 Sanat Naft Abadan|publisher=Tarafdari|language=Persian|date=29 November 2018|accessdate=17 December 2018}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nOn 30 December 2012, Tariq made his international debut for the [[Iraq national football team|Iraqi senior team]], against [[Tunisia national football team|Tunisia]], in a friendly match that ended in a 2\u20131 loss for Iraq.<ref name=\"Iraq vs. Tunisia - 30 December 2012\">{{cite web|title=Iraq vs. Tunisia - 30 December 2012|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2012/12/30/world/friendlies/iraq/tunisia/1415985/|website=Soccerway|language=Arabic}}</ref> Tariq, on that day, became the youngest player in the history of the [[Iraq national football team]] to wear the Iraqi shirt at the age of 16.<ref name=\"ACUP\"/>\n\n===2013 Gulf Cup===\nThe [[2013 Gulf Cup of Nations|2013 Gulf Cup]] was the tournament that led Tariq to success and made him shine. He started the first match of [[Iraq national football team|Iraq]], as a [[Left winger (football)|left winger]], against [[Saudi Arabia national football team|Saudi Arabia]], that ended in a 2\u20130 win for Iraq.<ref name=\"Iraq 2-0 Saudi Arabia - 6 January 2013\">{{cite web|title=Iraq 2-0 Saudi Arabia|url=http://www.gulfcup.com/soccer/matches/matcha.php?match_id=340&period=21|website=Gulf Cup|language=Arabic}}</ref><ref name=\"Iraq vs. Saudi Arabia - 6 January 2013\">{{cite web|title=Iraq vs. Saudi Arabia - 6 January 2013|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2013/01/06/asia/gulf-cup/saudi-arabia/iraq/1404981/|website=Soccerway|language=Arabic}}</ref> Tariq went on to start the second match of Iraq, against [[Kuwait national football team|Kuwait]], that ended in a 1\u20130 win for Iraq.<ref name=\"Kuwait 0-1 Iraq - 9 January 2013\">{{cite web|title=Kuwait 0-1 Iraq|url=http://www.gulfcup.com/soccer/matches/matcha.php?match_id=343&period=21|website=Gulf Cup|language=Arabic}}</ref><ref name=\"Iraq vs. Kuwait - 9 January 2013\">{{cite web|title=Iraq vs. Kuwait - 9 January 2013|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2013/01/09/asia/gulf-cup/iraq/kuwait/1404982/?ICID=PL_MS_05|website=Soccerway|language=Arabic}}</ref> In Iraq's third match, against [[Yemen national football team|Yemen]], Tariq stayed on the bench, being replaced with [[Nabeel Sabah]] as the left winger. The match ended in a 2\u20130 win for Iraq.<ref name=\"Yemen 0-2 Iraq - 12 January 2013\">{{cite web|title=Yemen 0-2 Iraq|url=http://www.gulfcup.com/soccer/matches/matcha.php?match_id=348&period=21|website=Gulf Cup|language=Arabic}}</ref><ref name=\"Iraq vs. Yemen - 12 January 2013\">{{cite web|title=Iraq vs. Yemen - 12 January 2013|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2013/01/12/asia/gulf-cup/iraq/yemen/1404985/?ICID=PL_MS_09|website=Soccerway|language=Arabic}}</ref> Tariq started the semi-final match against [[Bahrain national football team|Bahrain]]. The match went to extra time and then penalties, after a 1\u20131 draw. Iraq won 4\u20132 on penalties.<ref name=\"Bahrain 3-5 Iraq - 15 January 2013\">{{cite web|title=Bahrain 3-5 Iraq|url=http://www.gulfcup.com/soccer/matches/matcha.php?match_id=350&period=21|website=Gulf Cup|language=Arabic}}</ref><ref name=\"Iraq vs. Bahrain - 15 January 2013\">{{cite web|title=Iraq vs. Bahrain - 15 January 2013|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2013/01/15/asia/gulf-cup/iraq/bahrain/1418681/?ICID=PL_MS_02|website=Soccerway|language=Arabic}}</ref> In the final, Tariq started as a [[left midfielder]], against [[UAE national football team|UAE]], in the match that ended in a 2\u20131 loss for Iraq. Therefore, Iraq became the runners-up of the 2013 edition.<ref name=\"Iraq 1-2 UAE - 18 January 2013\">{{cite web|title=Iraq 1-2 UAE|url=http://www.gulfcup.com/soccer/matches/matcha.php?match_id=352&period=21|website=Gulf Cup|language=Arabic|access-date=2015-05-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141129112506/http://www.gulfcup.com/soccer/matches/matcha.php?match_id=352&period=21|archive-date=2014-11-29|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name=\"Iraq vs. UAE - 18 January 2013\">{{cite web|title=Iraq vs. UAE - 18 January 2013|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2013/01/18/asia/gulf-cup/united-arab-emirates/iraq/1418682/?ICID=PL_MS_01|website=Soccerway|language=Arabic}}</ref>\n\n===2015 AFC Asian Cup qualification===\nTariq contributed in 4 matches out of the total 6 for [[Iraq national football team|Iraq]] in the [[2015 AFC Asian Cup qualification]]. The matches' results were a 1\u20130 win against [[Indonesia national football team|Indonesia]] on 6 February 2013,<ref name=\"Iraq 1-0 Indonesia - 6 February 2013\">{{cite web|title=Iraq 1-0 Indonesia - 6 February 2013|url=http://www.the-afc.com/afcasfeeds?fixtureid=6942&stageid=273&tMode=H&view=ajax&show=matchsummary|website=AFC ASIAN CUP AUSTRALIA 2015}}</ref> 0\u20131 loss against [[China national football team|China]] on 22 March,<ref name=\"China 1-0 Iraq - 22 March 2013\">{{cite web|title=China 1-0 Iraq - 22 March 2013|url=http://www.the-afc.com/afcasfeeds?fixtureid=6945&stageid=273&tMode=H&view=ajax&show=matchsummary|website=AFC ASIAN CUP AUSTRALIA 2015}}</ref> 1\u20132 loss against [[Saudi Arabia national football team|Saudi Arabia]] on 15 November,<ref name=\"Saudi Arabia 2-1 Iraq - 15 November 2013\">{{cite web|title=Saudi Arabia 2-1 Iraq - 15 November 2013|url=http://www.the-afc.com/afcasfeeds?fixtureid=6949&stageid=273&tMode=H&view=ajax&show=matchsummary|website=AFC ASIAN CUP AUSTRALIA 2015}}</ref> and a 2\u20130 win against Indonesia on 19 November.<ref name=\"Indonesia 0-2 Iraq - 19 November 2013\">{{cite web|title=Indonesia 0-2 Iraq - 19 November 2013|url=http://www.the-afc.com/afcasfeeds?fixtureid=6950&stageid=273&tMode=H&view=ajax&show=matchsummary|website=AFC ASIAN CUP AUSTRALIA 2015}}</ref> Eventually, Iraq qualified to the [[2015 AFC Asian Cup]] by winning 3\u20131 against China, where Tariq wasn't included.<ref name=\"Iraq 3-1 China - 5 March 2014\">{{cite web|title=Iraq 3-1 China - 5 March 2014|url=http://www.the-afc.com/afcasfeeds?fixtureid=6952&stageid=273&tMode=H&view=ajax&show=matchsummary|website=AFC ASIAN CUP AUSTRALIA 2015}}</ref>\n\n===2014 FIFA World Cup qualification===\nTariq played only two matches of the [[2014 FIFA World Cup qualification (AFC)]], in the [[2014 FIFA World Cup qualification \u2013 AFC Fourth Round|fourth round]]. The first, against [[Oman national football team|Oman]], on 4 June 2013, where he got subbed off in the 55th minute after failing to clear the ball. The match ended in a 1\u20130 win for Oman.<ref name=\"Oman 1-0 Iraq - 4 June 2013\">{{cite web|title=Oman 1-0 Iraq - 4 June 2013|url=https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/matches/round=257777/match=300191860/report.html|website=FIFA}}</ref> On the other match, against [[Australia national soccer team|Australia]], on 18 June, Tariq got subbed off again in the 75th minute. The match was also lost by [[Iraq national football team|Iraq]] and won 1\u20130 by Australia.<ref name=\"Australia 1-0 Iraq - 18 June 2013\">{{cite web|title=Australia 1-0 Iraq - 18 June 2013|url=https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/matches/round=257777/match=300191857/report.html|website=FIFA}}</ref> After this match, Iraq was at the bottom of Group B, having 5 points from 8 matches played, resulting in not qualifying to the World Cup.<ref name=\"2014 World Cup Qualification for Asia - Final Stages\">{{cite web|title=2014 World Cup Qualification for Asia - Final Stages|url=http://www.kooora.com/?c=5985&stage=4|website=Kooora|language=Arabic}}</ref>\n\n===2013 FIFA U20 World Cup===\nTariq was included in the [[2013 FIFA U-20 World Cup]] [[2013 FIFA U-20 World Cup squads|squad]]. He started in all of [[Iraq national football team|Iraq]]'s matches. In the first match of [[Iraq under-20 national football team|Iraq under-20 team]], they came up against [[England under-19 national football team|England]], where it ended in a hard 2\u20132 draw for Iraq.<ref name=\"England 2-2 Iraq - 23 June 2013\">{{cite web|title=England 2-2 Iraq - 23 June 2013|url=https://www.fifa.com/u20worldcup/matches/round=259235/match=300232818/report.html|website=FIFA}}</ref> In the second match, they were against [[Egypt national under-20 football team|Egypt]], where Tariq had his first yellow card with an international team in the 57th minute and it ended in a 2\u20131 win for Iraq.<ref name=\"Iraq 2-1 Egypt - 26 June 2013\">{{cite web|title=Iraq 2-1 Egypt - 26 June 2013|url=https://www.fifa.com/u20worldcup/matches/round=259235/match=300232825/report.html|website=FIFA}}</ref> In the third match, against [[Chile national under-20 football team|Chile]], it ended also in a 2\u20131 win for Iraq.<ref name=\"Iraq 2-1 Chile - 29 June 2013\">{{cite web|title=Iraq 2-1 Chile - 29 June 2013|url=https://www.fifa.com/u20worldcup/matches/round=259235/match=300232822/report.html|website=FIFA}}</ref> In the Round of 16, Iraq won over [[Paraguay national under-20 football team|Paraguay]], after the match went to extra time, 1\u20130.<ref name=\"Iraq 1-0 Paraguay - 3 July 2013\">{{cite web|title=Iraq 1-0 Paraguay - 3 July 2013|url=https://www.fifa.com/u20worldcup/matches/round=259233/match=300232827/report.html|website=FIFA}}</ref> In the quarterfinal, Iraq won over [[Korea Republic national under-20 football team|Korea Republic]]. After the match ended in a 3\u20133 draw, it went to penalties, where Iraq won 5\u20134.<ref name=\"Iraq 3-3 Korea Republic (Iraq won on penalties 5-4) - 7 July 2013\">{{cite web|title=Iraq 3-3 Korea Republic (Iraq won on penalties 5-4) - 7 July 2013|url=https://www.fifa.com/u20worldcup/matches/round=259231/match=300232836/report.html|website=FIFA}}</ref> In the semifinal, Iraq lost against [[Uruguay national under-20 football team|Uruguay]]. After the match ended in a 1\u20131 draw, it went to penalties again, but this time, Iraq lost 6-7, with Tariq scoring his penalty.<ref name=\"Iraq 1-1 Uruguay (Uruguay won on penalties 6-7) - 10 July 2013\">{{cite web|title=Iraq 1-1 Uruguay (Uruguay won on penalties 6-7) - 10 July 2013|url=https://www.fifa.com/u20worldcup/matches/round=259229/match=300232828/report.html|website=FIFA}}</ref>\n\n===2014 Asian Games===\nTariq was one of the best players that played in the [[Football at the 2014 Asian Games \u2013 Men|2014 Asian Games]], scoring four goals, being the top scorer for [[Iraq under-23 national football team|Iraq]], along with [[Younis Mahmoud]]. Tariq started in all of Iraq's matches. He scored in Iraq's second match, on 17 September 2014, against [[Japan national under-23 football team|Japan]], in the 12th minute.<ref name=\"Japan 1 vs. 3 Iraq - 17 September 2014\">{{cite web|title=Japan 1 vs. 3 Iraq - 17 September 2014|url=http://www.incheon2014.kr/Sports/FB/Result?RSC=FBM400D03&lang=en|website=17th Asian Games Incheon 2014|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924042548/http://www.incheon2014.kr/Sports/FB/Result?RSC=FBM400D03&lang=en|archivedate=24 September 2015}}</ref> Tariq was the man of the match in Iraq's third game, against [[Kuwait national under-23 football team|Kuwait]], scoring two goals in the 16th and 62nd minutes and playing quite well.<ref name=\"Kuwait 0 vs. 3 Iraq - 21 September 2014\">{{cite web|title=Kuwait 0 vs. 3 Iraq - 21 September 2014|url=http://www.incheon2014.kr/Sports/FB/Result?RSC=FBM400D06&lang=en|website=17th Asian Games Incheon 2014|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150518100057/http://www.incheon2014.kr/Sports/FB/Result?RSC=FBM400D06&lang=en|archivedate=18 May 2015}}</ref> Tariq scored his fourth goal in Iraq's round of 16 match, against [[Tajikistan national under-23 football team|Tajikistan]], in the early 7th minute.<ref name=\"Iraq 4 vs. 2 Tajikistan - 26 September 2014\">{{cite web|title=Iraq 4 vs. 2 Tajikistan - 26 September 2014|url=http://www.incheon2014.kr/Sports/FB/Result?RSC=FBM400406&lang=en|website=17th Asian Games Incheon 2014|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150518100100/http://www.incheon2014.kr/Sports/FB/Result?RSC=FBM400406&lang=en|archivedate=18 May 2015}}</ref> Iraq won in the quarterfinal, 3\u20130 against [[Saudi Arabia national under-23 football team|Saudi Arabia]],<ref name=\"Saudi Arabia 0 vs. 3 Iraq - 28 September 2014\">{{cite web|title=Saudi Arabia 0 vs. 3 Iraq - 28 September 2014|url=http://www.incheon2014.kr/Sports/FB/Result?RSC=FBM400303&lang=en|website=17th Asian Games Incheon 2014|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924042536/http://www.incheon2014.kr/Sports/FB/Result/?RSC=FBM400303&lang=en|archivedate=24 September 2015}}</ref> but lost in the semifinal, against [[North Korea national under-23 football team|North Korea]], 0\u20131, where Tariq didn't perform that well.<ref name=\"Iraq 0 vs. 1 North Korea - 30 September 2014\">{{cite web|title=Iraq 0 vs. 1 North Korea - 30 September 2014|url=http://www.incheon2014.kr/Sports/FB/Result?RSC=FBM400202&lang=en|website=17th Asian Games Incheon 2014|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924042543/http://www.incheon2014.kr/Sports/FB/Result?RSC=FBM400202&lang=en|archivedate=24 September 2015}}</ref> In the third place match, Iraq won, gaining the bronze medal.<ref name=\"Thailand 0 vs. 1 Iraq - 2 October 2014\">{{cite web|title=Thailand 0 vs. 1 Iraq - 2 October 2014|url=http://www.incheon2014.kr/Sports/FB/Result?RSC=FBM400102&lang=en|website=17th Asian Games Incheon 2014|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150518100103/http://www.incheon2014.kr/Sports/FB/Result?RSC=FBM400102&lang=en|archivedate=18 May 2015}}</ref>\n\n===2014 Gulf Cup===\nTariq was a part of the squad that had the worst ever performance for [[Iraq national football team|Iraq]] in the [[Gulf Cup of Nations|Gulf Cup]], since the [[2009 Gulf Cup of Nations|2009 edition]], in the [[2014 Gulf Cup of Nations|2014 Gulf Cup]]. He started in all of the three matches of Iraq, lost 0\u20131 against [[Kuwait national football team|Kuwait]],<ref name=\"Iraq vs. Kuwait - 14 November 2014\">{{cite web|title=Iraq vs. Kuwait - 14 November 2014|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2014/11/14/asia/gulf-cup/iraq/kuwait/1896331/|website=Soccerway|language=Arabic}}</ref> drew 1\u20131 with [[Oman national football team|Oman]], where Tariq got a yellow card,<ref name=\"Iraq vs. Oman - 17 November 2014\">{{cite web|title=Iraq vs. Oman - 17 November 2014|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2014/11/17/asia/gulf-cup/iraq/oman/1896335/|website=Soccerway|language=Arabic}}</ref> and lost 2\u20130 against the [[UAE national football team|UAE]].<ref name=\"UAE vs. Iraq - 20 November 2014\">{{cite web|title=UAE vs. Iraq - 20 November 2014|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2014/11/20/asia/gulf-cup/united-arab-emirates/iraq/1896337/|website=Soccerway|language=Arabic}}</ref>\n\n===2015 AFC Asian Cup===\nTariq was included in [[Iraq national football team|Iraq]]'s squad for the [[2015 AFC Asian Cup]], but he only played 57 minutes of the first match of Iraq, against [[Jordan national football team|Jordan]].<ref name=\"Jordan 0-1 Iraq - 12 January 2015\">{{cite web|title=Jordan 0-1 Iraq - 12 January 2015|url=http://www.the-afc.com/afcasfeeds?fixtureid=8258&stageid=327&tMode=C&view=ajax&show=matchsummary|website=AFC ASIAN CUP AUSTRALIA 2015}}</ref> Iraq eventually reached the semi-final and lost, ending in 4th place.<ref name=\"Iraq gets 4th place at AFC Asian Cup\">{{cite news|title=Iraq gets 4th place at AFC Asian Cup|url=http://en.alforatnews.com/modules/news/article.php?storyid=15608|agency=Alforat News}}</ref>\n\n===2019 AFC Asian cup===\nTariq participated in the [[2019 AFC Asian Cup]], hosted by UAE. Tariq was one of Iraq's key players in the tournament, helping them reach the round of 16 where they were knocked out by Qatar in a 1\u20130 loss.\n\n===International goals===\n:''Scores and results list Iraq's goal tally first.''<ref name=\"NFT\">{{cite web|url=https://www.national-football-teams.com/player/29198/Humam_Tariq.html|title=Tariq, Humam|publisher=National Football Teams}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! # !! Date !! Venue !! Opponent !! Score !! Result !! Competition\n|-\n| 1. || 28 March 2015 || [[The Sevens Stadium]], [[Dubai]]|| {{fb|Congo DR}} || align=center | '''2'''\u20131 || align=center | 2\u20131 || rowspan=2 | [[Exhibition game|Friendly]]\n|-\n| 2. || 28 December 2018|| [[Suheim Bin Hamad Stadium]], [[Doha]]|| {{fb|Palestine}} || align=center | '''1'''\u20130 || align=center | 1\u20130\n|-\n| 3. || 8 January 2019 || [[Zayed Sports City Stadium]], [[Abu Dhabi]] || {{fb|VIE}} || align=center | '''2'''\u20132 || align=center | 3\u20132 ||[[2019 AFC Asian Cup Group D|2019 AFC Asian Cup]]\n|}\n\n==Style of play==\n{{Quote box| width = 25%| align = right| quoted = 1| quote = The secret for the success of [[Younis Mahmoud|Younis]] at the [[2013 Gulf Cup of Nations|Gulf Cup]] was Humam, and the secret to the future success of Younis will be Humam Tariq, because of the quick link-up play from Humam, as he's the fastest player on the flanks to Younis, assisting him and one of the important keys to opening the door of the opposition is that he's the quickest player in Iraq (on the ball).| salign = left| source = \u2014 [[Hakim Shaker]] commenting on Tariq<ref name=\"Humam Tariq full scout report - Outside of the Boot\" />}}\n\nTariq uses his small frame and explosive pace to burst past defenders and find space on the flank and down the middle. His distribution is already excellent for such a young man. The midfielder is an excellent crosser of the ball and he is also known for his good finishing which leads to plenty of goals, and his confident passing can open up any game.<ref name=\"Humam Tariq style - Eyefootball.com\">{{cite web|last1=Patel|first1=Ketan|title=Humam Tariq|url=https://www.eyefootball.com/news/23535/Humam-Tariq.html|website=Eyefootball.com|date=June 7, 2015}}</ref> Often compared to [[Raheem Sterling]], Tariq plays in an offensive midfield role and has a combination of speed and vision that is not that common. He has an explosive quickness in the first few meters and a good technique.<ref name=\"Humam Tariq skills - The Next Messi\">{{cite web|title=Humam Tariq|url=http://nextmessi.com/2014/08/humam-tariq/|website=The Next Messi|date=August 27, 2014}}</ref> Due to his build and style of play, he has often been compared to [[Lionel Messi]], gaining him the nickname \"Iraqi Messi\".\n\nTariq's definitive position could be as a deep-lying forward, behind a central striker, giving him the freedom of movement, to draw opposing players out of position and exploit holes in the opposition's defense. He doesn't look or play anything like an old fashioned attacking wide-man, but is deployed as more of an unorthodox modern-day winger, tucking in when his team is without the ball and often asked to press the opposition to regain back possession.<ref name=\"Humam Tariq full scout report - Outside of the Boot\" /> His exceptional crossing, passing, finishing, skills and electric pace, combined with his experience at a young age, make Tariq one of the best Asian talents to look forward to.\n\n==Personal life==\nHumam Tariq was born to the Naoush family from the [[Adhamiyah]] district in [[Baghdad]].<ref name=\"Families of Adhamiyah - ShakwMakw\">{{cite web|title=Families of Adhamiyah|url=http://www.shakwmakw.com/vb/showthread.php?t=366707|website=ShakwMakw|language=Arabic}}</ref> He is the grandson of Faraj Naoush, the creator of Confectionery of Faraj Naoush and His Sons, which was created in 1954.<ref name=\"Faraj Naoush 1954 - Al-Gardenia\">{{cite web|last1=Mahmoud|first1=Suroor Merza|title=Engravings that talk about the regions of al-Hara, al-Safinah and Saada street|url=http://www.algardenia.com/2014-04-04-19-52-20/menouats/10915-2014-06-12-09-53-16.html|website=Al-Gardenia|language=Arabic}}</ref> It was one of the best confectionery shops in Iraq, especially, during the [[Sanctions against Iraq]] in the 1990s. Humam helped out in the family business in his spare time making the sweets.<ref name=\"Faraj Naoush commercial 1999 - Youtube\">{{cite web|last1=Naoush|first1=Harith|title=Faraj Naoush and His Sons commercial 1999|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QeFapAc15eM|website=Youtube|language=Arabic|date=January 17, 2012}}</ref><ref name=OLY>{{cite web|last1=Mubarak|first1=Hassanin|title=Iraq Olympic Team Profile|url=https://ahdaaf.me/2016/08/02/iraq-olympic-team-profile/}}</ref> Humam is married. His son Tariq was born in July 2017.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BXPe7dIAiss|title=Humam on Instagram|language=en}}</ref>\n\n==Honours==\n===Club===\n;Al-Quwa Al-Jawiya\n*[[AFC Cup]]: [[2016 AFC Cup|2016]], [[2017 AFC Cup|2017]]\n*[[Iraq FA Cup]]: [[2016 Iraq FA Cup Final|2015\u201316]]\n*[[Iraqi Premier League]]: [[2016\u201317 Iraqi Premier League|2016\u201317]]\n\n===International===\n;Iraq U-19\n*[[AFC U-19 Championship]] runner-up: [[2012 AFC U-19 Championship|2012]]\n;Iraq U-20\n*[[FIFA U-20 World Cup]] fourth place: [[2013 FIFA U-20 World Cup|2013]]\n;Iraq U-22\n*[[AFC U-22 Championship]] winner: [[2013 AFC U-22 Championship|2013]]\n;Iraq U-23\n*[[Football at the Asian Games|Asian Games]] bronze medallist: [[Football at the 2014 Asian Games \u2013 Men|2014]]\n;Iraq\n*[[Arabian Gulf Cup]] runner-up: [[2013 Gulf Cup of Nations|2013]]\n*[[AFC Asian Cup]] fourth-place: [[2015 AFC Asian Cup|2015]]\n\n===Individual===\n*World Military Cup Asian Qualification Zone Best Player: 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.alahwartv.net/pages/news.php?nid=14430|title=Best player in the World Military Cup Asian Zone qualifications|language=Arabic|access-date=2013-07-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150518082545/http://www.alahwartv.net/pages/news.php?nid=14430|archive-date=2015-05-18|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n*Outside of the Boot's 100 Best Young Players to Watch: 2015.<ref name=\"100 Best Young Players to Watch in 2015 - Outside of the Boot\">{{cite web|title=100 Best Young Players to Watch in 2015, Midfielders 35 \u2013 21|url=http://outsideoftheboot.com/2014/12/12/100-best-young-players-2015-midfielders/|website=Outside of the Boot}}</ref>\n*[[Soccer Iraq#Team of the Decade|Soccer Iraq Team of the Decade]]: 2010\u20132019\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Navboxes colour\n|title= Iraq squads\n| bg          = white\n| bordercolor = #008000\n|list1=\n{{Iraq squad 2015 AFC Asian Cup}}\n{{Iraq men's football squad 2016 Summer Olympics}}\n{{Iraq squad 2019 AFC Asian Cup}}\n}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Tariq, Humam}}\n[[Category:1996 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Association football wingers]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Baghdad]]\n[[Category:Iraqi footballers]]\n[[Category:Iraqi expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Al-Quwa Al-Jawiya players]]\n[[Category:Al Ahli Club (Dubai) players]]\n[[Category:Al Dhafra FC players]]\n[[Category:Esteghlal F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Iraqi expatriate sportspeople in the United Arab Emirates]]\n[[Category:Iraqi expatriate sportspeople in Iran]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in the United Arab Emirates]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Iran]]\n[[Category:Iraq international footballers]]\n[[Category:Footballers at the 2014 Asian Games]]\n[[Category:2015 AFC Asian Cup players]]\n[[Category:2019 AFC Asian Cup players]]\n[[Category:Asian Games medalists in football]]\n[[Category:Asian Games bronze medalists for Iraq]]\n[[Category:Footballers at the 2016 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Olympic footballers of Iraq]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 2014 Asian Games]]\n[[Category:UAE Pro League players]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football biography\n| fullname = Humam Tariq Faraj Naoush\n| image = Pre-Iran Iraq press conference 20190115 05.jpg\n| image_size = \n| caption = Humam Tariq in 2019\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1996|2|10}}\n| birth_place = [[Baghdad]], Iraq\n| height = 1.71 m\n| position = [[Midfielder#Winger|Winger]], [[Attacking midfielder]]\n| currentclub = [[Ismaily SC|Ismaily]]\n| clubnumber = 10\n| youthyears1 = 2006\u20132007\n| youthclubs1 = [[Al-Zawra'a SC|Al Zawraa]]\n| youthyears2 = 2007\u20132010\n| youthclubs2 = [[Al-Quwa Al-Jawiya]]\n| years1 = 2010\u20132014\n| years2 = 2014\u20132016\n| years3 = 2014\u20132015\n| years4 = 2015\u20132016\n| years5 = 2016\u20132018\n| years6 = 2018\u20132019\n| years7 = 2019\u2013\n| clubs1 = [[Al-Quwa Al-Jawiya]]\n| clubs2 = [[Al-Ahli Dubai F.C.|Al-Ahli]]\n| clubs3 = \u2192 [[Al Dhafra SCC|Al Dhafra]] (loan)\n| clubs4 = \u2192 [[Al-Quwa Al-Jawiya]] (loan)\n| clubs5 = [[Al-Quwa Al-Jawiya]]\n| clubs6 = [[Esteghlal F.C.|Esteghlal]]\n| clubs7 =  [[Ismaily SC|Ismaily]]\n| caps1 = 46\n| caps2 = 0\n| caps3 = 20\n| caps4 = 14\n| caps5 = 53\n| caps6 = 14\n| caps7 = 8\n| goals1 = 4\n| goals2 = 0\n| goals3 = 2\n| goals4 = 1\n| goals5 = 6\n| goals6 = 1\n| goals7 = 2\n| nationalyears1 = 2012\u20132013\n| nationalyears2 = 2012\u20132016\n| nationalyears3 = 2012\u2013\n| nationalteam1 = [[Iraq under-20 national football team|Iraq U20]]\n| nationalteam2 = [[Iraq under-23 national football team|Iraq U23]]\n| nationalteam3 = [[Iraq national football team|Iraq]]\n| nationalcaps1 = 13\n| nationalgoals1 = 0\n| nationalcaps2 = 15\n| nationalgoals2 = 5\n| nationalcaps3 = 63\n| nationalgoals3 = 3\n| medaltemplates = {{MedalCountry | {{IRQ}}}}\n{{MedalSport  | Men's [[Association football|football]]}}\n{{MedalCompetition | [[Asian Games]]}}\n{{MedalBronze  | [[2014 Asian Games|2014 Incheon]] | [[Football at the 2014 Asian Games|Team]]}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[AFC U-19 Championship]]}}\n{{Medal|RU|[[2012 AFC U-19 Championship]]|[[Iraq under-20 national football team|Team]]}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[AFC U-22 Championship]]}}\n{{Medal|1st|[[2013 AFC U-22 Championship]]|[[Iraq under-23 national football team|Team]]}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[Gulf Cup of Nations]]}}\n{{Medal|RU|[[2013 Gulf Cup of Nations]]|[[Iraq national football team|Team]]}}\n| ntupdate = 14 November 2019\n| club-update = 27 April 2019\n}}\n\n'''Humam Tariq Faraj Naoush''' ({{lang-ar|\u0647\u0645\u0627\u0645 \u0637\u0627\u0631\u0642 \u0641\u0631\u062c \u0646\u0639\u0648\u0634}}; born 10 February 1996 in [[Baghdad]]) is an [[Iraq]]i professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays for [[Ismaily SC|Ismaily]] and the [[Iraq national football team|Iraq national team]] as [[Midfielder#Winger|winger]]. Tariq has long been considered one of Iraq's most talented footballers. He has been nicknamed the \"Iraqi [[Lionel Messi|Messi]]\". He has represented Iraq at Under-19, Under-20, Under-22, Under-23 and full international level, making his debut for the national team at the age of 16, making him the youngest Iraqi in history to represent the senior team. Humam represented Iraq at the [[Football at the 2016 Summer Olympics|Rio Olympics]] in 2016, playing in all 3 of Iraq's matches against Denmark, Brazil and South Africa. Tariq has also played at the [[2013 FIFA U-20 World Cup|2013 FIFA Under-20 World Cup]], where he was one of Iraq's star players as the underdogs went on a run to the semi-final. At senior level, he has played at the [[2015 AFC Asian Cup]], where they beat the odds and reached the semi-final.\n\n==Club career==\n\n===Early career===\nTariq started playing football at a very young age and often participated in local matches and could regularly be seen playing as a child in public. This eventually caught the attention of Baghdad's biggest clubs. He decided he wanted to pursue a career in football, and from an early age he use to play with older kids at the local shaabiya football pitches near where he grew up before he joined the youth teams in the academy of Iraqi giants [[Al-Zawraa]], He stayed with Al Zawraa for a few months but later decided that he wanted to play for his boyhood club [[Al-Quwa Al-Jawiya]], who he joined in 2007 at the age of 11.<ref name=ACUP>{{cite web|last1=Mubarak|first1=Hassanin|title=Profile of Iraq\u2019s 23-Man 2015 Asian Cup Squad|url=https://iraqsport.wordpress.com/2014/12/29/profiles-of-iraqs-23-man-2015-asian-cup-squad//}}</ref><ref name=\"Humam Tariq full scout report - Outside of the Boot\">{{cite web|last1=Mubarak|first1=Hassanin|title=Scout Report - Humam Tariq: Al Dhafra SCC and Iraq\u2019s talented youngster|url=http://outsideoftheboot.com/2015/04/29/scout-report-humam-tariq-al-dhafra-scc-and-iraqs-talented-youngster/|website=Outside of the Boot|date=April 29, 2015}}</ref>\n\n===Al-Quwa Al-Jawiya===\n====2009\u201310====\nAt a young age, Tariq started his football career, by joining [[Al-Quwa Al-Jawiya]]'s academy, where he kept getting promoted until, in 2010, he joined the senior team at the age of just 14.<ref name=\"Humam Tariq talks to Al-Bayyina\">{{cite web|title=Humam Tariq, the Olympic team and Al-Quwa Al-Jawiya player to Al-Bayyina|url=http://www.al-bayyna.com/modules.php?name=News&file=article&sid=52083|website=Al-Bayyina|language=Arabic}}</ref> He started playing for the senior team, in the [[2009\u201310 Iraqi Premier League]]. He made his debut with Al-Quwa Al-Jawiya, on 26 May 2010, in a match against [[Salahaddin FC]], where the match ended in a 2\u20130 win for Al-Jawiya.<ref name=\"Humam Tariq Jawiya debut - Goalzz\">{{cite web|title=All Soccer Matches on 26 May 2010|url=http://www.goalzz.com/?region=-1&area=0&dd=26&mm=5&yy=2010|website=Goalzz}}</ref>\n\n====2010\u201311====\nHe appeared every two or three matches as substitute. Al-Quwa Al-Jawiya finished in 2nd place in the groups stage, being qualified to the third place match, where they lost against [[Al-Sinaa SC]] 0\u20131.<ref name=\"Iraq 2010/11\">{{cite web|title=Iraq 2010/11|url=http://www.rsssf.com/tablesi/iraq2011.html|website=RSSSF}}</ref>\n\n====2011\u201312====\nTariq scored his first goal in his third season with [[Al-Quwa Al-Jawiya]], on 27 April 2012, in a match against [[Zakho FC]], three minutes after the beginning of the match, which ended in a 1\u20131 draw.<ref name=\"Soccerway (27 April 2012)\">{{cite web|title=Zakho vs. Al Quwa Al Jawiya - 27 April 2012|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2012/04/27/iraq/iraqi-league/zakho/al-quwa-al-jawiya/1221816/?ICID=PL_MS_25|website=Soccerway|language=Arabic}}</ref> Tariq scored his second goal in a match against [[Al-Sinaa SC|Al-Sinaa]], which ended in a 2\u20131 loss for [[Al-Quwa Al-Jawiya]].<ref name=\"Soccerway (12 July 2012)\">{{cite web|title=Al Sinaa vs. Al Quwa Al Jawiya - 12 July 2012|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2012/07/12/iraq/iraqi-league/al-sinaah/al-quwa-al-jawiya/1221835/|website=Soccerway|language=Arabic}}</ref> Tariq scored his third goal in a match against [[Arbil FC]], which ended in a 1\u20131 draw.<ref name=\"Soccerway (16 August 2012)\">{{cite web|title=Arbil vs. Al Quwa Al Jawiya|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2012/08/16/iraq/iraqi-league/arbil/al-quwa-al-jawiya/1221898/|website=Soccerway|language=Arabic}}</ref> Tariq scored only three goals in this season. [[Al-Quwa Al-Jawiya]] finished in 3rd place in the league table, at 74 points, while [[Arbil FC]] became the champions, at 83 points.<ref name=\"Iraq 2011/12\">{{cite web|title=Iraq 2011/12|url=http://www.rsssf.com/tablesi/iraq2012.html|website=RSSSF}}</ref>\n\n====2012\u201313====\nIn the [[2012\u201313 Iraqi Premier League]], Tariq scored only a single goal against [[Kirkuk FC]].<ref name=\"Soccerway (7 December 2012)\">{{cite web|title=Kirkuk vs. Al Quwa Al Jawiya - 7 December 2012|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2012/12/17/iraq/iraqi-league/kirkuk/al-quwa-al-jawiya/1421756/|website=Soccerway|language=Arabic}}</ref> [[Al-Quwa Al-Jawiya]] finished in 3rd place, at 69 points, while [[Al Shorta SC]] became the champions, at 72 points, with Tariq not finishing the league season.<ref name=\"Iraq 2012/13\">{{cite web|title=Iraq 2012/13|url=http://www.rsssf.com/tablesi/iraq2013.html|website=RSSSF}}</ref> In the [[2012\u201313 UAFA Club Cup]], Tariq scored a goal, in the first leg of the match, against [[Shabab Al-Dhahiriya SC]] from [[State of Palestine|Palestine]], which ended in a 3\u20130 victory for Al-Quwa Al-Jawiya.<ref name=\"2012/13 UAFA Club Cup - Round 1\">{{cite web|title=2012/13 UAFA Club Cup - Round 1|url=http://www.kooora.com/?c=6933&stage=2|website=Kooora|language=Arabic}}</ref> Tariq did not stay with Al-Quwa Al-Jawiya until the end of the tournament. Eventually, Al-Quwa Al-Jawiya was eliminated, in the quarterfinals, by [[Raja Casablanca]] from [[Morocco]].<ref name=\"2012/13 UAFA Club Cup - Quarterfinals\">{{cite web|title=2012/13 UAFA Club Cup - Quarterfinals|url=http://www.kooora.com/?c=6933&stage=3|website=Kooora|language=Arabic}}</ref> In Tariq's last days in the club, on 24 May 2014, he was fined with $10,000 by the club's management because Tariq missed his team's training camp in [[Sulaymaniyah]].<ref name=\"Humam Tariq fined with 10k from al-Jawiya - Hatha al-Youm\">{{cite news|title=Al-Quwa Al-Jawiya fine their player, Humam Tariq, with 10 million dinars|url=http://hathalyoum.net/sit/358983.htm|agency=Hatha al-Youm|date=May 25, 2014|language=Arabic|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150702102454/http://hathalyoum.net/sit/358983.htm|archivedate=July 2, 2015}}</ref>\n\n===Al Ahli===\nOn 29 January 2013, at the age of 16, Tariq signed a contract worth $9,582 per week with [[Al-Ahli Dubai F.C.|Al-Ahli]], who bought him for \u20ac600,000, to play for them for 5 years, with bonuses and good efforts income added. Al Ahli also provided an apartment for Tariq in [[Dubai]], a personal car and free transportation between Baghdad and Dubai for Tariq and his family.<ref name=\"Humam Tariq's contract\">{{cite web|title=Humam Tariq and Al-Ahli|url=http://forum.kooora.com/?t=32106250|website=Kooora|language=Arabic}}</ref> Although Tariq signed the contract in January 2013, he had to wait over a year to join the squad, because he wasn't going to be 18 years old until 10 February 2014, at which point he wasn't allowed to join up with his new club.<ref name=\"Humam Tariq's contract\" /> He was loaned to [[Al Dhafra SCC|Al Dhafra]] after playing only two friendly matches with Al Ahli.<ref name=\"Humam Tariq Dhafra loan\">{{cite news|title=Al Dhafra from UAE gets the services of Humam Tariq in a loan contract|url=http://www.alsumaria.tv/news/112436/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B8%D9%81%D8%B1%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A5%D9%85%D8%A7%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%AA%D9%8A-%D9%8A%D8%AD%D8%B5%D9%84-%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%89-%D8%AE%D8%AF%D9%85%D8%A7%D8%AA-%D9%87%D9%85%D8%A7%D9%85-%D8%B7%D8%A7%D8%B1/ar|agency=Al Sumaria|language=Arabic}}</ref>\n\n====Failed Transfers to Turkey====\nOn 14 June 2015, Al-Ahli received an official offer from an unnamed Turkish team to either buy or loan Tariq.<ref name=\"Turkish offer to sign the Iraqi Humam Tariq - :24\">{{cite news|title=Turkish offer to sign the Iraqi Humam Tariq|url=http://24.ae/article/165720/%D8%B9%D8%B1%D8%B6-%D8%AA%D8%B1%D9%83%D9%8A-%D9%84%D9%84%D8%AA%D8%B9%D8%A7%D9%82%D8%AF-%D9%85%D8%B9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B9%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%82%D9%8A-%D9%87%D9%85%D8%A7%D9%85-%D8%B7%D8%A7%D8%B1%D9%82.aspx|agency=:24|date=June 14, 2015|language=Arabic}}</ref> After five days, Tariq's agent, Najm Mohammed, stated that the negotiations between the unnamed Turkish side and Al-Ahli broke down after Al-Ahli demanded $400,000 for Humam but the team wasn't willing to pay more than $200,000.<ref name=\"Humam Tariq broke Turkish negotiations - Hamrin News\">{{cite news|title=Two Saudi clubs sign two Iraqi players and the negotiations of signing Humam Tariq for a Turkish team broke|url=http://hamrinnews.net/sport/3519.html|agency=Hamrin News|date=June 19, 2015|language=Arabic}}</ref> Al-Ahli received an offer from another team in the [[S\u00fcper Lig]] and it was [[Bursaspor]]. Al-Ahli initially accepted the offer.<ref name=\"Bursaspor offer - Al Bayan\">{{cite news|last1=Zahdi|first1=Ehab|title=Offer from Buraspor to buy Humam Tariq|url=http://www.albayan.ae/sports/emirates/2015-06-22-1.2400798|agency=Al Bayan|language=Arabic|date=June 22, 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"Humam Tariq Bursaspor - Bursa Hakimiyet\">{{cite news|title=Humam Tariq beklemede|url=http://www.bursahakimiyet.com.tr/haber/bursaspor/humam-tariq-beklemede-85841.html|agency=Bursa Hakimiyet|date=June 19, 2015|language=Turkish|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150627201636/http://www.bursahakimiyet.com.tr/haber/bursaspor/humam-tariq-beklemede-85841.html|archivedate=June 27, 2015}}</ref> But, again, on 30 June, Tariq's agent announced that the deal failed, in the last moments, because Bursaspor offered a low amount of money and the offer was rejected by Al-Ahli.<ref name=\"Bursaspor breaks down with Humam Tariq - Al-Mada Newspaper\">{{cite news|title=Deal of Humam Tariq transferring to Bursaspor breaks down|url=http://www.almadapaper.net/ar/news/490815/%D9%81%D8%B4%D9%84-%D8%B5%D9%81%D9%82%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%86%D8%AA%D9%82%D8%A7%D9%84-%D9%87%D9%85%D8%A7%D9%85--%D8%A5%D9%84%D9%89-%D8%A8%D9%88%D8%B1%D8%B5%D8%A7-%D8%B3%D8%A8%D9%88%D8%B1|agency=Al-Mada Newspaper|issue=3399|date=June 30, 2015|language=Arabic}}</ref> In July 2015, two teams from the [[Iraqi Premier League]] showed interest in signing Tariq, his last team, [[Al-Quwa Al-Jawiya]],<ref name=\"Tariq close to Al-Quwa Al-Jawiya - Al-Bayan Al-Riyadhi\">{{cite news|last1=Zahdi|first1=Ehab|title=Humam Tariq gets close to Al-Quwa Al-Jawiya|url=http://www.albayan.ae/sports/all-games/2015-07-07-1.2410877|agency=Al-Bayan Al-Riyadhi|date=July 7, 2015|language=Arabic}}</ref> and [[Al Shorta SC|Al Shorta]].<ref name=\"Hakeem Shakir calls Tariq to join Al Shorta - Iraq99\">{{cite news|last1=Jaloob|first1=Dhurgham Ismael|title=Hakeem Shakir calls Younis Mahmoud and Humam Tariq to join Al Shorta|url=http://www.iraq99.com/534439/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%A7%D8%B6%D8%A9-%D8%AD%D9%83%D9%8A%D9%85-%D8%B4%D8%A7%D9%83%D8%B1-%D9%8A%D8%AF%D8%B9%D9%88-%D9%8A%D9%88%D9%86%D8%B3-%D9%85%D8%AD%D9%85%D9%88%D8%AF-%D9%88%D9%87%D9%85%D8%A7.html|agency=Iraq99|date=July 15, 2015|language=Arabic|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924040339/http://www.iraq99.com/534439/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%A7%D8%B6%D8%A9-%D8%AD%D9%83%D9%8A%D9%85-%D8%B4%D8%A7%D9%83%D8%B1-%D9%8A%D8%AF%D8%B9%D9%88-%D9%8A%D9%88%D9%86%D8%B3-%D9%85%D8%AD%D9%85%D9%88%D8%AF-%D9%88%D9%87%D9%85%D8%A7.html|archivedate=September 24, 2015}}</ref>\n\n====Al Dhafra (loan)====\nOn 1 October 2014, Tariq was loaned to [[Al Dhafra FC|Al Dhafra]], without playing a single official game for [[Al-Ahli Dubai F.C.|Al-Ahli]]. His loan contract stated that Tariq will play for Al Dhafra for the [[2014\u201315 UAE Pro-League|2014\u201315]] season, which can be extended.<ref name=\"Humam Tariq Dhafra loan\" />\n\nTariq played his debut match, in the 2014\u201315 season, on 5 October, against [[Emirates Club]]. He played for 77 minutes and got subbed off for [[Ali Al-Hammadi]].<ref name=\"Al Dhafra vs. Emirates - 5 October 2014\">{{cite web|title=Al Dhafra vs. Emirates - 5 October 2014|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2014/10/05/united-arab-emirates/premier-league/al-dhafra/emirates-club-ras-al-khaimah/1714751/|website=Soccerway|language=Arabic}}</ref> Tariq scored his first goal with [[Al Dhafra SCC|Al Dhafra]] on 29 November, against [[Al-Ittihad Kalba SC|Al-Ittihad Kalba]], in the 19th minute,<ref name=\"Diop and Humam lead Al-Dhafra to the first win in the league over Ittihad Kalba\">{{cite news|title=Diop and Humam lead Al-Dhafra to the first win in the league over Ittihad Kalba|url=http://www.emaratalyoum.com/sports/local/2014-11-30-1.733251|agency=Emirates Today|date=29 November 2014|language=Arabic}}</ref> rocketing the ball from outside the penalty box into the right corner of the goal, from a pass by [[Makhete Diop]].<ref name=\"Debut Goal - Dhafra - Youtube\">{{cite web|title=Goal of Humam Tariq against Ittihad Kalba in the UAE Pro League (29/11/2014)|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-f4WWpN3a-s|website=Youtube|language=Arabic}}</ref> His second goal with Al Dhafra was one of the fastest goals in the [[UAE Arabian Gulf League]], on 10 May 2015, in the 4th minute, against [[Al-Shabab (UAE)|Al-Shabab]].<ref name=\"Arabian Gulf League: Al-Shabab trips over Al-Dhafra and loses 2nd place\">{{cite news|title=Arabian Gulf League: Al-Shabab trips over Al-Dhafra and loses 2nd place|url=http://24.ae/article/157680/%D8%AF%D9%88%D8%B1%D9%8A-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AE%D9%84%D9%8A%D8%AC-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B9%D8%B1%D8%A8%D9%8A-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B4%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%A8-%D9%8A%D8%AA%D8%B9%D8%AB%D8%B1-%D8%A3%D9%85%D8%A7%D9%85-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B8%D9%81%D8%B1%D8%A9-%D9%88%D9%8A%D9%81%D9%82%D8%AF-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%88%D8%B5%D8%A7%D9%81%D8%A9.aspx|agency=:24|date=10 May 2015|language=Arabic}}</ref> Tariq finished the league season with Al Dhafra in 12th place at 26 points, only one place away from relegation.<ref>{{Cite web|url = https://int.soccerway.com/national/united-arab-emirates/premier-league/20142015/regular-season/r26021/|title = 2014-15 UAE Arabian Gulf League|date = |accessdate = |website = Soccerway|publisher = |last = |first = |language = Arabic}}</ref>\n\nIn the [[UAE President's Cup]], Tariq played Al Dhafra's match in the Round of 16, on 15 May 2015. He had an assist in a goal for [[Bilal Najjarine]] from a free kick, crossed by Tariq to Bilal's head. Tariq was injured, in that match, with a muscle strain.<ref>{{Cite news|url = http://www.albayan.ae/sports/emirates/2015-05-23-1.2380050|title = Humam Tariq: I'm 90% fit|last = |first = |date = |work = |access-date = |via = |publisher = Al-Bayan Al-Riyadhi|language = Arabic}}</ref> Al Dhafra won 7\u20136 on penalties after a 1\u20131 draw.<ref>{{Cite web|url = https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2015/05/15/united-arab-emirates/presidents-cup/ahli-al-fujirah/al-dhafra/1699521/|title = Al-Fujerah vs. Al-Dhafra - 15 May 2015|date = |accessdate = |website = Soccerway|publisher = |last = |first = |language = Arabic}}</ref> In the quarterfinals, Tariq started the match against [[Ajman Club|Ajman]], where he had another assist in the first goal, by crossing the ball to [[Makhete Diop]]'s head and into the goal, in the 62nd minute.<ref>{{Cite web|url = https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KkrjxXFjR0s|title = Al Dhafra 2-0 Ajman - UAE President's Cup 2014-2015|date = |accessdate = |website = Youtube|publisher = |last = |first = }}</ref> The match ended in a 2\u20130 win for Al Dhafra. In the semifinals, against [[Al-Ahli Dubai F.C.|Al-Ahli]], Tariq wasn't allowed to play because of the friendly agreement between Al Dhafra and Al Ahli that doesn't allow him to play in a match against Al Ahli.<ref>{{Cite news|url = http://www.iraq99.com/237738/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%A7%D8%B6%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%8A%D9%88%D9%85-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B8%D9%81%D8%B1%D8%A9-%D9%8A%D8%B3%D8%B9%D9%89-%D9%84%D9%83%D8%AA%D8%A7%D8%A8%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AA%D8%A7.html|archive-url = https://archive.is/20151021035637/http://www.iraq99.com/237738/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%A7%D8%B6%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%8A%D9%88%D9%85-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B8%D9%81%D8%B1%D8%A9-%D9%8A%D8%B3%D8%B9%D9%89-%D9%84%D9%83%D8%AA%D8%A7%D8%A8%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AA%D8%A7.html|url-status = dead|archive-date = 21 October 2015|title = Al Dhafra looks forward for writing history... and Al Ahli's eyes on the most precious of cups|last = Jaloob|first = Dhirgam Ismael|date = 30 May 2015|language = Arabic}}</ref> Al Dhafra lost the match 0\u20132.<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://www.emaratalyoum.com/sports/local/2015-05-31-1.789131|title = Al-Ahli defeats Al-Dhafra and qualifies to the final|date = 31 May 2015|accessdate = |website = Emirates Today|publisher = |last = Mustafa|first = Sayyid|language = Arabic}}</ref> Tariq finished his season with his team that he was loaned to with a total of 22 appearances, that included 2 goals and 2 assists.<ref name=\"Humam Tariq - Soccerway\">{{cite web|title=Humam Tariq|url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/humam-tarek--/241430/|website=Soccerway|language=Arabic}}</ref> After the end of the season, Al Dhafra didn't show interest in extending Tariq's contract. Therefore, he returned to Al-Ahli.<ref name=\"Humam Tariq out of Al Dhafra\">{{cite news|title=Asia Angle: From Didier Drogba to Robinho - Players who could be moving in and out of Asia|url=http://sport360.com/article/football/38517/asia-angle-didier-drogba-robinho-players-who-could-be-moving-and-out-asia|agency=Sport 360|date=June 23, 2015}}</ref>\n\n====Al-Quwa Al-Jawiya====\nIn 2015, Tariq returned to Jawiya in a loan deal for the season and played in the league and [[Iraq FA Cup|FA Cup]], where he scored in the [[2016 Iraq FA Cup Final|FA Cup final]] which Jawiya won by two goals to win the cup. After a successful loan spell at Jawiya, Humam returned permanently in 2016 where he has consistently impressed for the Iraqi outfit, regaining him a call up to the national team and new rumours of a move abroad.\n\n===Esteghlal===\n[[File:Humam Tariq.jpg|thumb|Tariq playing for Esteghlal in 2017]] \nAfter failing to join [[Elaz\u0131\u011fspor]] in the [[TFF First League]],<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.elazighakimiyethaber.com/humam-tariq-olmadi/31092|title=Humam Tariq olmad\u0131!|language=tr-TR}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://gunisigigazetesi.net/humam-tariq-konusunda-olumsuz-rapor-vermedim/57604|title=Humam Tar\u0131q konusunda olumsuz rapor vermedim|last=Gazetesi|first=G\u00fcn\u0131\u015f\u0131\u011f\u0131|language=tr-TR}}</ref> Tariq officially joined [[Esteghlal F.C.|Esteghlal]] on a three-year contract on 1 August 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fcesteghlal.ir/news/item/2759/\u0628\u0627+\u0627\u0639\u0644\u0627\u0645+\u0641\u062a\u062d\u06cc\u061b+\u0637\u0627\u0631\u0642+\u0647\u0645\u0627\u0645+\u0627\u0633\u062a\u0642\u0644\u0627\u0644\u06cc+\u0634\u062f|title=\u0628\u0627\u0632\u06cc\u06a9\u0646 \u062a\u06cc\u0645 \u0645\u0644\u06cc \u0639\u0631\u0627\u0642 \u0628\u0627 \u0627\u0645\u0636\u0627\u06cc \u0642\u0631\u0627\u0631\u062f\u0627\u062f\u06cc 3 \u0633\u0627\u0644\u0647 \u0628\u0647 \u0627\u0633\u062a\u0642\u0644\u0627\u0644 \u067e\u06cc\u0648\u0633\u062a.|trans-title=Iraq international joined Esteghlal on a three-year contract|publisher=Esteghlal|language=Persian|date=1 August 2018|accessdate=1 August 2018}}</ref> He was assigned the number 17 shirt in Esteghlal.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://90tv.ir/news/\u0634\u0645\u0627\u0631\u0647-\u067e\u06cc\u0631\u0627\u0647\u0646-\u0628\u0627\u0632\u06cc\u06a9\u0646\u0627\u0646-\u0627\u0633\u062a\u0642\u0644\u0627\u0644-\u062f\u0631-\u0644\u06cc\u06af-\u0642\u0647\u0631\u0645\u0627\u0646\u0627\u0646-\u0622\u0633\u06cc\u0627-\u0645\u0634\u062e\u0635-\u0634\u062f|title=\u0634\u0645\u0627\u0631\u0647 \u067e\u06cc\u0631\u0627\u0647\u0646 \u0628\u0627\u0632\u06cc\u06a9\u0646\u0627\u0646 \u0627\u0633\u062a\u0642\u0644\u0627\u0644 \u062f\u0631 \u0644\u06cc\u06af \u0642\u0647\u0631\u0645\u0627\u0646\u0627\u0646 \u0622\u0633\u06cc\u0627 \u0645\u0634\u062e\u0635 \u0634\u062f|trans-title=The jersey numbers of Esteghlal players for AFC Champions league were revealed.|publisher=[[Navad]]|language=Persian|date=14 August 2018|accessdate=17 December 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn 16 August 2018, Tariq made his competitive debut for Esteghlal as a second-half substitute in a 1\u20130 away defeat against [[F.C. Pars Jonoubi Jam|Pars Jonoubi Jam]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tarafdari.com/node/1057600?page=3|title=\u067e\u0627\u0631\u0633 \u062c\u0646\u0648\u0628\u06cc \u062c\u0645 1-0 \u0627\u0633\u062a\u0642\u0644\u0627\u0644 \u062a\u0647\u0631\u0627\u0646|trans-title=Pars Jonoubi Jam 1-0 Esteghlal|publisher=Tarafdari|language=Persian|date=16 August 2018|accessdate=17 December 2018}}</ref> On 29 November 2018, he scored his first goal for the club in a 3\u20130 victory over [[Sanat Naft Abadan F.C.|Sanat Naft Abadan]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tarafdari.com/node/1160086|title=\u0627\u0633\u062a\u0642\u0644\u0627\u0644 3-0 \u0635\u0646\u0639\u062a \u0646\u0641\u062a \u0622\u0628\u0627\u062f\u0627\u0646\u061b \u062e\u06cc\u0632 \u0622\u0628\u06cc \u0647\u0627 \u0628\u0647 \u0633\u0645\u062a \u0628\u0627\u0644\u0627\u06cc \u062c\u062f\u0648\u0644 \u0628\u0627 \u062f\u0631\u062e\u0634\u0634 \u0641\u0631\u0634\u06cc\u062f \u0627\u0633\u0645\u0627\u0639\u06cc\u0644\u06cc|trans-title= Esteghlal 3-0 Sanat Naft Abadan|publisher=Tarafdari|language=Persian|date=29 November 2018|accessdate=17 December 2018}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nOn 30 December 2012, Tariq made his international debut for the [[Iraq national football team|Iraqi senior team]], against [[Tunisia national football team|Tunisia]], in a friendly match that ended in a 2\u20131 loss for Iraq.<ref name=\"Iraq vs. Tunisia - 30 December 2012\">{{cite web|title=Iraq vs. Tunisia - 30 December 2012|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2012/12/30/world/friendlies/iraq/tunisia/1415985/|website=Soccerway|language=Arabic}}</ref> Tariq, on that day, became the youngest player in the history of the [[Iraq national football team]] to wear the Iraqi shirt at the age of 16.<ref name=\"ACUP\"/>\n\n===2013 Gulf Cup===\nThe [[2013 Gulf Cup of Nations|2013 Gulf Cup]] was the tournament that led Tariq to success and made him shine. He started the first match of [[Iraq national football team|Iraq]], as a [[Left winger (football)|left winger]], against [[Saudi Arabia national football team|Saudi Arabia]], that ended in a 2\u20130 win for Iraq.<ref name=\"Iraq 2-0 Saudi Arabia - 6 January 2013\">{{cite web|title=Iraq 2-0 Saudi Arabia|url=http://www.gulfcup.com/soccer/matches/matcha.php?match_id=340&period=21|website=Gulf Cup|language=Arabic}}</ref><ref name=\"Iraq vs. Saudi Arabia - 6 January 2013\">{{cite web|title=Iraq vs. Saudi Arabia - 6 January 2013|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2013/01/06/asia/gulf-cup/saudi-arabia/iraq/1404981/|website=Soccerway|language=Arabic}}</ref> Tariq went on to start the second match of Iraq, against [[Kuwait national football team|Kuwait]], that ended in a 1\u20130 win for Iraq.<ref name=\"Kuwait 0-1 Iraq - 9 January 2013\">{{cite web|title=Kuwait 0-1 Iraq|url=http://www.gulfcup.com/soccer/matches/matcha.php?match_id=343&period=21|website=Gulf Cup|language=Arabic}}</ref><ref name=\"Iraq vs. Kuwait - 9 January 2013\">{{cite web|title=Iraq vs. Kuwait - 9 January 2013|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2013/01/09/asia/gulf-cup/iraq/kuwait/1404982/?ICID=PL_MS_05|website=Soccerway|language=Arabic}}</ref> In Iraq's third match, against [[Yemen national football team|Yemen]], Tariq stayed on the bench, being replaced with [[Nabeel Sabah]] as the left winger. The match ended in a 2\u20130 win for Iraq.<ref name=\"Yemen 0-2 Iraq - 12 January 2013\">{{cite web|title=Yemen 0-2 Iraq|url=http://www.gulfcup.com/soccer/matches/matcha.php?match_id=348&period=21|website=Gulf Cup|language=Arabic}}</ref><ref name=\"Iraq vs. Yemen - 12 January 2013\">{{cite web|title=Iraq vs. Yemen - 12 January 2013|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2013/01/12/asia/gulf-cup/iraq/yemen/1404985/?ICID=PL_MS_09|website=Soccerway|language=Arabic}}</ref> Tariq started the semi-final match against [[Bahrain national football team|Bahrain]]. The match went to extra time and then penalties, after a 1\u20131 draw. Iraq won 4\u20132 on penalties.<ref name=\"Bahrain 3-5 Iraq - 15 January 2013\">{{cite web|title=Bahrain 3-5 Iraq|url=http://www.gulfcup.com/soccer/matches/matcha.php?match_id=350&period=21|website=Gulf Cup|language=Arabic}}</ref><ref name=\"Iraq vs. Bahrain - 15 January 2013\">{{cite web|title=Iraq vs. Bahrain - 15 January 2013|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2013/01/15/asia/gulf-cup/iraq/bahrain/1418681/?ICID=PL_MS_02|website=Soccerway|language=Arabic}}</ref> In the final, Tariq started as a [[left midfielder]], against [[UAE national football team|UAE]], in the match that ended in a 2\u20131 loss for Iraq. Therefor, Iraq became the runners-up of the 2013 edition.<ref name=\"Iraq 1-2 UAE - 18 January 2013\">{{cite web|title=Iraq 1-2 UAE|url=http://www.gulfcup.com/soccer/matches/matcha.php?match_id=352&period=21|website=Gulf Cup|language=Arabic|access-date=2015-05-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141129112506/http://www.gulfcup.com/soccer/matches/matcha.php?match_id=352&period=21|archive-date=2014-11-29|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name=\"Iraq vs. UAE - 18 January 2013\">{{cite web|title=Iraq vs. UAE - 18 January 2013|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2013/01/18/asia/gulf-cup/united-arab-emirates/iraq/1418682/?ICID=PL_MS_01|website=Soccerway|language=Arabic}}</ref>\n\n===2015 AFC Asian Cup qualification===\nTariq contributed in 4 matches out of the total 6 for [[Iraq national football team|Iraq]] in the [[2015 AFC Asian Cup qualification]]. The matches' results were a 1\u20130 win against [[Indonesia national football team|Indonesia]] on 6 February 2013,<ref name=\"Iraq 1-0 Indonesia - 6 February 2013\">{{cite web|title=Iraq 1-0 Indonesia - 6 February 2013|url=http://www.the-afc.com/afcasfeeds?fixtureid=6942&stageid=273&tMode=H&view=ajax&show=matchsummary|website=AFC ASIAN CUP AUSTRALIA 2015}}</ref> 0\u20131 loss against [[China national football team|China]] on 22 March,<ref name=\"China 1-0 Iraq - 22 March 2013\">{{cite web|title=China 1-0 Iraq - 22 March 2013|url=http://www.the-afc.com/afcasfeeds?fixtureid=6945&stageid=273&tMode=H&view=ajax&show=matchsummary|website=AFC ASIAN CUP AUSTRALIA 2015}}</ref> 1\u20132 loss against [[Saudi Arabia national football team|Saudi Arabia]] on 15 November,<ref name=\"Saudi Arabia 2-1 Iraq - 15 November 2013\">{{cite web|title=Saudi Arabia 2-1 Iraq - 15 November 2013|url=http://www.the-afc.com/afcasfeeds?fixtureid=6949&stageid=273&tMode=H&view=ajax&show=matchsummary|website=AFC ASIAN CUP AUSTRALIA 2015}}</ref> and a 2\u20130 win against Indonesia on 19 November.<ref name=\"Indonesia 0-2 Iraq - 19 November 2013\">{{cite web|title=Indonesia 0-2 Iraq - 19 November 2013|url=http://www.the-afc.com/afcasfeeds?fixtureid=6950&stageid=273&tMode=H&view=ajax&show=matchsummary|website=AFC ASIAN CUP AUSTRALIA 2015}}</ref> Eventually, Iraq qualified to the [[2015 AFC Asian Cup]] by winning 3\u20131 against China, where Tariq wasn't included.<ref name=\"Iraq 3-1 China - 5 March 2014\">{{cite web|title=Iraq 3-1 China - 5 March 2014|url=http://www.the-afc.com/afcasfeeds?fixtureid=6952&stageid=273&tMode=H&view=ajax&show=matchsummary|website=AFC ASIAN CUP AUSTRALIA 2015}}</ref>\n\n===2014 FIFA World Cup qualification===\nTariq played only two matches of the [[2014 FIFA World Cup qualification (AFC)]], in the [[2014 FIFA World Cup qualification \u2013 AFC Fourth Round|fourth round]]. The first, against [[Oman national football team|Oman]], on 4 June 2013, where he got subbed off in the 55th minute after failing to clear the ball. The match ended in a 1\u20130 win for Oman.<ref name=\"Oman 1-0 Iraq - 4 June 2013\">{{cite web|title=Oman 1-0 Iraq - 4 June 2013|url=https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/matches/round=257777/match=300191860/report.html|website=FIFA}}</ref> On the other match, against [[Australia national soccer team|Australia]], on 18 June, Tariq got subbed off again in the 75th minute. The match was also lost by [[Iraq national football team|Iraq]] and won 1\u20130 by Australia.<ref name=\"Australia 1-0 Iraq - 18 June 2013\">{{cite web|title=Australia 1-0 Iraq - 18 June 2013|url=https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/matches/round=257777/match=300191857/report.html|website=FIFA}}</ref> After this match, Iraq was at the bottom of Group B, having 5 points from 8 matches played, resulting in not qualifying to the World Cup.<ref name=\"2014 World Cup Qualification for Asia - Final Stages\">{{cite web|title=2014 World Cup Qualification for Asia - Final Stages|url=http://www.kooora.com/?c=5985&stage=4|website=Kooora|language=Arabic}}</ref>\n\n===2013 FIFA U20 World Cup===\nTariq was included in the [[2013 FIFA U-20 World Cup]] [[2013 FIFA U-20 World Cup squads|squad]]. He started in all of [[Iraq national football team|Iraq]]'s matches. In the first match of [[Iraq under-20 national football team|Iraq under-20 team]], they came up against [[England under-19 national football team|England]], where it ended in a hard 2\u20132 draw for Iraq.<ref name=\"England 2-2 Iraq - 23 June 2013\">{{cite web|title=England 2-2 Iraq - 23 June 2013|url=https://www.fifa.com/u20worldcup/matches/round=259235/match=300232818/report.html|website=FIFA}}</ref> In the second match, they were against [[Egypt national under-20 football team|Egypt]], where Tariq had his first yellow card with an international team in the 57th minute and it ended in a 2\u20131 win for Iraq.<ref name=\"Iraq 2-1 Egypt - 26 June 2013\">{{cite web|title=Iraq 2-1 Egypt - 26 June 2013|url=https://www.fifa.com/u20worldcup/matches/round=259235/match=300232825/report.html|website=FIFA}}</ref> In the third match, against [[Chile national under-20 football team|Chile]], it ended also in a 2\u20131 win for Iraq.<ref name=\"Iraq 2-1 Chile - 29 June 2013\">{{cite web|title=Iraq 2-1 Chile - 29 June 2013|url=https://www.fifa.com/u20worldcup/matches/round=259235/match=300232822/report.html|website=FIFA}}</ref> In the Round of 16, Iraq won over [[Paraguay national under-20 football team|Paraguay]], after the match went to extra time, 1\u20130.<ref name=\"Iraq 1-0 Paraguay - 3 July 2013\">{{cite web|title=Iraq 1-0 Paraguay - 3 July 2013|url=https://www.fifa.com/u20worldcup/matches/round=259233/match=300232827/report.html|website=FIFA}}</ref> In the quarterfinal, Iraq won over [[Korea Republic national under-20 football team|Korea Republic]]. After the match ended in a 3\u20133 draw, it went to penalties, where Iraq won 5\u20134.<ref name=\"Iraq 3-3 Korea Republic (Iraq won on penalties 5-4) - 7 July 2013\">{{cite web|title=Iraq 3-3 Korea Republic (Iraq won on penalties 5-4) - 7 July 2013|url=https://www.fifa.com/u20worldcup/matches/round=259231/match=300232836/report.html|website=FIFA}}</ref> In the semifinal, Iraq lost against [[Uruguay national under-20 football team|Uruguay]]. After the match ended in a 1\u20131 draw, it went to penalties again, but this time, Iraq lost 6-7, with Tariq scoring his penalty.<ref name=\"Iraq 1-1 Uruguay (Uruguay won on penalties 6-7) - 10 July 2013\">{{cite web|title=Iraq 1-1 Uruguay (Uruguay won on penalties 6-7) - 10 July 2013|url=https://www.fifa.com/u20worldcup/matches/round=259229/match=300232828/report.html|website=FIFA}}</ref>\n\n===2014 Asian Games===\nTariq was one of the best players that played in the [[Football at the 2014 Asian Games \u2013 Men|2014 Asian Games]], scoring four goals, being the top scorer for [[Iraq under-23 national football team|Iraq]], along with [[Younis Mahmoud]]. Tariq started in all of Iraq's matches. He scored in Iraq's second match, on 17 September 2014, against [[Japan national under-23 football team|Japan]], in the 12th minute.<ref name=\"Japan 1 vs. 3 Iraq - 17 September 2014\">{{cite web|title=Japan 1 vs. 3 Iraq - 17 September 2014|url=http://www.incheon2014.kr/Sports/FB/Result?RSC=FBM400D03&lang=en|website=17th Asian Games Incheon 2014|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924042548/http://www.incheon2014.kr/Sports/FB/Result?RSC=FBM400D03&lang=en|archivedate=24 September 2015}}</ref> Tariq was the man of the match in Iraq's third game, against [[Kuwait national under-23 football team|Kuwait]], scoring two goals in the 16th and 62nd minutes and playing quite well.<ref name=\"Kuwait 0 vs. 3 Iraq - 21 September 2014\">{{cite web|title=Kuwait 0 vs. 3 Iraq - 21 September 2014|url=http://www.incheon2014.kr/Sports/FB/Result?RSC=FBM400D06&lang=en|website=17th Asian Games Incheon 2014|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150518100057/http://www.incheon2014.kr/Sports/FB/Result?RSC=FBM400D06&lang=en|archivedate=18 May 2015}}</ref> Tariq scored his fourth goal in Iraq's round of 16 match, against [[Tajikistan national under-23 football team|Tajikistan]], in the early 7th minute.<ref name=\"Iraq 4 vs. 2 Tajikistan - 26 September 2014\">{{cite web|title=Iraq 4 vs. 2 Tajikistan - 26 September 2014|url=http://www.incheon2014.kr/Sports/FB/Result?RSC=FBM400406&lang=en|website=17th Asian Games Incheon 2014|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150518100100/http://www.incheon2014.kr/Sports/FB/Result?RSC=FBM400406&lang=en|archivedate=18 May 2015}}</ref> Iraq won in the quarterfinal, 3\u20130 against [[Saudi Arabia national under-23 football team|Saudi Arabia]],<ref name=\"Saudi Arabia 0 vs. 3 Iraq - 28 September 2014\">{{cite web|title=Saudi Arabia 0 vs. 3 Iraq - 28 September 2014|url=http://www.incheon2014.kr/Sports/FB/Result?RSC=FBM400303&lang=en|website=17th Asian Games Incheon 2014|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924042536/http://www.incheon2014.kr/Sports/FB/Result/?RSC=FBM400303&lang=en|archivedate=24 September 2015}}</ref> but lost in the semifinal, against [[North Korea national under-23 football team|North Korea]], 0\u20131, where Tariq didn't perform that well.<ref name=\"Iraq 0 vs. 1 North Korea - 30 September 2014\">{{cite web|title=Iraq 0 vs. 1 North Korea - 30 September 2014|url=http://www.incheon2014.kr/Sports/FB/Result?RSC=FBM400202&lang=en|website=17th Asian Games Incheon 2014|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924042543/http://www.incheon2014.kr/Sports/FB/Result?RSC=FBM400202&lang=en|archivedate=24 September 2015}}</ref> In the third place match, Iraq won, gaining the bronze medal.<ref name=\"Thailand 0 vs. 1 Iraq - 2 October 2014\">{{cite web|title=Thailand 0 vs. 1 Iraq - 2 October 2014|url=http://www.incheon2014.kr/Sports/FB/Result?RSC=FBM400102&lang=en|website=17th Asian Games Incheon 2014|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150518100103/http://www.incheon2014.kr/Sports/FB/Result?RSC=FBM400102&lang=en|archivedate=18 May 2015}}</ref>\n\n===2014 Gulf Cup===\nTariq was a part of the squad that had the worst ever performance for [[Iraq national football team|Iraq]] in the [[Gulf Cup of Nations|Gulf Cup]], since the [[2009 Gulf Cup of Nations|2009 edition]], in the [[2014 Gulf Cup of Nations|2014 Gulf Cup]]. He started in all of the three matches of Iraq, lost 0\u20131 against [[Kuwait national football team|Kuwait]],<ref name=\"Iraq vs. Kuwait - 14 November 2014\">{{cite web|title=Iraq vs. Kuwait - 14 November 2014|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2014/11/14/asia/gulf-cup/iraq/kuwait/1896331/|website=Soccerway|language=Arabic}}</ref> drew 1\u20131 with [[Oman national football team|Oman]], where Tariq got a yellow card,<ref name=\"Iraq vs. Oman - 17 November 2014\">{{cite web|title=Iraq vs. Oman - 17 November 2014|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2014/11/17/asia/gulf-cup/iraq/oman/1896335/|website=Soccerway|language=Arabic}}</ref> and lost 2\u20130 against the [[UAE national football team|UAE]].<ref name=\"UAE vs. Iraq - 20 November 2014\">{{cite web|title=UAE vs. Iraq - 20 November 2014|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2014/11/20/asia/gulf-cup/united-arab-emirates/iraq/1896337/|website=Soccerway|language=Arabic}}</ref>\n\n===2015 AFC Asian Cup===\nTariq was included in [[Iraq national football team|Iraq]]'s squad for the [[2015 AFC Asian Cup]], but he only played 57 minutes of the first match of Iraq, against [[Jordan national football team|Jordan]].<ref name=\"Jordan 0-1 Iraq - 12 January 2015\">{{cite web|title=Jordan 0-1 Iraq - 12 January 2015|url=http://www.the-afc.com/afcasfeeds?fixtureid=8258&stageid=327&tMode=C&view=ajax&show=matchsummary|website=AFC ASIAN CUP AUSTRALIA 2015}}</ref> Iraq eventually reached the semi-final and lost, ending in 4th place.<ref name=\"Iraq gets 4th place at AFC Asian Cup\">{{cite news|title=Iraq gets 4th place at AFC Asian Cup|url=http://en.alforatnews.com/modules/news/article.php?storyid=15608|agency=Alforat News}}</ref>\n\n===2019 AFC Asian cup===\nTariq participated in the [[2019 AFC Asian Cup]], hosted by UAE. Tariq was one of Iraq's key players in the tournament, helping them reach the round of 16 where they were knocked out by Qatar in a 1\u20130 loss.\n\n===International goals===\n:''Scores and results list Iraq's goal tally first.''<ref name=\"NFT\">{{cite web|url=https://www.national-football-teams.com/player/29198/Humam_Tariq.html|title=Tariq, Humam|publisher=National Football Teams}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! # !! Date !! Venue !! Opponent !! Score !! Result !! Competition\n|-\n| 1. || 28 March 2015 || [[The Sevens Stadium]], [[Dubai]]|| {{fb|Congo DR}} || align=center | '''2'''\u20131 || align=center | 2\u20131 || rowspan=2 | [[Exhibition game|Friendly]]\n|-\n| 2. || 28 December 2018|| [[Suheim Bin Hamad Stadium]], [[Doha]]|| {{fb|Palestine}} || align=center | '''1'''\u20130 || align=center | 1\u20130\n|-\n| 3. || 8 January 2019 || [[Zayed Sports City Stadium]], [[Abu Dhabi]] || {{fb|VIE}} || align=center | '''2'''\u20132 || align=center | 3\u20132 ||[[2019 AFC Asian Cup Group D|2019 AFC Asian Cup]]\n|}\n\n==Style of play==\n{{Quote box| width = 25%| align = right| quoted = 1| quote = The secret for the success of [[Younis Mahmoud|Younis]] at the [[2013 Gulf Cup of Nations|Gulf Cup]] was Humam, and the secret to the future success of Younis will be Humam Tariq, because of the quick link-up play from Humam, as he's the fastest player on the flanks to Younis, assisting him and one of the important keys to opening the door of the opposition is that he's the quickest player in Iraq (on the ball).| salign = left| source = \u2014 [[Hakim Shaker]] commenting on Tariq<ref name=\"Humam Tariq full scout report - Outside of the Boot\" />}}\n\nTariq uses his small frame and explosive pace to burst past defenders and find space on the flank and down the middle. His distribution is already excellent for such a young man. The midfielder is an excellent crosser of the ball and he is also known for his good finishing which leads to plenty of goals, and his confident passing can open up any game.<ref name=\"Humam Tariq style - Eyefootball.com\">{{cite web|last1=Patel|first1=Ketan|title=Humam Tariq|url=https://www.eyefootball.com/news/23535/Humam-Tariq.html|website=Eyefootball.com|date=June 7, 2015}}</ref> Often compared to [[Raheem Sterling]], Tariq plays in an offensive midfield role and has a combination of speed and vision that is not that common. He has an explosive quickness in the first few meters and a good technique.<ref name=\"Humam Tariq skills - The Next Messi\">{{cite web|title=Humam Tariq|url=http://nextmessi.com/2014/08/humam-tariq/|website=The Next Messi|date=August 27, 2014}}</ref> Due to his build and style of play, he has often been compared to [[Lionel Messi]], gaining him the nickname \"Iraqi Messi\".\n\nTariq's definitive position could be as a deep-lying forward, behind a central striker, giving him the freedom of movement, to draw opposing players out of position and exploit holes in the opposition's defense. He doesn't look or play anything like an old fashioned attacking wide-man, but is deployed as more of an unorthodox modern-day winger, tucking in when his team is without the ball and often asked to press the opposition to regain back possession.<ref name=\"Humam Tariq full scout report - Outside of the Boot\" /> His exceptional crossing, passing, finishing, skills and electric pace, combined with his experience at a young age, make Tariq one of the best Asian talents to look forward to.\n\n==Personal life==\nHumam Tariq was born to the Naoush family from the [[Adhamiyah]] district in [[Baghdad]].<ref name=\"Families of Adhamiyah - ShakwMakw\">{{cite web|title=Families of Adhamiyah|url=http://www.shakwmakw.com/vb/showthread.php?t=366707|website=ShakwMakw|language=Arabic}}</ref> He is the grandson of Faraj Naoush, the creator of Confectionery of Faraj Naoush and His Sons, which was created in 1954.<ref name=\"Faraj Naoush 1954 - Al-Gardenia\">{{cite web|last1=Mahmoud|first1=Suroor Merza|title=Engravings that talk about the regions of al-Hara, al-Safinah and Saada street|url=http://www.algardenia.com/2014-04-04-19-52-20/menouats/10915-2014-06-12-09-53-16.html|website=Al-Gardenia|language=Arabic}}</ref> It was one of the best confectionery shops in Iraq, especially, during the [[Sanctions against Iraq]] in the 1990s. Humam helped out in the family business in his spare time making the sweets.<ref name=\"Faraj Naoush commercial 1999 - Youtube\">{{cite web|last1=Naoush|first1=Harith|title=Faraj Naoush and His Sons commercial 1999|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QeFapAc15eM|website=Youtube|language=Arabic|date=January 17, 2012}}</ref><ref name=OLY>{{cite web|last1=Mubarak|first1=Hassanin|title=Iraq Olympic Team Profile|url=https://ahdaaf.me/2016/08/02/iraq-olympic-team-profile/}}</ref> Humam is married. His son Tariq was born on July 2017.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BXPe7dIAiss|title=Humam on Instagram|language=en}}</ref>\n\n==Honours==\n===Club===\n;Al-Quwa Al-Jawiya\n*[[AFC Cup]]: [[2016 AFC Cup|2016]], [[2017 AFC Cup|2017]]\n*[[Iraq FA Cup]]: [[2016 Iraq FA Cup Final|2015\u201316]]\n*[[Iraqi Premier League]]: [[2016\u201317 Iraqi Premier League|2016\u201317]]\n\n===International===\n;Iraq U-19\n*[[AFC U-19 Championship]] runner-up: [[2012 AFC U-19 Championship|2012]]\n;Iraq U-20\n*[[FIFA U-20 World Cup]] fourth place: [[2013 FIFA U-20 World Cup|2013]]\n;Iraq U-22\n*[[AFC U-22 Championship]] winner: [[2013 AFC U-22 Championship|2013]]\n;Iraq U-23\n*[[Football at the Asian Games|Asian Games]] bronze medallist: [[Football at the 2014 Asian Games \u2013 Men|2014]]\n;Iraq\n*[[Arabian Gulf Cup]] runner-up: [[2013 Gulf Cup of Nations|2013]]\n*[[AFC Asian Cup]] fourth-place: [[2015 AFC Asian Cup|2015]]\n\n===Individual===\n*World Military Cup Asian Qualification Zone Best Player: 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.alahwartv.net/pages/news.php?nid=14430|title=Best player in the World Military Cup Asian Zone qualifications|language=Arabic|access-date=2013-07-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150518082545/http://www.alahwartv.net/pages/news.php?nid=14430|archive-date=2015-05-18|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n*Outside of the Boot's 100 Best Young Players to Watch: 2015.<ref name=\"100 Best Young Players to Watch in 2015 - Outside of the Boot\">{{cite web|title=100 Best Young Players to Watch in 2015, Midfielders 35 \u2013 21|url=http://outsideoftheboot.com/2014/12/12/100-best-young-players-2015-midfielders/|website=Outside of the Boot}}</ref>\n*[[Soccer Iraq#Team of the Decade|Soccer Iraq Team of the Decade]]: 2010\u20132019\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Navboxes colour\n|title= Iraq squads\n| bg          = white\n| bordercolor = #008000\n|list1=\n{{Iraq squad 2015 AFC Asian Cup}}\n{{Iraq men's football squad 2016 Summer Olympics}}\n{{Iraq squad 2019 AFC Asian Cup}}\n}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Tariq, Humam}}\n[[Category:1996 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Association football wingers]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Baghdad]]\n[[Category:Iraqi footballers]]\n[[Category:Iraqi expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Al-Quwa Al-Jawiya players]]\n[[Category:Al Ahli Club (Dubai) players]]\n[[Category:Al Dhafra FC players]]\n[[Category:Esteghlal F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Iraqi expatriate sportspeople in the United Arab Emirates]]\n[[Category:Iraqi expatriate sportspeople in Iran]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in the United Arab Emirates]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Iran]]\n[[Category:Iraq international footballers]]\n[[Category:Footballers at the 2014 Asian Games]]\n[[Category:2015 AFC Asian Cup players]]\n[[Category:2019 AFC Asian Cup players]]\n[[Category:Asian Games medalists in football]]\n[[Category:Asian Games bronze medalists for Iraq]]\n[[Category:Footballers at the 2016 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Olympic footballers of Iraq]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 2014 Asian Games]]\n[[Category:UAE Pro League players]]\n", "name_user": "John of Reading", "label": "safe", "comment": "Typo/generalfixes, replaced: on July 2017 \u2192 in July 2017, Therefor \u2192 Therefore", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Humam_Tariq"}
{"title_page": "Archie Gemmill", "text_new": "{{EngvarB|date=April 2013}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2013}}\n{{lead too short|date=January 2010}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Archie Gemmill\n| image = \n| fullname = Archibald Gemmill<ref name=Hugman>{{Hugman|7138|accessdate=29 November 2019}}</ref>\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=y|1947|3|24}}<ref name=Hugman/>\n| birth_place = [[Paisley, Renfrewshire|Paisley]],<ref name=Hugman/> Scotland\n| currentclub  =\n| height = {{height|m=1.65}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.worldfootball.net/spieler_profil/Alex-Kyle/|title=Alexander Kyle|work=worldfootball.net}}</ref>\n| position = [[Midfielder]]\n| years1 = 1964\u20131967  \n| clubs1 = [[St Mirren F.C.|St Mirren]] \n| caps1 = 65   \n| goals1 = 9  \n| years2 = 1967\u20131970  \n| clubs2 = [[Preston North End F.C.|Preston North End]] \n| caps2 = 99  \n| goals2 = 13  \n| years3 = 1970\u20131977  \n| clubs3 = [[Derby County F.C.|Derby County]] \n| caps3 = 261  \n| goals3 =  17  \n| years4 = 1977\u20131979  \n| clubs4 = [[Nottingham Forest F.C.|Nottingham Forest]] \n| caps4 = 58   \n| goals4 =  4  \n| years5 = 1979\u20131982  \n| clubs5 = [[Birmingham City F.C.|Birmingham City]] \n| caps5 = 97  \n| goals5 =  12  \n| years6 = 1982 \n| clubs6 = [[Jacksonville Tea Men]] \n| caps6 = 32   \n| goals6 =  2  \n| years7 = 1982 \n| clubs7 = [[Wigan Athletic F.C.|Wigan Athletic]] \n| caps7 = 11   \n| goals7 =  0  \n| years8 = 1982\u20131984\n| clubs8 = [[Derby County F.C.|Derby County]] \n| caps8 = 63   \n| goals8 =  8  \n| totalcaps  = 686\n| totalgoals = 65\n| nationalyears1 = 1971\u20131981\n| nationalteam1 = [[Scotland national football team|Scotland]]\n| nationalcaps1 = 43  \n| nationalgoals1 = 8 \n| manageryears1 = 1994\u20131996\n| managerclubs1 = [[Rotherham United F.C.|Rotherham United]]\n| manageryears2 = 2005\u20132009\n| managerclubs2 = [[Scotland national under-19 football team|Scotland U19]]\n}}\n\n'''Archibald Gemmill''' (born 24 March 1947) is a Scottish former [[association football|footballer]]. During his career he won the [[European Cup]], three [[English football champions|English league titles]] and captained his national side.  He scored a goal against the [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands]] in the [[1978 FIFA World Cup]], which is regularly cited as one of the greatest scored in the competition.\n\n==Club career==\n===Early career===\nGemmill was born in [[Paisley, Renfrewshire]]. His early career at [[St Mirren F.C.|St Mirren]] was ruined by a succession of injuries, not least a broken ankle in early 1966. He was sent on to replace [[Jim Clunie]] on 13 August 1966 in a [[Scottish League Cup]] tie at [[Shawfield Stadium|Shawfield]] to become the first tactical substitute in Scottish football history.<ref>[http://www.stmirren.info/Players/Archie%20Gemmill.htm Archie Gemmill player profile] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060504032542/http://www.stmirren.info/Players/Archie%20Gemmill.htm |date=4 May 2006 }}, www.stmirren.info</ref> Gemmill was sold for [[pound sterling|\u00a3]]13,000 to [[Preston North End F.C.|Preston North End]].\n\n===Derby County===\nHe came to the attention of [[Peter Taylor (footballer, born 1928)|Peter Taylor]], Derby County's assistant manager. Taylor then told Derby manager, [[Brian Clough]], about Gemmill who had been considering signing for the reigning champions [[Everton F.C.|Everton]]. Clough saw him as a player who could pass well and had the type of energy that would drive an attack forward. Clough drove to Gemmill's house. When the player refused to sign for Derby (who had never won the [[English football champions|league title]]), Clough told him that he was going to sleep outside in the car. \"But my wife invited him in and he stayed the night,\" Gemmill said. Clough, eventually, got his man for \u00a360,000 over [[fried egg]]s the following morning.\n\nGemmill scored only three goals for the Rams that season, but they became Football League champions the following year. He was suspended for the [[European Cup 1972-73|1973 European Cup]] semi-final, but he became club captain in place of the injured [[Roy McFarland]] when the Rams won their second title in 1975. He made 324 appearances in total for the club and scored 25 goals. He left Derby after playing five times for them early in the 1977/78 season.<ref name=gemm>[http://www.sporting-heroes.net/football/nottingham-forest-fc/archie-gemmill-5060/league-appearances-for-forest_a14705/ \"Archie Gemmill  Nottingham Forest FC, Sporting Heroes]</ref>\n\n===Nottingham Forest===\n\nGemmill joined [[Nottingham Forest F.C.|Nottingham Forest]] for \u00a325,000 in September 1977<ref name=gemm/> becoming the third ex Derby title winning player of Clough's to join him at Forest. [[John O'Hare]] and [[John McGovern (footballer)|John McGovern]] were the other two. He played 58 times for Forest in the league, scoring three goals. He was integral to the success of the club in the late 1970s, but was dropped for the [[1979 European Cup Final]]. Gemmill referred to the decision later:<ref name = \"BBC interview\"/> {{quote|I was devastated at the time. I was led to believe I'd be playing in the match... I was far from happy. I hated every minute of the 90 and I hated afterwards as well.}}\n\n===Later career===\n\nHe signed for [[Birmingham City F.C.|Birmingham City]] debuting on 18 August 1979 in a 4\u20133 defeat at home to [[Fulham F.C.|Fulham]]. He played 97 League matches for the Blues, scoring 12 goals.\n\nIn early 1982, Gemmill crossed the Atlantic to play for the [[Jacksonville Tea Men]] of the [[North American Soccer League (1968-1984)|NASL]]. He only stayed for one season playing 32 league games.\n\nIn September 1982, he joined up with former teammate and club manager [[Larry Lloyd]] at [[Wigan Athletic F.C.|Wigan Athletic]] but only stayed for 11 matches. He returned to Derby County as player-coach to become [[Peter Taylor (footballer, born 1928)|Peter Taylor]]'s first signing for the club in 1982. He retired from playing in 1984.\n\n==International career==\nGemmill played 43 times and scored eight goals for [[Scotland national football team|Scotland]], and captained the team on 22 occasions. \n\nThe most famous moment of Gemmill's career when he scored a goal against the [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands]] in a Group D fixture at the [[1978 FIFA World Cup|1978 World Cup]], which is regularly rated as amongst the greatest goals ever scored in a World Cup match.<ref>[http://www.cbc.ca/sports/worldcup2006/history/events/top10-goals.html TOP 10 WORLD CUP GOALS OF ALL TIME], [[CBC Sports]].</ref><ref>[http://msn.foxsports.com/soccer/story/471494/World-Cup-Top-Tens:-Top-Ten-Goals World Cup Top Tens: Top Ten Goals]  {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080512150249/http://msn.foxsports.com/soccer/story/471494/World-Cup-Top-Tens%3A-Top-Ten-Goals |date=12 May 2008 }}, [[Fox Sports (USA)|Fox Sports]], 3 May 2002.</ref> Scotland needed to win the game by three goals to qualify for the next stage of the tournament, having had very poor results in their first two games. With his team leading 2\u20131 in the 68th minute, Gemmill scored a goal which was described by ''[[The Scotsman]]'' as follows: {{quote|In 68 minutes, however, Scotland went 3\u20131 up when Archie Gemmill scored one of the great goals of this World Cup so far. The little midfield player homed in on goal, played a magnificent one-two with [[Kenny Dalglish|Dalglish]], then sprinted into the box and thumped a glorious goal past [[Jan Jongbloed|Jongbloed]] to revive all the hopes which had died the death this past fortnight. It was an extraordinary goal and an extraordinary moment. Suddenly Scotland were dreaming of glory again\".<ref>[http://sport.scotsman.com/topics.cfm?tid=658&id=1287982002 The lion roars  \u2013 too late], ''[[The Scotsman]]'', 11 June 1978.</ref>}} Three minutes later, [[Johnny Rep]] scored a second goal for the Netherlands, which was deflected off Gemmill's outstretched leg and flew past [[Alan Rough]]'s dive. The game ended 3\u20132, denying Scotland a spot in the second round.\n\nThe goal is referenced in the film ''[[Trainspotting (movie)|Trainspotting]]'', in which characters Tommy and Lizzie decide to make love while watching a homemade [[pornography|porno]] film, only to see it has been replaced with a football tape called \"100 Great Goals\" which features Gemmill's strike. At the same time, Renton ([[Ewan McGregor]]), who had switched the tapes in their cases and borrowed Tommy and Lizzie's tape, says after [[orgasm|climaxing]] during [[Sexual intercourse|sex]], \"I haven't felt that good since Archie Gemmill scored against [[Netherlands national football team|Holland]] in 1978!\" Gemmill first saw ''Trainspotting'' on a club outing with [[Rotherham United F.C.|Rotherham]], and his reaction was:<ref name = \"BBC interview\">[http://www.bbc.co.uk/nottingham/content/articles/2005/09/29/archie_gemmill_interview_feature.shtml Archie, Archie Gemmill!], [[BBC]].</ref> \"I got absolutely slaughtered by the lads... to be fair I was a bit embarrassed by it.\"\n\n==After playing==\nGemmill returned to Nottingham Forest to be a coach alongside [[Brian Clough]] in 1984. Later he  [[manager (association football)|managed]] [[Rotherham United F.C.|Rotherham United]] for two seasons in the mid-1990s.\n\nHis son [[Scot Gemmill]] became a [[Scotland national football team|Scotland]] player in the 1990s. In 1970, Archie drove his pregnant wife back to Scotland to ensure that Scot would be born there.<ref name = \"Scot\">Grant, Michael. [http://findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_qn4156/is_20020331/ai_n12575359 Scotland: Scot Gemmill; 'If it was up to my dad I wouldn't be here], ''[[Sunday Herald]]'', 31 March 2002.</ref> Archie became unhappy that Scot was selected for squads but was rarely used in games.<ref name = \"Scot\"/> He eventually told Scot to stop making himself available for selection, but Scot disagreed and continued to play for Scotland until late in his career.<ref name = \"Scot\"/>\n\nGemmill managed the [[Scotland national under-19 football team]] that finished second in the [[2006 UEFA European Under-19 Football Championship]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/internationals/5221720.stm |title=Scotland U19 1-2 Spain U19 |work=BBC Sport |publisher=BBC |date=29 July 2006 |accessdate=16 April 2014}}</ref> and thereby qualified for the [[2007 FIFA U-20 World Cup]] in Canada.\n\n==Career statistics==\n===International appearances===\n\n{| class=wikitable style=\"text-align:center\"\n|+ Appearances and goals by national team and year<ref>{{SFA Profile|id=113777}}</ref>\n|-\n!National team!!Year!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=\"9\"|[[Scotland national football team|Scotland]]\n|1971||3||1\n|-\n|1972||4||0\n|-\n|1975||2||0\n|-\n|1976||6||1\n|-\n|1977||7||0\n|-\n|1978||10||4\n|-\n|1979||2||1\n|-\n|1980||7||1\n|-\n|1981||2||0\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total!!43!!8\n|}\n\n===International goals===\n\n:''Scores and results list Scotland's goal tally first''\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! No. !! Date !! Venue !! Opponent !! Score !! Result !! Competition !! Ref\n|-\n| align=center | 1. || 13 October 1971 || [[Hampden Park]], [[Glasgow]] || {{fb|POR}} || align=center | 2\u20131 || align=center | 2\u20131 || [[UEFA Euro 1972 qualifying]] || <ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rsssf.com/tabless/scot-intres1975.html |title=Scotland \u2013 International Matches 1971\u20131975 |website= |publisher=RSSSF |date=17 October 2019 |accessdate=4 November 2019 |first1=Alan |last1=Brown |first2=Gabriele |last2=Tossani}}</ref>\n|-\n| align=center| 2. || 8 May 1976 || Hampden Park, Glasgow || {{fb|NIR}} || align=center | 1\u20130 || align=center | 3\u20130 || [[1975\u201376 British Home Championship]] || <ref name = \"rsssf 76\">{{cite web |url=http://www.rsssf.com/tabless/scot-intres1980.html |title=Scotland \u2013 International Matches 1976\u20131980 |website= |publisher=RSSSF |date=23 May 2019 |accessdate=4 November 2019 |first1=Alan |last1=Brown |first2=Gabriele |last2=Tossani}}</ref>\n|-\n| align=center| 3. || 22 February 1978 || Hampden Park, Glasgow || {{fb|BUL}} || align=center | 1\u20131 || align=center | 2\u20131 || [[Friendly match]] || <ref name = \"rsssf 76\"/>\n|-\n| align=center | 4. || rowspan=2|11 June 1978 || rowspan=2| [[Estadio Malvinas Argentinas|Estadio Ciudad de Mendoza]], [[Mendoza, Argentina|Mendoza]] || rowspan=2|{{fb|NED}} || align=center | 2\u20131 || rowspan=2 align=center | 3\u20132 ||rowspan=2| [[1978 FIFA World Cup]] ||rowspan=2|<ref name = \"rsssf 76\"/>\n|-\n| align=center | 5. || align=center | 3\u20131\n|-\n| align=center | 6. || 25 October 1978 || Hampden Park, Glasgow || {{fb|NOR}} || align=center | 3\u20132 || align=center | 3\u20132 || [[UEFA Euro 1980 qualifying]] ||<ref name = \"rsssf 76\"/>\n|-\n| align=center | 7. || 17 October 1979 || Hampden Park, Glasgow || {{fb|AUT}} || align=center | 1\u20131 || align=center | 1\u20131 || UEFA Euro 1980 qualifying ||<ref name = \"rsssf 76\"/>\n|-\n| align=center | 8. || 26 March 1980 || Hampden Park, Glasgow || {{fb|POR}} || align=center | 4\u20131 || align=center | 4\u20131 || UEFA Euro 1980 qualifying ||<ref name = \"rsssf 76\"/>\n|-\n|}\n\n== Honours ==\n'''Player'''\n;Derby County\n* [[Football League First Division|First Division]]: [[1971\u201372 in English football|1971\u201372]], [[1974\u201375 in English football|1974\u201375]]\n* [[FA Community Shield|FA Charity Shield]]: [[1975 FA Charity Shield|1975]]\n\n;Nottingham Forest\n* [[Football League First Division|First Division]]: [[1977\u201378 in English football|1977\u201378]]\n* [[Football League Cup]]: [[1978 Football League Cup Final|1977\u201378]], [[1979 Football League Cup Final|1978\u201379]]\n* FA Charity Shield 1978\n* [[European Cup]]: [[1979 European Cup Final|1978\u201379]]\n\n'''Manager'''\n;Rotherham United\n* [[Football League Trophy]]: [[1995\u201396 Football League Trophy|1995\u201396]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n*Archie Gemmill, ''Both Sides of the Border'', 296 pages (12 September 2005), Publisher: Hodder & Stoughton Ltd ({{ISBN|0-340-89570-5}})\n*John Hodge and Irvine Welsh, ''Trainspotting: Screenplay'', Faber and Faber, 2000 ({{ISBN|0-571-20320-5}})\n\n{{Navboxes colour\n| title = Awards\n| bg    = gold\n| fg    = navy\n| list1 = \n{{Goal of the Season}}\n{{1979\u201380 Football League Second Division PFA Team of the Year}}\n{{Derby County F.C. Player of the Year}}\n{{Scottish Football Hall of Fame}}\n}}\n{{Scotland Squad 1978 World Cup}}\n{{Rotherham United F.C. managers}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Gemmill, Archie}}\n[[Category:1947 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1978 FIFA World Cup players]]\n[[Category:Birmingham City F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Derby County F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n[[Category:Jacksonville Tea Men players]]\n[[Category:North American Soccer League (1968\u20131984) players]]\n[[Category:Nottingham Forest F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Paisley, Renfrewshire]]\n[[Category:Scottish Football Hall of Fame inductees]]\n[[Category:Preston North End F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Scotland international footballers]]\n[[Category:Expatriate soccer players in the United States]]\n[[Category:Scottish footballers]]\n[[Category:St Mirren F.C. players]]\n[[Category:English Football League players]]\n[[Category:Wigan Athletic F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Scottish Football League players]]\n[[Category:Derby County F.C. non-playing staff]]\n[[Category:Scotland under-23 international footballers]]\n[[Category:Scottish Sports Hall of Fame inductees]]\n[[Category:Scottish expatriate sportspeople in the United States]]\n[[Category:Scottish expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:UEFA Champions League winning players]]\n", "text_old": "{{EngvarB|date=April 2013}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2013}}\n{{lead too short|date=January 2010}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Archie Gemmill\n| image = \n| fullname = Archibald Gemmill<ref name=Hugman>{{Hugman|7138|accessdate=29 November 2019}}</ref>\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=y|1947|3|24}}<ref name=Hugman/>\n| birth_place = [[Paisley, Renfrewshire|Paisley]],<ref name=Hugman/> Scotland\n| currentclub  =\n| height = {{height|m=1.65}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.worldfootball.net/spieler_profil/archie-gemmill/|title=Archie Gemmill|work=worldfootball.net}}</ref>\n| position = [[Midfielder]]\n| years1 = 1964\u20131967  \n| clubs1 = [[St Mirren F.C.|St Mirren]] \n| caps1 = 65   \n| goals1 = 9  \n| years2 = 1967\u20131970  \n| clubs2 = [[Preston North End F.C.|Preston North End]] \n| caps2 = 99  \n| goals2 = 13  \n| years3 = 1970\u20131977  \n| clubs3 = [[Derby County F.C.|Derby County]] \n| caps3 = 261  \n| goals3 =  17  \n| years4 = 1977\u20131979  \n| clubs4 = [[Nottingham Forest F.C.|Nottingham Forest]] \n| caps4 = 58   \n| goals4 =  4  \n| years5 = 1979\u20131982  \n| clubs5 = [[Birmingham City F.C.|Birmingham City]] \n| caps5 = 97  \n| goals5 =  12  \n| years6 = 1982 \n| clubs6 = [[Jacksonville Tea Men]] \n| caps6 = 32   \n| goals6 =  2  \n| years7 = 1982 \n| clubs7 = [[Wigan Athletic F.C.|Wigan Athletic]] \n| caps7 = 11   \n| goals7 =  0  \n| years8 = 1982\u20131984\n| clubs8 = [[Derby County F.C.|Derby County]] \n| caps8 = 63   \n| goals8 =  8  \n| totalcaps  = 686\n| totalgoals = 65\n| nationalyears1 = 1971\u20131981\n| nationalteam1 = [[Scotland national football team|Scotland]]\n| nationalcaps1 = 43  \n| nationalgoals1 = 8 \n| manageryears1 = 1994\u20131996\n| managerclubs1 = [[Rotherham United F.C.|Rotherham United]]\n| manageryears2 = 2005\u20132009\n| managerclubs2 = [[Scotland national under-19 football team|Scotland U19]]\n}}\n\n'''Archibald Gemmill''' (born 24 March 1947) is a Scottish former [[association football|footballer]]. During his career he won the [[European Cup]], three [[English football champions|English league titles]] and captained his national side.  He scored a goal against the [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands]] in the [[1978 FIFA World Cup]], which is regularly cited as one of the greatest scored in the competition.\n\n==Club career==\n===Early career===\nGemmill was born in [[Paisley, Renfrewshire]]. His early career at [[St Mirren F.C.|St Mirren]] was ruined by a succession of injuries, not least a broken ankle in early 1966. He was sent on to replace [[Jim Clunie]] on 13 August 1966 in a [[Scottish League Cup]] tie at [[Shawfield Stadium|Shawfield]] to become the first tactical substitute in Scottish football history.<ref>[http://www.stmirren.info/Players/Archie%20Gemmill.htm Archie Gemmill player profile] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060504032542/http://www.stmirren.info/Players/Archie%20Gemmill.htm |date=4 May 2006 }}, www.stmirren.info</ref> Gemmill was sold for [[pound sterling|\u00a3]]13,000 to [[Preston North End F.C.|Preston North End]].\n\n===Derby County===\nHe came to the attention of [[Peter Taylor (footballer, born 1928)|Peter Taylor]], Derby County's assistant manager. Taylor then told Derby manager, [[Brian Clough]], about Gemmill who had been considering signing for the reigning champions [[Everton F.C.|Everton]]. Clough saw him as a player who could pass well and had the type of energy that would drive an attack forward. Clough drove to Gemmill's house. When the player refused to sign for Derby (who had never won the [[English football champions|league title]]), Clough told him that he was going to sleep outside in the car. \"But my wife invited him in and he stayed the night,\" Gemmill said. Clough, eventually, got his man for \u00a360,000 over [[fried egg]]s the following morning.\n\nGemmill scored only three goals for the Rams that season, but they became Football League champions the following year. He was suspended for the [[European Cup 1972-73|1973 European Cup]] semi-final, but he became club captain in place of the injured [[Roy McFarland]] when the Rams won their second title in 1975. He made 324 appearances in total for the club and scored 25 goals. He left Derby after playing five times for them early in the 1977/78 season.<ref name=gemm>[http://www.sporting-heroes.net/football/nottingham-forest-fc/archie-gemmill-5060/league-appearances-for-forest_a14705/ \"Archie Gemmill  Nottingham Forest FC, Sporting Heroes]</ref>\n\n===Nottingham Forest===\n\nGemmill joined [[Nottingham Forest F.C.|Nottingham Forest]] for \u00a325,000 in September 1977<ref name=gemm/> becoming the third ex Derby title winning player of Clough's to join him at Forest. [[John O'Hare]] and [[John McGovern (footballer)|John McGovern]] were the other two. He played 58 times for Forest in the league, scoring three goals. He was integral to the success of the club in the late 1970s, but was dropped for the [[1979 European Cup Final]]. Gemmill referred to the decision later:<ref name = \"BBC interview\"/> {{quote|I was devastated at the time. I was led to believe I'd be playing in the match... I was far from happy. I hated every minute of the 90 and I hated afterwards as well.}}\n\n===Later career===\n\nHe signed for [[Birmingham City F.C.|Birmingham City]] debuting on 18 August 1979 in a 4\u20133 defeat at home to [[Fulham F.C.|Fulham]]. He played 97 League matches for the Blues, scoring 12 goals.\n\nIn early 1982, Gemmill crossed the Atlantic to play for the [[Jacksonville Tea Men]] of the [[North American Soccer League (1968-1984)|NASL]]. He only stayed for one season playing 32 league games.\n\nIn September 1982, he joined up with former teammate and club manager [[Larry Lloyd]] at [[Wigan Athletic F.C.|Wigan Athletic]] but only stayed for 11 matches. He returned to Derby County as player-coach to become [[Peter Taylor (footballer, born 1928)|Peter Taylor]]'s first signing for the club in 1982. He retired from playing in 1984.\n\n==International career==\nGemmill played 43 times and scored eight goals for [[Scotland national football team|Scotland]], and captained the team on 22 occasions. \n\nThe most famous moment of Gemmill's career when he scored a goal against the [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands]] in a Group D fixture at the [[1978 FIFA World Cup|1978 World Cup]], which is regularly rated as amongst the greatest goals ever scored in a World Cup match.<ref>[http://www.cbc.ca/sports/worldcup2006/history/events/top10-goals.html TOP 10 WORLD CUP GOALS OF ALL TIME], [[CBC Sports]].</ref><ref>[http://msn.foxsports.com/soccer/story/471494/World-Cup-Top-Tens:-Top-Ten-Goals World Cup Top Tens: Top Ten Goals]  {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080512150249/http://msn.foxsports.com/soccer/story/471494/World-Cup-Top-Tens%3A-Top-Ten-Goals |date=12 May 2008 }}, [[Fox Sports (USA)|Fox Sports]], 3 May 2002.</ref> Scotland needed to win the game by three goals to qualify for the next stage of the tournament, having had very poor results in their first two games. With his team leading 2\u20131 in the 68th minute, Gemmill scored a goal which was described by ''[[The Scotsman]]'' as follows: {{quote|In 68 minutes, however, Scotland went 3\u20131 up when Archie Gemmill scored one of the great goals of this World Cup so far. The little midfield player homed in on goal, played a magnificent one-two with [[Kenny Dalglish|Dalglish]], then sprinted into the box and thumped a glorious goal past [[Jan Jongbloed|Jongbloed]] to revive all the hopes which had died the death this past fortnight. It was an extraordinary goal and an extraordinary moment. Suddenly Scotland were dreaming of glory again\".<ref>[http://sport.scotsman.com/topics.cfm?tid=658&id=1287982002 The lion roars  \u2013 too late], ''[[The Scotsman]]'', 11 June 1978.</ref>}} Three minutes later, [[Johnny Rep]] scored a second goal for the Netherlands, which was deflected off Gemmill's outstretched leg and flew past [[Alan Rough]]'s dive. The game ended 3\u20132, denying Scotland a spot in the second round.\n\nThe goal is referenced in the film ''[[Trainspotting (movie)|Trainspotting]]'', in which characters Tommy and Lizzie decide to make love while watching a homemade [[pornography|porno]] film, only to see it has been replaced with a football tape called \"100 Great Goals\" which features Gemmill's strike. At the same time, Renton ([[Ewan McGregor]]), who had switched the tapes in their cases and borrowed Tommy and Lizzie's tape, says after [[orgasm|climaxing]] during [[Sexual intercourse|sex]], \"I haven't felt that good since Archie Gemmill scored against [[Netherlands national football team|Holland]] in 1978!\" Gemmill first saw ''Trainspotting'' on a club outing with [[Rotherham United F.C.|Rotherham]], and his reaction was:<ref name = \"BBC interview\">[http://www.bbc.co.uk/nottingham/content/articles/2005/09/29/archie_gemmill_interview_feature.shtml Archie, Archie Gemmill!], [[BBC]].</ref> \"I got absolutely slaughtered by the lads... to be fair I was a bit embarrassed by it.\"\n\n==After playing==\nGemmill returned to Nottingham Forest to be a coach alongside [[Brian Clough]] in 1984. Later he  [[manager (association football)|managed]] [[Rotherham United F.C.|Rotherham United]] for two seasons in the mid-1990s.\n\nHis son [[Scot Gemmill]] became a [[Scotland national football team|Scotland]] player in the 1990s. In 1970, Archie drove his pregnant wife back to Scotland to ensure that Scot would be born there.<ref name = \"Scot\">Grant, Michael. [http://findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_qn4156/is_20020331/ai_n12575359 Scotland: Scot Gemmill; 'If it was up to my dad I wouldn't be here], ''[[Sunday Herald]]'', 31 March 2002.</ref> Archie became unhappy that Scot was selected for squads but was rarely used in games.<ref name = \"Scot\"/> He eventually told Scot to stop making himself available for selection, but Scot disagreed and continued to play for Scotland until late in his career.<ref name = \"Scot\"/>\n\nGemmill managed the [[Scotland national under-19 football team]] that finished second in the [[2006 UEFA European Under-19 Football Championship]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/internationals/5221720.stm |title=Scotland U19 1-2 Spain U19 |work=BBC Sport |publisher=BBC |date=29 July 2006 |accessdate=16 April 2014}}</ref> and thereby qualified for the [[2007 FIFA U-20 World Cup]] in Canada.\n\n==Career statistics==\n===International appearances===\n\n{| class=wikitable style=\"text-align:center\"\n|+ Appearances and goals by national team and year<ref>{{SFA Profile|id=113777}}</ref>\n|-\n!National team!!Year!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=\"9\"|[[Scotland national football team|Scotland]]\n|1971||3||1\n|-\n|1972||4||0\n|-\n|1975||2||0\n|-\n|1976||6||1\n|-\n|1977||7||0\n|-\n|1978||10||4\n|-\n|1979||2||1\n|-\n|1980||7||1\n|-\n|1981||2||0\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total!!43!!8\n|}\n\n===International goals===\n\n:''Scores and results list Scotland's goal tally first''\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! No. !! Date !! Venue !! Opponent !! Score !! Result !! Competition !! Ref\n|-\n| align=center | 1. || 13 October 1971 || [[Hampden Park]], [[Glasgow]] || {{fb|POR}} || align=center | 2\u20131 || align=center | 2\u20131 || [[UEFA Euro 1972 qualifying]] || <ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rsssf.com/tabless/scot-intres1975.html |title=Scotland \u2013 International Matches 1971\u20131975 |website= |publisher=RSSSF |date=17 October 2019 |accessdate=4 November 2019 |first1=Alan |last1=Brown |first2=Gabriele |last2=Tossani}}</ref>\n|-\n| align=center| 2. || 8 May 1976 || Hampden Park, Glasgow || {{fb|NIR}} || align=center | 1\u20130 || align=center | 3\u20130 || [[1975\u201376 British Home Championship]] || <ref name = \"rsssf 76\">{{cite web |url=http://www.rsssf.com/tabless/scot-intres1980.html |title=Scotland \u2013 International Matches 1976\u20131980 |website= |publisher=RSSSF |date=23 May 2019 |accessdate=4 November 2019 |first1=Alan |last1=Brown |first2=Gabriele |last2=Tossani}}</ref>\n|-\n| align=cen