{"title_page": "3 Idiots", "text_new": "{{short description|2009 Indian Hindi language comedy film}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=February 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2020}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = 3 Idiots\n| image          = Threeidiots2.jpg\n| alt            = <!-- see WP:ALT -->\n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| director       = [[Rajkumar Hirani]]\n| producer       = [[Vidhu Vinod Chopra]]\n| screenplay     = [[Abhijat Joshi]]<br />[[Rajkumar Hirani]]<br />Vidhu Vinod Chopra\n| story          = [[Rajkumar Hirani]]<br />Abhijat Joshi\n| based on       = ''[[Five Point Someone]]'' by <br/>[[Chetan Bhagat]]\n| starring       = {{plainlist|\n* [[Aamir Khan]]\n* [[R. Madhavan|Madhavan]]\n* [[Sharman Joshi]]\n* [[Kareena Kapoor]]\n* [[Boman Irani]]\n* [[Omi Vaidya]]\n}}\n| narrator       = [[R. Madhavan|Madhavan]]\n| music          = [[S. Bhattacharya]]\n| cinematography = [[C. K. Muraleedharan]]\n| editing        = Rajkumar Hirani\n| studio         = [[Vinod Chopra Films]]\n| distributor    = [[Reliance Entertainment|Reliance BIG Pictures]]\n| released       = {{Film date|2009|12|25|India|df=y}}\n| runtime        = 170 minutes<ref name=Runtime>{{cite web|title=''3 IDIOTS'' (12A)|url=http://www.bbfc.co.uk/releases/3-idiots-0|work=[[British Board of Film Classification]]|accessdate=5 October 2012|date=17 December 2009}}</ref>\n| country        = India\n| language       = [[Hindi]]\n| budget         = {{INR}} 55 [[crore]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.economictimes.indiatimes.com/2012-08-26/news/33386102_1_box-office-movie-rotten-tomatoes/2|title=Business of Rs 100-cr films: Who gets what and why|work=[[The Economic Times]]|publisher=[[The Times Group]]|date=26 August 2012|accessdate=22 February 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"exchange\"/>\n| gross          = <!--Do not remove-->{{Estimation}}<!--per discussion at WP:ICTF--> {{INR}} 460 crore<ref name=\":1\"/><ref name=\"hollywoodreporter\"/>\n}}\n'''''3 Idiots''''' is a 2009 Indian [[Hindi]]-language [[Coming-of-age story|coming-of-age]] [[comedy-drama]] film co-written (with [[Abhijat Joshi]]) and directed by [[Rajkumar Hirani]]. Starring [[Aamir Khan]], [[R. Madhavan|Madhavan]], [[Sharman Joshi]], [[Kareena Kapoor]], [[Boman Irani]] and [[Omi Vaidya]], the film follows the friendship of three students at an Indian [[engineering college]] and is a [[satire]] about the social pressures under an Indian education system.<ref name=\"scmp\"/><ref name=\"economic_china\"/><ref name=\"kaist\"/> The film is narrated through parallel dramas, one in the present and the other ten years in the past. It also incorporated real Indian inventions, namely those created by Remya Jose,<ref name=\"jose\"/> Mohammad Idris,<ref name=\"nif\"/> Jahangir Painter<ref name=\"mid\"/> and [[Sonam Wangchuk (engineer)|Sonam Wangchuk]].<ref name=\"telegraphindia\"/>\n\nProduced by [[Vidhu Vinod Chopra]] under the banner [[Vinod Chopra Films]], ''3 Idiots'' received widespread critical<ref name=\"rt\"/> and commercial success upon its release on 25 December 2009. The film was the highest-grossing film in its opening weekend in [[India]], had the highest opening day collections for an [[Indian film]] up until that point and also held the record for the highest net collections in the first week for a Bollywood film. It also became one of the few Indian films at the time to become successful in [[East Asia]]n markets such as [[China]]<ref name=overseas>{{cite web|title=Three Idiots Creates History in China|url=http://www.boxofficeindia.com/boxnewsdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=3866&nCat=|work=30 December 2011|publisher=BoxOfficeIndia. Com|accessdate=30 December 2011}}</ref> and [[Japan]],<ref name=\"qz\"/> eventually bringing its worldwide gross to {{INR|link=yes}}392{{nbsp}}[[crore]] ($90{{nbsp}}million){{efn|name=Gross}}<ref name=\":1\"/><ref name=\"hollywoodreporter\"/> \u2014 it was the [[List of highest-grossing Indian films|highest-grossing Indian film ever]] at the time.<ref name=\"forbes\"/> The film also had a social impact on attitudes to [[education in India]].<ref name=\"Hussain\"/>\n\nThe film won six [[Filmfare Awards]] including [[Filmfare Award for Best Film|Best Film]] and three [[National Film Awards]] including [[National Film Award for Best Popular Film Providing Wholesome Entertainment|Best Popular Film]]. Overseas, it won the Grand Prize at Japan's Videoyasan Awards<ref name=\"videoyasan\"/><ref name=\"nikkatsu\"/><ref name=\"qz\"/> while was nominated for [[Japan Academy Prize for Outstanding Foreign Language Film|Best Outstanding Foreign Language Film]] at the [[Japan Academy Prize (film)|Japan Academy Awards]]<ref name=\"japan-hungama\"/><ref name=\"japan-ibn\"/> and Best Foreign Film at China's [[Beijing International Film Festival]].<ref name=\"maoyan\"/> This film was remade in [[Tamil language|Tamil]] as ''[[Nanban (2012 film)|Nanban]]'' (2012), which also received critical praise and commercial success.<ref name=\"nanban_ibn\">{{cite web|url=http://www.moneycontrol.com/news/entertainment/will-nanban-repeatmagic3-idiots_650433.html |title=Will 'Nanban' repeat the magic of '3 Idiots'? \u2013 IBNLive.com |publisher=[[CNBC]] |accessdate=5 March 2012}}</ref><ref name=\"nanban_hindustantimes\">{{cite web |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/Entertainment/Reviews/Gautaman-Bhaskaran-s-review-Nanban/Article1-797009.aspx |title=Gautaman Bhaskaran's review: Nanban |work=[[Hindustan Times]] |date=14 January 2012 |accessdate=5 March 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120312175929/http://www.hindustantimes.com/Entertainment/Reviews/Gautaman-Bhaskaran-s-review-Nanban/Article1-797009.aspx |archivedate=12 March 2012  }}</ref> ''Nanban'' had a [[Telugu cinema|Telugu]] dubbed version titled ''[[Snehitudu]].'' A [[Mexico|Mexican]] remake, ''[[3 idiotas]]'', was also released in 2017.<ref>{{cite web|title=3 idiotas se estrenar\u00e1 en el 2017|url=http://www.debate.com.mx/show/3-idiotas-se-estrenara-en-el-2017-20160713-0024.html}}</ref>\n\n== Plot ==\nIn the year 1999, Farhan Qureshi and Raju Rastogi begin their college year in the prestigious Imperial College of [[Engineering]] (ICE) in [[Delhi]]. They are joined by Ranchoddas Chanchad, nicknamed \"Rancho\", as their roommate. They meet Manmohan a.k.a. \"Millimetre\", an adolescent boy helping the students . He is persuaded by Rancho to sneak into school and get educated. While Farhan chose to pursue engineering over his passion for photography to appease his father, Raju has taken the course in an attempt to end his family's poverty and is always afraid of failing. Rancho, on the other hand, is genuinely passionate in science and engineering. He believes in hands-on learning and tends to give unorthodox answers in class, resulting in him coming into conflict with the professors, particularly the institution's director, Viru Sahastrabuddhe, whom the ICE community nicknames \"Virus\". Virus's traditional and strict philosophies on education contrast sharply with Rancho's carefree love of learning. Meanwhile, Chatur, nicknamed \"Silencer\" (because of his nature of silently farting), is an arrogant student with little knowledge of Hindi due to his Ugandan-Tamilian upbringing, who is obsessed with topping the exams and invariably learns by rote.\n\nSometime later, the trio finds that a student named Joy Lobo, whose interest in machines was as much as Rancho, committed [[suicide]] by [[Suicide by hanging|hanging himself]], which was caused by [[Depression (mood)|depression]] after Virus informs Joy's father that Joy would be unable to graduate that year due to a delay in his submission of an assignment. Joy had taken longer as he wanted to perfect his breakthrough drone design of a quad-copter, and also due to a break on account of his father's brief illness. Rancho criticises Virus' method of teaching and tries to show him how much pressure engineers face when they study, angering him further. Rancho visits his friends' families, and later, the trio then gatecrashes the wedding of Virus' elder daughter, Mona to eat good food. They meet and befriend Pia, who turns out to be Virus' younger daughter and a resident student at the city's hospital. Rancho advises Pia not to marry her fianc\u00e9e Suhas Tandon because he's madly obsessed with expensive jewellery, brands, and prices and has no true love for her. Rancho gives Pia a demo on Suhas' attitude by spilling mint sauce on his shoes to annoy him. When Virus spots the trio, he summons Farhan and Raju on the next working day and tells them of the consequences of being friends with Rancho by comparing their families' incomes. He tells them that Rancho comes from a very rich family and does not need to worry about getting good grades and making a career. Affected, Raju moves out and into Chatur's room. During the Teachers Day celebration, Chatur is humiliated when he delivers a Hindi speech modified by Rancho and as a result, he bets Rancho that ten years later, they would see who is more successful. Sometime later, Pia is at the mall with Suhas and spots Rancho with an invention named after Virus; The Virus Inverter. Rancho explains to Pia that he dislikes the way her father teaches his students and that they end up lame like Suhas. Rancho plays a prank on Suhas, pretending that Pia lost her watch, to prove that Suhas shows more value to expensive stuff rather than her. Fed up with Suhas' behaviour, she tells him off. Rancho and Pia save Raju's dying father; Raju reconciles with his friends while Pia falls in love with Rancho.\n\nOne night during their senior year, Farhan and Raju are upset that they are trailing behind in their grades every year and that Rancho is always in the front of every school picture. Farhan exposes Rancho of not telling Pia that he is in love with her and hasn't told her for the past four years. The three friends drunkenly break into the Sahastrabuddhe residence so that Rancho can propose to Pia. As the trio escape, Virus recognises Raju and, on the next day, threatens to expel him unless he writes a letter recommending Rancho for expulsion. Unwilling to betray Rancho or disappoint his family, Raju unsuccessfully attempts suicide and ends up in a [[coma]]. With intensive care and support from his friends, Raju recovers just in time for his first job interview on the campus, which he succeeds in cracking. Meanwhile, Rancho and Pia post Farhan's letter to his favourite Hungarian wildlife photographer Andre Istvan, who offers him a position as an assistant. On Rancho's advice, he communicates his dream to his father, who though reluctant at first, gives his blessings for the sake of his son's happiness.\n\nInfuriated by this and Rancho's influence, Virus sets a difficult final exam paper to fail Raju, wherein Pia tries to help the trio by revealing to them the location of the exam paper in her father's office; unfortunately, Virus finds out and expels them. Pia confronts Virus about her brother who had committed suicide because he couldn't meet Virus' expectation of clearing the engineering exam. That same night, the pregnant Mona goes into labour during a heavy storm that cuts off all traffic and electricity in the city. Rancho and the other students help them by using their engineering knowledge to quickly modify a [[vacuum cleaner]] into a [[ventouse]] and deliver the baby with the help of Pia over a video call. A grateful Virus finally acknowledges Rancho as an extraordinary student and revokes their expulsion. On graduation day, Rancho suddenly disappears shortly after the ceremony ends.\n\nTen years later, in 2009, Farhan is a successful wildlife photographer, while Raju is married and settled with his family in a comfortable lifestyle with a corporate job and Chatur is married and the vice-president of a reputable corporation in the [[United States]] wanting to crack a business deal with a world renowned scientist and businessman with 400 patents to his name, Phunsukh Wangdu for whom he has been asking an appointment for over 1 year  ; none among the three of them have heard from Rancho since graduation. Reuniting at the ICE campus, after Chatur reminds them about the bet,they travel to Shimla, where Rancho was spotted in the background of a snapshot taken by Chatur's secretary, Tracy, who was trying to get an appointment with Wangdu. Chatur then went through the Shimla directory and found the address of Rancho. Upon arrival, they meet a man who turns out to be the real Ranchoddas Chanchad ([[Javed Jaffrey]]) at his father's funeral and the photos of the Rancho they knew replaced with the real one. From him, Farhan and Raju learn that the Rancho they knew was actually \"Chhote\", the smart son of the gardener who was a servant to the Chanchad family who would sneak into school wearing Ranchoddas' old uniform and help Ranchoddas with his schoolwork until he was found out by a teacher who told Ranchoddas' father.Ranchoddas' father then arranged for Chhote to attend ICE in his son's name so that  Ranchoddas could take credit for the degree while  he was in London for 4 years . He also told Chhote to cut off all contact with his ICE friends after graduating but Chhote was sure that Farhan and Raju would come looking for him. Ranchoddas provides Chhote's address in [[Ladakh]], where he is a schoolteacher. On the way, they pass [[Manali, Himachal Pradesh|Manali]] where against Chatur's wishes, they rescue and prevent Pia from marrying Suhas, who is now a changed man but reverts to his old ways when Raju, disguised as the housekeeping man, puts mint sauce on his wedding jacket, making Raju run away from the wedding in his attire. \n\nUpon arrival in Ladakh, the four head to the village school and witness the young students' inventions that resemble Chhote's college projects. They are reunited with the adult educated Manmohan, now going by the nickname \"Centimetre\" who has now become a helper for Chhote after receiving a letter from him to help him. He tells them that Chhote never forgot about them, stealing and keeping Pia's scooter helmet as a memento, reading Farhan's photography books and Raju's blog. He then tells them where to find Chhote. The four happily reunite with Chhote  to which Pia and Chhote smooch, while Chatur, unaware of Chhote's secret thinking he is Rancho, insults and asks Chhote to sign a contract stating that he is the least successful person; Chhote does so without commenting. As Chatur walks away triumphantly, Chhote reveals that his real name is Phunsukh Wangdu, to his friends' and Pia's surprise and delight. Realizing this, a horrified Chatur accepts his defeat and pleads him to sign his contract while Phunsukh and his friends run away laughing. In the end,  Wangdu tells everyone his theory: \"Follow excellence and success will by itself follow you\".\n\n== Cast ==\n* [[Aamir Khan]] as Ranchoddas \"Rancho\" Shamaldas Chanchad / Chhote / Phunsukh Wangdu, one of the titular trio in the engineering college who vanishes after graduation and whom his two friends hunt for 5 years, while telling stories of their time in college together. Rancho was prodigal student, with contempt for the inhumanity of the college's system. At the end of the film, he is shown to be a famous scientist, entrepreneur and business magnate who also teaches young children when he takes a break from researching.\n* [[R. Madhavan|Madhavan]] as Farhan Qureshi, the film's narrator and one of the trio whose father persuades him to study engineering over his dream career of wildlife photography; in the end he is shown to have published several books of photographs.\n* [[Sharman Joshi]] as Raju Rastogi, another of the trio who comes from an impoverished family with a mother who is a retired school teacher and a paralysed father who worked as a postman. In the flashback story, his family was unable to afford the car that would be demanded as a [[Dowry system in India|dowry]] for his sister. In the present story, he is a settled married man in Delhi who has freed his family from poverty by becoming a wealthy executive.\n* [[Kareena Kapoor]] as Piya Sahastrabuddhe, Virus' younger daughter, an intelligent and capable doctor. Despite her father's disapproval, she and Rancho fall in love.\n* [[Boman Irani]] as Dr. Viru Sahastrabuddhe, the college's strict director known as \"Virus\" and Pia and Mona's father who acts as the film's antagonist. He stubbornly sticks to a doctrinal method of teaching, putting him at odds with Rancho. At the end, he is shown to have changed his doctrinal methods of teaching.\n* [[Omi Vaidya]] as Chatur Ramalingam, a [[Indians in Uganda|Ugandan-Indian]] educated in [[Tamil language|Tamil]]-speaking [[Pondicherry]] who has little knowledge of Hindi. His habit of being gassy due to consumption of pills to enhance his memorisation earns him the nickname Silencer. In the present story, he is vice-president of an American company (Rockledge Corporation) who discovers his success being overshadowed by Rancho in the end of the film. [[Baradwaj Rangan]] wrote that Chatur being a Tamil from Uganda makes him \"twice removed from the North Indians around him \u2013 a stranger to the nation as well as the national language.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/reviews/article87588.ece|title=3 Idiots|last=Rangan|first=Baradwaj|date=27 December 2009|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151127143622/http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/reviews/article87588.ece|archive-date=27 November 2015|work=[[New Indian Express]]}}</ref>\n* [[Rahul Kumar (actor)|Rahul Kumar]] as young Manmohan (nicknamed Millimetre), and [[Dushyant Wagh]] as adult Manmohan (Centimetre). As an adolescent, he earns a small living by doing errands for students, such as laundry, finishing assignments and getting groceries. Rancho persuades him to buy a school uniform and sneak into school to gain an education. Later he becomes an assistant to Rancho/Phunsukh Wangdu in Ladakh.\n* [[Mona Singh]] as Mona Sahastrabuddhe, Pia's elder sister and Virus's first daughter.\n* [[Parikshit Sahni]] as Mr Qureshi, Farhan's father, a strict but loving parent who just wants his son to be happy.\n* Farida Dadi as Mrs. Qureshi, Farhan's mother, a loving and caring parent.\n* [[Amardeep Jha]] as Mrs. Rastogi, Raju's mother, a retired schoolteacher and dedicated mother.\n* Mukund Bhatt as Mr. Rastogi, Raju's paralysed father who used to work as a postman.\n* Rajendra Patwardhan as Govind, Viru's personal assistant.\n* [[Javed Jaffrey]] as the real Ranchoddas Shyamaldas Chanchad. It is from him that Raju and Farhan learn the truth: Chanchad's father sponsored an orphaned servant boy called 'Chhote', who had demonstrated his intelligence and love of learning, to earn a degree in his name, while the real Ranchoddas was in London. He appreciates what Chhote did for him, and tells Raju and Farhan where to find him.\n* [[Arun Bali]] as Shyamaldas Chanchad, father of Ranchoddas Shyamaldas Chanchad.\n* [[Ali Fazal]] as Joy Lobo, a student with a passion for machines. After Virus tells him that he will not graduate, he commits suicide.\n* [[Akhil Mishra]] as Librarian Dubey.\n* [[Rohitash Gaud]] as Ranchoddas' (Real Ranchodas) servant.\n* [[Achyut Potdar]] as Machine Class Professor\n* [[Madhav Vaze]] as Joy Lobo's father.\n* Olivier Sanjay Lafont as Suhas Tandon, Piya's ex-fianc\u00e9, who cares only about money and ostentation.\n* [[Jayant Kripalani]] as a company head who conducts Raju's job interview.\n* Atul Tiwari as R.D. Tripathi, Education Minister in Auditorium during Silencer's speech.\n* Rajeev Ravindranathan as ragging senior student.\n* [[Supriya Shukla]] as Nurse with Pia.\n\n== Production ==\n[[Principal photography]] began on 28 July 2008. Hirani and his team left in late August for the shoot with the principal cast. The film was shot in [[Delhi]], [[Bangalore]], [[Mumbai]], [[Ladakh]], [[Chail, Himachal Pradesh|Chail]] and [[Shimla]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.filmapia.com/published/movies/3/3-idiots | title=Movie Locations for 3 Idiots|publisher=filmapia.com}}</ref> Aamir and the rest of the cast began shooting in early September. Hirani planned to wrap up the film by December.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiafm.com/news/2008/07/28/11730/index.html |title=Rajkumar Hirani's 3 Idiots goes on floors |publisher=indiafm.com |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080804233117/http://www.indiafm.com/news/2008/07/28/11730/index.html |archivedate=4 August 2008 }}</ref> The first scene was shot in an aircraft with Madhavan. From Mumbai, the crew and cast comprising Aamir and Kareena went to Ladakh for a 20-day schedule.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://ia.rediff.com/movies/2008/aug/28look1.htm |title=Shooting for 3 Idiots underway |publisher=Rediff}}</ref> Filming of the ICE college scenes took place at the [[Indian Institute of Management Bangalore|Indian Institute of Management, Bangalore]] campus for 33 days as a part of the second schedule of production. The dormitory scenes were filmed at the institution's female dormitory block.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thaindian.com/newsportal/uncategorized/shooting-three-idiots-is-like-holidaying-for-aamir-khan_100143291.html |title=Shooting 'Three Idiots' is like holidaying |publisher=the indian.com |access-date=11 February 2009 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120321022923/http://www.thaindian.com/newsportal/uncategorized/shooting-three-idiots-is-like-holidaying-for-aamir-khan_100143291.html |archive-date=21 March 2012 |url-status=dead  }}</ref>\n\nThe brains behind these innovations include Remya Jose, a student from [[Kerala]], who created the pedal operated washing-machine;<ref name=\"jose\">{{cite news|last=Raphael|first=Lisa|title=Watch This 14-Year-Old Girl's Washing Machine Hack in Action|url=http://www.brit.co/remya-jose-pedal-washing-machine/|accessdate=10 November 2016|publisher=Brit + Co.|date=19 June 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VhlUVdbU9Lk|title=Remya Jose's pedal operated washing machine / exercise machine|website=You Tube|publisher=Remya Jose|last1=Jose|first1=Remya|accessdate=10 November 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ecoideaz.com/innovative-green-ideas/pedal-power-machines|title=Innovative Pedal Power Machines|date=3 February 2015|website=www.ecoideaz.com/innovative-green-ideas/pedal-power-machines|publisher=Ecoideaz|last1=Sreelakshmy|first1=V.U.|accessdate=10 November 2016}}</ref> Mohammad Idris, a barber from Hasanpur Kalan in [[Meerut]] district in [[Uttar Pradesh]], who invented a bicycle-powered horse clipper;<ref name=\"nif\">{{cite web|url=http://nif.org.in/innovation/Cycle_Operated_Horse_Shaver/229|title=Cycle operated horse shaver|website=www.nif.org.in|publisher=National Innovation Fund|accessdate=10 November 2016}}</ref> and Jahangir Painter, a painter from Maharashtra, who made the scooter-powered flour mill.<ref name=\"mid\">{{cite web|url=http://www.mid-day.com/news/2009/dec/281209-3-idiots-scooter-flour-mill-Inventions-Pune.htm|title=The real brains behind 3 idiots|last=Sabnis|first=Vivek |date=28 December 2009|publisher=[[Mid Day]]|accessdate=29 April 2010|location=Pune}}</ref> The character Phunsuk Wangdu may have also drawn inspiration from [[Ladakh]]i inventor [[Sonam Wangchuk (engineer)|Sonam Wangchuk]], a mechanical engineering graduate from the [[National Institute of Technology, Srinagar]].<ref name=\"telegraphindia\">{{cite news|last=Menon|first=Shyam G.|title=What you did not watch in 3 Idiots - Rethink after Ladakh education initiative fell victim to bureaucracy and resentment|url=https://www.telegraphindia.com/1100719/jsp/frontpage/story_12700204.jsp|publisher=[[The Telegraph (Calcutta)]]|date=19 July 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Secmol founder Sonam Wangchuk wins Magasaysay Award |url=https://www.nationalheraldindia.com/national/secmol-founder-wins-magasaysay-award-sonam-wangchuk |accessdate=25 March 2020 |work=National Herald |date=3 August 2018 |language=en}}</ref>\n\n== Soundtrack ==\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = 3 Idiots\n| type       = Soundtrack\n| artist     = [[S. Bhattacharya]]\n| cover      = \n| alt        =\n| released   = 2009\n| recorded   =\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Feature film soundtrack]]\n| length     = 29:22\n| label      = [[T-Series (company)|T-Series]]\n| producer   = [[S. Bhattacharya]]\n| prev_title = [[Billu]]\n| prev_year  = 2009\n| next_title = [[Action Replayy]]\n| next_year  = 2010\n}}\n\n{{Album ratings\n| rev1 = [[Bollywood Hungama]]\n| rev1Score = {{Rating|3.5|5}}<ref>{{cite web|title=3 Idiots : Music Review by Joginder Tuteja |url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/musicreview/13910/index.html |work=Bollywood Hungama |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090519105032/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/musicreview/13910/index.html |archivedate=19 May 2009 }}</ref>\n| rev2 = Behindwoods\n| rev2Score = {{Rating|3.5|5}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/bollywood/hindi-music-reviews/3-idiots.html|title= 3 Idiots Music review|work=Behindwoods}}</ref>\n| rev3 = [[Rediff]]\n| rev3Score = {{Rating|3|5}}<ref>{{cite web|title=3 Idiots: Short 'n' sweet soundtrack|url=http://movies.rediff.com/report/2009/nov/11/music-review-3-idiots.htm|work=Rediff}}</ref>\n| rev4 = Planet Bollywood\n| rev4Score = {{Rating|7|10}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.planetbollywood.com/displayReview.php?id=m110909062049|title=3 Idiots|work=Planet Bollywood}}</ref>\n|noprose=yes}}\n\nThe film's soundtrack has music and lyrics by [[S. Bhattacharya]]. Bhattacharya won his 2nd National Award for his lyrics in Behti Hawa Sa. The film was the first time [[S. Bhattacharya]] composed for an Aamir Khan film after having composed numerous hit soundtracks for Salman and Shahrukh Khan. Although he had compsosed the background score to [[Raakh]] in 1989, the film had no songs.All the songs were major hits. \n\n{{Track listing\n| all_writing = \n| headline = Track listing\n| extra_column = Singer(s)\n| title1 = Aal Izz Well\n| length1 = 4:34\n| extra1 = [[Sonu Nigam]], [[Shaan (singer)|Shaan]], [[S. Bhattacharya]]\n| title2 = Zoobi Doobi\n| length2 = 4:06\n| extra2 = Sonu Nigam, [[Shreya Ghoshal]]\n| title3 = Behti Hawa Sa Tha Woh\n| length3 = 4:59\n| extra3 = [[S. Bhattacharya]], Shaan\n| title4 = Give Me Some Sunshine\n| length4 = 4:05\n| extra4 = [[Suraj Jagan]], [[Sharman Joshi]], [[Rahat Fateh Ali Khan]]\n| title5 = Jaane Nahin Denge Tujhe\n| length5 = 3:30\n| extra5 = Sonu Nigam\n| title6 = Zoobi Doobi\n| note6 = Remix\n| length6 = 3:27\n| extra6 = Sonu Nigam, Shreya Ghoshal\n| title7 = Aal Izz Well\n| note7 = Remix\n| length7 = 4:41\n| extra7 = Sonu Nigam, Shaan, [[S. Bhattacharya]], Jaive Samsun\n| total_length = 29:22\n| title8 = \n| length8 = \n| title9 = \n| length9 = \n| title10 = \n| length10 = \n}}\n\n== Release ==\nThe film initially opened up on 1550 prints worldwide.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://businessofcinema.com/bollywood-news/3-idiots-releases-with-highest-ever-print-screen-count/30196|title=3 Idiots releases with highest ever print & screen count|publisher=BusinessofCinema|accessdate=28 December 2011}}</ref> 3 Idiots was released in 1800 theatres in India, which was at that time a big domestic release.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-08-11/news-interviews/41268470_1_100-crore-club-chennai-express-150-cr |title=100-crore club is past, Its 150-crore club for 'Chennai Express' |work=The Times of India|accessdate=11 August 2013}}</ref> ''3 Idiots'' was released in 415 screens overseas.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/talaash-is-aamir-khans-film-a-hit-even-before-the-release/307969-8-66.html |title=Talaash: Is Aamir Khan's film a hit even before the release? |work=CNN IBN |accessdate=25 April 2013}}</ref>\n\nIt was expected to be the first Indian film to be officially released on [[YouTube]] on 25 March 2010, only 12 weeks after its initial theatrical release. Officially, it was released on YouTube in May 2012, but its access has since been restricted.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yto4_QFoLdA |title=3 idiots |publisher=YouTube |accessdate=14 May 2012}}</ref>However, it has been made available for online streaming on [[Netflix]], [[Prime Video]] and [[Sony LIV]].<ref>{{cite web|title=3 Idiots|url=https://reelgood.com/movie/3-idiots-2009|publisher=Reelgood.comlanguage=en}}</ref>\n\nThe film released in [[Taiwan]] on December 2010, followed by [[Hong Kong]] on 1 September 2011.<ref name=\"hkfilmart\"/> In [[China]], it was released as ''San Geshagua'' (\"Three Idiots\"),<ref name=\"economic_china\"/> in December 2011.<ref name=\"economictimes\"/> In [[South Korea]], it was released in 2011.<ref name=\"kaist\"/> Alongside the original Hindi version, a [[Mandarin Chinese]] dubbed version was also released, with the popular actress [[Tang Wei]] (known for ''[[Lust, Caution]]'') voicing Kareena Kapoor's role<ref name=\"hindu_china\">{{cite news|last=Krishnan|first=Ananth|title=Success of 3 Idiots breaks China's Bollywood Great Wall|url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/Success-of-3-Idiots-breaks-Chinas-Bollywood-Great-Wall/article13349901.ece|newspaper=[[The Hindu]]|accessdate=29 March 2012|location=Beijing, China|date=2 January 2012}}</ref> and [[Huang Bo]] voicing Aamir Khan's role (Khan and Bo later collaborated again on ''[[Secret Superstar]]'').<ref>{{cite news|title=\u9ec4\u6e24\u732e\u5531\u300a\u795e\u79d8\u5de8\u661f\u300b\u4e3b\u9898\u66f2 \u963f\u7c73\u5c14\u6c57\u98d9\u5c71\u4e1c\u8bdd|url=http://ent.sina.com.cn/m/c/2018-01-25/doc-ifyqwiqk3852226.shtml|work=Sina|date=25 January 2018}}</ref>\n\nFollowing its success in other [[Cinema of Asia|Asian markets]], Japanese distributor [[Nikkatsu]] announced plans to release the film in [[Japan]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Indian films set to make inroads in Japan?  |url=http://in.lifestyle.yahoo.com/indian-films-set-inroads-japan-092639925.html|publisher=[[Yahoo! News]]|accessdate=29 March 2012|date=17 October 2011}}</ref> It was released there in June 2013,<ref name=\"qz\"/> with the title \u304d\u3063\u3068\u3001\u3046\u307e\u304f\u3044\u304f (''Kitto, Umaku Iku'').<ref>{{cite web|title=\u304d\u3063\u3068\u3001\u3046\u307e\u304f\u3044\u304f|url=https://filmarks.com/movies/53954|website=Filmarks|publisher=[[Culture Convenience Club]]|accessdate=27 January 2018|language=ja}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n===Box office===\nThe film's worldwide lifetime gross was {{INR|link=yes}}459.96{{nbsp}}[[crore]] ([[US$]]90{{nbsp}}million),{{efn|name=Gross|''3 Idiots'' worldwide gross: {{INR}}{{#expr:273.82+186.142}}&nbsp;crore (US$90&nbsp;million)<ref name=\"hollywoodreporter\"/>\n*Domestic: {{INR}} 273.82&nbsp;crore<ref>{{cite web|title=Top India Grossers All Time|url=https://www.boxofficeindia.com/india-total-gross.php|website=[[Box Office India]]|accessdate=12 November 2017}}</ref> (US$57.05&nbsp;million)<ref>{{cite web|title=Yearly Average Rates (48 INR per USD)|url=https://www.ofx.com/en-gb/forex-news/historical-exchange-rates/yearly-average-rates/|website=[[OFX (company)|OFX]]|year=2009|access-date=13 November 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170713183556/https://www.ofx.com/en-gb/forex-news/historical-exchange-rates/yearly-average-rates/|archive-date=13 July 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n*Overseas: US$30.5&nbsp;million<ref name=\"ibtimes\">{{cite news|last=Hooli|first=Shekhar|title=Baahubali 2 overseas box office collection: Rajamouli's film beats Chennai Express, Kabali's lifetime record in 1st weekend|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/baahubali-2-overseas-box-office-collection-rajamoulis-film-beats-chennai-express-kabalis-725036|work=[[International Business Times]]|date=1 May 2017|language=en}}</ref> ({{INR}} 186.142 crore)<ref name=\"exchange\">{{cite web |title=Exchange Rates (61.03 INR per USD) |work=[[The World Factbook]] |publisher=[[Central Intelligence Agency]] |url=https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/fields/2076.html |year=2013 |access-date=16 November 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150215024949/https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook//fields/2076.html |archive-date=15 February 2015 |url-status=dead  }}</ref>\n}}<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite news|url=http://www.timesnownews.com/entertainment/box-office/article/deepika-padukone-padmaavat-beats-aamir-khan-dhoom-3-and-salman-khans-tiger-zinda-hai-at-the-box-office/202889|title=Deepika Padukone's Padmaavat beats Aamir Khan's Dhoom 3 and Salman Khan's Tiger Zinda Hai at the box office|date=27 February 2018|work=[[Times Now]]}}</ref><ref name=\"hollywoodreporter\">{{cite news|title=Q&A: Aamir Khan|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/qampa-aamir-khan-26582|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=11 August 2010|language=en}}</ref> making it the [[List of highest-grossing Indian films|highest-grossing Indian film]] at the time.<ref name=\"forbes\">{{cite news|last=Cain|first=Rob|title=It's Another Diwali Clash of Titans As Ajay's 'Golmaal' Takes on Aamir's 'Superstar'|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/robcain/2017/10/11/its-another-diwali-clash-of-titans-as-ajays-golmaal-takes-on-aamirs-superstar/|work=[[Forbes]]|date=11 October 2017|language=en}}</ref><ref name=\"boxofficeindia\">{{cite web|url=http://www.boxofficeindia.com/boxnewsdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=5979&nCat= |title=Boxofficeindia.com |accessdate=8 August 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131105220137/http://boxofficeindia.com/boxnewsdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=5979&nCat= |archivedate=5 November 2013 }}</ref> The film was listed in [[Guinness World Records]] for the record of highest box office film gross for a [[Bollywood]] film.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.guinnessworldrecords.com/records-1000/highest-box-office-film-gross-for-a-bollywood-film/ |title=You are here:Global Home > Explore Records > Highest box office film gross for a Bollywood film |publisher=[[Guinness World Records]]|date=4 October 2012 |accessdate=4 October 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.guinnessworldrecords.in/news/2012/8/happy-independence-day-our-top-10-records-from-india-44243/|title=You are here:Home >News >2012 >8 >Happy Independence Day: Our Top 10 records from India |publisher=[[Guinness World Records]]|date=4 October 2012 |accessdate=4 October 2012}}</ref>\n\n==== India ====\nThe film created the highest collection record for paid previews with [[Indian rupee|{{INR}}]]27.5&nbsp;million that time, which was broken by ''[[Chennai Express]]'' (2013).<ref>http://www.boxofficeindia.com/boxnewsdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=5936&nCat=</ref><ref name=\"boxofficeindia3\">{{cite web|url=http://www.boxofficeindia.com/boxnewsdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=5937&nCat|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130922174013/http://www.boxofficeindia.com/boxnewsdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=5937&nCat |archive-date=22 September 2013 |url-status=dead|title=Boxofficeindia.com|accessdate=8 August 2014}}</ref> In its four-day first weekend, the film netted {{INRConvert|38|c|year=2009}}, and broke the record held by ''[[Ghajini (2008 film)|Ghajini]]'' for the first weekend collections.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.filmbiz.asia/news/dabangg-breaks-india-records|title=Dabangg breaks India records|publisher=Film Business Asia|accessdate=28 November 2011|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131110152151/http://www.filmbiz.asia/news/dabangg-breaks-india-records|archivedate=10 November 2013}}</ref> By the first week, the film netted {{INRConvert|79|c|year=2009}}, again breaking the box office record held by ''Ghajini''.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.telegraphindia.com/1100224/jsp/nation/story_12144926.jsp|title=My Name plays on but Idiots shifts bar|publisher=[[The Telegraph (Kolkata)|The Telegraph]]|accessdate=28 November 2011}}</ref> ''3 Idiots'' had nett grossed {{INRConvert|56|c|year=2009}} in its 2nd week, {{INRConvert|302.5|m}} during the third week, {{INRConvert|16|c|year=2009}} in its fourth week and {{INRConvert|9.75|c|year=2009}} in fifth to make a total of {{INR}} 202&nbsp;crore in five weeks,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.koimoi.com/box-office/shah-rukhs-happy-new-year-beats-salmans-kicks-worldwide-collections/|title=Shah Rukh's Happy New Year Beats Salman's Kick's Worldwide Collections|first=Koimoi com|last=Team|date=13 November 2014}}</ref> first Indian film ever to collect this huge amount, hence established the [[100 Crore Club|{{INRConvert|200|c}} Club]].<ref>http://bollywoodmoviereview.in/200-crores-club/bollywood/</ref> Its final domestic gross in India was {{INR}} 273.82 crore (US$57.05 million).{{efn|name=Gross}}\n\n==== Overseas ====\n''3 Idiots'' became the then [[List of highest-grossing Indian films in overseas markets|highest-grossing Indian film in overseas markets]], with an overseas gross of US$30.5&nbsp;million ({{INR}} 186&nbsp;crore).{{efn|name=Gross}} Its first weekend opening collection overseas was $4&nbsp;million.<ref>{{cite web|title=Talaash Is Excellent Overseas|url=http://businesstoday.intoday.in/story/talaash-overseas-box-office-collection-jab-tak-hai-jaan/1/190417.html|publisher=BT Online Bureau|accessdate=7 December 2012}}</ref><ref name=\"Overseas opening\">{{cite web|title=Talaash beats 3 Idiots record at overseas box office|url=http://www.boxofficeindia.com/overdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=5172&nCat=|publisher=[[Box Office India]]|accessdate=5 December 2012}}</ref> It set record collections for Indian-produced films in territories such as the [[United States]]<ref name=\"highest\">{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/films/news/aamir-khans-3-idiots-becomes-bollywoods-biggest-grosser-1859492.html|title=Aamir Khan's '3 Idiots' becomes Bollywood's biggest grosser|work=The Independent|date=6 January 2010|accessdate=21 November 2010}}</ref> and [[Australia]].<ref name=\"mojo3\" /> In the United States, the film earned $6.5&nbsp;million since its opening,<ref name=highest /><ref name=\"mojo3\">{{cite web|url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=3idiots.htm|title=3 Idiots (2009)|website=Box Office Mojo|accessdate=29 April 2010| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20100507171808/http://boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=3idiots.htm| archivedate= 7 May 2010 | url-status= live}}</ref> in addition to over $2.5&nbsp;million in the [[United Kingdom]], over $2&nbsp;million in [[Canada]], and nearly $1&nbsp;million in Australia.<ref name=\"mojo3\" /> ''3 Idiots'' has the biggest first week total in the US with around $3&nbsp;million over its first four days.<ref>{{cite web|title=Don 2 Second Biggest First Week Grosser Ever in US|url=http://www.boxofficeindia.com/boxnewsdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=3871&nCat=|publisher=[[Box Office India]]|accessdate=5 December 2012}}</ref>\n\n====East Asia====\nUnusual for an Indian film at the time, ''3 Idiots'' became a success in [[East Asia]]n markets.<ref name=\"economic_china\" /> ''3 Idiots'' had a wide release in East Asian markets including [[China]], [[South Korea]] and [[Hong Kong]].<ref name=\"dhoom3idiotsoverseas\">{{cite web |url=http://www.boxofficeindia.com/overdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=6354&nCat= |title=Dhoom 3 Set For ALL TIME RECORD Overseas |publisher=[[Box Office India]] |date=1 January 2014 |accessdate=1 January 2014 |url-status=bot: unknown |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140105151547/http://www.boxofficeindia.com/overdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=6354&nCat= |archivedate=5 January 2014  }}</ref> The film had the longest showing period at cinemas in [[Taiwan]], for more than two months from December 2010, breaking the record of ''[[Avatar (2009 film)|Avatar]]'', with over [[New Taiwan dollar|NT$]]10&nbsp;million (US$629,024)<ref name=\"mojo3\" /> grossed. ''3 Idiots'' was the first aired Indian film in Hong Kong, where it grossed [[Hong Kong dollar|HK$]]22&nbsp;million at the box office since its showing from 1 September 2011 through January 2012,<ref name=\"hkfilmart\">{{cite web|url=http://www.hkfilmart.com/newsread.asp?newsid=4198 |title=hkfilmart.com |publisher=hkfilmart.com |date=January 2012 |accessdate=5 March 2012 |archiveurl=https://translate.google.com/translate?sl=zh-CN&tl=en&js=n&prev=_t&hl=en&ie=UTF-8&layout=2&eotf=1&u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.hkfilmart.com%2Fnewsread.asp%3Fnewsid%3D4198 |archivedate=29 March 2012}}</ref> the equivalent of US$3.02&nbsp;million.<ref name=\"boi-note\">{{cite web|title=PK - Movie|url=https://boxofficeindia.com/movie-story.php?movieid=2482|website=[[Box Office India]]|accessdate=3 February 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"mojo3\" /> It was the 14th highest-grossing film of 2011 at the Hong Kong box office.<ref>{{cite web|title=2011 Hong Kong Yearly Box Office Results|url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/intl/hongkong/yearly/?yr=2011&p=.htm|website=[[Box Office Mojo]]|accessdate=8 December 2017|language=en}}</ref>\n\nIn South Korea, where it was released in 2011, the film grossed {{KRW|3,416,415,900}}<ref>{{cite web|title=KOFIC \uc601\ud654\uad00 \uc785\uc7a5\uad8c \ud1b5\ud569\uc804\uc0b0\ub9dd : \uc601\ud654\uc815\ubcf4|url=http://www.kobis.or.kr/kobis/business/mast/mvie/searchMovieList.do|website=[[Korean Film Council]]|year=2016|accessdate=25 April 2018|language=ko}}</ref> (US$3,084,647).<ref>{{cite web|title=Historical Exchange Rates Tool & Forex History Data (1107.555 KRW per USD)|url=https://www.ofx.com/en-gb/forex-news/historical-exchange-rates/|website=[[OFX (company)|OFX]]|year=2011|accessdate=25 April 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180619140101/https://www.ofx.com/en-gb/forex-news/historical-exchange-rates/|archive-date=19 June 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref> The film was number-one at the South Korean box office for five weeks,<ref name=\"kaist\"/> drawing an audience of 459,686 viewers.<ref>{{cite web|title=\uc601\ud654 <\uc138 \uc5bc\uac04\uc774>|url=http://movie.daum.net/moviedb/main?movieId=55287|website=[[Daum (web portal)|Daum]]|date=11 September 2016|accessdate=10 February 2018|language=ko}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Frater|first=Patrick|title=Aamir Khan's 'PK' Heads for September Release in Korea|url=https://variety.com/2015/film/asia/aamir-khans-pk-release-in-korea-1201553130/|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=30 July 2015}}</ref>\n\nIn China, where it is known as ''San Geshagua'' (\"Three Idiots\"),<ref name=\"economic_china\">{{cite news|last=Vasi|first=Nazia|title=Why Chinese identify with Aamir Khan's 3 Idiots, Rancho & All Izz Well|url=http://articles.economictimes.indiatimes.com/2011-10-15/news/30283532_1_three-idiots-films-hong-kong|accessdate=29 March 2012|newspaper=[[The Economic Times]]|date=15 October 2011}}</ref> the film grossed [[Indian rupee|{{INR}}]]11 crore in 2 weeks in December 2011,<ref name=\"economictimes\">{{cite news|url=http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/industry/media/entertainment/3-idiots-wins-over-chinese-collects-rs-11-crore-in-two-weeks/articleshow/11286751.cms |title=3 Idiots wins over Chinese, collects Rs 11 crore in two weeks|accessdate=29 December 2011|newspaper=[[The Economic Times]]|date=29 December 2011|last1=Chumbhale|first1=Ameya}}</ref> eventually crossing the $2&nbsp;million mark within 18 days,<ref name=overseas /> and nearly $3&nbsp;million within a month, as of 5 January 2012.<ref>{{cite news|last=Hazlewood|first=Phil |title=Bollywood looks east to tap Chinese market |url=http://www.livemint.com/2012/01/05152937/Bollywood-looks-east-to-tap-Ch.html|accessdate=29 March 2012|newspaper=[[Mint (newspaper)|Mint]]|date=5 January 2012|agency=[[The Wall Street Journal]]}}</ref>\n\nUpon its release in the Japanese market in June 2013, it went on to collect around [[Japanese yen|\u00a5]]100&nbsp;million ({{INR}} 61&nbsp;million) in its first two weeks of run&nbsp;\u2013 that makes the film the highest grossing Hindi film ever in Japan. Its final gross in Japan was \u00a5150{{nbsp}}million<ref>{{cite journal|title=2014\u5e742\u6708\u4e0b\u65ec\u6c7a\u7b97\u7279\u5225\u53f7|journal=[[Kinema Junpo]]|date=February 2014|issue=1656|page=212}}</ref> (US$1.6 million).<ref name=\"qz\">{{cite news|title=Japan is going gaga over Bollywood|url=https://qz.com/310502/japan-is-going-gaga-over-bollywood/|work=[[Quartz (publication)|Quartz]]|date=11 December 2014}}</ref> The film's final gross in East Asian markets was US${{formatnum:{{#expr:629024+3020000+3084647+3000000+1600000}}|}} ({{INR|69.2 crore}}).<ref name=\"exchange\"/>\n\n===Critical response===\n==== India ====\n[[Subhash K. Jha]] stated: \"It's not that ''3 Idiots'' is a flawless work of art. But it is a vital, inspiring and life-revising work of contemporary art with some heart imbued into every part. In a country where students are driven to suicide by their impossible curriculum, ''3 Idiots'' provides hope. Maybe cinema can't save lives. But cinema, sure as hell, can make you feel life is worth living. ''3 Idiots'' does just that, and much more. The director takes the definition of entertainment into directions of social comment\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/celebrities/features/type/view/id/583/ |title=Subhash K Jha speaks about ''3 Idiots'' |publisher=Bollywoodhungama.com |date=26 December 2009 |accessdate=21 November 2010}}</ref> [[Nikhat Kazmi]] of ''[[The Times of India]]'' gave it four and a half stars and suggests that, \"The film is a laugh riot, despite being high on fundas [\u2026] Hirani carries forward his simplistic 'humanism alone works' philosophy of the ''[[Lage Raho Munna Bhai]]'' series in ''3 Idiots'' too, making it a warm and vivacious signature tune to 2009. The second half of the film does falter in parts, specially the child birth sequence, but it doesn't take long for the film to jump back on track.\"<ref>{{cite web|author =Nikhat Kazmi |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/movie-reviews/hindi/3-Idiots/movie-review/5373913.cms |title=3 Idiots review |work=The Times of India|date=24 December 2009 |accessdate=21 November 2010}}</ref> Mayank Shekhar of the ''[[Hindustan Times]]'' gave the film three and a half out of five stars and comments that \"this is the sort of movie you'll take home with a smile and a song on your lips.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/Review-3-Idiots/H1-Article1-490233.aspx |title=3 Idiots review |work=Hindustan Times|date=24 December 2009 |accessdate=21 November 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110830022823/http://www.hindustantimes.com/Review-3-Idiots/H1-Article1-490233.aspx |archivedate=30 August 2011  }}</ref> [[Taran Adarsh]] of [[Bollywood Hungama]] gave ''3 Idiots'' four and a half out of five stars and states: \"On the whole, ''3 Idiots'' easily ranks amongst Aamir, Rajkumar Hirani and Vidhu Vinod Chopra's finest films. Do yourself and your family a favour: Watch ''3 Idiots.'' It's emotional, it's entertaining, it's enlightening. The film has tremendous youth appeal and feel-good factor to work in a big way.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/review/13910/index.html |title=3 Idiots review |publisher=Bollywood Hungama |accessdate=21 November 2010| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20101104160008/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/review/13910/index.html| archivedate= 4 November 2010 | url-status= live}}</ref> Kaveree Bamzai of ''[[India Today]]'' gave ''3 Idiots'' five stars and argues that \"it's a lovely story, of a man from nowhere who wanted to learn, told like a fairy tale, with the secret heart carrying its coded message of setting all of us free.\"<ref>{{cite web|author=Kaveree Bamzai |url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/site/Story/76291/3+Idiots:+Laugh.+Cry.+Fly.+Go+watch+it..html?complete=1 |title=3 Idiots: Laugh. Cry. Fly. Go watch it |publisher=India Today |date=24 December 2009 |accessdate=21 November 2010 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100114010140/http://indiatoday.intoday.in/site/Story/76291/3%2BIdiots%3A%2BLaugh.%2BCry.%2BFly.%2BGo%2Bwatch%2Bit..html?complete=1 |archivedate=14 January 2010 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nSonia Chopra of [[Sify]] gave the film 3 stars and said \"Though a bit too calculated and designed, 3 Idiots is still an ok option for the significant message, interesting cast and scattered breezy moments.\"<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.sify.com/movies/3-idiots-has-a-munnabhai-hangover-review-bollywood-14925000.html |title= 3 Idiots has a Munnabhai hangover|publisher=[[Sify]]|accessdate=19 December 2011}}</ref> [[Rajeev Masand]] of ''[[CNN-IBN]]'' gave the film three out of five stars and states: \"Going home after watching ''3 Idiots'' I felt like I'd just been to my favorite restaurant only to be a tad under-whelmed by their signature dish. It was a satisfying meal, don't get me wrong, but not the best meal I'd been expecting.\"<ref>{{cite web|author =<!--Updated 1136 hrs 3 February 2010(+5:30 GMT)--> |url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/masands-movie-review-3-idiots-satisfying-but-not-the-best/107739-8.html |title=3 Idiots review: CNN-IBN |work=CNN IBN |date=3 February 2010 |accessdate=21 November 2010}}</ref> Shubhra Gupta from ''[[The Indian Express]]'' also gave it 3 stars, stating \"'3 Idiots' does not do as much for me. The emotional truth that shone through both the 'Munnabhai' movies doesn't come through strongly enough.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indianexpress.com/news/3-idiots/559131/0|title=3 Idiots|work=[[The Indian Express]]|accessdate=18 February 2012}}</ref> Raja Sen of [[Rediff]] gave the film two out of five stars and states: \"Rajkumar Hirani's one of the directors of the decade, a man with immense talent and a knack for storytelling. On his debut, he hit a hundred. With his second, he hit a triple century. This time, he fishes outside the offstump, tries to play shots borrowed from other batters, and hits and misses to provide a patchy, 32*-type innings. It's okay, boss, *chalta hai*. Even Sachin has an off day, and we still have great hope.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://movies.rediff.com/report/2009/dec/24/review-three-idiots.htm |title=Rediff review |publisher=Movies.rediff.com |date=24 December 2009 |accessdate=21 November 2010| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20101106121348/http://movies.rediff.com/report/2009/dec/24/review-three-idiots.htm| archivedate= 6 November 2010 | url-status= live}}</ref>\n\n==== Overseas ====\nThe film has received praise overseas. On [[Rotten Tomatoes]], the film holds a rare [[List of films with a 100% rating on Rotten Tomatoes|100%]] \"Fresh\" critics' rating based on 13 reviews, with an [[Weighted mean|average score]] of 7.44 out of 10.<ref name=\"rt\">{{cite web|title=Three Idiots|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/3_idiots/|website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]|accessdate=7 October 2017|language=en}}</ref> Derek Elley of ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'' wrote that \"''3 Idiots'' takes a while to lay out its game plan but pays off emotionally in its second half.\" Robert Abele of ''[[Los Angeles Times]]'' wrote that there's an \"unavoidable ''[[joie de vivre]]'' (symbolized by Rancho's meditative mantra 'All is well') and a performance charm that make this one of the more naturally gregarious Bollywood imports.\" Louis Proyect described it as a \"fabulous achievement across the board. A typical Bollywood confection but also social commentary on a dysfunctional engineering school system that pressures huge numbers of students into suicide.\"<ref>{{Rotten Tomatoes|3_idiots|Three Idiots (2009)}}</ref>\n\nThe film was praised by critics in [[East Asia]] and [[Southeast Asia]]. ''[[South China Morning Post]]'' wrote that the film \"wraps a heavy message in light comedy. It is satire at its best, a powerful indictment of India's education system in which students cram for exams while stifling their dreams.\"<ref name=\"scmp\">{{cite news|title=3 Idiots (Film)|url=http://www.scmp.com/article/978499/3-idiots-film|work=[[South China Morning Post]]|date=9 September 2011|language=en}}</ref> Chaerim Oh of ''[[KAIST|KAIST Herald]]'' wrote that \"the film never harshly denounces the educational system but instead uncovers disturbing truths and unseen consequences of tremendous pressure upon students\" and that \"if you don't end up crying like I did (or won't admit that you did), you'll still enjoy the movie.\"<ref name=\"kaist\">{{cite news|title=Embrace Your Nerdiness with 3 Idiots|url=http://herald.kaist.ac.kr/news/articleView.html?idxno=285|accessdate=29 March 2012|newspaper=KAIST Herald|date=4 December 2011|author=Chaerim Oh|agency=[[KAIST]]}}</ref> In [[Japan]], Yuri Wakabayashi of [[:ja:\u6620\u753b.com|Eiga]] also gave the film a positive review.<ref>{{cite web|title=\u304d\u3063\u3068\u3001\u3046\u307e\u304f\u3044\u304f : \u6620\u753b\u8a55\u8ad6\u30fb\u6279\u8a55|url=http://eiga.com/movie/77899/critic/|website=[[:ja:\u6620\u753b.com|Eiga]]|date=8 May 2013|language=ja-JP}}</ref>\n\nIn 2013, renowned Hollywood filmmaker [[Steven Spielberg]] praised ''3 Idiots'', which he had seen three times and said he \"loved the emotional undertones.\" He listed it as one of five films that he connects with, along with ''[[The Godfather]]'' (1972) and his own work on ''[[E.T. the Extra-Terrestrial]]'' (1982), ''[[Saving Private Ryan]]'' (1998) and ''[[Jaws (film)|Jaws]]'' (1975).<ref>{{cite news|title=I've watched 3 Idiots thrice, admits Steven Spielberg|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/hollywood/i-ve-watched-3-idiots-thrice-admits-steven-spielberg/story-q4FjZUBWitY6zlvPa7TYRK.html|work=[[Hindustan Times]]|date=17 March 2013|language=en}}</ref>\n\n== Pre-release business ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"  style=\"margin:auto; margin:auto;\"\n|+'''''3 Idiots'' Pre-release business<ref name=\"planetbollywood\">{{cite web|url=http://planetbollywood.com/displayArticle.php?id=n083109031345|title=3 Idiots : Big Procures Worldwide Rights (Sans Satellite & Home Video) for 65 Crore!|website=Planet Bollywood News|accessdate=8 August 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141107095130/http://planetbollywood.com/displayArticle.php?id=n083109031345|archive-date=7 November 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref>'''\n! Territories and ancillary revenues\n! Price\n|-\n|  Satellite rights with a TV channel [Sony]\n| {{INRConvert|22|c}}\n|-\n| Worldwide distribution rights\n| {{INRConvert|65|c}}\n|-\n| Music rights (T~Series)\n|{{INRConvert|12|c}}\n|-\n|Total\n|{{INRConvert|99|c}}\n|-\n|}\n* The figures don't include the Print and Advertising (P&A) costs.\n\n== Awards ==\n{{Main|List of accolades received by 3 Idiots}}\n\nThe film won 58 accolades from Indian film awards; among these are six [[Filmfare Awards]] including [[Filmfare Best Film Award|Best Film]] and [[Filmfare Best Director Award|Best Director]], three [[National Film Awards]] including [[National Film Award for Best Popular Film Providing Wholesome Entertainment|Best Popular Film]], ten [[Star Screen Awards]], seventeen [[IIFA Awards]], five [[Global Indian Music Academy Awards|GIMA Awards]], two [[Apsara Awards]] and seven Bollywood Hungama Surfers Choice Movie Awards.\n\nIn China, it was nominated for the Best Foreign Film prize at the first [[Beijing International Film Festival]] in 2011.<ref name=\"maoyan\">{{cite web|title=\u4e09\u50bb\u5927\u95f9\u5b9d\u83b1\u575e|url=https://maoyan.com/films/43|website=[[Maoyan]]|accessdate=1 March 2018}}</ref> In Japan, it was nominated in the [[Japan Academy Prize for Outstanding Foreign Language Film|Best Outstanding Foreign Language Film]] category at the [[37th Japan Academy Prize|37th]] [[Japan Academy Prize (film)|Japan Academy Awards]] in 2014;<ref name=\"japan-hungama\">{{cite web|title=3 Idiots to race for Japan Academy Awards|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/2382254/3-Idiots-to-race-for-Japan-Academy-Awards|website=[[Bollywood Hungama]]|date=27 January 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"japan-ibn\">{{cite web|title=Aamir Khan's '3 Idiots' nominated for Japan Academy Awards|url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/aamir-khans-3-idiots-nominated-for-japan-academy-awards/448063-8-66.html|website=[[IBN Live]]|publisher=[[CNN-News18]]|date=27 January 2014|url-status=bot: unknown|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140129033801/http://ibnlive.in.com/news/aamir-khans-3-idiots-nominated-for-japan-academy-awards/448063-8-66.html|archivedate=29 January 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=3 Idiots nominated for Japan Academy Awards|url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/3-idiots-nominated-for-japan-academy-awards/1/340066.html|website=[[India Today]]|date=27 January 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Film 3 Idiots nominated for 37th Japanese Academy Awards 2014|url=http://news.biharprabha.com/2014/01/film-3-idiots-nominated-for-37th-japanese-academy-awards-2014/|work=IANS|date=26 January 2014|publisher=Biharprabha News|accessdate=27 January 2014}}</ref> the award was eventually won by ''[[Les Mis\u00e9rables (2012 film)|Les Miserables]]''. In addition, ''3 Idiots'' won the Grand Prize at the 4th Videoyasan Awards,<ref name=\"videoyasan\">{{cite web|title=\u7b2c\uff14\u56de\u30d3\u30c7\u30aa\u5c4b\u3055\u3093\u5927\u8cde|url=http://www.kinenote.com/main/feature/videoyasan04/|website=[[:ja:KINENOTE|KINENOTE]]|year=2014|accessdate=14 December 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"nikkatsu\">{{cite web|title=\u300e\u304d\u3063\u3068\u3001\u3046\u307e\u304f\u3044\u304f\u300f \u304c\u3001\u7b2c4\u56de\u30d3\u30c7\u30aa\u5c4b\u3055\u3093\u5927\u8cde\u306e \u300a\u5927\u8cde\u300b \u3092\u53d7\u8cde\u3057\u307e\u3057\u305f\uff01|url=http://www.nikkatsu.com/news/201403/001723.html|website=[[Nikkatsu]]|date=25 March 2014|language=ja-JP}}</ref> held by a Japanese organisation of home video retailers in 2014;<ref name=\"qz\"/> ''3 Idiots'' was selected as 2013's best video release, beating thousands of films, [[anime]] and television shows,<ref name=\"nikkatsu\"/> including domestic Japanese and foreign [[Cinema of the United States|Hollywood]] productions.<ref name=\"qz\"/>\n\n== Controversies ==\nPrior to the release of the film director [[Rajkumar Hirani]] commented on the relationship between ''[[Five Point Someone \u2013 What not to do at IIT|Five Point Someone]]'' by [[Chetan Bhagat]] and ''3 Idiots'' stating:\n:Chetan gave me this book to read and I wanted to make a film on it. But I knew right from the start that I could not make a film completely on the book, as it was very anecdotal and a film needs a plot. So I had decided to rewrite it in a screenplay format. You'll see that the film is very different from the book. After I wrote the script, I called Chetan and narrated it to him. I told him that if he did not like the script, I would stop the project. But he was okay with it.<ref>[http://movies.rediff.com/slide-show/2009/dec/23/slide-show-1-rajkumar-hirani-on-3idiots.htm#contentTop \"Aamir's dedication is mistaken as interference\"], rediff.com, 23 December 2009.</ref>\n\nThe day after the film opened, Chetan also noted:\n:Initially I did sit down with Raju and Abhijat while they were deciding to make a film based on '5 Point Someone'. I even went to IIT with Abhijat a couple of times. But it was just not possible for me to be involved at every stage of the screenplay writing process since I was in Hong Kong at that time, working full-time and busy writing other books. Moreover, Abhijat is based in USA, Raju was in the US for quite a while working on the screenplay but it was not practical for me to do that [\u2026] The film retains the soul of the book. ''3 Idiots'' is different from the book but at the same time it does borrow many things from the book. The core theme and message of the film is coming from the book itself. And that's why the makers have officially credited the film as 'Based on a novel by Chetan Bhagat.'<ref name=\"Bhagatint\">[https://www.filmibeat.com/bollywood/features/2009/chetan-bhagat-interview-261209.html \u201c3 Idiots retains the soul of Five Point Someone\u201d], Chetan Bhagat interview, ''One India''.</ref>\n\nA controversy developed a few days after the release, however, over the fact that Chetan's credit, \"Based on the novel ''Five Point Someone'' by Chetan Bhagat\" appeared in the closing credits rather than in the opening ones.<ref name=akinterview>{{cite web|url=http://www.glamsham.com/movies/interviews/02-aamir-khan-interview-011005.asp |title=Interview:Aamir Khan |publisher=Glamsham.com |accessdate=21 November 2010 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101123200554/http://glamsham.com/movies/interviews/02-aamir-khan-interview-011005.asp |archivedate=23 November 2010 |url-status=dead }}</ref> At that time, Bhagat stated that he \"was expecting an opening credit and I was quite surprised on not seeing it. They had bought the rights, made the payment and committed to a credit in the contract. It's there, but it's not about it being there, it's about the placement and the prominence.\"<ref>Sharma, Neha.[http://www.hindustantimes.com/Chetan-Bhagat-feeling-cheated/H1-Article1-491135.aspx \"Chetan Bhagat feeling cheated?\"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100225125702/http://www.hindustantimes.com/Chetan-Bhagat-feeling-cheated/H1-Article1-491135.aspx |date=25 February 2010 }}, ''Hindustan Times'', 27 December 2009.</ref> In a 31 December 2009 blog post on his personal website, Bhagat stated that he was told the movie was only 2\u20135% based on the book, but when he saw it, he felt that it was 70% of the book. He also argued that he was misled by the makers of the film, though he noted, that \"this has nothing to do with Mr Aamir Khan [\u2026] I am a big fan of Aamir and he has made my story reach people. However, he was told by the makers not to read the book, and he hasn't. Thus, he cannot comment on the issue in a meaningful manner.\"<ref>[http://www.chetanbhagat.com/blog/general/a-book-a-film-and-the-truth A book, a film and the truth] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101225052408/http://www.chetanbhagat.com/blog/general/a-book-a-film-and-the-truth |date=25 December 2010 }}\"</ref>\n\nA few people responded to Chetan's statements. According to the [[Indo-Asian News Service]] (IANS) producer [[Vidhu Vinod Chopra]] clarified that \"in the agreement between the producer and Bhagat, it was clearly mentioned that the author's name would be put in the closing credits\".<ref name=\"IANS\"/> IANS also reported that Chopra \"lost his cool\"<ref name=\"IANS\"/> and \"asked a reporter to shut up after being questioned whether his hit ''3 Idiots'' was lifted from author Chetan Bhagat's book ''Five Point Someone.''\"<ref name=\"IANS\">{{cite web|url=http://www.thaindian.com/newsportal/entertainment/vidhu-vinod-chopra-loses-cool-over-3-idiots-credit-row-lead_100297690.html |title=Vidhu Vinod Chopra loses cool over '3 Idiots' credit row (Lead) |publisher=Thaindian.com |accessdate=21 November 2010}}</ref> Chopra later apologised, stating: \"I really think I'm silly. I was provoked, but I shouldn't have done this. I saw myself on TV and saw how I was shouting 'shut up, shut up' like an animal. I told myself&nbsp;\u2014 'what nonsensical behaviour'.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2010-01-03/india/28134698_1_chetan-bhagat-vidhu-vinod-chopra-idiots |title=Vidhu apologises, Hirani flaunts pact with Chetan |work=The Times of India|date=3 January 2010 |accessdate=21 November 2010}}</ref> Aamir Khan also responded to these claims.<ref name=akinterview /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report_upset-aamir-khan-hits-out-at-novelist-chetan-bhagat_1329677 |title=Upset Aamir Khan hits out at novelist Chetan Bhagat|publisher=DNA India|date=1 January 2010 |accessdate=21 November 2010}}</ref> [[Rajkumar Hirani]] stated that \"We have officially bought the rights for the film. We drew a contract with him and it clearly mentions about the position of his credit. With open eyes he had seen the contract, consulted his lawyer and signed the agreement [\u2026] In the contract, we have said that the title would be given in the rolling credits. We haven't changed the font size. We haven't increased the speed of the title. It's exactly there where it was agreed to be.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2010-01-04/news-interviews/28142618_1_chetan-bhagat-due-credit-idiots |title=3 Idiots may sue Chetan Bhagat |work=The Times of India|date=4 January 2010|accessdate=21 November 2010}}</ref> Chetan Bhagat later apologised stating, \"I definitely do not have anything against team ''3 Idiots''. I may have some issues on the mistake they may have made but nothing about their personality or the kind of people they are. I apologise to their families if there was any distress caused to them. I also want to thank all my fans, who stood by me but I don't want them to turn against anyone especially Aamir.\"<ref>{{cite web|author =PTI |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2010-01-07/news-interviews/28117713_1_chetan-bhagat-credit-issue-due-credit |title=Fans, forgive Aamir: Chetan Bhagat |work=The Times of India|date=7 January 2010 |accessdate=21 November 2010}}</ref>\n\nIn an article published in ''[[Economic and Political Weekly]],'' Latika Gupta mentions that the film has serious problems when seen from the gender perspective, in particular that it follows the trend set by the 2007 film ''[[Jab We Met]]'' in its use of women's sexual vulnerability to create sensation and humor. In one scene, students, professors and the chief guest are seen bursting with laughter hearing a speech where the word ''balatkar'' (rape) figures 21 times and the word ''stan'' (breast) four times (in the English subtitles for international release, the words \"screwed\" and \"bosom\" are used instead).<ref name=\"Gupta\">{{cite journal|last1=Gupta|first1=Latika|title=Language, Cinema and State: A Gender Perspective|journal=Economic and Political Weekly|date= 5\u201311 June 2010|volume=45|issue=23|pages=86\u201388|jstor=27807110}}</ref>\n\n== Remakes ==\nA [[Tamil cinema|Tamil]]-language remake entitled ''[[Nanban (2012 film)|Nanban]]'' was released in 2012,<ref name=\"nanban_ibn\" /><ref name=\"nanban_hindustantimes\" /><ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2010-12-04/news-interviews/28258269_1_idiots-srikanth-and-jiiva-shankar-s-tamil |title=Tamil 3 Idiots' actors do style test&nbsp;\u2013 The Times of India |work=[[The Times of India]] |date=4 December 2010 |accessdate=11 December 2010}}</ref> and a Spanish-language [[Cinema of Mexico|Mexican]] remake named ''[[3 idiotas]]'' was released in 2017.<ref>{{cite web|title=3 idiotas se estrenar\u00e1 en el 2017\n|url=http://www.debate.com.mx/show/3-idiotas-se-estrenara-en-el-2017-20160713-0024.html}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.imdb.com/title/tt3685624/|title=3 Idiotas|via=www.imdb.com}}</ref>\n\n== Legacy ==\n=== Impact ===\nWhen ''3 Idiots'' made its television debut in July 2010, it drew an audience of 39{{nbsp}}million viewers in India.<ref name=\"hollywoodreporter\"/>\n\nWhen ''3 Idiots'' released in China, the country was only the 15th largest film market, partly due to China's widespread pirate [[DVD]] distribution at the time. However, it was the pirate market that introduced ''3 Idiots'' to most Chinese audiences, becoming a [[cult hit]] in the country. Aamir Khan gained a large growing Chinese fanbase as a result. By 2013, China grew to become the world's second largest film market (after the United States), paving the way for Aamir Khan's Chinese box office success, with ''[[Dhoom 3]]'' (2013), ''[[PK (film)|PK]]'' (2014), ''[[Dangal (film)|Dangal]]'' (2016)<ref name=\"forbes2\">{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/robcain/2017/06/08/how-a-52-year-old-indian-actor-became-chinas-favorite-movie-star/|title=How A 52-Year-Old Indian Actor Became China's Favorite Movie Star|first=Rob|last=Cain|website=Forbes}}</ref> and ''[[Secret Superstar]]'' (2017).\n\n''3 Idiots'' has been ranked China's 12th favourite film of all time according to ratings on popular Chinese film review site [[Douban]], with only one domestic [[Chinese film]] (''[[Farewell My Concubine (film)|Farewell My Concubine]]'') ranked higher.<ref name=\"forbes2\"/><ref name=\"theworldofchinese\">{{cite web|title=China's Favorite Movies|url=http://www.theworldofchinese.com/2017/05/chinas-favorite-movies/|website=[[The World of Chinese]]|date=19 May 2017|language=en}}</ref> The film holds an average rating of 9.2 out of 10 on Douban,<ref name=\"theworldofchinese\"/> with over 1.15 million votes.<ref>{{cite web|title=\u4e09\u50bb\u5927\u95f9\u5b9d\u83b1\u575e (\u8c46\u74e3)|url=https://movie.douban.com/subject/3793023/|website=[[Douban]]|accessdate=9 December 2017|language=zh-cmn-Hans}}</ref> On the [[Korean language|Korean]] site [[Naver]], audiences gave the film an average rating of 9.4 out of 10,<ref name=\"kaist\"/> and it is one of the top 30 highest-rated films on the site.<ref>{{cite web|title=\ub7ad\ud0b9 : \ub124\uc774\ubc84 \uc601\ud654|url=http://movie.naver.com/movie/sdb/rank/rmovie.nhn?sel=pnt&date=20171208|website=[[Naver]]|accessdate=8 December 2017}}</ref>\n\nOne reason for its success in [[East Asian cinema|East Asian markets]] such as China and Hong Kong is because of their similar education systems, thus many students were able to identify with the characters.<ref name=\"economic_china\" /> Chaerim Oh of ''[[KAIST|KAIST Herald]]'' wrote that the \"popularity of the movie, particularly in South Korea, can be traced back to the national background of the overly competitive education system. In Korea, students of all ages - from young elementary children to university graduate students - are trained to study under overwhelming pressure and extremely high academic standards. In short, this movie is, really, our own story.\"<ref name=\"kaist\"/>\n\nThe film had a social impact on attitudes to [[education in Asia]], including [[education in India]]<ref name=\"Hussain\">{{cite journal|last1=Hussain|first1=Sajjad|last2=Ahmad|first2=Nasir|title=The impact of the Indian movie, ''3 Idiots'' (2009), on attitudes to education|journal=Research in Drama Education: The Journal of Applied Theatre and Performance|date=28 April 2016|volume=21|issue=2|pages=242\u2013246|doi=10.1080/13569783.2016.1155439}}</ref> as well as other [[Asia]]n countries.<ref name=\"economic_china\" /> Chinese universities were \"even prescribing the film in their coursework as a kind of stress-relief in their classrooms.\"<ref name=\"hindu_china\"/>\n\n===''Big in Bollywood''===\n''Big in Bollywood'' (2011) is a [[documentary film]] about American actor [[Omi Vaidya]]'s journey from a struggling [[Cinema of the United States|Hollywood]] actor to a successful Bollywood breakthrough with ''3 Idiots''.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Heymont|first1=George|title=Big in Bollywood (That's What Friends Are For)|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/george-heymont/big-in-bollywood-movie_b_1122412.html|work=[[Huffington Post]]|date=1 December 2011}}</ref>\n\n==Possible sequel==\nWhen asked about plans of a ''3 Idiots'' sequel in an interview with [[Hindustan Times]], screenwriter Abhijat Joshi replied, saying, \"Honestly, I don't know. We have an idea for the 3 Idiots sequel, a ''[[Munna Bhai]]'' part three, and also for a [[PK (film)|''PK'']] sequel; but the [[PK (film)|''PK'']] and ''[[Munna Bhai]]'' sequels interest me the most. So, I think the ''3 Idiots'' sequel may happen in the future, but these two I really want to work on.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/sequels-to-pk-3-idiots-in-the-pipeline/article1-1296946.aspx |title=Sequels|accessdate=12 January 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150104203847/http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/sequels-to-pk-3-idiots-in-the-pipeline/article1-1296946.aspx |archivedate=4 January 2015 }}</ref>\n\nIn January 2016, director Rajkumar Hirani and actor Aamir Khan confirmed that they were considering a ''3 Idiots'' sequel. Khan told reporters, \"\"Raju Hirani has given me a hint about '''3 Idiots''<nowiki/>' sequel and I am giving you all a hint. The film will happen if and whenever he will write the script.\" Hirani agreed, saying \"this is one film that I really want to do.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/3-idiots-sequel-will-happen-when-rajkumar-hirani-is-ready-with-the-script-aamir-khan/|title=3 Idiots sequel will happen when Rajkumar Hirani is ready with the script: Aamir Khan|date=28 January 2016}}</ref>\n\nIn June 2018, Hirani was asked a question while promoting his upcoming film [[Sanju]] and he was quoted as saying, \"I definitely want to make a sequel to ''3 Idiots'', but it\u2019s still in the initial stage and we will take a fair amount of time to develop the script\".\n\nThe report also said that Hirani will begin shooting for the ''Munna Bhai'' sequel with [[Sanjay Dutt]] once Sanju releases. Work on 3 Idiots will begin only after Hirani is done with ''Munna Bhai 3.''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tribune.com.pk/story/1739904/4-film-maker-rajkumar-hirani-confirms-3-idiots-sequel/|title=Film-maker Rajkumar Hirani confirms '3 Idiots' sequel|date=22 June 2018|website=The Express Tribune}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n{{Portal bar|Bollywood|Film}}\n* [[List of highest-grossing Bollywood films]]\n* [[List of Bollywood highest-grossing films in overseas markets]]\n\n== Notes ==\n{{notelist}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n<!-- Please do not add links that are not official. Wikipedia is not a collection of links! -->\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xvszmNXdM4w Official trailer]&nbsp;\u2013 [[Vinod Chopra Films]]\n* {{IMDb title}}\n* {{Bollywood Hungama title|65530}}\n* {{AllMovie title}}\n* {{Mojo title}}\n* {{Rotten Tomatoes}}\n* {{Metacritic film}}\n* {{TCMDb title}}\n\n{{Rajkumar Hirani}}\n{{Vidhu Vinod Chopra}}\n{{National Film Award Wholesome Entertainment}}\n{{IIFA Award for Best Movie}}\n{{FilmfareAwardBestFilm}}\n{{Chetan Bhagat}}\n{{Shantanu Moitra}}\n\n[[Category:2009 films]]\n[[Category:2000s Hindi-language films]]\n[[Category:2000s buddy comedy films]]\n[[Category:2000s comedy-drama films]]\n[[Category:Coming-of-age comedy films]]\n[[Category:Coming-of-age drama films]]\n[[Category:Films scored by Shantanu Moitra]]\n[[Category:Films about education]]\n[[Category:Films about the education system in India]]\n[[Category:Films about teacher\u2013student relationships]]\n[[Category:Films about poverty]]\n[[Category:Films about suicide]]\n[[Category:Films about death]]\n[[Category:Films based on Indian novels]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Rajkumar Hirani]]\n[[Category:Films set in Delhi]]\n[[Category:Films set in Himachal Pradesh]]\n[[Category:Films set in Ladakh]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Bangalore]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Ladakh]]\n[[Category:Hindi films remade in other languages]]\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:Indian buddy comedy films]]\n[[Category:Indian comedy-drama films]]\n[[Category:Indian coming-of-age films]]\n[[Category:Indian nonlinear narrative films]]\n[[Category:Best Popular Film Providing Wholesome Entertainment National Film Award winners]]\n[[Category:Films that won the Best Audiography National Film Award]]\n[[Category:Films set in universities and colleges]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2009 Indian Hindi language comedy film}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=February 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2020}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = 3 Idiots\n| image          = Threeidiots2.jpg\n| alt            = <!-- see WP:ALT -->\n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| director       = [[Rajkumar Hirani]]\n| producer       = [[Vidhu Vinod Chopra]]\n| screenplay     = [[Abhijat Joshi]]<br />[[Rajkumar Hirani]]<br />Vidhu Vinod Chopra\n| story          = [[Rajkumar Hirani]]<br />Abhijat Joshi\n| based on       = ''[[Five Point Someone]]'' by <br/>[[Chetan Bhagat]]\n| starring       = {{plainlist|\n* [[Aamir Khan]]\n* [[R. Madhavan|Madhavan]]\n* [[Sharman Joshi]]\n* [[Kareena Kapoor]]\n* [[Boman Irani]]\n* [[Omi Vaidya]]\n}}\n| narrator       = [[R. Madhavan|Madhavan]]\n| music          = [[Shantanu Moitra]]\n| cinematography = [[C. K. Muraleedharan]]\n| editing        = Rajkumar Hirani\n| studio         = [[Vinod Chopra Films]]\n| distributor    = [[Reliance Entertainment|Reliance BIG Pictures]]\n| released       = {{Film date|2009|12|25|India|df=y}}\n| runtime        = 170 minutes<ref name=Runtime>{{cite web|title=''3 IDIOTS'' (12A)|url=http://www.bbfc.co.uk/releases/3-idiots-0|work=[[British Board of Film Classification]]|accessdate=5 October 2012|date=17 December 2009}}</ref>\n| country        = India\n| language       = [[Hindi]]\n| budget         = {{INR}} 55 [[crore]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.economictimes.indiatimes.com/2012-08-26/news/33386102_1_box-office-movie-rotten-tomatoes/2|title=Business of Rs 100-cr films: Who gets what and why|work=[[The Economic Times]]|publisher=[[The Times Group]]|date=26 August 2012|accessdate=22 February 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"exchange\"/>\n| gross          = <!--Do not remove-->{{Estimation}}<!--per discussion at WP:ICTF--> {{INR}} 460 crore<ref name=\":1\"/><ref name=\"hollywoodreporter\"/>\n}}\n'''''3 Idiots''''' is a 2009 Indian [[Hindi]]-language [[Coming-of-age story|coming-of-age]] [[comedy-drama]] film co-written (with [[Abhijat Joshi]]) and directed by [[Rajkumar Hirani]]. Starring [[Aamir Khan]], [[R. Madhavan|Madhavan]], [[Sharman Joshi]], [[Kareena Kapoor]], [[Boman Irani]] and [[Omi Vaidya]], the film follows the friendship of three students at an Indian [[engineering college]] and is a [[satire]] about the social pressures under an Indian education system.<ref name=\"scmp\"/><ref name=\"economic_china\"/><ref name=\"kaist\"/> The film is narrated through parallel dramas, one in the present and the other ten years in the past. It also incorporated real Indian inventions, namely those created by Remya Jose,<ref name=\"jose\"/> Mohammad Idris,<ref name=\"nif\"/> Jahangir Painter<ref name=\"mid\"/> and [[Sonam Wangchuk (engineer)|Sonam Wangchuk]].<ref name=\"telegraphindia\"/>\n\nProduced by [[Vidhu Vinod Chopra]] under the banner [[Vinod Chopra Films]], ''3 Idiots'' received widespread critical<ref name=\"rt\"/> and commercial success upon its release on 25 December 2009. The film was the highest-grossing film in its opening weekend in [[India]], had the highest opening day collections for an [[Indian film]] up until that point and also held the record for the highest net collections in the first week for a Bollywood film. It also became one of the few Indian films at the time to become successful in [[East Asia]]n markets such as [[China]]<ref name=overseas>{{cite web|title=Three Idiots Creates History in China|url=http://www.boxofficeindia.com/boxnewsdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=3866&nCat=|work=30 December 2011|publisher=BoxOfficeIndia. Com|accessdate=30 December 2011}}</ref> and [[Japan]],<ref name=\"qz\"/> eventually bringing its worldwide gross to {{INR|link=yes}}392{{nbsp}}[[crore]] ($90{{nbsp}}million){{efn|name=Gross}}<ref name=\":1\"/><ref name=\"hollywoodreporter\"/> \u2014 it was the [[List of highest-grossing Indian films|highest-grossing Indian film ever]] at the time.<ref name=\"forbes\"/> The film also had a social impact on attitudes to [[education in India]].<ref name=\"Hussain\"/>\n\nThe film won six [[Filmfare Awards]] including [[Filmfare Award for Best Film|Best Film]] and three [[National Film Awards]] including [[National Film Award for Best Popular Film Providing Wholesome Entertainment|Best Popular Film]]. Overseas, it won the Grand Prize at Japan's Videoyasan Awards<ref name=\"videoyasan\"/><ref name=\"nikkatsu\"/><ref name=\"qz\"/> while was nominated for [[Japan Academy Prize for Outstanding Foreign Language Film|Best Outstanding Foreign Language Film]] at the [[Japan Academy Prize (film)|Japan Academy Awards]]<ref name=\"japan-hungama\"/><ref name=\"japan-ibn\"/> and Best Foreign Film at China's [[Beijing International Film Festival]].<ref name=\"maoyan\"/> This film was remade in [[Tamil language|Tamil]] as ''[[Nanban (2012 film)|Nanban]]'' (2012), which also received critical praise and commercial success.<ref name=\"nanban_ibn\">{{cite web|url=http://www.moneycontrol.com/news/entertainment/will-nanban-repeatmagic3-idiots_650433.html |title=Will 'Nanban' repeat the magic of '3 Idiots'? \u2013 IBNLive.com |publisher=[[CNBC]] |accessdate=5 March 2012}}</ref><ref name=\"nanban_hindustantimes\">{{cite web |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/Entertainment/Reviews/Gautaman-Bhaskaran-s-review-Nanban/Article1-797009.aspx |title=Gautaman Bhaskaran's review: Nanban |work=[[Hindustan Times]] |date=14 January 2012 |accessdate=5 March 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120312175929/http://www.hindustantimes.com/Entertainment/Reviews/Gautaman-Bhaskaran-s-review-Nanban/Article1-797009.aspx |archivedate=12 March 2012  }}</ref> ''Nanban'' had a [[Telugu cinema|Telugu]] dubbed version titled ''[[Snehitudu]].'' A [[Mexico|Mexican]] remake, ''[[3 idiotas]]'', was also released in 2017.<ref>{{cite web|title=3 idiotas se estrenar\u00e1 en el 2017|url=http://www.debate.com.mx/show/3-idiotas-se-estrenara-en-el-2017-20160713-0024.html}}</ref>\n\n== Plot ==\nIn the year 1999, Farhan Qureshi and Raju Rastogi begin their college year in the prestigious Imperial College of [[Engineering]] (ICE) in [[Delhi]]. They are joined by Ranchoddas Chanchad, nicknamed \"Rancho\", as their roommate. They meet Manmohan a.k.a. \"Millimetre\", an adolescent boy helping the students . He is persuaded by Rancho to sneak into school and get educated. While Farhan chose to pursue engineering over his passion for photography to appease his father, Raju has taken the course in an attempt to end his family's poverty and is always afraid of failing. Rancho, on the other hand, is genuinely passionate in science and engineering. He believes in hands-on learning and tends to give unorthodox answers in class, resulting in him coming into conflict with the professors, particularly the institution's director, Viru Sahastrabuddhe, whom the ICE community nicknames \"Virus\". Virus's traditional and strict philosophies on education contrast sharply with Rancho's carefree love of learning. Meanwhile, Chatur, nicknamed \"Silencer\" (because of his nature of silently farting), is an arrogant student with little knowledge of Hindi due to his Ugandan-Tamilian upbringing, who is obsessed with topping the exams and invariably learns by rote.\n\nSometime later, the trio finds that a student named Joy Lobo, whose interest in machines was as much as Rancho, committed [[suicide]] by [[Suicide by hanging|hanging himself]], which was caused by [[Depression (mood)|depression]] after Virus informs Joy's father that Joy would be unable to graduate that year due to a delay in his submission of an assignment. Joy had taken longer as he wanted to perfect his breakthrough drone design of a quad-copter, and also due to a break on account of his father's brief illness. Rancho criticises Virus' method of teaching and tries to show him how much pressure engineers face when they study, angering him further. Rancho visits his friends' families, and later, the trio then gatecrashes the wedding of Virus' elder daughter, Mona to eat good food. They meet and befriend Pia, who turns out to be Virus' younger daughter and a resident student at the city's hospital. Rancho advises Pia not to marry her fianc\u00e9e Suhas Tandon because he's madly obsessed with expensive jewellery, brands, and prices and has no true love for her. Rancho gives Pia a demo on Suhas' attitude by spilling mint sauce on his shoes to annoy him. When Virus spots the trio, he summons Farhan and Raju on the next working day and tells them of the consequences of being friends with Rancho by comparing their families' incomes. He tells them that Rancho comes from a very rich family and does not need to worry about getting good grades and making a career. Affected, Raju moves out and into Chatur's room. During the Teachers Day celebration, Chatur is humiliated when he delivers a Hindi speech modified by Rancho and as a result, he bets Rancho that ten years later, they would see who is more successful. Sometime later, Pia is at the mall with Suhas and spots Rancho with an invention named after Virus; The Virus Inverter. Rancho explains to Pia that he dislikes the way her father teaches his students and that they end up lame like Suhas. Rancho plays a prank on Suhas, pretending that Pia lost her watch, to prove that Suhas shows more value to expensive stuff rather than her. Fed up with Suhas' behaviour, she tells him off. Rancho and Pia save Raju's dying father; Raju reconciles with his friends while Pia falls in love with Rancho.\n\nOne night during their senior year, Farhan and Raju are upset that they are trailing behind in their grades every year and that Rancho is always in the front of every school picture. Farhan exposes Rancho of not telling Pia that he is in love with her and hasn't told her for the past four years. The three friends drunkenly break into the Sahastrabuddhe residence so that Rancho can propose to Pia. As the trio escape, Virus recognises Raju and, on the next day, threatens to expel him unless he writes a letter recommending Rancho for expulsion. Unwilling to betray Rancho or disappoint his family, Raju unsuccessfully attempts suicide and ends up in a [[coma]]. With intensive care and support from his friends, Raju recovers just in time for his first job interview on the campus, which he succeeds in cracking. Meanwhile, Rancho and Pia post Farhan's letter to his favourite Hungarian wildlife photographer Andre Istvan, who offers him a position as an assistant. On Rancho's advice, he communicates his dream to his father, who though reluctant at first, gives his blessings for the sake of his son's happiness.\n\nInfuriated by this and Rancho's influence, Virus sets a difficult final exam paper to fail Raju, wherein Pia tries to help the trio by revealing to them the location of the exam paper in her father's office; unfortunately, Virus finds out and expels them. Pia confronts Virus about her brother who had committed suicide because he couldn't meet Virus' expectation of clearing the engineering exam. That same night, the pregnant Mona goes into labour during a heavy storm that cuts off all traffic and electricity in the city. Rancho and the other students help them by using their engineering knowledge to quickly modify a [[vacuum cleaner]] into a [[ventouse]] and deliver the baby with the help of Pia over a video call. A grateful Virus finally acknowledges Rancho as an extraordinary student and revokes their expulsion. On graduation day, Rancho suddenly disappears shortly after the ceremony ends.\n\nTen years later, in 2009, Farhan is a successful wildlife photographer, while Raju is married and settled with his family in a comfortable lifestyle with a corporate job and Chatur is married and the vice-president of a reputable corporation in the [[United States]] wanting to crack a business deal with a world renowned scientist and businessman with 400 patents to his name, Phunsukh Wangdu for whom he has been asking an appointment for over 1 year  ; none among the three of them have heard from Rancho since graduation. Reuniting at the ICE campus, after Chatur reminds them about the bet,they travel to Shimla, where Rancho was spotted in the background of a snapshot taken by Chatur's secretary, Tracy, who was trying to get an appointment with Wangdu. Chatur then went through the Shimla directory and found the address of Rancho. Upon arrival, they meet a man who turns out to be the real Ranchoddas Chanchad ([[Javed Jaffrey]]) at his father's funeral and the photos of the Rancho they knew replaced with the real one. From him, Farhan and Raju learn that the Rancho they knew was actually \"Chhote\", the smart son of the gardener who was a servant to the Chanchad family who would sneak into school wearing Ranchoddas' old uniform and help Ranchoddas with his schoolwork until he was found out by a teacher who told Ranchoddas' father.Ranchoddas' father then arranged for Chhote to attend ICE in his son's name so that  Ranchoddas could take credit for the degree while  he was in London for 4 years . He also told Chhote to cut off all contact with his ICE friends after graduating but Chhote was sure that Farhan and Raju would come looking for him. Ranchoddas provides Chhote's address in [[Ladakh]], where he is a schoolteacher. On the way, they pass [[Manali, Himachal Pradesh|Manali]] where against Chatur's wishes, they rescue and prevent Pia from marrying Suhas, who is now a changed man but reverts to his old ways when Raju, disguised as the housekeeping man, puts mint sauce on his wedding jacket, making Raju run away from the wedding in his attire. \n\nUpon arrival in Ladakh, the four head to the village school and witness the young students' inventions that resemble Chhote's college projects. They are reunited with the adult educated Manmohan, now going by the nickname \"Centimetre\" who has now become a helper for Chhote after receiving a letter from him to help him. He tells them that Chhote never forgot about them, stealing and keeping Pia's scooter helmet as a memento, reading Farhan's photography books and Raju's blog. He then tells them where to find Chhote. The four happily reunite with Chhote  to which Pia and Chhote smooch, while Chatur, unaware of Chhote's secret thinking he is Rancho, insults and asks Chhote to sign a contract stating that he is the least successful person; Chhote does so without commenting. As Chatur walks away triumphantly, Chhote reveals that his real name is Phunsukh Wangdu, to his friends' and Pia's surprise and delight. Realizing this, a horrified Chatur accepts his defeat and pleads him to sign his contract while Phunsukh and his friends run away laughing. In the end,  Wangdu tells everyone his theory: \"Follow excellence and success will by itself follow you\".\n\n== Cast ==\n* [[Aamir Khan]] as Ranchoddas \"Rancho\" Shamaldas Chanchad / Chhote / Phunsukh Wangdu, one of the titular trio in the engineering college who vanishes after graduation and whom his two friends hunt for 5 years, while telling stories of their time in college together. Rancho was prodigal student, with contempt for the inhumanity of the college's system. At the end of the film, he is shown to be a famous scientist, entrepreneur and business magnate who also teaches young children when he takes a break from researching.\n* [[R. Madhavan|Madhavan]] as Farhan Qureshi, the film's narrator and one of the trio whose father persuades him to study engineering over his dream career of wildlife photography; in the end he is shown to have published several books of photographs.\n* [[Sharman Joshi]] as Raju Rastogi, another of the trio who comes from an impoverished family with a mother who is a retired school teacher and a paralysed father who worked as a postman. In the flashback story, his family was unable to afford the car that would be demanded as a [[Dowry system in India|dowry]] for his sister. In the present story, he is a settled married man in Delhi who has freed his family from poverty by becoming a wealthy executive.\n* [[Kareena Kapoor]] as Piya Sahastrabuddhe, Virus' younger daughter, an intelligent and capable doctor. Despite her father's disapproval, she and Rancho fall in love.\n* [[Boman Irani]] as Dr. Viru Sahastrabuddhe, the college's strict director known as \"Virus\" and Pia and Mona's father who acts as the film's antagonist. He stubbornly sticks to a doctrinal method of teaching, putting him at odds with Rancho. At the end, he is shown to have changed his doctrinal methods of teaching.\n* [[Omi Vaidya]] as Chatur Ramalingam, a [[Indians in Uganda|Ugandan-Indian]] educated in [[Tamil language|Tamil]]-speaking [[Pondicherry]] who has little knowledge of Hindi. His habit of being gassy due to consumption of pills to enhance his memorisation earns him the nickname Silencer. In the present story, he is vice-president of an American company (Rockledge Corporation) who discovers his success being overshadowed by Rancho in the end of the film. [[Baradwaj Rangan]] wrote that Chatur being a Tamil from Uganda makes him \"twice removed from the North Indians around him \u2013 a stranger to the nation as well as the national language.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/reviews/article87588.ece|title=3 Idiots|last=Rangan|first=Baradwaj|date=27 December 2009|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151127143622/http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/reviews/article87588.ece|archive-date=27 November 2015|work=[[New Indian Express]]}}</ref>\n* [[Rahul Kumar (actor)|Rahul Kumar]] as young Manmohan (nicknamed Millimetre), and [[Dushyant Wagh]] as adult Manmohan (Centimetre). As an adolescent, he earns a small living by doing errands for students, such as laundry, finishing assignments and getting groceries. Rancho persuades him to buy a school uniform and sneak into school to gain an education. Later he becomes an assistant to Rancho/Phunsukh Wangdu in Ladakh.\n* [[Mona Singh]] as Mona Sahastrabuddhe, Pia's elder sister and Virus's first daughter.\n* [[Parikshit Sahni]] as Mr Qureshi, Farhan's father, a strict but loving parent who just wants his son to be happy.\n* Farida Dadi as Mrs. Qureshi, Farhan's mother, a loving and caring parent.\n* [[Amardeep Jha]] as Mrs. Rastogi, Raju's mother, a retired schoolteacher and dedicated mother.\n* Mukund Bhatt as Mr. Rastogi, Raju's paralysed father who used to work as a postman.\n* Rajendra Patwardhan as Govind, Viru's personal assistant.\n* [[Javed Jaffrey]] as the real Ranchoddas Shyamaldas Chanchad. It is from him that Raju and Farhan learn the truth: Chanchad's father sponsored an orphaned servant boy called 'Chhote', who had demonstrated his intelligence and love of learning, to earn a degree in his name, while the real Ranchoddas was in London. He appreciates what Chhote did for him, and tells Raju and Farhan where to find him.\n* [[Arun Bali]] as Shyamaldas Chanchad, father of Ranchoddas Shyamaldas Chanchad.\n* [[Ali Fazal]] as Joy Lobo, a student with a passion for machines. After Virus tells him that he will not graduate, he commits suicide.\n* [[Akhil Mishra]] as Librarian Dubey.\n* [[Rohitash Gaud]] as Ranchoddas' (Real Ranchodas) servant.\n* [[Achyut Potdar]] as Machine Class Professor\n* [[Madhav Vaze]] as Joy Lobo's father.\n* Olivier Sanjay Lafont as Suhas Tandon, Piya's ex-fianc\u00e9, who cares only about money and ostentation.\n* [[Jayant Kripalani]] as a company head who conducts Raju's job interview.\n* Atul Tiwari as R.D. Tripathi, Education Minister in Auditorium during Silencer's speech.\n* Rajeev Ravindranathan as ragging senior student.\n* [[Supriya Shukla]] as Nurse with Pia.\n\n== Production ==\n[[Principal photography]] began on 28 July 2008. Hirani and his team left in late August for the shoot with the principal cast. The film was shot in [[Delhi]], [[Bangalore]], [[Mumbai]], [[Ladakh]], [[Chail, Himachal Pradesh|Chail]] and [[Shimla]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.filmapia.com/published/movies/3/3-idiots | title=Movie Locations for 3 Idiots|publisher=filmapia.com}}</ref> Aamir and the rest of the cast began shooting in early September. Hirani planned to wrap up the film by December.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiafm.com/news/2008/07/28/11730/index.html |title=Rajkumar Hirani's 3 Idiots goes on floors |publisher=indiafm.com |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080804233117/http://www.indiafm.com/news/2008/07/28/11730/index.html |archivedate=4 August 2008 }}</ref> The first scene was shot in an aircraft with Madhavan. From Mumbai, the crew and cast comprising Aamir and Kareena went to Ladakh for a 20-day schedule.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://ia.rediff.com/movies/2008/aug/28look1.htm |title=Shooting for 3 Idiots underway |publisher=Rediff}}</ref> Filming of the ICE college scenes took place at the [[Indian Institute of Management Bangalore|Indian Institute of Management, Bangalore]] campus for 33 days as a part of the second schedule of production. The dormitory scenes were filmed at the institution's female dormitory block.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thaindian.com/newsportal/uncategorized/shooting-three-idiots-is-like-holidaying-for-aamir-khan_100143291.html |title=Shooting 'Three Idiots' is like holidaying |publisher=the indian.com |access-date=11 February 2009 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120321022923/http://www.thaindian.com/newsportal/uncategorized/shooting-three-idiots-is-like-holidaying-for-aamir-khan_100143291.html |archive-date=21 March 2012 |url-status=dead  }}</ref>\n\nThe brains behind these innovations include Remya Jose, a student from [[Kerala]], who created the pedal operated washing-machine;<ref name=\"jose\">{{cite news|last=Raphael|first=Lisa|title=Watch This 14-Year-Old Girl's Washing Machine Hack in Action|url=http://www.brit.co/remya-jose-pedal-washing-machine/|accessdate=10 November 2016|publisher=Brit + Co.|date=19 June 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VhlUVdbU9Lk|title=Remya Jose's pedal operated washing machine / exercise machine|website=You Tube|publisher=Remya Jose|last1=Jose|first1=Remya|accessdate=10 November 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ecoideaz.com/innovative-green-ideas/pedal-power-machines|title=Innovative Pedal Power Machines|date=3 February 2015|website=www.ecoideaz.com/innovative-green-ideas/pedal-power-machines|publisher=Ecoideaz|last1=Sreelakshmy|first1=V.U.|accessdate=10 November 2016}}</ref> Mohammad Idris, a barber from Hasanpur Kalan in [[Meerut]] district in [[Uttar Pradesh]], who invented a bicycle-powered horse clipper;<ref name=\"nif\">{{cite web|url=http://nif.org.in/innovation/Cycle_Operated_Horse_Shaver/229|title=Cycle operated horse shaver|website=www.nif.org.in|publisher=National Innovation Fund|accessdate=10 November 2016}}</ref> and Jahangir Painter, a painter from Maharashtra, who made the scooter-powered flour mill.<ref name=\"mid\">{{cite web|url=http://www.mid-day.com/news/2009/dec/281209-3-idiots-scooter-flour-mill-Inventions-Pune.htm|title=The real brains behind 3 idiots|last=Sabnis|first=Vivek |date=28 December 2009|publisher=[[Mid Day]]|accessdate=29 April 2010|location=Pune}}</ref> The character Phunsuk Wangdu may have also drawn inspiration from [[Ladakh]]i inventor [[Sonam Wangchuk (engineer)|Sonam Wangchuk]], a mechanical engineering graduate from the [[National Institute of Technology, Srinagar]].<ref name=\"telegraphindia\">{{cite news|last=Menon|first=Shyam G.|title=What you did not watch in 3 Idiots - Rethink after Ladakh education initiative fell victim to bureaucracy and resentment|url=https://www.telegraphindia.com/1100719/jsp/frontpage/story_12700204.jsp|publisher=[[The Telegraph (Calcutta)]]|date=19 July 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Secmol founder Sonam Wangchuk wins Magasaysay Award |url=https://www.nationalheraldindia.com/national/secmol-founder-wins-magasaysay-award-sonam-wangchuk |accessdate=25 March 2020 |work=National Herald |date=3 August 2018 |language=en}}</ref>\n\n== Soundtrack ==\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = 3 Idiots\n| type       = Soundtrack\n| artist     = [[Shantanu Moitra]]\n| cover      = \n| alt        =\n| released   = 2009\n| recorded   =\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Feature film soundtrack]]\n| length     = 29:22\n| label      = [[T-Series (company)|T-Series]]\n| producer   = Shantanu Moitra\n| prev_title = [[Phir Kabhi]]\n| prev_year  = 2009\n| next_title = [[Well Done Abba]]\n| next_year  = 2010\n}}\n\n{{Album ratings\n| rev1 = [[Bollywood Hungama]]\n| rev1Score = {{Rating|3.5|5}}<ref>{{cite web|title=3 Idiots : Music Review by Joginder Tuteja |url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/musicreview/13910/index.html |work=Bollywood Hungama |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090519105032/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/musicreview/13910/index.html |archivedate=19 May 2009 }}</ref>\n| rev2 = Behindwoods\n| rev2Score = {{Rating|3.5|5}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/bollywood/hindi-music-reviews/3-idiots.html|title= 3 Idiots Music review|work=Behindwoods}}</ref>\n| rev3 = [[Rediff]]\n| rev3Score = {{Rating|3|5}}<ref>{{cite web|title=3 Idiots: Short 'n' sweet soundtrack|url=http://movies.rediff.com/report/2009/nov/11/music-review-3-idiots.htm|work=Rediff}}</ref>\n| rev4 = Planet Bollywood\n| rev4Score = {{Rating|7|10}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.planetbollywood.com/displayReview.php?id=m110909062049|title=3 Idiots|work=Planet Bollywood}}</ref>\n|noprose=yes}}\n\nThe film's soundtrack is composed by [[Shantanu Moitra]] with lyrics penned by [[Swanand Kirkire]].\n\n{{Track listing\n| all_writing = \n| headline = Track listing\n| extra_column = Singer(s)\n| title1 = Aal Izz Well\n| length1 = 4:34\n| extra1 = [[Sonu Nigam]], [[Shaan (singer)|Shaan]], [[Swanand Kirkire]]\n| title2 = Zoobi Doobi\n| length2 = 4:06\n| extra2 = Sonu Nigam, [[Shreya Ghoshal]]\n| title3 = Behti Hawa Sa Tha Woh\n| length3 = 4:59\n| extra3 = [[Shantanu Moitra]], Shaan\n| title4 = Give Me Some Sunshine\n| length4 = 4:05\n| extra4 = [[Suraj Jagan]], [[Sharman Joshi]], [[Rahat Fateh Ali Khan]]\n| title5 = Jaane Nahin Denge Tujhe\n| length5 = 3:30\n| extra5 = Sonu Nigam\n| title6 = Zoobi Doobi\n| note6 = Remix\n| length6 = 3:27\n| extra6 = Sonu Nigam, Shreya Ghoshal\n| title7 = Aal Izz Well\n| note7 = Remix\n| length7 = 4:41\n| extra7 = Sonu Nigam, Shaan, Swanand Kirkire, Jaive Samsun\n| total_length = 29:22\n| title8 = \n| length8 = \n| title9 = \n| length9 = \n| title10 = \n| length10 = \n}}\n\n== Release ==\nThe film initially opened up on 1550 prints worldwide.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://businessofcinema.com/bollywood-news/3-idiots-releases-with-highest-ever-print-screen-count/30196|title=3 Idiots releases with highest ever print & screen count|publisher=BusinessofCinema|accessdate=28 December 2011}}</ref> 3 Idiots was released in 1800 theatres in India, which was at that time a big domestic release.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-08-11/news-interviews/41268470_1_100-crore-club-chennai-express-150-cr |title=100-crore club is past, Its 150-crore club for 'Chennai Express' |work=The Times of India|accessdate=11 August 2013}}</ref> ''3 Idiots'' was released in 415 screens overseas.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/talaash-is-aamir-khans-film-a-hit-even-before-the-release/307969-8-66.html |title=Talaash: Is Aamir Khan's film a hit even before the release? |work=CNN IBN |accessdate=25 April 2013}}</ref>\n\nIt was expected to be the first Indian film to be officially released on [[YouTube]] on 25 March 2010, only 12 weeks after its initial theatrical release. Officially, it was released on YouTube in May 2012, but its access has since been restricted.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yto4_QFoLdA |title=3 idiots |publisher=YouTube |accessdate=14 May 2012}}</ref>However, it has been made available for online streaming on [[Netflix]], [[Prime Video]] and [[Sony LIV]].<ref>{{cite web|title=3 Idiots|url=https://reelgood.com/movie/3-idiots-2009|publisher=Reelgood.comlanguage=en}}</ref>\n\nThe film released in [[Taiwan]] on December 2010, followed by [[Hong Kong]] on 1 September 2011.<ref name=\"hkfilmart\"/> In [[China]], it was released as ''San Geshagua'' (\"Three Idiots\"),<ref name=\"economic_china\"/> in December 2011.<ref name=\"economictimes\"/> In [[South Korea]], it was released in 2011.<ref name=\"kaist\"/> Alongside the original Hindi version, a [[Mandarin Chinese]] dubbed version was also released, with the popular actress [[Tang Wei]] (known for ''[[Lust, Caution]]'') voicing Kareena Kapoor's role<ref name=\"hindu_china\">{{cite news|last=Krishnan|first=Ananth|title=Success of 3 Idiots breaks China's Bollywood Great Wall|url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/Success-of-3-Idiots-breaks-Chinas-Bollywood-Great-Wall/article13349901.ece|newspaper=[[The Hindu]]|accessdate=29 March 2012|location=Beijing, China|date=2 January 2012}}</ref> and [[Huang Bo]] voicing Aamir Khan's role (Khan and Bo later collaborated again on ''[[Secret Superstar]]'').<ref>{{cite news|title=\u9ec4\u6e24\u732e\u5531\u300a\u795e\u79d8\u5de8\u661f\u300b\u4e3b\u9898\u66f2 \u963f\u7c73\u5c14\u6c57\u98d9\u5c71\u4e1c\u8bdd|url=http://ent.sina.com.cn/m/c/2018-01-25/doc-ifyqwiqk3852226.shtml|work=Sina|date=25 January 2018}}</ref>\n\nFollowing its success in other [[Cinema of Asia|Asian markets]], Japanese distributor [[Nikkatsu]] announced plans to release the film in [[Japan]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Indian films set to make inroads in Japan?  |url=http://in.lifestyle.yahoo.com/indian-films-set-inroads-japan-092639925.html|publisher=[[Yahoo! News]]|accessdate=29 March 2012|date=17 October 2011}}</ref> It was released there in June 2013,<ref name=\"qz\"/> with the title \u304d\u3063\u3068\u3001\u3046\u307e\u304f\u3044\u304f (''Kitto, Umaku Iku'').<ref>{{cite web|title=\u304d\u3063\u3068\u3001\u3046\u307e\u304f\u3044\u304f|url=https://filmarks.com/movies/53954|website=Filmarks|publisher=[[Culture Convenience Club]]|accessdate=27 January 2018|language=ja}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n===Box office===\nThe film's worldwide lifetime gross was {{INR|link=yes}}459.96{{nbsp}}[[crore]] ([[US$]]90{{nbsp}}million),{{efn|name=Gross|''3 Idiots'' worldwide gross: {{INR}}{{#expr:273.82+186.142}}&nbsp;crore (US$90&nbsp;million)<ref name=\"hollywoodreporter\"/>\n*Domestic: {{INR}} 273.82&nbsp;crore<ref>{{cite web|title=Top India Grossers All Time|url=https://www.boxofficeindia.com/india-total-gross.php|website=[[Box Office India]]|accessdate=12 November 2017}}</ref> (US$57.05&nbsp;million)<ref>{{cite web|title=Yearly Average Rates (48 INR per USD)|url=https://www.ofx.com/en-gb/forex-news/historical-exchange-rates/yearly-average-rates/|website=[[OFX (company)|OFX]]|year=2009|access-date=13 November 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170713183556/https://www.ofx.com/en-gb/forex-news/historical-exchange-rates/yearly-average-rates/|archive-date=13 July 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n*Overseas: US$30.5&nbsp;million<ref name=\"ibtimes\">{{cite news|last=Hooli|first=Shekhar|title=Baahubali 2 overseas box office collection: Rajamouli's film beats Chennai Express, Kabali's lifetime record in 1st weekend|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/baahubali-2-overseas-box-office-collection-rajamoulis-film-beats-chennai-express-kabalis-725036|work=[[International Business Times]]|date=1 May 2017|language=en}}</ref> ({{INR}} 186.142 crore)<ref name=\"exchange\">{{cite web |title=Exchange Rates (61.03 INR per USD) |work=[[The World Factbook]] |publisher=[[Central Intelligence Agency]] |url=https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/fields/2076.html |year=2013 |access-date=16 November 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150215024949/https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook//fields/2076.html |archive-date=15 February 2015 |url-status=dead  }}</ref>\n}}<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite news|url=http://www.timesnownews.com/entertainment/box-office/article/deepika-padukone-padmaavat-beats-aamir-khan-dhoom-3-and-salman-khans-tiger-zinda-hai-at-the-box-office/202889|title=Deepika Padukone's Padmaavat beats Aamir Khan's Dhoom 3 and Salman Khan's Tiger Zinda Hai at the box office|date=27 February 2018|work=[[Times Now]]}}</ref><ref name=\"hollywoodreporter\">{{cite news|title=Q&A: Aamir Khan|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/qampa-aamir-khan-26582|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=11 August 2010|language=en}}</ref> making it the [[List of highest-grossing Indian films|highest-grossing Indian film]] at the time.<ref name=\"forbes\">{{cite news|last=Cain|first=Rob|title=It's Another Diwali Clash of Titans As Ajay's 'Golmaal' Takes on Aamir's 'Superstar'|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/robcain/2017/10/11/its-another-diwali-clash-of-titans-as-ajays-golmaal-takes-on-aamirs-superstar/|work=[[Forbes]]|date=11 October 2017|language=en}}</ref><ref name=\"boxofficeindia\">{{cite web|url=http://www.boxofficeindia.com/boxnewsdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=5979&nCat= |title=Boxofficeindia.com |accessdate=8 August 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131105220137/http://boxofficeindia.com/boxnewsdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=5979&nCat= |archivedate=5 November 2013 }}</ref> The film was listed in [[Guinness World Records]] for the record of highest box office film gross for a [[Bollywood]] film.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.guinnessworldrecords.com/records-1000/highest-box-office-film-gross-for-a-bollywood-film/ |title=You are here:Global Home > Explore Records > Highest box office film gross for a Bollywood film |publisher=[[Guinness World Records]]|date=4 October 2012 |accessdate=4 October 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.guinnessworldrecords.in/news/2012/8/happy-independence-day-our-top-10-records-from-india-44243/|title=You are here:Home >News >2012 >8 >Happy Independence Day: Our Top 10 records from India |publisher=[[Guinness World Records]]|date=4 October 2012 |accessdate=4 October 2012}}</ref>\n\n==== India ====\nThe film created the highest collection record for paid previews with [[Indian rupee|{{INR}}]]27.5&nbsp;million that time, which was broken by ''[[Chennai Express]]'' (2013).<ref>http://www.boxofficeindia.com/boxnewsdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=5936&nCat=</ref><ref name=\"boxofficeindia3\">{{cite web|url=http://www.boxofficeindia.com/boxnewsdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=5937&nCat|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130922174013/http://www.boxofficeindia.com/boxnewsdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=5937&nCat |archive-date=22 September 2013 |url-status=dead|title=Boxofficeindia.com|accessdate=8 August 2014}}</ref> In its four-day first weekend, the film netted {{INRConvert|38|c|year=2009}}, and broke the record held by ''[[Ghajini (2008 film)|Ghajini]]'' for the first weekend collections.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.filmbiz.asia/news/dabangg-breaks-india-records|title=Dabangg breaks India records|publisher=Film Business Asia|accessdate=28 November 2011|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131110152151/http://www.filmbiz.asia/news/dabangg-breaks-india-records|archivedate=10 November 2013}}</ref> By the first week, the film netted {{INRConvert|79|c|year=2009}}, again breaking the box office record held by ''Ghajini''.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.telegraphindia.com/1100224/jsp/nation/story_12144926.jsp|title=My Name plays on but Idiots shifts bar|publisher=[[The Telegraph (Kolkata)|The Telegraph]]|accessdate=28 November 2011}}</ref> ''3 Idiots'' had nett grossed {{INRConvert|56|c|year=2009}} in its 2nd week, {{INRConvert|302.5|m}} during the third week, {{INRConvert|16|c|year=2009}} in its fourth week and {{INRConvert|9.75|c|year=2009}} in fifth to make a total of {{INR}} 202&nbsp;crore in five weeks,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.koimoi.com/box-office/shah-rukhs-happy-new-year-beats-salmans-kicks-worldwide-collections/|title=Shah Rukh's Happy New Year Beats Salman's Kick's Worldwide Collections|first=Koimoi com|last=Team|date=13 November 2014}}</ref> first Indian film ever to collect this huge amount, hence established the [[100 Crore Club|{{INRConvert|200|c}} Club]].<ref>http://bollywoodmoviereview.in/200-crores-club/bollywood/</ref> Its final domestic gross in India was {{INR}} 273.82 crore (US$57.05 million).{{efn|name=Gross}}\n\n==== Overseas ====\n''3 Idiots'' became the then [[List of highest-grossing Indian films in overseas markets|highest-grossing Indian film in overseas markets]], with an overseas gross of US$30.5&nbsp;million ({{INR}} 186&nbsp;crore).{{efn|name=Gross}} Its first weekend opening collection overseas was $4&nbsp;million.<ref>{{cite web|title=Talaash Is Excellent Overseas|url=http://businesstoday.intoday.in/story/talaash-overseas-box-office-collection-jab-tak-hai-jaan/1/190417.html|publisher=BT Online Bureau|accessdate=7 December 2012}}</ref><ref name=\"Overseas opening\">{{cite web|title=Talaash beats 3 Idiots record at overseas box office|url=http://www.boxofficeindia.com/overdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=5172&nCat=|publisher=[[Box Office India]]|accessdate=5 December 2012}}</ref> It set record collections for Indian-produced films in territories such as the [[United States]]<ref name=\"highest\">{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/films/news/aamir-khans-3-idiots-becomes-bollywoods-biggest-grosser-1859492.html|title=Aamir Khan's '3 Idiots' becomes Bollywood's biggest grosser|work=The Independent|date=6 January 2010|accessdate=21 November 2010}}</ref> and [[Australia]].<ref name=\"mojo3\" /> In the United States, the film earned $6.5&nbsp;million since its opening,<ref name=highest /><ref name=\"mojo3\">{{cite web|url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=3idiots.htm|title=3 Idiots (2009)|website=Box Office Mojo|accessdate=29 April 2010| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20100507171808/http://boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=3idiots.htm| archivedate= 7 May 2010 | url-status= live}}</ref> in addition to over $2.5&nbsp;million in the [[United Kingdom]], over $2&nbsp;million in [[Canada]], and nearly $1&nbsp;million in Australia.<ref name=\"mojo3\" /> ''3 Idiots'' has the biggest first week total in the US with around $3&nbsp;million over its first four days.<ref>{{cite web|title=Don 2 Second Biggest First Week Grosser Ever in US|url=http://www.boxofficeindia.com/boxnewsdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=3871&nCat=|publisher=[[Box Office India]]|accessdate=5 December 2012}}</ref>\n\n====East Asia====\nUnusual for an Indian film at the time, ''3 Idiots'' became a success in [[East Asia]]n markets.<ref name=\"economic_china\" /> ''3 Idiots'' had a wide release in East Asian markets including [[China]], [[South Korea]] and [[Hong Kong]].<ref name=\"dhoom3idiotsoverseas\">{{cite web |url=http://www.boxofficeindia.com/overdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=6354&nCat= |title=Dhoom 3 Set For ALL TIME RECORD Overseas |publisher=[[Box Office India]] |date=1 January 2014 |accessdate=1 January 2014 |url-status=bot: unknown |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140105151547/http://www.boxofficeindia.com/overdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=6354&nCat= |archivedate=5 January 2014  }}</ref> The film had the longest showing period at cinemas in [[Taiwan]], for more than two months from December 2010, breaking the record of ''[[Avatar (2009 film)|Avatar]]'', with over [[New Taiwan dollar|NT$]]10&nbsp;million (US$629,024)<ref name=\"mojo3\" /> grossed. ''3 Idiots'' was the first aired Indian film in Hong Kong, where it grossed [[Hong Kong dollar|HK$]]22&nbsp;million at the box office since its showing from 1 September 2011 through January 2012,<ref name=\"hkfilmart\">{{cite web|url=http://www.hkfilmart.com/newsread.asp?newsid=4198 |title=hkfilmart.com |publisher=hkfilmart.com |date=January 2012 |accessdate=5 March 2012 |archiveurl=https://translate.google.com/translate?sl=zh-CN&tl=en&js=n&prev=_t&hl=en&ie=UTF-8&layout=2&eotf=1&u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.hkfilmart.com%2Fnewsread.asp%3Fnewsid%3D4198 |archivedate=29 March 2012}}</ref> the equivalent of US$3.02&nbsp;million.<ref name=\"boi-note\">{{cite web|title=PK - Movie|url=https://boxofficeindia.com/movie-story.php?movieid=2482|website=[[Box Office India]]|accessdate=3 February 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"mojo3\" /> It was the 14th highest-grossing film of 2011 at the Hong Kong box office.<ref>{{cite web|title=2011 Hong Kong Yearly Box Office Results|url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/intl/hongkong/yearly/?yr=2011&p=.htm|website=[[Box Office Mojo]]|accessdate=8 December 2017|language=en}}</ref>\n\nIn South Korea, where it was released in 2011, the film grossed {{KRW|3,416,415,900}}<ref>{{cite web|title=KOFIC \uc601\ud654\uad00 \uc785\uc7a5\uad8c \ud1b5\ud569\uc804\uc0b0\ub9dd : \uc601\ud654\uc815\ubcf4|url=http://www.kobis.or.kr/kobis/business/mast/mvie/searchMovieList.do|website=[[Korean Film Council]]|year=2016|accessdate=25 April 2018|language=ko}}</ref> (US$3,084,647).<ref>{{cite web|title=Historical Exchange Rates Tool & Forex History Data (1107.555 KRW per USD)|url=https://www.ofx.com/en-gb/forex-news/historical-exchange-rates/|website=[[OFX (company)|OFX]]|year=2011|accessdate=25 April 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180619140101/https://www.ofx.com/en-gb/forex-news/historical-exchange-rates/|archive-date=19 June 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref> The film was number-one at the South Korean box office for five weeks,<ref name=\"kaist\"/> drawing an audience of 459,686 viewers.<ref>{{cite web|title=\uc601\ud654 <\uc138 \uc5bc\uac04\uc774>|url=http://movie.daum.net/moviedb/main?movieId=55287|website=[[Daum (web portal)|Daum]]|date=11 September 2016|accessdate=10 February 2018|language=ko}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Frater|first=Patrick|title=Aamir Khan's 'PK' Heads for September Release in Korea|url=https://variety.com/2015/film/asia/aamir-khans-pk-release-in-korea-1201553130/|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=30 July 2015}}</ref>\n\nIn China, where it is known as ''San Geshagua'' (\"Three Idiots\"),<ref name=\"economic_china\">{{cite news|last=Vasi|first=Nazia|title=Why Chinese identify with Aamir Khan's 3 Idiots, Rancho & All Izz Well|url=http://articles.economictimes.indiatimes.com/2011-10-15/news/30283532_1_three-idiots-films-hong-kong|accessdate=29 March 2012|newspaper=[[The Economic Times]]|date=15 October 2011}}</ref> the film grossed [[Indian rupee|{{INR}}]]11 crore in 2 weeks in December 2011,<ref name=\"economictimes\">{{cite news|url=http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/industry/media/entertainment/3-idiots-wins-over-chinese-collects-rs-11-crore-in-two-weeks/articleshow/11286751.cms |title=3 Idiots wins over Chinese, collects Rs 11 crore in two weeks|accessdate=29 December 2011|newspaper=[[The Economic Times]]|date=29 December 2011|last1=Chumbhale|first1=Ameya}}</ref> eventually crossing the $2&nbsp;million mark within 18 days,<ref name=overseas /> and nearly $3&nbsp;million within a month, as of 5 January 2012.<ref>{{cite news|last=Hazlewood|first=Phil |title=Bollywood looks east to tap Chinese market |url=http://www.livemint.com/2012/01/05152937/Bollywood-looks-east-to-tap-Ch.html|accessdate=29 March 2012|newspaper=[[Mint (newspaper)|Mint]]|date=5 January 2012|agency=[[The Wall Street Journal]]}}</ref>\n\nUpon its release in the Japanese market in June 2013, it went on to collect around [[Japanese yen|\u00a5]]100&nbsp;million ({{INR}} 61&nbsp;million) in its first two weeks of run&nbsp;\u2013 that makes the film the highest grossing Hindi film ever in Japan. Its final gross in Japan was \u00a5150{{nbsp}}million<ref>{{cite journal|title=2014\u5e742\u6708\u4e0b\u65ec\u6c7a\u7b97\u7279\u5225\u53f7|journal=[[Kinema Junpo]]|date=February 2014|issue=1656|page=212}}</ref> (US$1.6 million).<ref name=\"qz\">{{cite news|title=Japan is going gaga over Bollywood|url=https://qz.com/310502/japan-is-going-gaga-over-bollywood/|work=[[Quartz (publication)|Quartz]]|date=11 December 2014}}</ref> The film's final gross in East Asian markets was US${{formatnum:{{#expr:629024+3020000+3084647+3000000+1600000}}|}} ({{INR|69.2 crore}}).<ref name=\"exchange\"/>\n\n===Critical response===\n==== India ====\n[[Subhash K. Jha]] stated: \"It's not that ''3 Idiots'' is a flawless work of art. But it is a vital, inspiring and life-revising work of contemporary art with some heart imbued into every part. In a country where students are driven to suicide by their impossible curriculum, ''3 Idiots'' provides hope. Maybe cinema can't save lives. But cinema, sure as hell, can make you feel life is worth living. ''3 Idiots'' does just that, and much more. The director takes the definition of entertainment into directions of social comment\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/celebrities/features/type/view/id/583/ |title=Subhash K Jha speaks about ''3 Idiots'' |publisher=Bollywoodhungama.com |date=26 December 2009 |accessdate=21 November 2010}}</ref> [[Nikhat Kazmi]] of ''[[The Times of India]]'' gave it four and a half stars and suggests that, \"The film is a laugh riot, despite being high on fundas [\u2026] Hirani carries forward his simplistic 'humanism alone works' philosophy of the ''[[Lage Raho Munna Bhai]]'' series in ''3 Idiots'' too, making it a warm and vivacious signature tune to 2009. The second half of the film does falter in parts, specially the child birth sequence, but it doesn't take long for the film to jump back on track.\"<ref>{{cite web|author =Nikhat Kazmi |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/movie-reviews/hindi/3-Idiots/movie-review/5373913.cms |title=3 Idiots review |work=The Times of India|date=24 December 2009 |accessdate=21 November 2010}}</ref> Mayank Shekhar of the ''[[Hindustan Times]]'' gave the film three and a half out of five stars and comments that \"this is the sort of movie you'll take home with a smile and a song on your lips.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/Review-3-Idiots/H1-Article1-490233.aspx |title=3 Idiots review |work=Hindustan Times|date=24 December 2009 |accessdate=21 November 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110830022823/http://www.hindustantimes.com/Review-3-Idiots/H1-Article1-490233.aspx |archivedate=30 August 2011  }}</ref> [[Taran Adarsh]] of [[Bollywood Hungama]] gave ''3 Idiots'' four and a half out of five stars and states: \"On the whole, ''3 Idiots'' easily ranks amongst Aamir, Rajkumar Hirani and Vidhu Vinod Chopra's finest films. Do yourself and your family a favour: Watch ''3 Idiots.'' It's emotional, it's entertaining, it's enlightening. The film has tremendous youth appeal and feel-good factor to work in a big way.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/review/13910/index.html |title=3 Idiots review |publisher=Bollywood Hungama |accessdate=21 November 2010| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20101104160008/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/review/13910/index.html| archivedate= 4 November 2010 | url-status= live}}</ref> Kaveree Bamzai of ''[[India Today]]'' gave ''3 Idiots'' five stars and argues that \"it's a lovely story, of a man from nowhere who wanted to learn, told like a fairy tale, with the secret heart carrying its coded message of setting all of us free.\"<ref>{{cite web|author=Kaveree Bamzai |url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/site/Story/76291/3+Idiots:+Laugh.+Cry.+Fly.+Go+watch+it..html?complete=1 |title=3 Idiots: Laugh. Cry. Fly. Go watch it |publisher=India Today |date=24 December 2009 |accessdate=21 November 2010 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100114010140/http://indiatoday.intoday.in/site/Story/76291/3%2BIdiots%3A%2BLaugh.%2BCry.%2BFly.%2BGo%2Bwatch%2Bit..html?complete=1 |archivedate=14 January 2010 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nSonia Chopra of [[Sify]] gave the film 3 stars and said \"Though a bit too calculated and designed, 3 Idiots is still an ok option for the significant message, interesting cast and scattered breezy moments.\"<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.sify.com/movies/3-idiots-has-a-munnabhai-hangover-review-bollywood-14925000.html |title= 3 Idiots has a Munnabhai hangover|publisher=[[Sify]]|accessdate=19 December 2011}}</ref> [[Rajeev Masand]] of ''[[CNN-IBN]]'' gave the film three out of five stars and states: \"Going home after watching ''3 Idiots'' I felt like I'd just been to my favorite restaurant only to be a tad under-whelmed by their signature dish. It was a satisfying meal, don't get me wrong, but not the best meal I'd been expecting.\"<ref>{{cite web|author =<!--Updated 1136 hrs 3 February 2010(+5:30 GMT)--> |url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/masands-movie-review-3-idiots-satisfying-but-not-the-best/107739-8.html |title=3 Idiots review: CNN-IBN |work=CNN IBN |date=3 February 2010 |accessdate=21 November 2010}}</ref> Shubhra Gupta from ''[[The Indian Express]]'' also gave it 3 stars, stating \"'3 Idiots' does not do as much for me. The emotional truth that shone through both the 'Munnabhai' movies doesn't come through strongly enough.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indianexpress.com/news/3-idiots/559131/0|title=3 Idiots|work=[[The Indian Express]]|accessdate=18 February 2012}}</ref> Raja Sen of [[Rediff]] gave the film two out of five stars and states: \"Rajkumar Hirani's one of the directors of the decade, a man with immense talent and a knack for storytelling. On his debut, he hit a hundred. With his second, he hit a triple century. This time, he fishes outside the offstump, tries to play shots borrowed from other batters, and hits and misses to provide a patchy, 32*-type innings. It's okay, boss, *chalta hai*. Even Sachin has an off day, and we still have great hope.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://movies.rediff.com/report/2009/dec/24/review-three-idiots.htm |title=Rediff review |publisher=Movies.rediff.com |date=24 December 2009 |accessdate=21 November 2010| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20101106121348/http://movies.rediff.com/report/2009/dec/24/review-three-idiots.htm| archivedate= 6 November 2010 | url-status= live}}</ref>\n\n==== Overseas ====\nThe film has received praise overseas. On [[Rotten Tomatoes]], the film holds a rare [[List of films with a 100% rating on Rotten Tomatoes|100%]] \"Fresh\" critics' rating based on 13 reviews, with an [[Weighted mean|average score]] of 7.44 out of 10.<ref name=\"rt\">{{cite web|title=Three Idiots|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/3_idiots/|website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]|accessdate=7 October 2017|language=en}}</ref> Derek Elley of ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'' wrote that \"''3 Idiots'' takes a while to lay out its game plan but pays off emotionally in its second half.\" Robert Abele of ''[[Los Angeles Times]]'' wrote that there's an \"unavoidable ''[[joie de vivre]]'' (symbolized by Rancho's meditative mantra 'All is well') and a performance charm that make this one of the more naturally gregarious Bollywood imports.\" Louis Proyect described it as a \"fabulous achievement across the board. A typical Bollywood confection but also social commentary on a dysfunctional engineering school system that pressures huge numbers of students into suicide.\"<ref>{{Rotten Tomatoes|3_idiots|Three Idiots (2009)}}</ref>\n\nThe film was praised by critics in [[East Asia]] and [[Southeast Asia]]. ''[[South China Morning Post]]'' wrote that the film \"wraps a heavy message in light comedy. It is satire at its best, a powerful indictment of India's education system in which students cram for exams while stifling their dreams.\"<ref name=\"scmp\">{{cite news|title=3 Idiots (Film)|url=http://www.scmp.com/article/978499/3-idiots-film|work=[[South China Morning Post]]|date=9 September 2011|language=en}}</ref> Chaerim Oh of ''[[KAIST|KAIST Herald]]'' wrote that \"the film never harshly denounces the educational system but instead uncovers disturbing truths and unseen consequences of tremendous pressure upon students\" and that \"if you don't end up crying like I did (or won't admit that you did), you'll still enjoy the movie.\"<ref name=\"kaist\">{{cite news|title=Embrace Your Nerdiness with 3 Idiots|url=http://herald.kaist.ac.kr/news/articleView.html?idxno=285|accessdate=29 March 2012|newspaper=KAIST Herald|date=4 December 2011|author=Chaerim Oh|agency=[[KAIST]]}}</ref> In [[Japan]], Yuri Wakabayashi of [[:ja:\u6620\u753b.com|Eiga]] also gave the film a positive review.<ref>{{cite web|title=\u304d\u3063\u3068\u3001\u3046\u307e\u304f\u3044\u304f : \u6620\u753b\u8a55\u8ad6\u30fb\u6279\u8a55|url=http://eiga.com/movie/77899/critic/|website=[[:ja:\u6620\u753b.com|Eiga]]|date=8 May 2013|language=ja-JP}}</ref>\n\nIn 2013, renowned Hollywood filmmaker [[Steven Spielberg]] praised ''3 Idiots'', which he had seen three times and said he \"loved the emotional undertones.\" He listed it as one of five films that he connects with, along with ''[[The Godfather]]'' (1972) and his own work on ''[[E.T. the Extra-Terrestrial]]'' (1982), ''[[Saving Private Ryan]]'' (1998) and ''[[Jaws (film)|Jaws]]'' (1975).<ref>{{cite news|title=I've watched 3 Idiots thrice, admits Steven Spielberg|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/hollywood/i-ve-watched-3-idiots-thrice-admits-steven-spielberg/story-q4FjZUBWitY6zlvPa7TYRK.html|work=[[Hindustan Times]]|date=17 March 2013|language=en}}</ref>\n\n== Pre-release business ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"  style=\"margin:auto; margin:auto;\"\n|+'''''3 Idiots'' Pre-release business<ref name=\"planetbollywood\">{{cite web|url=http://planetbollywood.com/displayArticle.php?id=n083109031345|title=3 Idiots : Big Procures Worldwide Rights (Sans Satellite & Home Video) for 65 Crore!|website=Planet Bollywood News|accessdate=8 August 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141107095130/http://planetbollywood.com/displayArticle.php?id=n083109031345|archive-date=7 November 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref>'''\n! Territories and ancillary revenues\n! Price\n|-\n|  Satellite rights with a TV channel [Sony]\n| {{INRConvert|22|c}}\n|-\n| Worldwide distribution rights\n| {{INRConvert|65|c}}\n|-\n| Music rights (T~Series)\n|{{INRConvert|12|c}}\n|-\n|Total\n|{{INRConvert|99|c}}\n|-\n|}\n* The figures don't include the Print and Advertising (P&A) costs.\n\n== Awards ==\n{{Main|List of accolades received by 3 Idiots}}\n\nThe film won 58 accolades from Indian film awards; among these are six [[Filmfare Awards]] including [[Filmfare Best Film Award|Best Film]] and [[Filmfare Best Director Award|Best Director]], three [[National Film Awards]] including [[National Film Award for Best Popular Film Providing Wholesome Entertainment|Best Popular Film]], ten [[Star Screen Awards]], seventeen [[IIFA Awards]], five [[Global Indian Music Academy Awards|GIMA Awards]], two [[Apsara Awards]] and seven Bollywood Hungama Surfers Choice Movie Awards.\n\nIn China, it was nominated for the Best Foreign Film prize at the first [[Beijing International Film Festival]] in 2011.<ref name=\"maoyan\">{{cite web|title=\u4e09\u50bb\u5927\u95f9\u5b9d\u83b1\u575e|url=https://maoyan.com/films/43|website=[[Maoyan]]|accessdate=1 March 2018}}</ref> In Japan, it was nominated in the [[Japan Academy Prize for Outstanding Foreign Language Film|Best Outstanding Foreign Language Film]] category at the [[37th Japan Academy Prize|37th]] [[Japan Academy Prize (film)|Japan Academy Awards]] in 2014;<ref name=\"japan-hungama\">{{cite web|title=3 Idiots to race for Japan Academy Awards|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/2382254/3-Idiots-to-race-for-Japan-Academy-Awards|website=[[Bollywood Hungama]]|date=27 January 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"japan-ibn\">{{cite web|title=Aamir Khan's '3 Idiots' nominated for Japan Academy Awards|url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/aamir-khans-3-idiots-nominated-for-japan-academy-awards/448063-8-66.html|website=[[IBN Live]]|publisher=[[CNN-News18]]|date=27 January 2014|url-status=bot: unknown|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140129033801/http://ibnlive.in.com/news/aamir-khans-3-idiots-nominated-for-japan-academy-awards/448063-8-66.html|archivedate=29 January 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=3 Idiots nominated for Japan Academy Awards|url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/3-idiots-nominated-for-japan-academy-awards/1/340066.html|website=[[India Today]]|date=27 January 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Film 3 Idiots nominated for 37th Japanese Academy Awards 2014|url=http://news.biharprabha.com/2014/01/film-3-idiots-nominated-for-37th-japanese-academy-awards-2014/|work=IANS|date=26 January 2014|publisher=Biharprabha News|accessdate=27 January 2014}}</ref> the award was eventually won by ''[[Les Mis\u00e9rables (2012 film)|Les Miserables]]''. In addition, ''3 Idiots'' won the Grand Prize at the 4th Videoyasan Awards,<ref name=\"videoyasan\">{{cite web|title=\u7b2c\uff14\u56de\u30d3\u30c7\u30aa\u5c4b\u3055\u3093\u5927\u8cde|url=http://www.kinenote.com/main/feature/videoyasan04/|website=[[:ja:KINENOTE|KINENOTE]]|year=2014|accessdate=14 December 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"nikkatsu\">{{cite web|title=\u300e\u304d\u3063\u3068\u3001\u3046\u307e\u304f\u3044\u304f\u300f \u304c\u3001\u7b2c4\u56de\u30d3\u30c7\u30aa\u5c4b\u3055\u3093\u5927\u8cde\u306e \u300a\u5927\u8cde\u300b \u3092\u53d7\u8cde\u3057\u307e\u3057\u305f\uff01|url=http://www.nikkatsu.com/news/201403/001723.html|website=[[Nikkatsu]]|date=25 March 2014|language=ja-JP}}</ref> held by a Japanese organisation of home video retailers in 2014;<ref name=\"qz\"/> ''3 Idiots'' was selected as 2013's best video release, beating thousands of films, [[anime]] and television shows,<ref name=\"nikkatsu\"/> including domestic Japanese and foreign [[Cinema of the United States|Hollywood]] productions.<ref name=\"qz\"/>\n\n== Controversies ==\nPrior to the release of the film director [[Rajkumar Hirani]] commented on the relationship between ''[[Five Point Someone \u2013 What not to do at IIT|Five Point Someone]]'' by [[Chetan Bhagat]] and ''3 Idiots'' stating:\n:Chetan gave me this book to read and I wanted to make a film on it. But I knew right from the start that I could not make a film completely on the book, as it was very anecdotal and a film needs a plot. So I had decided to rewrite it in a screenplay format. You'll see that the film is very different from the book. After I wrote the script, I called Chetan and narrated it to him. I told him that if he did not like the script, I would stop the project. But he was okay with it.<ref>[http://movies.rediff.com/slide-show/2009/dec/23/slide-show-1-rajkumar-hirani-on-3idiots.htm#contentTop \"Aamir's dedication is mistaken as interference\"], rediff.com, 23 December 2009.</ref>\n\nThe day after the film opened, Chetan also noted:\n:Initially I did sit down with Raju and Abhijat while they were deciding to make a film based on '5 Point Someone'. I even went to IIT with Abhijat a couple of times. But it was just not possible for me to be involved at every stage of the screenplay writing process since I was in Hong Kong at that time, working full-time and busy writing other books. Moreover, Abhijat is based in USA, Raju was in the US for quite a while working on the screenplay but it was not practical for me to do that [\u2026] The film retains the soul of the book. ''3 Idiots'' is different from the book but at the same time it does borrow many things from the book. The core theme and message of the film is coming from the book itself. And that's why the makers have officially credited the film as 'Based on a novel by Chetan Bhagat.'<ref name=\"Bhagatint\">[https://www.filmibeat.com/bollywood/features/2009/chetan-bhagat-interview-261209.html \u201c3 Idiots retains the soul of Five Point Someone\u201d], Chetan Bhagat interview, ''One India''.</ref>\n\nA controversy developed a few days after the release, however, over the fact that Chetan's credit, \"Based on the novel ''Five Point Someone'' by Chetan Bhagat\" appeared in the closing credits rather than in the opening ones.<ref name=akinterview>{{cite web|url=http://www.glamsham.com/movies/interviews/02-aamir-khan-interview-011005.asp |title=Interview:Aamir Khan |publisher=Glamsham.com |accessdate=21 November 2010 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101123200554/http://glamsham.com/movies/interviews/02-aamir-khan-interview-011005.asp |archivedate=23 November 2010 |url-status=dead }}</ref> At that time, Bhagat stated that he \"was expecting an opening credit and I was quite surprised on not seeing it. They had bought the rights, made the payment and committed to a credit in the contract. It's there, but it's not about it being there, it's about the placement and the prominence.\"<ref>Sharma, Neha.[http://www.hindustantimes.com/Chetan-Bhagat-feeling-cheated/H1-Article1-491135.aspx \"Chetan Bhagat feeling cheated?\"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100225125702/http://www.hindustantimes.com/Chetan-Bhagat-feeling-cheated/H1-Article1-491135.aspx |date=25 February 2010 }}, ''Hindustan Times'', 27 December 2009.</ref> In a 31 December 2009 blog post on his personal website, Bhagat stated that he was told the movie was only 2\u20135% based on the book, but when he saw it, he felt that it was 70% of the book. He also argued that he was misled by the makers of the film, though he noted, that \"this has nothing to do with Mr Aamir Khan [\u2026] I am a big fan of Aamir and he has made my story reach people. However, he was told by the makers not to read the book, and he hasn't. Thus, he cannot comment on the issue in a meaningful manner.\"<ref>[http://www.chetanbhagat.com/blog/general/a-book-a-film-and-the-truth A book, a film and the truth] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101225052408/http://www.chetanbhagat.com/blog/general/a-book-a-film-and-the-truth |date=25 December 2010 }}\"</ref>\n\nA few people responded to Chetan's statements. According to the [[Indo-Asian News Service]] (IANS) producer [[Vidhu Vinod Chopra]] clarified that \"in the agreement between the producer and Bhagat, it was clearly mentioned that the author's name would be put in the closing credits\".<ref name=\"IANS\"/> IANS also reported that Chopra \"lost his cool\"<ref name=\"IANS\"/> and \"asked a reporter to shut up after being questioned whether his hit ''3 Idiots'' was lifted from author Chetan Bhagat's book ''Five Point Someone.''\"<ref name=\"IANS\">{{cite web|url=http://www.thaindian.com/newsportal/entertainment/vidhu-vinod-chopra-loses-cool-over-3-idiots-credit-row-lead_100297690.html |title=Vidhu Vinod Chopra loses cool over '3 Idiots' credit row (Lead) |publisher=Thaindian.com |accessdate=21 November 2010}}</ref> Chopra later apologised, stating: \"I really think I'm silly. I was provoked, but I shouldn't have done this. I saw myself on TV and saw how I was shouting 'shut up, shut up' like an animal. I told myself&nbsp;\u2014 'what nonsensical behaviour'.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2010-01-03/india/28134698_1_chetan-bhagat-vidhu-vinod-chopra-idiots |title=Vidhu apologises, Hirani flaunts pact with Chetan |work=The Times of India|date=3 January 2010 |accessdate=21 November 2010}}</ref> Aamir Khan also responded to these claims.<ref name=akinterview /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report_upset-aamir-khan-hits-out-at-novelist-chetan-bhagat_1329677 |title=Upset Aamir Khan hits out at novelist Chetan Bhagat|publisher=DNA India|date=1 January 2010 |accessdate=21 November 2010}}</ref> [[Rajkumar Hirani]] stated that \"We have officially bought the rights for the film. We drew a contract with him and it clearly mentions about the position of his credit. With open eyes he had seen the contract, consulted his lawyer and signed the agreement [\u2026] In the contract, we have said that the title would be given in the rolling credits. We haven't changed the font size. We haven't increased the speed of the title. It's exactly there where it was agreed to be.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2010-01-04/news-interviews/28142618_1_chetan-bhagat-due-credit-idiots |title=3 Idiots may sue Chetan Bhagat |work=The Times of India|date=4 January 2010|accessdate=21 November 2010}}</ref> Chetan Bhagat later apologised stating, \"I definitely do not have anything against team ''3 Idiots''. I may have some issues on the mistake they may have made but nothing about their personality or the kind of people they are. I apologise to their families if there was any distress caused to them. I also want to thank all my fans, who stood by me but I don't want them to turn against anyone especially Aamir.\"<ref>{{cite web|author =PTI |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2010-01-07/news-interviews/28117713_1_chetan-bhagat-credit-issue-due-credit |title=Fans, forgive Aamir: Chetan Bhagat |work=The Times of India|date=7 January 2010 |accessdate=21 November 2010}}</ref>\n\nIn an article published in ''[[Economic and Political Weekly]],'' Latika Gupta mentions that the film has serious problems when seen from the gender perspective, in particular that it follows the trend set by the 2007 film ''[[Jab We Met]]'' in its use of women's sexual vulnerability to create sensation and humor. In one scene, students, professors and the chief guest are seen bursting with laughter hearing a speech where the word ''balatkar'' (rape) figures 21 times and the word ''stan'' (breast) four times (in the English subtitles for international release, the words \"screwed\" and \"bosom\" are used instead).<ref name=\"Gupta\">{{cite journal|last1=Gupta|first1=Latika|title=Language, Cinema and State: A Gender Perspective|journal=Economic and Political Weekly|date= 5\u201311 June 2010|volume=45|issue=23|pages=86\u201388|jstor=27807110}}</ref>\n\n== Remakes ==\nA [[Tamil cinema|Tamil]]-language remake entitled ''[[Nanban (2012 film)|Nanban]]'' was released in 2012,<ref name=\"nanban_ibn\" /><ref name=\"nanban_hindustantimes\" /><ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2010-12-04/news-interviews/28258269_1_idiots-srikanth-and-jiiva-shankar-s-tamil |title=Tamil 3 Idiots' actors do style test&nbsp;\u2013 The Times of India |work=[[The Times of India]] |date=4 December 2010 |accessdate=11 December 2010}}</ref> and a Spanish-language [[Cinema of Mexico|Mexican]] remake named ''[[3 idiotas]]'' was released in 2017.<ref>{{cite web|title=3 idiotas se estrenar\u00e1 en el 2017\n|url=http://www.debate.com.mx/show/3-idiotas-se-estrenara-en-el-2017-20160713-0024.html}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.imdb.com/title/tt3685624/|title=3 Idiotas|via=www.imdb.com}}</ref>\n\n== Legacy ==\n=== Impact ===\nWhen ''3 Idiots'' made its television debut in July 2010, it drew an audience of 39{{nbsp}}million viewers in India.<ref name=\"hollywoodreporter\"/>\n\nWhen ''3 Idiots'' released in China, the country was only the 15th largest film market, partly due to China's widespread pirate [[DVD]] distribution at the time. However, it was the pirate market that introduced ''3 Idiots'' to most Chinese audiences, becoming a [[cult hit]] in the country. Aamir Khan gained a large growing Chinese fanbase as a result. By 2013, China grew to become the world's second largest film market (after the United States), paving the way for Aamir Khan's Chinese box office success, with ''[[Dhoom 3]]'' (2013), ''[[PK (film)|PK]]'' (2014), ''[[Dangal (film)|Dangal]]'' (2016)<ref name=\"forbes2\">{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/robcain/2017/06/08/how-a-52-year-old-indian-actor-became-chinas-favorite-movie-star/|title=How A 52-Year-Old Indian Actor Became China's Favorite Movie Star|first=Rob|last=Cain|website=Forbes}}</ref> and ''[[Secret Superstar]]'' (2017).\n\n''3 Idiots'' has been ranked China's 12th favourite film of all time according to ratings on popular Chinese film review site [[Douban]], with only one domestic [[Chinese film]] (''[[Farewell My Concubine (film)|Farewell My Concubine]]'') ranked higher.<ref name=\"forbes2\"/><ref name=\"theworldofchinese\">{{cite web|title=China's Favorite Movies|url=http://www.theworldofchinese.com/2017/05/chinas-favorite-movies/|website=[[The World of Chinese]]|date=19 May 2017|language=en}}</ref> The film holds an average rating of 9.2 out of 10 on Douban,<ref name=\"theworldofchinese\"/> with over 1.15 million votes.<ref>{{cite web|title=\u4e09\u50bb\u5927\u95f9\u5b9d\u83b1\u575e (\u8c46\u74e3)|url=https://movie.douban.com/subject/3793023/|website=[[Douban]]|accessdate=9 December 2017|language=zh-cmn-Hans}}</ref> On the [[Korean language|Korean]] site [[Naver]], audiences gave the film an average rating of 9.4 out of 10,<ref name=\"kaist\"/> and it is one of the top 30 highest-rated films on the site.<ref>{{cite web|title=\ub7ad\ud0b9 : \ub124\uc774\ubc84 \uc601\ud654|url=http://movie.naver.com/movie/sdb/rank/rmovie.nhn?sel=pnt&date=20171208|website=[[Naver]]|accessdate=8 December 2017}}</ref>\n\nOne reason for its success in [[East Asian cinema|East Asian markets]] such as China and Hong Kong is because of their similar education systems, thus many students were able to identify with the characters.<ref name=\"economic_china\" /> Chaerim Oh of ''[[KAIST|KAIST Herald]]'' wrote that the \"popularity of the movie, particularly in South Korea, can be traced back to the national background of the overly competitive education system. In Korea, students of all ages - from young elementary children to university graduate students - are trained to study under overwhelming pressure and extremely high academic standards. In short, this movie is, really, our own story.\"<ref name=\"kaist\"/>\n\nThe film had a social impact on attitudes to [[education in Asia]], including [[education in India]]<ref name=\"Hussain\">{{cite journal|last1=Hussain|first1=Sajjad|last2=Ahmad|first2=Nasir|title=The impact of the Indian movie, ''3 Idiots'' (2009), on attitudes to education|journal=Research in Drama Education: The Journal of Applied Theatre and Performance|date=28 April 2016|volume=21|issue=2|pages=242\u2013246|doi=10.1080/13569783.2016.1155439}}</ref> as well as other [[Asia]]n countries.<ref name=\"economic_china\" /> Chinese universities were \"even prescribing the film in their coursework as a kind of stress-relief in their classrooms.\"<ref name=\"hindu_china\"/>\n\n===''Big in Bollywood''===\n''Big in Bollywood'' (2011) is a [[documentary film]] about American actor [[Omi Vaidya]]'s journey from a struggling [[Cinema of the United States|Hollywood]] actor to a successful Bollywood breakthrough with ''3 Idiots''.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Heymont|first1=George|title=Big in Bollywood (That's What Friends Are For)|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/george-heymont/big-in-bollywood-movie_b_1122412.html|work=[[Huffington Post]]|date=1 December 2011}}</ref>\n\n==Possible sequel==\nWhen asked about plans of a ''3 Idiots'' sequel in an interview with [[Hindustan Times]], screenwriter Abhijat Joshi replied, saying, \"Honestly, I don't know. We have an idea for the 3 Idiots sequel, a ''[[Munna Bhai]]'' part three, and also for a [[PK (film)|''PK'']] sequel; but the [[PK (film)|''PK'']] and ''[[Munna Bhai]]'' sequels interest me the most. So, I think the ''3 Idiots'' sequel may happen in the future, but these two I really want to work on.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/sequels-to-pk-3-idiots-in-the-pipeline/article1-1296946.aspx |title=Sequels|accessdate=12 January 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150104203847/http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/sequels-to-pk-3-idiots-in-the-pipeline/article1-1296946.aspx |archivedate=4 January 2015 }}</ref>\n\nIn January 2016, director Rajkumar Hirani and actor Aamir Khan confirmed that they were considering a ''3 Idiots'' sequel. Khan told reporters, \"\"Raju Hirani has given me a hint about '''3 Idiots''<nowiki/>' sequel and I am giving you all a hint. The film will happen if and whenever he will write the script.\" Hirani agreed, saying \"this is one film that I really want to do.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/3-idiots-sequel-will-happen-when-rajkumar-hirani-is-ready-with-the-script-aamir-khan/|title=3 Idiots sequel will happen when Rajkumar Hirani is ready with the script: Aamir Khan|date=28 January 2016}}</ref>\n\nIn June 2018, Hirani was asked a question while promoting his upcoming film [[Sanju]] and he was quoted as saying, \"I definitely want to make a sequel to ''3 Idiots'', but it\u2019s still in the initial stage and we will take a fair amount of time to develop the script\".\n\nThe report also said that Hirani will begin shooting for the ''Munna Bhai'' sequel with [[Sanjay Dutt]] once Sanju releases. Work on 3 Idiots will begin only after Hirani is done with ''Munna Bhai 3.''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tribune.com.pk/story/1739904/4-film-maker-rajkumar-hirani-confirms-3-idiots-sequel/|title=Film-maker Rajkumar Hirani confirms '3 Idiots' sequel|date=22 June 2018|website=The Express Tribune}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n{{Portal bar|Bollywood|Film}}\n* [[List of highest-grossing Bollywood films]]\n* [[List of Bollywood highest-grossing films in overseas markets]]\n\n== Notes ==\n{{notelist}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n<!-- Please do not add links that are not official. Wikipedia is not a collection of links! -->\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xvszmNXdM4w Official trailer]&nbsp;\u2013 [[Vinod Chopra Films]]\n* {{IMDb title}}\n* {{Bollywood Hungama title|65530}}\n* {{AllMovie title}}\n* {{Mojo title}}\n* {{Rotten Tomatoes}}\n* {{Metacritic film}}\n* {{TCMDb title}}\n\n{{Rajkumar Hirani}}\n{{Vidhu Vinod Chopra}}\n{{National Film Award Wholesome Entertainment}}\n{{IIFA Award for Best Movie}}\n{{FilmfareAwardBestFilm}}\n{{Chetan Bhagat}}\n{{Shantanu Moitra}}\n\n[[Category:2009 films]]\n[[Category:2000s Hindi-language films]]\n[[Category:2000s buddy comedy films]]\n[[Category:2000s comedy-drama films]]\n[[Category:Coming-of-age comedy films]]\n[[Category:Coming-of-age drama films]]\n[[Category:Films scored by Shantanu Moitra]]\n[[Category:Films about education]]\n[[Category:Films about the education system in India]]\n[[Category:Films about teacher\u2013student relationships]]\n[[Category:Films about poverty]]\n[[Category:Films about suicide]]\n[[Category:Films about death]]\n[[Category:Films based on Indian novels]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Rajkumar Hirani]]\n[[Category:Films set in Delhi]]\n[[Category:Films set in Himachal Pradesh]]\n[[Category:Films set in Ladakh]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Bangalore]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Ladakh]]\n[[Category:Hindi films remade in other languages]]\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:Indian buddy comedy films]]\n[[Category:Indian comedy-drama films]]\n[[Category:Indian coming-of-age films]]\n[[Category:Indian nonlinear narrative films]]\n[[Category:Best Popular Film Providing Wholesome Entertainment National Film Award winners]]\n[[Category:Films that won the Best Audiography National Film Award]]\n[[Category:Films set in universities and colleges]]\n", "name_user": "123.208.171.16", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/3_Idiots"}
{"title_page": "The Sky Is Pink", "text_new": "{{short description|2019 film directed by Shonali Bose}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=March 2019}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = The Sky Is Pink\n| image          = The Sky Is Pink.jpg\n| alt            = The poster features a family, the couple and their two children, with spring like light green and light pink themed colour in the background. The poster also features the couple at the top. Text at the bottom of the poster reveals the tagline of the film while the text at the bottom of the poster reveals the title, name of the director, name of the producer, name of the distributor, the release date and the rest of the credits.\n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| director       = [[Shonali Bose]]\n| producer       = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Ronnie Screwvala]]\n* [[Siddharth Roy Kapur]]\n* Kilian Kerwin\n* [[Priyanka Chopra Jonas]]\n* Madhu Chopra\n}}\n| screenplay         = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Shonali Bose]]\n* Nilesh Maniyar\n* <small>(Additional)</small>\n* [[Juhi Chaturvedi]]\n* <small>(Hindi dialogues)</small>\n}}\n| starring       = {{Plainlist|\n* Priyanka Chopra Jonas\n* [[Farhan Akhtar]]\n* [[Zaira Wasim]]\n* [[Rohit Suresh Saraf]]\n}}\n| narrator       = Zaira Wasim\n| music          = {{Plainlist|\n'''Songs:'''\n* [[Pritam]]\n'''Score:'''\n* [[Mikey McCleary]]\n}}\n| cinematography = {{Plainlist|\n* Kartik Vijay\n* Nick Cooke\n}}\n| editing        = Manas Mittal\n| studio         = {{Plainlist|\n* [[RSVP Movies]]\n* Roy Kapur Films\n* [[Purple Pebble Pictures]]\n*Ivanhoe Pictures\n}}\n| distributor    = RSVP Movies\n| released       = {{Film date|2019|09|13|[[Toronto International Film Festival|TIFF]]|2019|10|11|df=y|India}}\n| runtime        = 143 minutes<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://bbfc.co.uk/releases/sky-pink-2019 |title=The Sky Is Pink (2019) |website=[[British Board of Film Classification]] |access-date=10 October 2019}}</ref>\n| country        = India\n| language       = Hindi\n| budget         = \n| gross          = {{Estimation}} {{INR}}34.41 crore<ref name=\"box:bbh\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movie/the-sky-is-pink/box-office/ |title=The Sky is Pink Box Office |website=Bollywood Hungama |access-date=25 October 2019}}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''''The Sky Is Pink''''' is a 2019 Indian [[Hindi]]-language [[biographical film]] written and directed by [[Shonali Bose]]. The film was co-produced by [[Siddharth Roy Kapur]], [[Ronnie Screwvala]] and [[Priyanka Chopra Jonas]] under their production companies of [[RSVP Movies]], Roy Kapur Films and [[Purple Pebble Pictures]] in association with Ivanhoe Pictures. The film stars Chopra Jonas, [[Farhan Akhtar]], [[Zaira Wasim]], and [[Rohit Suresh Saraf]]. Based on the real life story of [[Aisha Chaudhary]] who was diagnosed with [[pulmonary fibrosis]], the film tells the love story of her parents, Aditi and Niren, dealing with their daughter's illness.\n\nAditi Chaudhary approached Bose to make a film based on her daughter. Although intrigued by the story, Bose instead chose to depict the story of the couple from Aisha's point of view, focusing on their marriage and the effect of a child's illness on the lives of the parents and their relationship. Bose wrote the screenplay based on the details she has gathered through interviewing Aditi and Niren. Nilesh Maniyar wrote the additional screenplay while Hindi dialogue writing was done by [[Juhi Chaturvedi]]. Filming took place in Mumbai, London, Delhi and [[Andaman Islands|Andaman]]. [[Pritam]] composed the soundtrack and [[Gulzar]] wrote the lyrics for the songs.\n\nThe film premiered at the [[44th Toronto International Film Festival]] on 13 September 2019. It was released worldwide on 11 October 2019. ''The Sky Is Pink'' received generally positive reviews, with praise directed towards Bose's writing and direction and the performances. It did not perform well at the box office, grossing {{INR}}34.41 crore worldwide. The film received three [[Filmfare Awards]] nominations: [[Filmfare Critics Award for Best Film|Best Film (Critics)]], [[Filmfare Award for Best Actress|Best Actress]] for Chopra Jonas and [[Filmfare Award for Best Supporting Actress|Best Supporting Actress]] for Wasim.\n\n== Plot ==\n[[Aisha Chaudhary]] narrates the story of her parents, Moose (her mother) and Panda (her father) from [[afterlife]]. Aditi and Niren are a young couple who come from two different backgrounds. Aditi is from the posh end of the town, [[South Delhi]], where on another hand Niren is from a grounded middle-class family. The couple are shown to be in love, with \"an active sex life\" as Aisha's narration describes. The passionate and happy couple get married, and Aditi becomes pregnant with their first child Tanya, who dies within months of her birth due to the [[Severe combined immunodeficiency]] condition. Baby Tanya used to frequently become ill and, while Aditi was convinced it was a serious issue, Niren used to brush it off. Niren believed that negligence was the reason Tanya couldn't be treated sooner and blamed himself for the death of his child. As Aditi was mourning the death of her child, she was consoled by a Catholic church nun and decided to be baptised.\n\nAditi and Niren have a second child Ishaan. A few years later, Aditi bore their third child, another daughter, Aisha. They later learn that Aisha was born with the same Severe combined immunodeficiency condition as their first child, Aditi and Niren are heartbroken. After the doctors in Delhi give up on the treatment, the couple go to London where they learn that the disease could be treated by performing [[bone marrow transplant]]. However, they learn that the treatment is very costly. Niren starts working to earn the money while also asking for crowdfunding via a radio station. After several weeks, they learn that several people have donated money for Aisha's treatment. The surgery is successful but Aisha is kept under doctor's watch. Aditi decides to stay in London while Niren goes back to India with his family and his son Ishaan. Aditi grows overprotective of Aisha, over cleaning the apartment and other things to keep Aisha away from any potential infection.\n\nIshaan starts missing his mother while Niren is always thinking about Aditi and Aisha. This also starts affecting Aditi and Niren's relationship as Aditi is always occupied with Aisha and taking care of her. Months go by and Niren goes to London and asks Aditi to move back to India so that their relationship is not affected. He reasons with Aisha on the grounds that Aisha had gotten better and occasional doctor's visit can be done in India as well. Aditi tells him that they have to live here for a very long time as per doctor's recommendation till Aisha's condition is cured. The whole family moves here permanently till Aisha is cured. Niren's career grows in London and he becomes rich and their family becomes affluent.\n\nSeveral years later, Aisha has finally gotten better and Niren and Aditi decide to move back to India with their families. They shift to the outskirts of Delhi and buy an extravagant and massive bungalow. After a doctor's visit, Aditi and Niren learn that Aisha has been diagnosed with [[pulmonary fibrosis]], a side effect of the chemotherapy that was done to cure the previous disease. With less time on Aisha's life, Aditi sets out to fulfill all of Aisha's dreams such as adopting a pet (which Aditi did not allow due to the risk of infection), seeing the aquatic life and writing a book, among other things. As Aisha's condition worsens, Aditi grows more and more overprotective and due to over stress, suffers a psychotic breakdown and is hospitalized. Aditi does everything in her power to make sure Aisha gets to see the first copy of her book before she dies. Later, Aisha passes away.\n\nAfter the death of Aisha, Aditi and Niren's relationship is strained. While living together, they grow apart and are constantly fighting with each other. Aditi still cannot accept Aisha's death and constantly brings her in their fights. At a party, Niren shows Aisha's secret video that he had found, a video she had made about her parents. Niren wants Aditi to move with him to London so that she can forget Aisha which she finds insulting as she does not want to let Aisha's memories fade, particularly the house. With anger, Niren leaves for London while Aditi stays back. Aditi later goes to meet Niren in London and they reconcile.\n\n== Cast ==\nThe cast has been listed below:<ref name=\"cast&crew\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movie/the-sky-is-pink/cast/ |title=The Sky Is Pink Cast & Crew |work=[[Bollywood Hungama]] |access-date=3 March 2020}}</ref>\n{{Div col}}\n* [[Priyanka Chopra Jonas]] as Aditi Chaudhary\n* [[Farhan Akhtar]] as Niren Chaudhary\n* [[Zaira Wasim]] as [[Aisha Chaudhary]]\n* [[Rohit Suresh Saraf]] as Ishaan Chaudhary\n* Vidhaan Sharma as Young Ishaan\n* Manas Mittal as Anshu Tandon\n* Rajshri Deshpande as Anita Tandon\n* Lushin Dubey as Mrs. Tandon\n* Sunil Chitkara as Mr. Chaudhary\n* Nirupama Verma as Mrs. Chaudhary\n* Puja Sarup as Mohini\n* Gurpal Singh as Rj Arjun Gill\n* Sheena Khalid as Rita\n* Sudhanva Deshpande as Dr. Nirvick Gulati\n* Manisha Chudasama as Santoshi\n* Paras Rattan Sharda as Jeet\n* Salmin Sheriff as Dr. Batliwala\n* Rishi Deshpande as Tanya's Doctor\n* Virhi as Baby Tanya\n* Mala Hashmi as Christian Woman\n* Akshay Joshi as Store Assistant\n* Nargis Nandal as Pilot\n* Raabia Marici as Ishaan's Girlfriend\n{{Div col end}}\n\n== Production ==\n=== Development and writing ===\nThe production of the film started when [[Aisha Chaudhary]]'s mother Aditi approached [[Shonali Bose]] to make a film about her daughter. Chaudhary had seen the trailer of Bose's last film ''[[Margarita with a Straw]]'' (2015) thirty times and was eager to watch the film, saying \"I hope I live to see this film.\"<ref name=\"tnie\">{{Cite news |last=Mitra |first=Shilajit |url=https://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/hindi/2019/oct/09/indian-culture-is-better-equipped-to-deal-with-grief-the-sky-is-pink-director-shonali-bose-2044820.html |title=Indian culture is better equipped to deal with grief: 'The Sky Is Pink' director Shonali Bose |date=9 October 2019 |work=[[The New Indian Express]] |access-date=2 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"th\">{{Cite news |last=Namrata |first=Joshi |url=https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/all-cinema-has-an-inherent-patriarchal-ideology/article29410318.ece |title=All cinema has an inherent patriarchal ideology: Shonali Bose |date=13 September 2019 |work=[[The Hindu]] |access-date=2 March 2020}}</ref> However, she passed away at the age of 18 after being diagnosed with [[pulmonary fibrosis]], two weeks after watching the trailer and never got to see the film. Nine months later, Aditi Chaudhary tracked down Bose who was then living in [[Los Angeles]]. Aditi was adamant as she only wanted Bose to tell the story of her daughter.<ref name=\"th\" /><ref name=\"ht\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/sky-is-pink-director-shonali-bose-says-death-of-her-son-end-of-marriage-drew-her-to-the-story/story-otpNEnfTrDPR1OKaNeBWJJ.html |title=Sky is Pink director Shonali Bose says death of her son, end of marriage drew her to the story |date=10 September 2019 |work=[[Hindustan Times]] |access-date=2 March 2020}}</ref> Initially, they interacted over [[Skype]]. Later, Bose personally interviewed both Aditi and Niren Chaudhary for eight hours a day for two weeks to gather all the details.<ref name=\"tnie\" /><ref name=\"scroll\">{{Cite news |last=Ramnath |first=Nandini |url=https://scroll.in/reel/936799/the-sky-is-pink-director-shonali-bose-it-is-a-rare-couple-who-survive-the-death-of-their-child |title=\u2018The Sky is Pink\u2019 director Shonali Bose: \u2018It is a rare couple who survive the death of their child\u2019 |date=10 September 2019 |work=[[Scroll.in|Scroll]] |access-date=2 March 2020}}</ref> Bose said that \"They talked and cried and healed through the process of those narrations.\"<ref name=\"tnie\" /> Bose had said that she was drawn towards the story as she herself had lost her son so was she ready to explore the subject cinematically and bringing some of her own unique perspective to it.<ref name=\"th\" /><ref name=\"outlook\">{{Cite news |last=Roy |first=Lachmi Deb |url=https://www.outlookindia.com/website/story/entertainment-news-shonali-bose-on-the-sky-is-pink-har-ek-ka-apna-sky-hota-hai-what-colour-is-your-sky/339168 |title=Shonali Bose On \u2018The Sky Is Pink\u2019: \u201cHar Ek Ka Apna Sky Hota Hai. What Colour Is Your Sky?\u201d |date=22 September 2019 |work=[[Outlook (Indian magazine)|Outlook]] |access-date=2 March 2020}}</ref> However, she was more interested in telling the story of Aditi and Niren, a couple, dealing with the illness of their child, saying \"I was drawn to the story, not of a heroic teenager defying death, but the parents who had to deal with it.\"<ref name=\"th\" /> Bose said she was \"intrigued and inspired\" by the Chaudharys' relationship, adding \"It is a rare couple who survive the death of their child.\"<ref name=\"scroll\" /> She said she wanted to explore \"what happens to a love story, to a marriage, when faced with the loss of a child\", explaining \"My own marriage ended when I lost my son. 80% of people\u2019s marriages end when they lose a child.\"<ref name=\"ht\" /><ref name=\"scroll\" /> She wanted to make an unusual romantic film and the lives of Aditi and Niren were exactly unusual like the film she wanted to make.<ref name=\"outlook\" /> In December 2018, Ivanhoe Pictures came on board to co-finance and co-produce the film.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://variety.com/2018/film/asia/ivanhoe-pictures-priyanka-chopra-the-sky-is-pink-1203085471/ |title=Ivanhoe Pictures Boards Priyanka Chopra\u2019s \u2018The Sky is Pink\u2019 |last=Frater |first=Patrick |date=10 December 218 |website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |access-date=6 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nBose began writing the screenplay based on the narration she had heard from the Chaudharys by approaching it as a love story of two people who fell in love when they were \"only 16 and now at 57 are still inseparable\" despite major tragedies that tear most couples apart.<ref name=\"scroll\" /><ref name=\"outlook\" /> Bose chose to tell the film from Aisha's point of view, focusing on 25 years of her parents' marriage.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Blyth, Antonia |url=https://deadline.com/video/the-sky-is-pink-priyanka-chopra-shonali-bose-tiff-toronto/ |title=Priyanka Chopra: 'The Sky Is Pink' Has \"Moments Of Joy, Moments Of Tragedy\" \u2014 Toronto Studio |date=8 September 2019 |access-date=14 September 2019 |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]}}</ref> Nilesh Maniyar, a longtime collaborator of Bose, had also met Aditi and Niren and wanted to make a documentary about Aisha as he felt there was more to explore and saw Bose's film as very different than his, both projects being in different formats. Since Maniyar had also done his research on Aisha's life, Bose invited him to write the additional screenplay.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Negi |first=Shristi |url=https://www.news18.com/news/movies/the-sky-is-pink-writer-nilesh-maniyar-deconstructs-priyanka-chopras-psychotic-breakdown-scene-2367617.html |title=The Sky Is Pink Writer Nilesh Maniyar Deconstructs Priyanka Chopra's Psychotic Breakdown Scene |date=31 October 2019 |work=[[CNN News18]] |access-date=2 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"confirms\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.deccanchronicle.com/entertainment/bollywood/090718/priyanka-chopra-shonali-bose-abhishek-farhan-zaira-sky-is-pink-script.html |title=Priyanka confirms Shonali Bose\u2019s film, reveals title, mystery continues over hero |date=9 July 2018 |work=[[Deccan Chronicle]] |access-date=3 March 2020}}</ref> [[Juhi Chaturvedi]] wrote the Hindi dialogues.<ref name=\"confirms\" /> Bose wanted to stay true to the real life events and depict them as it unfolded in their lives, without fictionalising or deflecting from actual incidents. She said \"The story, facts and events in the film are completely true. I wrote the script as close as possible to the truth. So, when deciding the look and feel of the film, I decided to stay with realism and be as authentic as possible.\"<ref name=\"th\" /><ref name=\"scroll\" /> While writing the script, Bose met with Aisha's family and friends and inquired everything about her. She also read Aisha's writing, including her emails to her brother and the artwork she had made. Bose revealed that feel connected with Aisha even though they never met.<ref name=\"scroll\" /> In handling the subject, Bose consciously chose to be realistic and avoid melodramatic and manipulative set-ups to express emotions.<ref name=\"th\" /> She said \"I am also very conscious of steering clear of melodrama and exploiting or manipulating you with overwrought emotions. I want you to feel what my characters feel but also give you space. This is part of my film form.\"<ref name=\"scroll\" /> In an interview with [[Scroll.in|Scroll]], Bose revealed that in early drafts, Aditi was the main protagonist as she was written to be the central figure in the story, but later strengthened Niren's role and they became equal in the final draft.<ref name=\"scroll\" />\n\n[[Siddharth Roy Kapur]] had liked Bose's previous film and had expressed his desire to work with her.<ref name=\"rediff\">{{Cite news |last=Chhabra |first=Aseem |url=https://www.rediff.com/movies/report/sky-is-pink-required-big-stars/20191010.htm |title='Sky Is Pink required big stars' |date=10 October 2020 |work=[[Rediff.com]] |access-date=2 March 2020}}</ref> After the acquisition of [[UTV Motion Pictures]] by [[The Walt Disney Company]], Kapur was appointed managing director of the company of [[The Walt Disney Company India]] in 2014 and produced several films under the new name as he had previously done with UTV. Kapur established his own company, Roy Kapur Films, in January 2017.<ref name=\"rediff\" /> When Bose found out about his new production house, she approached him with the script of ''The Sky Is Pink'' and Kapur picked it to be the first film under of his company.<ref name=\"rediff\" /><ref name=\"mint\">{{Cite news |last=Sharma |first=Sanjukta |url=https://www.livemint.com/Consumer/vK8fluGeIY8nXR4h4b7RUO/Embracing-technology-is-the-only-way-to-remain-relevant-Sid.html |title=Embracing technology is the only way to remain relevant: Siddharth Roy Kapur |date=22 September 2019 |work=[[Mint (newspaper)|Mint]] |access-date=2 March 2020}}</ref> He said that he found the script wonderfully moving, told with wit, humour, depth and feeling.<ref name=\"mint\" /> As a part of a [[first look deal]] with [[RSVP Movies]], Kapur set the film there, thus collaborating with [[Ronnie Screwvala]], the ex-UTV Studio head, as producers.<ref name=\"rediff\" /> Bose considers ''The Sky Is Pink'' as the culmination of her ''Delhi trilogy'', a series of unrelated films based on \"mother-child relationship\" and that are set in Delhi. The other first two films being ''[[Amu (film)|Amu]]'' (2005) and ''Margarita with a Straw''.<ref name=\"delhitrilogy\">{{cite news|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/shonali-bose-the-sky-is-pink-completes-my-trilogy-on-delhi/articleshow/71464651.cms|title=Shonali Bose: The Sky Is Pink completes my trilogy on Delhi|last=Kaushik|first=Divya|work=The Times of India|date=7 October 2019|access-date=18 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== Casting and characters ===\nThe film's casting news first came out in May 2018 suggesting that [[Priyanka Chopra]], [[Abhishek Bachchan]] and [[Zaira Wasim]] had been cast in Bose's next untitled. The media reports suggested that Wasim was cast as Aisha Chaudhary, with Chopra and Bachchan playing her parents.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/bollywood/story/abhishek-bachchan-and-priyanka-chopra-to-play-parents-to-zaira-wasim-1235853-2018-05-18 |title=Abhishek-Priyanka to play Zaira Wasim's parents in Shonali Bose's film? |date=18 May 2018 |work=[[India Today]] |access-date=3 March 2020}}</ref> A month later media reports claimed that [[Farhan Akhtar]] had replaced Bachchan and now he would be playing the father.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.dnaindia.com/bollywood/report-farhan-akhtar-replaces-abhishek-bachchan-in-shonali-bose-s-next-to-star-opposite-priyanka-chopra-zaira-wasim-2629148 |title=Farhan Akhtar replaces Abhishek Bachchan in Shonali Bose's next; to star opposite Priyanka Chopra, Zaira Wasim |date=25 June 2018 |work=[[Daily News and Analysis]] |access-date=3 March 2020}}</ref> Chopra confirmed her involvement on 9 July 2018 by posting a picture of the script of ''The Sky Is Pink'' on her [[Instagram]] account, revealing the title of the film.<ref name=\"confirms\" /> The official announcement followed the next day, confirming Akhtar and Wasim's casting in the film.<ref name=\"announcement\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/farhan-akhtar-may-replace-abhishek-bachchan-in-shonali-boses-the-sky-is-pink-opposite-priyanka-chopra-4702601.html |title=Farhan Akhtar, Priyanka Chopra, Zaira Wasim confirmed to star in Shonali Bose's The Sky Is Pink |date=10 July 2018 |work=[[Firstpost]] |access-date=3 March 2020}}</ref> It is the second film to feature Chopra and Akhtar opposite each other after ''[[Dil Dhadakne Do]]'' (2015).<ref name=\"announcement\" /> [[Rohit Suresh Saraf]] was cast as Aisha's brother Ishaan after four rounds of auditions over a period of four months.<ref name=\"saraf\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.telegraphindia.com/entertainment/rohit-saraf-s-sky/cid/1710754 |title=Rohit Saraf's sky |last=Paul |first=Ushnota |date=11 October 2019 |website=The Telegraph |access-date=6 March 2020}}</ref> The film marked the return of Chopra to Bollywood films after three years as she was busy with her Hollywood work.<ref name=\"theweek\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.theweek.in/news/entertainment/2019/10/03/Priyanka-Chopra-reveals-how-The-Sky-is-Pink-reminded-her-of-her-parents.html |title=Priyanka Chopra reveals how 'The Sky is Pink' reminded her of her parents |last=[[Press Trust of India]] |date=3 October 2019 |website=[[The Week (Indian magazine)|The Week]] |access-date=6 March 2020}}</ref> After coming on board the film as an actor, Chopra asked her Kapur and Screwvala to join them as the producer as she believed in the film and wanted to take more responsibility of the film and learn about producing from them.<ref name=\"theweek\" /> Kapur and Screwvala, both frequent collaborators of Chopra (who had starred in several of their films under UTV), agreed to bring her as a producer, thus making ''The Sky Is Pink'' making the first Hindi film to be produced under Chopra's company [[Purple Pebble Pictures]].<ref name=\"theweek\" />\n\nChopra was drawn to the film because of the story and the way it was written, explaining that she found the treatment of a heavy subject with humour was refreshing and beautiful.<ref name=\"wion\">{{Cite news |last=Sen |first=Shomini |url=https://www.wionews.com/entertainment/priyanka-chopra-on-why-she-chose-sky-is-pink-as-her-comeback-film-254196 |title=Priyanka Chopra on why she chose \u2018The Sky Is Pink\u2019 as her comeback film |date=7 October 2019 |work=[[WION (TV channel)|WION]] |access-date=15 April 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"refinery\">{{Cite news |last=Cohen |first=Anne |url=https://www.refinery29.com/en-us/2019/10/8556156/priyanka-chopra-jonas-movie-the-sky-is-pink-interview |title=Priyanka Chopra Jonas\u2019 Latest Role Will Definitely Surprise You |date=11 October 2019 |work=[[Refinery29]] |access-date=15 April 2020}}</ref> She found her character Aditi immersive and described her as \"a ferocious mom\".<ref name=\"theweek\" /><ref name=\"telegraph\">{{Cite news |last=Roy |first=Priyanka |url=https://www.telegraphindia.com/entertainment/bollywood/priyanka-chopra-jonas-on-the-sky-is-pink-and-battling-nerves-of-the-good-kind/cid/1712150 |title=Priyanka Chopra Jonas on the Sky Is Pink and battling nerves of \u2018the good kind\u2019 |date=16 October 2019 |work=The Telegraph |access-date=15 April 2020}}</ref> Chopra did a lot of preparations and research before the filming and also met the real life Aditi.<ref name=\"iepriyanka\">{{Cite news |last=Sahani |first=Alaka |url=https://indianexpress.com/article/express-sunday-eye/priyanka-chopra-the-sky-is-pink-6066665/ |title=Priyanka Chopra: If you want the sky, you\u2019ve to find a way to reach it |date=13 October 2019 |work=The Indian Exress |access-date=15 April 2020}}</ref> Bose was against Chopra meeting Aditi but Chopra was adamant that she must meet her to get into her head as Aditi treated the situation much different than her husband and she felt like she needed to have those difficult conversations with her.<ref name=\"telegraph2\">{{Cite news |last=Paul |first=Ushnota |url=https://www.telegraphindia.com/entertainment/desi-girl-sits-down-for-a-chat-on-new-film-anniversary-plans-and-stardom/cid/1708393?ref=also-read_story-page |title='Desi Girl' sits down for a chat on new film, anniversary plans and stardom |date=29 September 2019 |work=The Telegraph |access-date=15 April 2020}}</ref> The actress revealed that she was also depended on Bose and would ask a lot of questions about the character and she imbibed a lot from Bose and Aditi and Bose's interpretation Aditi.<ref name=\"telegraph\" /><ref name=\"telegraph2\" /> She said \"I'm not a mother, I needed to understand from both Aditi and Shonali who have both lost their children... where does that take you? What do you feel in your heart?\" She said that Aditi reminded of her own mother as she found similarities between her own mother and Aditi and chose to channel her in Aditi.<ref name=\"refinery\" /> Not being a mother, she found the role challenging, saying that the \"film was scaring me in every scene\" but felt that the role made her experience two different aspects of motherhood.\"<ref name=\"wion\" />\n\nAkhtar also chose the film because of the story which he found \"moving and incredibly inspiring\" and the people involved in the film. Like Chopra, Akhtar too relied on Bose's vision of Niren to form his character.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/bollywood/story/farhan-akhtar-the-sky-is-pink-received-applause-from-international-audience-because-of-its-story-1606008-2019-10-03 |title=Farhan Akhtar: The Sky Is Pink received applause from international audience because of its story |date=3 October 2019 |work=India Today |access-date=15 April 2020}}</ref> Akhtar was also instructed to not meet the real life Aditi and Niren before the filming as Bose did not want her actors to get influenced or to imitate them.<ref name=\"tniefarhan\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/hindi/2019/oct/10/the-pain-of-losing-a-child-is-unimaginable-farhan-akhtar-on-his-role-in-the-sky-is-pink-2045271.html |title=\u2018The pain of losing a child is unimaginable\u2019: Farhan Akhtar on his role in 'The Sky Is Pink' |date=10 October 2019 |work=[[The New Indian Express]] |access-date=15 April 2020}}</ref> He was given filmed interviews of the family for their research. Akhtar found that the research material in form of writing and the footage helped him create his own version of Niren.<ref name=\"tniefarhan\" /> He did get to meet Niren while filming and he felt that they both had a lot in common. Being a parent, Akhtar found easy to relate with his character.<ref name=\"telegraph3\">{{Cite news |last=Roy |first=Priyanka |url=https://www.telegraphindia.com/entertainment/the-sky-is-pink-is-a-great-story-farhan-akhtar/cid/1710663 |title='The Sky is Pink' is a great story: Farhan Akhtar |date=10 October 2019 |work=The Telegraph |access-date=15 April 2020}}</ref> Conversely he said \"the challenge was not in feeling the kind of parental love I needed to evoke, but imagining what losing a child could potentially feel like.\"<ref name=\"telegraph3\" /> He said that he chose to not over-dramatise his portrayal as \"the real parents never over-dramatised their situation\". Akhtar said \"They dealt with the whole thing in such an amazingly normal way, which will seem very abnormal to other people. People will wonder, \u2018How are they happy and smiling all the time?\u2019 But that\u2019s how they dealt with it. They wanted to give their daughter a joyous life\u2026 they didn\u2019t want her to be mournful and keep thinking about the end, they just wanted her to be happy as long as she was here\u2026. It\u2019s so, so inspiring.\"<ref name=\"telegraph3\" />\n\nLike Chopra and Akhtar, Wasim was too drawn to the towards the story of the film and revealed that she had immediately fell in love with the story.<ref name=\"filmingbegins\">{{cite news|url=http://www.asianage.com/entertainment/bollywood/080818/the-sky-is-pink-priyanka-farhan-and-zaira-begin-filming-for-shonali-boses-film.html|title=The Sky Is Pink: Priyanka, Farhan and Zaira begin filming for Shonali Bose's film|work=[[The Asian Age]]|date=8 August 2018|access-date=15 April 2020}}</ref> Of her character, Wasim said \"It is a character that touched my heart and I am honoured to be playing this role.\"<ref name=\"filmingbegins\"/> Saraf described his character Ishaan saying he is someone who becomes the pillar of the family during the tragedy. He revealed that portraying the character was delightful as he got to explore human emotions a lot more than he had before in his career.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/celebrities/story/rohit-saraf-it-was-always-a-dream-to-work-with-priyanka-chopra-1607218-2019-10-08 |title=Rohit Saraf: It was always a dream to work with Priyanka Chopra |last=Singh |first=Suhani |date=8 October 2019 |website=India Today |access-date=6 March 2020}}</ref> Unlike the rest of the cast, Saraf was not allowed to see the documented footage of the Chaudhary family as Bose thought he would not be able to take that well.<ref name=\"saraf\" /> To prepare for his character, Saraf had researched a lot about the Chaudhary family during the audition process. After his casting, he stopped his research and relied mostly on Bose's inputs on her advice and the collaborative efforts of the cast which he said enhanced his performance.<ref name=\"saraf\" />\n\nCostume designer Eka Lakhani designed the clothes for the cast.<ref name=\"cast&crew\"/> Since the film spans 25 years, the characters of Aditi and Niren's looks undergo several transformations as they age. These changes were mostly accomplished by make-up and hair styling.<ref name=\"transformation\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.outlookindia.com/website/story/entertainment-news-priyanka-chopra-jonas-and-farhan-akhtars-transformation-in-the-sky-is-pink/340216 |title=Priyanka Chopra Jonas And Farhan Akhtar\u2019s Transformation In \u2018The Sky Is Pink\u2019 |date=9 October 2019 |website=Outlook |access-date=6 March 2020}}</ref> Chopra's hair inform the age of her character; when her character is young the hair is longer and it gets shorter as she ages in the film, short hair at 50.<ref name=\"transformation\" /> Staying true to the real life, Aditi was given a glamorous and make-up heavy look as she had made an effort to look glamorous and throughout her 40s, with her philosophy being \"when life sucks, look like a million bucks\".<ref name=\"wion\" /> Chopra had suggested to put on some weight and grey colour to showcase character's aging in the film but Bose outright declined her request.<ref name=\"refinery\" /> Bose felt it would be a cliche move to show Aditi as dowdy in the later portions of the film and not true to the real life Aditi who is very glamorous and likes to dress up even in hard moments of life.<ref name=\"refinery\" /> Akhtar's Character, when younger sports curly hair while is groomed when his character matures and is given mustache in the later portions of the film.<ref name=\"transformation\" />\n\n=== Filming ===\n[[Principal photography]] of ''The Sky Is Pink'' began on 8 August 2018 in [[Mumbai]] with all of its cast members.<ref name=\"filmingbegins\"/> Kartik Vijay and Nick Cooke handled the cinematography while production design was done by Aradhana Seth.<ref name=\"cast&crew\"/> The second schedule of the film began on 13 October 2018 in [[London]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/priyanka-chopra-farhan-akhtar-zaira-wasim-begin-shooting-for-second-schedule-of-the-sky-is-pink-in-london-5373861.html|title=Priyanka Chopra, Farhan Akhtar, Zaira Wasim begin shooting for second schedule of The Sky Is Pink in London||work=Firstpost|date=13 October 2018|access-date=18 April 2020}}</ref> The London schedule consisted of six days which concluded on 19 October 2018.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.indiatvnews.com/entertainment/bollywood-priyanka-chopra-zaira-wasim-wrap-london-schedule-of-the-sky-is-pink-see-pictures-473795|title=Priyanka Chopra, Zaira Wasim wrap London schedule of The Sky Is Pink. See pictures|work=India TV|date=19 October 2018|access-date=18 April 2020}}</ref> The filming moved to [[Delhi]] as a part of the second schedule on 12 November 2018.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://m.economictimes.com/magazines/panache/amidst-her-wedding-prep-priyanka-chopra-is-in-new-delhi-shooting-for-the-sky-is-pink/articleshow/66586166.cms|title=Amidst her wedding prep, Priyanka Chopra is in New Delhi shooting for 'The Sky Is Pink'|work=The Economic Times|date=12 November 2018|access-date=18 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/priyanka-chopra-shares-photos-from-the-sky-is-pink-sets-5449581/|title=Priyanka Chopra gives a sneak-peek into Delhi schedule of The Sky is Pink|publisher=Press Trust of India|work=The Indian Express|date=16 November 2018|access-date=18 April 2020}}</ref> The scenes were filmed at several locations in Delhi including [[Chandani Chowk]] which Bose specifically chose to show the culture of the locality on film.<ref name=\"delhitrilogy\"/> Bose said \"Delhi has a lot of character and every locality means something. You can capture its beauty in the greenery here, the charm of [[Old Delhi|old Delhi]] \u2013 this mix is very interesting.\"<ref name=\"delhitrilogy\"/> While filming in the locality a \"sea of people\" gathered to watch Chopra and Akhtar who were filming their scenes on a terrace.<ref name=\"delhitrilogy\"/> The second schedule of the film was complete in the last week of November.<ref name=\"delhischedulewrap\">{{cite news|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/priyanka-chopra-nick-jonas-the-sky-is-pink-wrap-5463347/|title=Priyanka Chopra wraps The Sky Is Pink schedule, team organises farewell party for the bride-to-be|work=The Indian Express|date=25 November 2018|access-date=18 April 2020}}</ref> Chopra, who was getting married on 1 December 2018, filmed her scenes till four days before her wedding to [[Nick Jonas]]. The producer of the film, Siddharth Roy Kapur praised the actress for her commitment, saying \"Priyanka has been wonderful. She will be shooting with us right till the very eve of her nuptials, which I think shows a tremendous amount of professionalism.\"<ref name=\"delhischedulewrap\"/> The producers and Bose were accommodating and they created a separate \"wedding approvals room\" for the actress to approve her wedding preparation details to her team, between filming her scenes for the film.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.republicworld.com/entertainment-news/bollywood-news/the-sky-is-pink-priyanka-was-shooting-until-4-days-before-her-wedding.html|title=The Sky Is Pink: Priyanka Was Shooting Until 4 Days Before Her Wedding|last=Raut|first=Mamta|work=Republic World|date=2 October 2019|access-date=18 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.dnaindia.com/bollywood/report-when-i-met-shonali-nick-jonas-was-not-in-picture-priyanka-chopra-on-preparing-for-wedding-between-the-sky-is-pink-2792117|title='When I met Shonali, Nick Jonas was not in picture': Priyanka Chopra on preparing for wedding between 'The Sky Is Pink'|work=Daily News and Analysis|date=24 September 2019|access-date=18 April 2020}}</ref> In February 2019, Bose announced that the final schedule would of the film will be filmed in March.<ref name=\"finalschedule\">{{cite news|url=https://www.dnaindia.com/bollywood/report-priyanka-chopra-farhan-akhtar-to-shoot-final-schedule-of-the-sky-is-pink-in-march-2718066|title=Priyanka Chopra, Farhan Akhtar to shoot final schedule of \u2018The Sky Is Pink\u2019 in March|work=Daily News and Analysis|date=9 February 2019|access-date=18 April 2020}}</ref> The final schedule of the film began in the [[Andaman Islands]] on 1 March 2019 and continued till 9 March 2019 when the filming wrapped.<ref name=\"finalschedule\"/><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/the-sky-is-pink-priyanka-chopra-farhan-akhtar-zaira-wasim-wrap-up-shoot-in-andaman-nicobar-islands-6236601.html|title=The Sky Is Pink: Priyanka Chopra, Farhan Akhtar, Zaira Wasim wrap up shoot in Andaman & Nicobar Islands|work=Firstpost|date=11 March 2019|access-date=18 April 2020}}</ref> Although the filming was completed, Bose revealed that a song was still left to be shot.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/hindi/2019/mar/14/shooting-complete-for-priyanka-chopras-the-sky-is-pink-1950745.html|title=Shooting complete for Priyanka Chopra\u2019s 'The Sky Is Pink'|work=The New Indian Express|date=14 March 2019|access-date=18 April 2020}}</ref> The filming of the song started on 6 June 2019 in Mumbai and was shot over five days.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/bollywood/story/priyanka-chopra-to-shoot-for-a-song-for-the-sky-is-pink-in-mumbai-next-month-1521527-2019-05-10|title=Priyanka Chopra to shoot for a song for The Sky Is Pink in Mumbai next month|work=India Today|date=10 May 2019|access-date=18 April 2020}}</ref> The said song \"Pink Gulaabi Sky\" was supposed to feature in the film as the part of the plot but Bose felt it did not go with the flow of the story. It was cut from the final film and was ultimately used as a promotional song.<ref name=\"promotionalsong\">{{cite news|url=https://www.filmfare.com/news/bollywood/heres-why-the-song-pink-gulaabi-sky-was-edited-out-of-the-sky-is-pink-36651.html|title=Here\u2019s why the song Pink Gulaabi Sky was edited out of The Sky is Pink|work=Filmfare|date=9 October 2019|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref> Bose complimented the producers for agreeing with her decision to cut the song, saying \"When we shot the song, I thought that it was a fun number and looked lovely. Later, I was surprised to see that the makers are in sync with my view. Considering the fact that the team had spent a lot of money to shoot the song, it requires guts to take a decision like this\".<ref name=\"promotionalsong\"/> The film was shot over ten months.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/priyanka-chopra-attends-the-sky-is-pink-wrap-up-party-with-zaira-wasim-writes-note-on-instagram-6796891.html|title=Priyanka Chopra attends The Sky is Pink wrap up party with Zaira Wasim, writes note on Instagram|publisher=Asian News International|work=Firstpost|date=12 June 2019|access-date=18 April 2020}}</ref> The film was edited by Manas Mittal.<ref name=\"cast&crew\"/>\n\n== Soundtrack ==\n{{Infobox album\n| name         = The Sky Is Pink\n| type         = soundtrack\n| artist       = [[Pritam]]\n| cover        = \n| border       = yes\n| alt          = \n| released     = 4 October 2019\n| recorded     = \n| venue        = \n| studio       = \n| genre        = [[Feature film soundtrack]]\n| length       = 21:08\n| language     = [[Hindi language|Hindi]]\n| label        = [[Zee Music Company]]\n| producer     = \n| prev_title   = [[Chhichhore]]\n| prev_year    = 2019\n| year         = 2019\n| next_title   = [[Love Aaj Kal (2020 film)|Love Aaj Kal]]\n| next_year    = 2020\n}}\n\nThe film's music is composed by [[Pritam]] while lyrics are written by [[Gulzar]].<ref name=\"th\" /> It contains four original songs and a reprisal, with vocals provided by singers such as [[Arijit Singh]], [[Antara Mitra]], [[Arjun Kanungo]], [[Lisa Mishra]], Shashwat Singh, [[Jonita Gandhi]] and Sreerama Chandra.<ref name=\"itunes\" /> The soundtrack was released on 4 October 2019 by [[Zee Music Company]].<ref name=\"itunes\" /> Though not a part of the main soundtrack, the film features an end credit song titled \"For Aisha\" composed by Aisha Chaudhary's brother Ishaan under his band name \"Memba\". The song is sung by the [[Nooran Sisters]], Naomi Wild and Evan Giia.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://open.spotify.com/album/5He2R0dw92kc4N9tg4v7zc|title=For Aisha (Featured in \"The Sky Is Pink\")|work=[[Spotify]]|access-date=18 April 2020}}</ref> [[Anvita Dutt]] wrote the song with Memba, Wild and Giia.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.jiosaavn.com/lyrics/for-aisha-featured-in-the-sky-is-pink-lyrics/HyNabjVcX3A|title=For Aisha (Featured in \"The Sky Is Pink\") Lyrics|work=[[JioSaavn]]|access-date=18 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n{{Track listing\n| headline       = Track listing<ref name=\"itunes\">{{Cite web |url=https://music.apple.com/in/album/the-sky-is-pink-original-motion-picture-soundtrack/1482434710 |title=The Sky Is Pink (Original Motion Picture Soundtrack) |website=[[iTunes]] |access-date=4 March 2020}}</ref>\n| total_length   = 21:28\n| extra_column   = Singer(s)\n| title1         = Dil Hi Toh Hai\n| extra1         = [[Arijit Singh]], [[Antara Mitra]]\n| music1         = [[Pritam]]\n| lyrics1        = Gulzar\n| length1        = 4:40\n| title2         = Nadaaniyaan\n| extra2         = [[Arjun Kanungo]], Lisa Mishra\n| music2         = Pritam\n| lyrics2        = Gulzar\n| length2        = 4:18\n| title3         = Zindagi\n| extra3         = Arijit Singh\n| music3         = Pritam\n| lyrics3        = Gulzar\n| length3        = 4:09\n| title4         = Pink Gulaabi Sky\n| extra4         = Shashwat Singh, [[Jonita Gandhi]]\n| music4         = Pritam\n| lyrics4        = Gulzar\n| length4        = 3:20\n| title5         = Dil Hi Toh Hai\n| note5          = Reprise\n| extra5         = Sreerama Chandra, Antara Mitra\n| music5         = Pritam\n| lyrics5        = Gulzar\n| length5        = 4:41\n}}\n\n== Marketing and release ==\nThe film was one of the most anticipated Indian films of 2019.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.filmfare.com/features/sky-is-pink-5-reasons-why-you-must-watch-the-priyanka-chopra-and-farhan-akhtar-starrer-36720.html|title=The Sky Is Pink: 5 reasons why you must watch the Priyanka Chopra and Farhan Akhtar starrer|last=Nihalani|first=Akash|work=Filmfare|date=11 October 2019|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"firstlook\">{{cite news|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/first-look-of-priyanka-chopra-starrer-the-sky-is-pink-revealed-zaira-wasim-5846742/|title=The first look of Priyanka Chopra starrer The Sky is Pink revealed|work=The Indian Express|date=24 July 2019|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref> The first look of the film was was released on 23 July 2019.<ref name=\"firstlook\"/> Several exclusive stills from the films were released on 8 September 2019.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/the-sky-is-pink-priyanka-chopra-farhan-akhtar-share-new-stills-ahead-of-world-premiere-at-tiff-2019-7304781.html|title=The Sky is Pink: Priyanka Chopra, Farhan Akhtar share new stills ahead of world premiere at TIFF 2019|work=Firstpost|date=8 September 2019|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref> The first poster was released on 9 September 2019 and Chopra [[tweeted]] that the official trailer would be released the next day.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/the-sky-is-pink-priyanka-chopra-shares-stunning-first-poster-for-her-comeback-hindi-film-trailer-out-on-tuesday/story-LPsIHPGI6pS6R0bbxU0E9M.html|title=The Sky Is Pink: Priyanka Chopra shares stunning first poster for her comeback Hindi film, trailer out on Tuesday|work=Hindustan Times|date=|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref> [[Firstpost]] commented that the \"aesthetically-pleasing poster\" looked \"fun-filled and refreshing.\"<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/the-sky-is-pink-priyanka-chopra-shares-films-first-poster-ahead-of-trailer-release-on-10-september-7311481.html|title=The Sky is Pink: Priyanka Chopra shares film's first poster ahead of trailer release on 10 September|work=Firstpost|date=9 September 2019|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref> The trailer of the film was released on 10 September 2019.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/the-sky-is-pink-trailer-farhan-akhtar-priyanka-chopra-fight-for-zaira-wasims-survival-in-shonali-bose-film-7314701.html|title=The Sky Is Pink trailer: Farhan Akhtar, Priyanka Chopra fight for Zaira Wasim's survival in Shonali Bose film|work=Firstpost|date=10 September 2019|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref> The ''[[Huffington Post]]'' felt that the film looked like a \"winner\" while ''[[The New Indian Express]]'' called the trailer \"heart warming\", noting it \"promises to be a love story high on emotional quotient with an equal amount of humour.\"<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.in/entry/the-sky-is-pink-trailer-priyanka-chopra_in_5d772427e4b075210231c55b|title=The Sky Is Pink Trailer: Priyanka Chopra, Farhan Akhtar's Film Looks Like A Winner|last=Pathak|first=Ankur|work=Huffington Post|date=10 September 2019|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/hindi/2019/sep/10/watch--farhan-priyanka-warming-our-hearts-in-the-sky-is-pink-trailer-2031627.html|title=Watch: Farhan, Priyanka warming our hearts in 'The Sky is Pink' trailer|work=The New Indian Express|date=10 September 2019|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn July 2019, media reported that ''The Sky Is Pink'' was selected to premiere at the [[44th Toronto International Film Festival]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/priyanka-chopras-the-sky-is-pink-set-for-world-premiere-at-toronto-international-film-festival-2019/articleshow/70354747.cms |title=Priyanka Chopra's 'The Sky is Pink' set for world premiere at Toronto International Film Festival 2019 |publisher=Press Trust of India |work=Times of India |date=24 July 2019 |access-date=24 July 2019}}</ref> The only Asian film to be selected for \"Gala Presentation\", ''The Sky Is Pink'' premiered at the festival at the [[Roy Thomson Hall]] on 13 September 2019 and received a 15 minute long standing ovation.<ref name=\"tiffpremiere\">{{cite news|url=https://www.outlookindia.com/website/story/entertainment-news-the-sky-is-pink-gets-standing-ovation-at-its-world-premiere-at-tiff-2019/338836|title=\u2018The Sky Is Pink\u2019 Gets Standing Ovation At Its World Premiere At TIFF 2019|last=Roy|first=Lachmi Deb|work=Outlook|date=17 September 2019|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref> The premiere sold-out and was attended by 2000 people. This was followed by an another sold-out screening at the [[Elgin Theatre (Ottawa)|Elgin Theatre]].<ref name=\"tiffpremiere\"/> The Chaudhary family were in the attendance at the premiere along with the cast, director and the producers.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ndtv.com/entertainment/the-sky-is-pink-at-toronto-film-festival-priyanka-chopra-farhan-akhtar-shibani-dandekar-attend-world-2100748|title=The Sky Is Pink At Toronto Film Festival: Priyanka Chopra, Farhan Akhtar-Shibani Dandekar Attend World Premiere|last=Goyal|first=Divya|work=NDTV|date=14 September 2019|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref> The film also premiered at the [[24th Busan International Film Festival]] and the [[BFI London Film Festival|2019 BFI London Film Festival]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/bollywood/sky-pink-will-premiered-london-film-festival-busan-film-festival/|title=The Sky Is Pink will be premiered in the London Film Festival and Busan Film Festival|work=Bollywood Hungama|date=5 September 2019|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe promotions of the film started in the last week of September.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.news18.com/news/lifestyle/priyanka-chopra-takes-fans-behind-the-scenes-of-the-sky-is-pink-promotions-2323777.html|title=Priyanka Chopra Takes Fans Behind The Scenes of The Sky is Pink Promotions|last=Kashyap|first=Antara|work=|date=26 September 2019|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref> Chopra, Akhtar, Saraf and Bose took part in the promotions of the film.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.mid-day.com/photos/priyanka-chopra-farhan-akhtar-shonali-bose-rohit-saraf-promote-the-sky-is-pink/62863|title=Priyanka Chopra, Farhan Akhtar, Shonali Bose, Rohit Saraf promote The Sky Is Pink|work=[[Mid Day]]|date=29 September 2019|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref> On the other hand, Wasim, who had retired from acting due to her religious beliefs by the time of marketing, did not take part in the film's promotions.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/bollywood/story/after-quitting-films-zaira-wasim-opts-out-of-the-sky-is-pink-promotions-1560141-2019-07-02|title=Zaira Wasim opts out of The Sky Is Pink promotions after exiting films|work=India Today|date=2 July 2019|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/the-sky-is-pink-priyanka-chopra-shares-her-thoughts-on-zaira-wasims-decision-to-quit-bollywood/articleshow/71287080.cms|title='The Sky Is Pink': Priyanka Chopra shares her thoughts on Zaira Wasim\u2019s decision to quit Bollywood|work=The Times of India|date=25 September 2019|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref> After promoting the film in India, Chopra promoted the film in the United States by appearing on American prime time talk show ''[[The Tonight Show Starring Jimmy Fallon]]'' and the day time talk show [[The View (talk show)|The View]].<ref name=\"talkshow\">{{cite news|url=https://www.business-standard.com/article/news-ani/priyanka-chopra-to-promote-the-sky-is-pink-on-the-jimmy-fallon-talk-show-119101100239_1.html|title=Priyanka Chopra to promote 'The Sky is Pink' on the Jimmy Fallon talk show|publisher=[[Asian News International]]|work=[[Business Standard]]|date=11 October 2019|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.republicworld.com/entertainment-news/bollywood-news/the-sky-is-pink-priyanka-chopra-promotes-her-upcoming-film-in-usa.html|title=The Sky Is Pink: Priyanka Chopra Promotes Her Upcoming Film In The USA|last=Nair|first=Tarun|work=Republic World|date=11 October 2019|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref> ''The Sky Is Pink'' became the first Indian film to be promoted on American television.<ref name=\"talkshow\"/> The film was released on 11 October 2019. It received a [[Limited release|limited release]] in the United States.<ref name=\"rt\">{{cite news|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/the_sky_is_pink|title=The Sky Is Pink (2019)|work=Rotten Tomatoes|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n[[Netflix]] brought the worldwide streaming rights of the film, a first for an Indian film.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.outlookindia.com/website/story/entertainment-news-costs-already-covered-for-priyanka-chopra-jonas-and-farhan-akhtars-the-sky-is-pink/340286|title=Costs Already Covered For Priyanka Chopra Jonas And Farhan Akhtar\u2019s \u2018The Sky Is Pink\u2019|last=Roy|first=Lachmi Deb|work=Outlook|date=10 October 2019|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref> It became available on the platform on 11 December 2019.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.thequint.com/entertainment/hot-on-web/new-on-netflix-december-2019-the-sky-is-pink-you-season-2|title=New on Netflix This December:The Sky is Pink, Love Happens, You S2|work=[[The Quint]]|date=29 November 2019|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref> The film is also available on [[Apple TV Plus]].<ref name=\"rt\"/>\n\n== Reception ==\n=== Critical response ===\nThe film received generally positive reviews.<ref name=\"ibtimes.co.in\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.ibtimes.co.in/sky-pink-movie-review-rating-critics-cant-stop-praising-priyanka-chopra-farhan-akhtar-starrer-806940 |title=Sky Is Pink movie review and rating: Critics can't stop praising Priyanka Chopra-Farhan Akhtar starrer |last=Sarkar |first=Suparno |date=10 October 2019 |website=International Business Times, India Edition}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.ndtv.com/entertainment/the-sky-is-pink-box-office-collection-day-1-priyanka-chopra-and-farhan-akhtars-film-gets-a-slow-star-2115790 |title=The Sky Is Pink Box Office Collection Day 1: Priyanka Chopra And Farhan Akhtar's Film Gets A Slow Start |website=NDTV.com}}</ref> On the [[review aggregator]] website [[Rotten Tomatoes]], the film holds a rating of 71% based on 17 reviews, with an [[Weighted arithmetic mean|average rating]] of 6/10.<ref name=\"rotten:cr0\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/the_sky_is_pink |title=THE SKY IS PINK |website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]] |publisher=[[Fandango (company)|Fandango Media]] |access-date=17 October 2019}}</ref>\n\nDevesh Sharma of ''[[Filmfare]]'' rated the film four stars out of five, lauding the film's ability to make viewers laugh despite its tragic undertone. He concluded, writing \"this bitter-sweet film will make you laugh, will make you cry and will surely make you ruminate on the glorious uncertainty of life.\"<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.filmfare.com/reviews/bollywood-movies/movie-review-the-sky-is-pink-36641.html |title=Movie Review: The Sky Is Pink |website=filmfare.com}}</ref> Writing for ''[[Mid Day]]'', film critic [[Mayank Shekhar]] rated the film with three and half stars out of five, praising Bose for telling an \"astonishingly dark personal story with reasonable hope\" that never felt exploitative or manipulative. He complemented the \"smart\" screenplay which he felt was structured to dive viewers \"deeper and deeper\" into the characters and circumstances on screen.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.mid-day.com/articles/the-sky-is-pink-movie-review-cry-bucket-loads-cant-help/21877166 |title=The Sky is Pink Movie Review: Cry bucket-loads; can't help |date=10 October 2019 |website=mid-day}}</ref> Priyanka Sinha Jha of ''[[CNN-News18]]'', praising Chopra Jonas, Akhtar and Wasim for their performances, and wrote, \"The real hero in this instance, however, would have to be the zany uplifting story and to that effect, with ''The Sky is Pink'', Bose delivers a fitting salutation to life.\"<ref>{{Cite news |last=Sinha Jha |first=Priyanka |url=https://www.news18.com/news/movies/the-sky-is-pink-movie-review-priyanka-chopra-farhan-akhtar-film-is-all-shades-of-life-2340281.html |title=The Sky Is Pink Movie Review: Priyanka Chopra-Farhan Akhtar Film is All Shades of Life |date=10 October 2019 |work=CNN-News18 |access-date=10 October 2019}}</ref> Writing for ''[[NDTV]]'' [[Saibal Chatterjee]], rated the film with three and half stars out of five, and praised Bose for her direction and writing.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.ndtv.com/entertainment/the-sky-is-pink-movie-review-priyanka-chopra-lends-this-unmissable-film-a-starry-edge-3-5-stars-out-2114432 |title=The Sky Is Pink Movie Review: Priyanka Chopra Lends This Unmissable Film A Starry Edge |last=Chatterjee |first=Saibal |date=10 October 2019 |website=NDTV |access-date=10 October 2019}}</ref> Sreeparna Sengupta of ''[[The Times of India]]'' gave the film three and half stars out of five, praising the performances of Chopra Jonas, Akhtar and Wasim, she noted that the film scored high on the emotional quotient. She opined that though the film was lengthy and screenplay needed more focus, 'the emotional arc' and the 'stellar performances' kept the interest going. Concluding, she wrote, \"''The Sky is Pink'' is definitely a stirring watch.\"<ref>{{Cite news |last=Sengupta |first=Sreeparna |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/movie-reviews/the-sky-is-pink/movie-review/71509561.cms |title=The Sky Is Pink Movie Review: An emotional, stirring watch |date=10 October 2019 |work=The Times of India |access-date=10 October 2019}}</ref> Teo Bugbee of ''[[The New York Times]]'' lauded Bose for achieving a balanced tone in the film, writing \"The writer and director Shonali Bose bounces from tone to tone, livening the somber subject matter with bright hues, quippy dialogue and an ever-jubilant score.\"<ref name=\"nytimes.com\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/10/10/movies/the-sky-is-pink-review.html |title=\u2018The Sky Is Pink\u2019 Review: A Story Told From the Grave |last=Bugbee |first=Teo |date=10 October 2019 |via=NYTimes.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.indiewire.com/2019/10/the-sky-is-pink-review-1202178086/ |title=\u2018The Sky Is Pink\u2019 Review: An Unusual Grief Drama Obsessed With the Possibility of Life After Death |last=Erbland |first=Kate |last2=Erbland |first2=Kate |date=9 October 2019}}</ref>\n\n[[Rajeev Masand]] criticised the film's \"blatant manipulation\" but added that \"there are moments that left me with a heavy heart\".<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.rajeevmasand.com/reviews/our-films/pain-relief-2/ |title=Pain relief |last=Masand |first=Rajeev |date=11 October 2019 |website=RajeevMasand.com}}</ref> Dennis Harvey of ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'' too disliked the film and wrote that the \"somewhat bland polish on all levels doesn\u2019t much assist the raw pain that should be at this story\u2019s center\".<ref>{{Cite news |last=Harvey |first=Dennis |url=https://variety.com/2019/film/reviews/the-sky-is-pink-review-1203336082/ |title=Toronto Film Review: \u2018The Sky is Pink\u2019 |date=18 September 2019 |work=Variety}}</ref> Vinayak Chakraborty of ''[[Outlook (Indian magazine)|Outlook]]'' rated the film with three stars out of five, criticizing the \"flashback-driven storyline\" and its runtime which he felt was too long at nearly two and half hours. However, he opined that the film still works with all its flaws.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.outlookindia.com/newsscroll/the-sky-is-pink-sensitive-but-soppy-ians-review-rating-/1637218 |title=''The Sky Is Pink'': Sensitive but Soppy (IANS Review; Rating: ***) |website=[[Outlook (Indian magazine)|Outlook]]}}</ref> [[Anupama Chopra]] of ''[[Film Companion]]'' found the film to be \"sensitive\" but highly \"sanitized\". She wrote \"The Sky is Pink is sincere and heartfelt but it never gets raw or messy.\"<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.filmcompanion.in/the-sky-is-pink-movie-review-by-anupama-chopra-farhan-akhtar-priyanka-chopra-zaira-wasim |title=The Sky Is Pink Review By Anupama Chopra: A Sincere Yet Sanitised Look At Extreme Anguish |date=11 October 2019}}</ref> Shubhra Gupta of ''[[The Indian Express]]'' rated the film with two stars out of five. According to her, the film only occasionally worked. She opined the film felt \"both constructed and sentimental\", writing \"With the material at hand, you expect a legitimate heart-breaker but this one left me mostly unmoved.\"<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/movie-review/the-sky-is-pink-movie-review-rating-priyanka-chopra-6061269/ |title=The Sky Is Pink movie review: The colour barely seeps into the film |date=11 October 2019}}</ref>\n\n=== Box office ===\n''The Sky Is Pink'' collected {{INR}}2.50 crore on the opening day, {{INR}}4.00 crore on the second day, and {{INR}}4.20 on the third day, taking its opening weekend collection to {{INR}}10.70 crore in India. Film earned {{INR}}15.15 crore in its first week.\n\n{{As of|2019|10|24}}, with a gross of {{INR}}23.85 crore in India and {{INR}}10.56 crore overseas, the film has a worldwide gross collection of {{INR}}34.41 crore. It did not perform well at the box office.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Tuteja, Joginder |url=https://www.moneycontrol.com/news/trends/entertainment/priyanka-chopra-and-farhan-akhars-the-sky-is-pink-a-commercial-flop-that-deserves-better-4549841.html |title=Priyanka Chopra and Farhan Akhar\u2019s The Sky Is Pink \u2013 A commercial flop that deserves better |date=19 October 2019 |work=Money Control |access-date=19 October 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Accolades ==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\"\n|-\n!scope=\"col\"| Award\n\n!scope=\"col\"| Category\n!scope=\"col\"| Recipient(s) and nominee(s)\n!scope=\"col\"| Result\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\"| {{Abbr|Ref.|Reference(s)}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=\"3\" | [[Filmfare Awards | 65th FilmFare Awards]]\n| [[Filmfare Award for Best Actress|Best Actress]]\n| {{Sort|Chopra|[[Priyanka Chopra]]}}\n| {{nom}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"3\"|<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.filmfare.com/awards/filmfare-awards-2020/nominations |title=Nominations for 65th Amazon Filmfare Awards 2020 |work=Filmfare |access-date=3 February 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Filmfare Award for Best Supporting Actress|Best Supporting Actress]]\n| {{Sort|Wasim|[[Zaira Wasim]]}}\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Filmfare Critics Award for Best Film|Best Film (Critics)]]\n| {{Sort|Bose|[[Shonali Bose]]}}\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=\"2\" | [[International Indian Film Academy Awards |21st International Indian Film Academy Awards]]\n\n| [[IIFA Award for Best Actress|Best Actress]]\n| {{Sort|Chopra|[[Priyanka Chopra]]}}\n| {{pending}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"|<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://iifaawards2020.iifa.com/ |title=IIFA 2020 Nominees |website=[[International Indian Film Academy Awards]] |access-date=5 March 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[IIFA Award for Best Male Playback Singer|Best Male Playback Singer]]\n| {{Sort|Singh|[[Arijit Singh]] \u2013 Dil Hi Toh Hai}}\n| {{pending}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=\"5\" | [[Screen Awards | 26th Screen Awards]]\n| Best Film (Critics)\n| ''The Sky Is Pink''\n| {{nom}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"5\"|<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.hotstar.com/in/tv/star-screen-awards/s-449/main-event-2020/1260015949 |title=26 Star Screen Awards |website=[[Hotstar]] |url-status=live |access-date=5 March 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| Best Director (Critics)\n| {{Sort|Bose|[[Shonali Bose]]}}\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Screen Award for Best Actress (Critics)|Best Actress (Critics)]]\n| {{Sort|Chopra|[[Priyanka Chopra]]}}\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Screen Award for Best Actor (Critics)|Best Actor (Critics)]]\n| {{Sort|Akhtar|[[Farhan Akhtar]]}}\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Screen Award for Best Supporting Actress|Best Supporting Actress]]\n| {{Sort|Wasim|[[Zaira Wasim]]}}\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n*{{IMDb title|tt8902990}}\n* [https://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movie/the-sky-is-pink/ The Sky is Pink] on [[Bollywood Hungama]]\n* {{Rotten Tomatoes|https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/the_sky_is_pink}}\n\n{{Shonali Bose}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Sky Is Pink, The}}\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:2010s biographical drama films]]\n[[Category:2019 films]]\n[[Category:2010s Hindi-language films]]\n[[Category:Indian biographical drama films]]\n[[Category:Indian films based on actual events]]\n[[Category:Films about diseases]]\n[[Category:Medical-themed films]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2019 film directed by Shonali Bose}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=March 2019}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = The Sky Is Pink\n| image          = The Sky Is Pink.jpg\n| alt            = The poster features a family, the couple and their two children, with spring like light green and light pink themed colour in the background. The poster also features the couple at the top. Text at the bottom of the poster reveals the tagline of the film while the text at the bottom of the poster reveals the title, name of the director, name of the producer, name of the distributor, the release date and the rest of the credits.\n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| director       = [[Shonali Bose]]\n| producer       = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Ronnie Screwvala]]\n* [[Siddharth Roy Kapur]]\n* Kilian Kerwin\n* [[Priyanka Chopra Jonas]]\n* Madhu Chopra\n}}\n| screenplay         = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Shonali Bose]]\n* Nilesh Maniyar\n* <small>(Additional)</small>\n* [[Juhi Chaturvedi]]\n* <small>(Hindi dialogues)</small>\n}}\n| starring       = {{Plainlist|\n* Priyanka Chopra Jonas\n* [[Farhan Akhtar]]\n* [[Zaira Wasim]]\n* [[Rohit Suresh Saraf]]\n}}\n| narrator       = Zaira Wasim\n| music          = {{Plainlist|\n'''Songs:'''\n* [[Pritam]]\n'''Score:'''\n* [[Mikey McCleary]]\n}}\n| cinematography = {{Plainlist|\n* Kartik Vijay\n* Nick Cooke\n}}\n| editing        = Manas Mittal\n| studio         = {{Plainlist|\n* [[RSVP Movies]]\n* Roy Kapur Films\n* [[Purple Pebble Pictures]]\n*Ivanhoe Pictures\n}}\n| distributor    = RSVP Movies\n| released       = {{Film date|2019|09|13|[[Toronto International Film Festival|TIFF]]|2019|10|11|df=y|India}}\n| runtime        = 143 minutes<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://bbfc.co.uk/releases/sky-pink-2019 |title=The Sky Is Pink (2019) |website=[[British Board of Film Classification]] |access-date=10 October 2019}}</ref>\n| country        = India\n| language       = Hindi\n| budget         = \n| gross          = {{Estimation}} {{INR}}34.41 crore<ref name=\"box:bbh\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movie/the-sky-is-pink/box-office/ |title=The Sky is Pink Box Office |website=Bollywood Hungama |access-date=25 October 2019}}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''''The Sky Is Pink''''' is a 2019 Indian [[Hindi]]-language [[biographical film]] written and directed by [[Shonali Bose]]. The film was co-produced by [[Siddharth Roy Kapur]], [[Ronnie Screwvala]] and [[Priyanka Chopra Jonas]] under their production companies of [[RSVP Movies]], Roy Kapur Films and [[Purple Pebble Pictures]] in association with Ivanhoe Pictures. The film stars Chopra Jonas, [[Farhan Akhtar]], [[Zaira Wasim]], and [[Rohit Suresh Saraf]]. Based on the real life story of [[Aisha Chaudhary]] who was diagnosed with [[pulmonary fibrosis]], the film tells the love story of her parents, Aditi and Niren, dealing with their daughter's illness.\n\nAditi Chaudhary approached Bose to make a film based on her daughter. Although intrigued by the story, Bose instead chose to depict the story of the couple from Aisha's point of view, focusing on their marriage and the effect of a child's illness on the lives of the parents and their relationship. Bose wrote the screenplay based on the details she has gathered through interviewing Aditi and Niren. Nilesh Maniyar wrote the additional screenplay while Hindi dialogue writing was done by [[Juhi Chaturvedi]]. Filming took place in Mumbai, London, Delhi and [[Andaman Islands|Andaman]]. [[Pritam]] composed the soundtrack and [[Gulzar]] wrote the lyrics for the songs.\n\nThe film premiered at the [[44th Toronto International Film Festival]] on 13 September 2019. It was released worldwide on 11 October 2019. ''The Sky Is Pink'' received generally positive reviews, with praise directed towards Bose's writing and direction and the performances. It did not perform well at the box office, grossing {{INR}}34.41 crore worldwide. The film received three [[Filmfare Awards]] nominations: [[Filmfare Critics Award for Best Film|Best Film (Critics)]], [[Filmfare Award for Best Actress|Best Actress]] for Chopra Jonas and [[Filmfare Award for Best Supporting Actress|Best Supporting Actress]] for Wasim.\n\n== Plot ==\n[[Aisha Chaudhary]] narrates the story of her parents, Moose (her mother) and Panda (her father) from [[afterlife]]. Aditi and Niren are a young couple who come from two different backgrounds. Aditi is from the posh end of the town, [[South Delhi]], where on another hand Niren is from a grounded middle-class family. The couple are shown to be in love, with \"an active sex life\" as Aisha's narration describes. The passionate and happy couple get married, and Aditi becomes pregnant with their first child Tanya, who dies within months of her birth due to the [[Severe combined immunodeficiency]] condition. Baby Tanya used to frequently become ill and, while Aditi was convinced it was a serious issue, Niren used to brush it off. Niren believed that negligence was the reason Tanya couldn't be treated sooner and blamed himself for the death of his child. As Aditi was mourning the death of her child, she was consoled by a Catholic church nun and decided to be baptised.\n\nAditi and Niren have a second child Ishaan. A few years later, Aditi bore their third child, another daughter, Aisha. They later learn that Aisha was born with the same Severe combined immunodeficiency condition as their first child, Aditi and Niren are heartbroken. After the doctors in Delhi give up on the treatment, the couple go to London where they learn that the disease could be treated by performing [[bone marrow transplant]]. However, they learn that the treatment is very costly. Niren starts working to earn the money while also asking for crowdfunding via a radio station. After several weeks, they learn that several people have donated money for Aisha's treatment. The surgery is successful but Aisha is kept under doctor's watch. Aditi decides to stay in London while Niren goes back to India with his family and his son Ishaan. Aditi grows overprotective of Aisha, over cleaning the apartment and other things to keep Aisha away from any potential infection.\n\nIshaan starts missing his mother while Niren is always thinking about Aditi and Aisha. This also starts affecting Aditi and Niren's relationship as Aditi is always occupied with Aisha and taking care of her. Months go by and Niren goes to London and asks Aditi to move back to India so that their relationship is not affected. He reasons with Aisha on the grounds that Aisha had gotten better and occasional doctor's visit can be done in India as well. Aditi tells him that they have to live here for a very long time as per doctor's recommendation till Aisha's condition is cured. The whole family moves here permanently till Aisha is cured. Niren's career grows in London and he becomes rich and their family becomes affluent.\n\nSeveral years later, Aisha has finally gotten better and Niren and Aditi decide to move back to India with their families. They shift to the outskirts of Delhi and buy an extravagant and massive bungalow. After a doctor's visit, Aditi and Niren learn that Aisha has been diagnosed with [[pulmonary fibrosis]], a side effect of the chemotherapy that was done to cure the previous disease. With less time on Aisha's life, Aditi sets out to fulfill all of Aisha's dreams such as adopting a pet (which Aditi did not allow due to the risk of infection), seeing the aquatic life and writing a book, among other things. As Aisha's condition worsens, Aditi grows more and more overprotective and due to over stress, suffers a psychotic breakdown and is hospitalized. Aditi does everything in her power to make sure Aisha gets to see the first copy of her book before she dies. Later, Aisha passes away.\n\nAfter the death of Aisha, Aditi and Niren's relationship is strained. While living together, they grow apart and are constantly fighting with each other. Aditi still cannot accept Aisha's death and constantly brings her in their fights. At a party, Niren shows Aisha's secret video that he had found, a video she had made about her parents. Niren wants Aditi to move with him to London so that she can forget Aisha which she finds insulting as she does not want to let Aisha's memories fade, particularly the house. With anger, Niren leaves for London while Aditi stays back. Aditi later goes to meet Niren in London and they reconcile.\n\n== Cast ==\nThe cast has been listed below:<ref name=\"cast&crew\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movie/the-sky-is-pink/cast/ |title=The Sky Is Pink Cast & Crew |work=[[Bollywood Hungama]] |access-date=3 March 2020}}</ref>\n{{Div col}}\n* [[Priyanka Chopra Jonas]] as Aditi Chaudhary\n* [[Farhan Akhtar]] as Niren Chaudhary\n* [[Zaira Wasim]] as [[Aisha Chaudhary]]\n* [[Rohit Suresh Saraf]] as Ishaan Chaudhary\n* Vidhaan Sharma as Young Ishaan\n* Manas Mittal as Anshu Tandon\n* Rajshri Deshpande as Anita Tandon\n* Lushin Dubey as Mrs. Tandon\n* Sunil Chitkara as Mr. Chaudhary\n* Nirupama Verma as Mrs. Chaudhary\n* Puja Sarup as Mohini\n* Gurpal Singh as Rj Arjun Gill\n* Sheena Khalid as Rita\n* Sudhanva Deshpande as Dr. Nirvick Gulati\n* Manisha Chudasama as Santoshi\n* Paras Rattan Sharda as Jeet\n* Salmin Sheriff as Dr. Batliwala\n* Rishi Deshpande as Tanya's Doctor\n* Virhi as Baby Tanya\n* Mala Hashmi as Christian Woman\n* Akshay Joshi as Store Assistant\n* Nargis Nandal as Pilot\n* Raabia Marici as Ishaan's Girlfriend\n{{Div col end}}\n\n== Production ==\n=== Development and writing ===\nThe production of the film started when [[Aisha Chaudhary]]'s mother Aditi approached [[Shonali Bose]] to make a film about her daughter. Chaudhary had seen the trailer of Bose's last film ''[[Margarita with a Straw]]'' (2015) thirty times and was eager to watch the film, saying \"I hope I live to see this film.\"<ref name=\"tnie\">{{Cite news |last=Mitra |first=Shilajit |url=https://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/hindi/2019/oct/09/indian-culture-is-better-equipped-to-deal-with-grief-the-sky-is-pink-director-shonali-bose-2044820.html |title=Indian culture is better equipped to deal with grief: 'The Sky Is Pink' director Shonali Bose |date=9 October 2019 |work=[[The New Indian Express]] |access-date=2 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"th\">{{Cite news |last=Namrata |first=Joshi |url=https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/all-cinema-has-an-inherent-patriarchal-ideology/article29410318.ece |title=All cinema has an inherent patriarchal ideology: Shonali Bose |date=13 September 2019 |work=[[The Hindu]] |access-date=2 March 2020}}</ref> However, she passed away at the age of 18 after being diagnosed with [[pulmonary fibrosis]], two weeks after watching the trailer and never got to see the film. Nine months later, Aditi Chaudhary tracked down Bose who was then living in [[Los Angeles]]. Aditi was adamant as she only wanted Bose to tell the story of her daughter.<ref name=\"th\" /><ref name=\"ht\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/sky-is-pink-director-shonali-bose-says-death-of-her-son-end-of-marriage-drew-her-to-the-story/story-otpNEnfTrDPR1OKaNeBWJJ.html |title=Sky is Pink director Shonali Bose says death of her son, end of marriage drew her to the story |date=10 September 2019 |work=[[Hindustan Times]] |access-date=2 March 2020}}</ref> Initially, they interacted over [[Skype]]. Later, Bose personally interviewed both Aditi and Niren Chaudhary for eight hours a day for two weeks to gather all the details.<ref name=\"tnie\" /><ref name=\"scroll\">{{Cite news |last=Ramnath |first=Nandini |url=https://scroll.in/reel/936799/the-sky-is-pink-director-shonali-bose-it-is-a-rare-couple-who-survive-the-death-of-their-child |title=\u2018The Sky is Pink\u2019 director Shonali Bose: \u2018It is a rare couple who survive the death of their child\u2019 |date=10 September 2019 |work=[[Scroll.in|Scroll]] |access-date=2 March 2020}}</ref> Bose said that \"They talked and cried and healed through the process of those narrations.\"<ref name=\"tnie\" /> Bose had said that she was drawn towards the story as she herself had lost her son so was she ready to explore the subject cinematically and bringing some of her own unique perspective to it.<ref name=\"th\" /><ref name=\"outlook\">{{Cite news |last=Roy |first=Lachmi Deb |url=https://www.outlookindia.com/website/story/entertainment-news-shonali-bose-on-the-sky-is-pink-har-ek-ka-apna-sky-hota-hai-what-colour-is-your-sky/339168 |title=Shonali Bose On \u2018The Sky Is Pink\u2019: \u201cHar Ek Ka Apna Sky Hota Hai. What Colour Is Your Sky?\u201d |date=22 September 2019 |work=[[Outlook (Indian magazine)|Outlook]] |access-date=2 March 2020}}</ref> However, she was more interested in telling the story of Aditi and Niren, a couple, dealing with the illness of their child, saying \"I was drawn to the story, not of a heroic teenager defying death, but the parents who had to deal with it.\"<ref name=\"th\" /> Bose said she was \"intrigued and inspired\" by the Chaudharys' relationship, adding \"It is a rare couple who survive the death of their child.\"<ref name=\"scroll\" /> She said she wanted to explore \"what happens to a love story, to a marriage, when faced with the loss of a child\", explaining \"My own marriage ended when I lost my son. 80% of people\u2019s marriages end when they lose a child.\"<ref name=\"ht\" /><ref name=\"scroll\" /> She wanted to make an unusual romantic film and the lives of Aditi and Niren were exactly unusual like the film she wanted to make.<ref name=\"outlook\" /> In December 2018, Ivanhoe Pictures came on board to co-finance and co-produce the film.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://variety.com/2018/film/asia/ivanhoe-pictures-priyanka-chopra-the-sky-is-pink-1203085471/ |title=Ivanhoe Pictures Boards Priyanka Chopra\u2019s \u2018The Sky is Pink\u2019 |last=Frater |first=Patrick |date=10 December 218 |website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |access-date=6 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nBose began writing the screenplay based on the narration she had heard from the Chaudharys by approaching it as a love story of two people who fell in love when they were \"only 16 and now at 57 are still inseparable\" despite major tragedies that tear most couples apart.<ref name=\"scroll\" /><ref name=\"outlook\" /> Bose chose to tell the film from Aisha's point of view, focusing on 25 years of her parents' marriage.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Blyth, Antonia |url=https://deadline.com/video/the-sky-is-pink-priyanka-chopra-shonali-bose-tiff-toronto/ |title=Priyanka Chopra: 'The Sky Is Pink' Has \"Moments Of Joy, Moments Of Tragedy\" \u2014 Toronto Studio |date=8 September 2019 |access-date=14 September 2019 |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]}}</ref> Nilesh Maniyar, a longtime collaborator of Bose, had also met Aditi and Niren and wanted to make a documentary about Aisha as he felt there was more to explore and saw Bose's film as very different than his, both projects being in different formats. Since Maniyar had also done his research on Aisha's life, Bose invited him to write the additional screenplay.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Negi |first=Shristi |url=https://www.news18.com/news/movies/the-sky-is-pink-writer-nilesh-maniyar-deconstructs-priyanka-chopras-psychotic-breakdown-scene-2367617.html |title=The Sky Is Pink Writer Nilesh Maniyar Deconstructs Priyanka Chopra's Psychotic Breakdown Scene |date=31 October 2019 |work=[[CNN News18]] |access-date=2 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"confirms\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.deccanchronicle.com/entertainment/bollywood/090718/priyanka-chopra-shonali-bose-abhishek-farhan-zaira-sky-is-pink-script.html |title=Priyanka confirms Shonali Bose\u2019s film, reveals title, mystery continues over hero |date=9 July 2018 |work=[[Deccan Chronicle]] |access-date=3 March 2020}}</ref> [[Juhi Chaturvedi]] wrote the Hindi dialogues.<ref name=\"confirms\" /> Bose wanted to stay true to the real life events and depict them as it unfolded in their lives, without fictionalising or deflecting from actual incidents. She said \"The story, facts and events in the film are completely true. I wrote the script as close as possible to the truth. So, when deciding the look and feel of the film, I decided to stay with realism and be as authentic as possible.\"<ref name=\"th\" /><ref name=\"scroll\" /> While writing the script, Bose met with Aisha's family and friends and inquired everything about her. She also read Aisha's writing, including her emails to her brother and the artwork she had made. Bose revealed that feel connected with Aisha even though they never met.<ref name=\"scroll\" /> In handling the subject, Bose consciously chose to be realistic and avoid melodramatic and manipulative set-ups to express emotions.<ref name=\"th\" /> She said \"I am also very conscious of steering clear of melodrama and exploiting or manipulating you with overwrought emotions. I want you to feel what my characters feel but also give you space. This is part of my film form.\"<ref name=\"scroll\" /> In an interview with [[Scroll.in|Scroll]], Bose revealed that in early drafts, Aditi was the main protagonist as she was written to be the central figure in the story, but later strengthened Niren's role and they became equal in the final draft.<ref name=\"scroll\" />\n\n[[Siddharth Roy Kapur]] had liked Bose's previous film and had expressed his desire to work with her.<ref name=\"rediff\">{{Cite news |last=Chhabra |first=Aseem |url=https://www.rediff.com/movies/report/sky-is-pink-required-big-stars/20191010.htm |title='Sky Is Pink required big stars' |date=10 October 2020 |work=[[Rediff.com]] |access-date=2 March 2020}}</ref> After the acquisition of [[UTV Motion Pictures]] by [[The Walt Disney Company]], Kapur was appointed managing director of the company of [[The Walt Disney Company India]] in 2014 and produced several films under the new name as he had previously done with UTV. Kapur established his own company, Roy Kapur Films, in January 2017.<ref name=\"rediff\" /> When Bose found out about his new production house, she approached him with the script of ''The Sky Is Pink'' and Kapur picked it to be the first film under of his company.<ref name=\"rediff\" /><ref name=\"mint\">{{Cite news |last=Sharma |first=Sanjukta |url=https://www.livemint.com/Consumer/vK8fluGeIY8nXR4h4b7RUO/Embracing-technology-is-the-only-way-to-remain-relevant-Sid.html |title=Embracing technology is the only way to remain relevant: Siddharth Roy Kapur |date=22 September 2019 |work=[[Mint (newspaper)|Mint]] |access-date=2 March 2020}}</ref> He said that he found the script wonderfully moving, told with wit, humour, depth and feeling.<ref name=\"mint\" /> As a part of a [[first look deal]] with [[RSVP Movies]], Kapur set the film there, thus collaborating with [[Ronnie Screwvala]], the ex-UTV Studio head, as producers.<ref name=\"rediff\" /> Bose considers ''The Sky Is Pink'' as the culmination of of her ''Delhi trilogy'', a series of unrelated films based on \"mother-child relationship\" and that are set in Delhi. The other first two films being ''[[Amu (film)|Amu]]'' (2005) and ''Margarita with a Straw''.<ref name=\"delhitrilogy\">{{cite news|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/shonali-bose-the-sky-is-pink-completes-my-trilogy-on-delhi/articleshow/71464651.cms|title=Shonali Bose: The Sky Is Pink completes my trilogy on Delhi|last=Kaushik|first=Divya|work=The Times of India|date=7 October 2019|access-date=18 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== Casting and characters ===\nThe film's casting news first came out in May 2018 suggesting that [[Priyanka Chopra]], [[Abhishek Bachchan]] and [[Zaira Wasim]] had been cast in Bose's next untitled. The media reports suggested that Wasim was cast as Aisha Chaudhary, with Chopra and Bachchan playing her parents.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/bollywood/story/abhishek-bachchan-and-priyanka-chopra-to-play-parents-to-zaira-wasim-1235853-2018-05-18 |title=Abhishek-Priyanka to play Zaira Wasim's parents in Shonali Bose's film? |date=18 May 2018 |work=[[India Today]] |access-date=3 March 2020}}</ref> A month later media reports claimed that [[Farhan Akhtar]] had replaced Bachchan and now he would be playing the father.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.dnaindia.com/bollywood/report-farhan-akhtar-replaces-abhishek-bachchan-in-shonali-bose-s-next-to-star-opposite-priyanka-chopra-zaira-wasim-2629148 |title=Farhan Akhtar replaces Abhishek Bachchan in Shonali Bose's next; to star opposite Priyanka Chopra, Zaira Wasim |date=25 June 2018 |work=[[Daily News and Analysis]] |access-date=3 March 2020}}</ref> Chopra confirmed her involvement on 9 July 2018 by posting a picture of the script of ''The Sky Is Pink'' on her [[Instagram]] account, revealing the title of the film.<ref name=\"confirms\" /> The official announcement followed the next day, confirming Akhtar and Wasim's casting in the film.<ref name=\"announcement\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/farhan-akhtar-may-replace-abhishek-bachchan-in-shonali-boses-the-sky-is-pink-opposite-priyanka-chopra-4702601.html |title=Farhan Akhtar, Priyanka Chopra, Zaira Wasim confirmed to star in Shonali Bose's The Sky Is Pink |date=10 July 2018 |work=[[Firstpost]] |access-date=3 March 2020}}</ref> It is the second film to feature Chopra and Akhtar opposite each other after ''[[Dil Dhadakne Do]]'' (2015).<ref name=\"announcement\" /> [[Rohit Suresh Saraf]] was cast as Aisha's brother Ishaan after four rounds of auditions over a period of four months.<ref name=\"saraf\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.telegraphindia.com/entertainment/rohit-saraf-s-sky/cid/1710754 |title=Rohit Saraf's sky |last=Paul |first=Ushnota |date=11 October 2019 |website=The Telegraph |access-date=6 March 2020}}</ref> The film marked the return of Chopra to Bollywood films after three years as she was busy with her Hollywood work.<ref name=\"theweek\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.theweek.in/news/entertainment/2019/10/03/Priyanka-Chopra-reveals-how-The-Sky-is-Pink-reminded-her-of-her-parents.html |title=Priyanka Chopra reveals how 'The Sky is Pink' reminded her of her parents |last=[[Press Trust of India]] |date=3 October 2019 |website=[[The Week (Indian magazine)|The Week]] |access-date=6 March 2020}}</ref> After coming on board the film as an actor, Chopra asked her Kapur and Screwvala to join them as the producer as she believed in the film and wanted to take more responsibility of the film and learn about producing from them.<ref name=\"theweek\" /> Kapur and Screwvala, both frequent collaborators of Chopra (who had starred in several of their films under UTV), agreed to bring her as a producer, thus making ''The Sky Is Pink'' making the first Hindi film to be produced under Chopra's company [[Purple Pebble Pictures]].<ref name=\"theweek\" />\n\nChopra was drawn to the film because of the story and the way it was written, explaining that she found the treatment of a heavy subject with humour was refreshing and beautiful.<ref name=\"wion\">{{Cite news |last=Sen |first=Shomini |url=https://www.wionews.com/entertainment/priyanka-chopra-on-why-she-chose-sky-is-pink-as-her-comeback-film-254196 |title=Priyanka Chopra on why she chose \u2018The Sky Is Pink\u2019 as her comeback film |date=7 October 2019 |work=[[WION (TV channel)|WION]] |access-date=15 April 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"refinery\">{{Cite news |last=Cohen |first=Anne |url=https://www.refinery29.com/en-us/2019/10/8556156/priyanka-chopra-jonas-movie-the-sky-is-pink-interview |title=Priyanka Chopra Jonas\u2019 Latest Role Will Definitely Surprise You |date=11 October 2019 |work=[[Refinery29]] |access-date=15 April 2020}}</ref> She found her character Aditi immersive and described her as \"a ferocious mom\".<ref name=\"theweek\" /><ref name=\"telegraph\">{{Cite news |last=Roy |first=Priyanka |url=https://www.telegraphindia.com/entertainment/bollywood/priyanka-chopra-jonas-on-the-sky-is-pink-and-battling-nerves-of-the-good-kind/cid/1712150 |title=Priyanka Chopra Jonas on the Sky Is Pink and battling nerves of \u2018the good kind\u2019 |date=16 October 2019 |work=The Telegraph |access-date=15 April 2020}}</ref> Chopra did a lot of preparations and research before the filming and also met the real life Aditi.<ref name=\"iepriyanka\">{{Cite news |last=Sahani |first=Alaka |url=https://indianexpress.com/article/express-sunday-eye/priyanka-chopra-the-sky-is-pink-6066665/ |title=Priyanka Chopra: If you want the sky, you\u2019ve to find a way to reach it |date=13 October 2019 |work=The Indian Exress |access-date=15 April 2020}}</ref> Bose was against Chopra meeting Aditi but Chopra was adamant that she must meet her to get into her head as Aditi treated the situation much different than her husband and she felt like she needed to have those difficult conversations with her.<ref name=\"telegraph2\">{{Cite news |last=Paul |first=Ushnota |url=https://www.telegraphindia.com/entertainment/desi-girl-sits-down-for-a-chat-on-new-film-anniversary-plans-and-stardom/cid/1708393?ref=also-read_story-page |title='Desi Girl' sits down for a chat on new film, anniversary plans and stardom |date=29 September 2019 |work=The Telegraph |access-date=15 April 2020}}</ref> The actress revealed that she was also depended on Bose and would ask a lot of questions about the character and she imbibed a lot from Bose and Aditi and Bose's interpretation Aditi.<ref name=\"telegraph\" /><ref name=\"telegraph2\" /> She said \"I'm not a mother, I needed to understand from both Aditi and Shonali who have both lost their children... where does that take you? What do you feel in your heart?\" She said that Aditi reminded of her own mother as she found similarities between her own mother and Aditi and chose to channel her in Aditi.<ref name=\"refinery\" /> Not being a mother, she found the role challenging, saying that the \"film was scaring me in every scene\" but felt that the role made her experience two different aspects of motherhood.\"<ref name=\"wion\" />\n\nAkhtar also chose the film because of the story which he found \"moving and incredibly inspiring\" and the people involved in the film. Like Chopra, Akhtar too relied on Bose's vision of Niren to form his character.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/bollywood/story/farhan-akhtar-the-sky-is-pink-received-applause-from-international-audience-because-of-its-story-1606008-2019-10-03 |title=Farhan Akhtar: The Sky Is Pink received applause from international audience because of its story |date=3 October 2019 |work=India Today |access-date=15 April 2020}}</ref> Akhtar was also instructed to not meet the real life Aditi and Niren before the filming as Bose did not want her actors to get influenced or to imitate them.<ref name=\"tniefarhan\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/hindi/2019/oct/10/the-pain-of-losing-a-child-is-unimaginable-farhan-akhtar-on-his-role-in-the-sky-is-pink-2045271.html |title=\u2018The pain of losing a child is unimaginable\u2019: Farhan Akhtar on his role in 'The Sky Is Pink' |date=10 October 2019 |work=[[The New Indian Express]] |access-date=15 April 2020}}</ref> He was given filmed interviews of the family for their research. Akhtar found that the research material in form of writing and the footage helped him create his own version of Niren.<ref name=\"tniefarhan\" /> He did get to meet Niren while filming and he felt that they both had a lot in common. Being a parent, Akhtar found easy to relate with his character.<ref name=\"telegraph3\">{{Cite news |last=Roy |first=Priyanka |url=https://www.telegraphindia.com/entertainment/the-sky-is-pink-is-a-great-story-farhan-akhtar/cid/1710663 |title='The Sky is Pink' is a great story: Farhan Akhtar |date=10 October 2019 |work=The Telegraph |access-date=15 April 2020}}</ref> Conversely he said \"the challenge was not in feeling the kind of parental love I needed to evoke, but imagining what losing a child could potentially feel like.\"<ref name=\"telegraph3\" /> He said that he chose to not over-dramatise his portrayal as \"the real parents never over-dramatised their situation\". Akhtar said \"They dealt with the whole thing in such an amazingly normal way, which will seem very abnormal to other people. People will wonder, \u2018How are they happy and smiling all the time?\u2019 But that\u2019s how they dealt with it. They wanted to give their daughter a joyous life\u2026 they didn\u2019t want her to be mournful and keep thinking about the end, they just wanted her to be happy as long as she was here\u2026. It\u2019s so, so inspiring.\"<ref name=\"telegraph3\" />\n\nLike Chopra and Akhtar, Wasim was too drawn to the towards the story of the film and revealed that she had immediately fell in love with the story.<ref name=\"filmingbegins\">{{cite news|url=http://www.asianage.com/entertainment/bollywood/080818/the-sky-is-pink-priyanka-farhan-and-zaira-begin-filming-for-shonali-boses-film.html|title=The Sky Is Pink: Priyanka, Farhan and Zaira begin filming for Shonali Bose's film|work=[[The Asian Age]]|date=8 August 2018|access-date=15 April 2020}}</ref> Of her character, Wasim said \"It is a character that touched my heart and I am honoured to be playing this role.\"<ref name=\"filmingbegins\"/> Saraf described his character Ishaan saying he is someone who becomes the pillar of the family during the tragedy. He revealed that portraying the character was delightful as he got to explore human emotions a lot more than he had before in his career.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/celebrities/story/rohit-saraf-it-was-always-a-dream-to-work-with-priyanka-chopra-1607218-2019-10-08 |title=Rohit Saraf: It was always a dream to work with Priyanka Chopra |last=Singh |first=Suhani |date=8 October 2019 |website=India Today |access-date=6 March 2020}}</ref> Unlike the rest of the cast, Saraf was not allowed to see the documented footage of the Chaudhary family as Bose thought he would not be able to take that well.<ref name=\"saraf\" /> To prepare for his character, Saraf had researched a lot about the Chaudhary family during the audition process. After his casting, he stopped his research and relied mostly on Bose's inputs on her advice and the collaborative efforts of the cast which he said enhanced his performance.<ref name=\"saraf\" />\n\nCostume designer Eka Lakhani designed the clothes for the cast.<ref name=\"cast&crew\"/> Since the film spans 25 years, the characters of Aditi and Niren's looks undergo several transformations as they age. These changes were mostly accomplished by make-up and hair styling.<ref name=\"transformation\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.outlookindia.com/website/story/entertainment-news-priyanka-chopra-jonas-and-farhan-akhtars-transformation-in-the-sky-is-pink/340216 |title=Priyanka Chopra Jonas And Farhan Akhtar\u2019s Transformation In \u2018The Sky Is Pink\u2019 |date=9 October 2019 |website=Outlook |access-date=6 March 2020}}</ref> Chopra's hair inform the age of her character; when her character is young the hair is longer and it gets shorter as she ages in the film, short hair at 50.<ref name=\"transformation\" /> Staying true to the real life, Aditi was given a glamorous and make-up heavy look as she had made an effort to look glamorous and throughout her 40s, with her philosophy being \"when life sucks, look like a million bucks\".<ref name=\"wion\" /> Chopra had suggested to put on some weight and grey colour to showcase character's aging in the film but Bose outright declined her request.<ref name=\"refinery\" /> Bose felt it would be a cliche move to show Aditi as dowdy in the later portions of the film and not true to the real life Aditi who is very glamorous and likes to dress up even in hard moments of life.<ref name=\"refinery\" /> Akhtar's Character, when younger sports curly hair while is groomed when his character matures and is given mustache in the later portions of the film.<ref name=\"transformation\" />\n\n=== Filming ===\n[[Principal photography]] of ''The Sky Is Pink'' began on 8 August 2018 in [[Mumbai]] with all of its cast members.<ref name=\"filmingbegins\"/> Kartik Vijay and Nick Cooke handled the cinematography while production design was done by Aradhana Seth.<ref name=\"cast&crew\"/> The second schedule of the film began on 13 October 2018 in [[London]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/priyanka-chopra-farhan-akhtar-zaira-wasim-begin-shooting-for-second-schedule-of-the-sky-is-pink-in-london-5373861.html|title=Priyanka Chopra, Farhan Akhtar, Zaira Wasim begin shooting for second schedule of The Sky Is Pink in London||work=Firstpost|date=13 October 2018|access-date=18 April 2020}}</ref> The London schedule consisted of six days which concluded on 19 October 2018.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.indiatvnews.com/entertainment/bollywood-priyanka-chopra-zaira-wasim-wrap-london-schedule-of-the-sky-is-pink-see-pictures-473795|title=Priyanka Chopra, Zaira Wasim wrap London schedule of The Sky Is Pink. See pictures|work=India TV|date=19 October 2018|access-date=18 April 2020}}</ref> The filming moved to [[Delhi]] as a part of the second schedule on 12 November 2018.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://m.economictimes.com/magazines/panache/amidst-her-wedding-prep-priyanka-chopra-is-in-new-delhi-shooting-for-the-sky-is-pink/articleshow/66586166.cms|title=Amidst her wedding prep, Priyanka Chopra is in New Delhi shooting for 'The Sky Is Pink'|work=The Economic Times|date=12 November 2018|access-date=18 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/priyanka-chopra-shares-photos-from-the-sky-is-pink-sets-5449581/|title=Priyanka Chopra gives a sneak-peek into Delhi schedule of The Sky is Pink|publisher=Press Trust of India|work=The Indian Express|date=16 November 2018|access-date=18 April 2020}}</ref> The scenes were filmed at several locations in Delhi including [[Chandani Chowk]] which Bose specifically chose to show the culture of the locality on film.<ref name=\"delhitrilogy\"/> Bose said \"Delhi has a lot of character and every locality means something. You can capture its beauty in the greenery here, the charm of [[Old Delhi|old Delhi]] \u2013 this mix is very interesting.\"<ref name=\"delhitrilogy\"/> While filming in the locality a \"sea of people\" gathered to watch Chopra and Akhtar who were filming their scenes on a terrace.<ref name=\"delhitrilogy\"/> The second schedule of the film was complete in the last week of November.<ref name=\"delhischedulewrap\">{{cite news|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/priyanka-chopra-nick-jonas-the-sky-is-pink-wrap-5463347/|title=Priyanka Chopra wraps The Sky Is Pink schedule, team organises farewell party for the bride-to-be|work=The Indian Express|date=25 November 2018|access-date=18 April 2020}}</ref> Chopra, who was getting married on 1 December 2018, filmed her scenes till four days before her wedding to [[Nick Jonas]]. The producer of the film, Siddharth Roy Kapur praised the actress for her commitment, saying \"Priyanka has been wonderful. She will be shooting with us right till the very eve of her nuptials, which I think shows a tremendous amount of professionalism.\"<ref name=\"delhischedulewrap\"/> The producers and Bose were accommodating and they created a separate \"wedding approvals room\" for the actress to approve her wedding preparation details to her team, between filming her scenes for the film.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.republicworld.com/entertainment-news/bollywood-news/the-sky-is-pink-priyanka-was-shooting-until-4-days-before-her-wedding.html|title=The Sky Is Pink: Priyanka Was Shooting Until 4 Days Before Her Wedding|last=Raut|first=Mamta|work=Republic World|date=2 October 2019|access-date=18 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.dnaindia.com/bollywood/report-when-i-met-shonali-nick-jonas-was-not-in-picture-priyanka-chopra-on-preparing-for-wedding-between-the-sky-is-pink-2792117|title='When I met Shonali, Nick Jonas was not in picture': Priyanka Chopra on preparing for wedding between 'The Sky Is Pink'|work=Daily News and Analysis|date=24 September 2019|access-date=18 April 2020}}</ref> In February 2019, Bose announced that the final schedule would of the film will be filmed in March.<ref name=\"finalschedule\">{{cite news|url=https://www.dnaindia.com/bollywood/report-priyanka-chopra-farhan-akhtar-to-shoot-final-schedule-of-the-sky-is-pink-in-march-2718066|title=Priyanka Chopra, Farhan Akhtar to shoot final schedule of \u2018The Sky Is Pink\u2019 in March|work=Daily News and Analysis|date=9 February 2019|access-date=18 April 2020}}</ref> The final schedule of the film began in the [[Andaman Islands]] on 1 March 2019 and continued till 9 March 2019 when the filming wrapped.<ref name=\"finalschedule\"/><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/the-sky-is-pink-priyanka-chopra-farhan-akhtar-zaira-wasim-wrap-up-shoot-in-andaman-nicobar-islands-6236601.html|title=The Sky Is Pink: Priyanka Chopra, Farhan Akhtar, Zaira Wasim wrap up shoot in Andaman & Nicobar Islands|work=Firstpost|date=11 March 2019|access-date=18 April 2020}}</ref> Although the filming was completed, Bose revealed that a song was still left to be shot.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/hindi/2019/mar/14/shooting-complete-for-priyanka-chopras-the-sky-is-pink-1950745.html|title=Shooting complete for Priyanka Chopra\u2019s 'The Sky Is Pink'|work=The New Indian Express|date=14 March 2019|access-date=18 April 2020}}</ref> The filming of the song started on 6 June 2019 in Mumbai and was shot over five days.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/bollywood/story/priyanka-chopra-to-shoot-for-a-song-for-the-sky-is-pink-in-mumbai-next-month-1521527-2019-05-10|title=Priyanka Chopra to shoot for a song for The Sky Is Pink in Mumbai next month|work=India Today|date=10 May 2019|access-date=18 April 2020}}</ref> The said song \"Pink Gulaabi Sky\" was supposed to feature in the film as the part of the plot but Bose felt it did not go with the flow of the story. It was cut from the final film and was ultimately used as a promotional song.<ref name=\"promotionalsong\">{{cite news|url=https://www.filmfare.com/news/bollywood/heres-why-the-song-pink-gulaabi-sky-was-edited-out-of-the-sky-is-pink-36651.html|title=Here\u2019s why the song Pink Gulaabi Sky was edited out of The Sky is Pink|work=Filmfare|date=9 October 2019|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref> Bose complimented the producers for agreeing with her decision to cut the song, saying \"When we shot the song, I thought that it was a fun number and looked lovely. Later, I was surprised to see that the makers are in sync with my view. Considering the fact that the team had spent a lot of money to shoot the song, it requires guts to take a decision like this\".<ref name=\"promotionalsong\"/> The film was shot over ten months.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/priyanka-chopra-attends-the-sky-is-pink-wrap-up-party-with-zaira-wasim-writes-note-on-instagram-6796891.html|title=Priyanka Chopra attends The Sky is Pink wrap up party with Zaira Wasim, writes note on Instagram|publisher=Asian News International|work=Firstpost|date=12 June 2019|access-date=18 April 2020}}</ref> The film was edited by Manas Mittal.<ref name=\"cast&crew\"/>\n\n== Soundtrack ==\n{{Infobox album\n| name         = The Sky Is Pink\n| type         = soundtrack\n| artist       = [[Pritam]]\n| cover        = \n| border       = yes\n| alt          = \n| released     = 4 October 2019\n| recorded     = \n| venue        = \n| studio       = \n| genre        = [[Feature film soundtrack]]\n| length       = 21:08\n| language     = [[Hindi language|Hindi]]\n| label        = [[Zee Music Company]]\n| producer     = \n| prev_title   = [[Chhichhore]]\n| prev_year    = 2019\n| year         = 2019\n| next_title   = [[Love Aaj Kal (2020 film)|Love Aaj Kal]]\n| next_year    = 2020\n}}\n\nThe film's music is composed by [[Pritam]] while lyrics are written by [[Gulzar]].<ref name=\"th\" /> It contains four original songs and a reprisal, with vocals provided by singers such as [[Arijit Singh]], [[Antara Mitra]], [[Arjun Kanungo]], [[Lisa Mishra]], Shashwat Singh, [[Jonita Gandhi]] and Sreerama Chandra.<ref name=\"itunes\" /> The soundtrack was released on 4 October 2019 by [[Zee Music Company]].<ref name=\"itunes\" /> Though not a part of the main soundtrack, the film features an end credit song titled \"For Aisha\" composed by Aisha Chaudhary's brother Ishaan under his band name \"Memba\". The song is sung by the [[Nooran Sisters]], Naomi Wild and Evan Giia.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://open.spotify.com/album/5He2R0dw92kc4N9tg4v7zc|title=For Aisha (Featured in \"The Sky Is Pink\")|work=[[Spotify]]|access-date=18 April 2020}}</ref> [[Anvita Dutt]] wrote the song with Memba, Wild and Giia.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.jiosaavn.com/lyrics/for-aisha-featured-in-the-sky-is-pink-lyrics/HyNabjVcX3A|title=For Aisha (Featured in \"The Sky Is Pink\") Lyrics|work=[[JioSaavn]]|access-date=18 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n{{Track listing\n| headline       = Track listing<ref name=\"itunes\">{{Cite web |url=https://music.apple.com/in/album/the-sky-is-pink-original-motion-picture-soundtrack/1482434710 |title=The Sky Is Pink (Original Motion Picture Soundtrack) |website=[[iTunes]] |access-date=4 March 2020}}</ref>\n| total_length   = 21:28\n| extra_column   = Singer(s)\n| title1         = Dil Hi Toh Hai\n| extra1         = [[Arijit Singh]], [[Antara Mitra]]\n| music1         = [[Pritam]]\n| lyrics1        = Gulzar\n| length1        = 4:40\n| title2         = Nadaaniyaan\n| extra2         = [[Arjun Kanungo]], Lisa Mishra\n| music2         = Pritam\n| lyrics2        = Gulzar\n| length2        = 4:18\n| title3         = Zindagi\n| extra3         = Arijit Singh\n| music3         = Pritam\n| lyrics3        = Gulzar\n| length3        = 4:09\n| title4         = Pink Gulaabi Sky\n| extra4         = Shashwat Singh, [[Jonita Gandhi]]\n| music4         = Pritam\n| lyrics4        = Gulzar\n| length4        = 3:20\n| title5         = Dil Hi Toh Hai\n| note5          = Reprise\n| extra5         = Sreerama Chandra, Antara Mitra\n| music5         = Pritam\n| lyrics5        = Gulzar\n| length5        = 4:41\n}}\n\n== Marketing and release ==\nThe film was one of the most anticipated Indian films of 2019.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.filmfare.com/features/sky-is-pink-5-reasons-why-you-must-watch-the-priyanka-chopra-and-farhan-akhtar-starrer-36720.html|title=The Sky Is Pink: 5 reasons why you must watch the Priyanka Chopra and Farhan Akhtar starrer|last=Nihalani|first=Akash|work=Filmfare|date=11 October 2019|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"firstlook\">{{cite news|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/first-look-of-priyanka-chopra-starrer-the-sky-is-pink-revealed-zaira-wasim-5846742/|title=The first look of Priyanka Chopra starrer The Sky is Pink revealed|work=The Indian Express|date=24 July 2019|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref> The first look of the film was was released on 23 July 2019.<ref name=\"firstlook\"/> Several exclusive stills from the films were released on 8 September 2019.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/the-sky-is-pink-priyanka-chopra-farhan-akhtar-share-new-stills-ahead-of-world-premiere-at-tiff-2019-7304781.html|title=The Sky is Pink: Priyanka Chopra, Farhan Akhtar share new stills ahead of world premiere at TIFF 2019|work=Firstpost|date=8 September 2019|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref> The first poster was released on 9 September 2019 and Chopra [[tweeted]] that the official trailer would be released the next day.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/the-sky-is-pink-priyanka-chopra-shares-stunning-first-poster-for-her-comeback-hindi-film-trailer-out-on-tuesday/story-LPsIHPGI6pS6R0bbxU0E9M.html|title=The Sky Is Pink: Priyanka Chopra shares stunning first poster for her comeback Hindi film, trailer out on Tuesday|work=Hindustan Times|date=|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref> [[Firstpost]] commented that the \"aesthetically-pleasing poster\" looked \"fun-filled and refreshing.\"<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/the-sky-is-pink-priyanka-chopra-shares-films-first-poster-ahead-of-trailer-release-on-10-september-7311481.html|title=The Sky is Pink: Priyanka Chopra shares film's first poster ahead of trailer release on 10 September|work=Firstpost|date=9 September 2019|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref> The trailer of the film was released on 10 September 2019.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/the-sky-is-pink-trailer-farhan-akhtar-priyanka-chopra-fight-for-zaira-wasims-survival-in-shonali-bose-film-7314701.html|title=The Sky Is Pink trailer: Farhan Akhtar, Priyanka Chopra fight for Zaira Wasim's survival in Shonali Bose film|work=Firstpost|date=10 September 2019|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref> The ''[[Huffington Post]]'' felt that the film looked like a \"winner\" while ''[[The New Indian Express]]'' called the trailer \"heart warming\", noting it \"promises to be a love story high on emotional quotient with an equal amount of humour.\"<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.in/entry/the-sky-is-pink-trailer-priyanka-chopra_in_5d772427e4b075210231c55b|title=The Sky Is Pink Trailer: Priyanka Chopra, Farhan Akhtar's Film Looks Like A Winner|last=Pathak|first=Ankur|work=Huffington Post|date=10 September 2019|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/hindi/2019/sep/10/watch--farhan-priyanka-warming-our-hearts-in-the-sky-is-pink-trailer-2031627.html|title=Watch: Farhan, Priyanka warming our hearts in 'The Sky is Pink' trailer|work=The New Indian Express|date=10 September 2019|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn July 2019, media reported that ''The Sky Is Pink'' was selected to premiere at the [[44th Toronto International Film Festival]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/priyanka-chopras-the-sky-is-pink-set-for-world-premiere-at-toronto-international-film-festival-2019/articleshow/70354747.cms |title=Priyanka Chopra's 'The Sky is Pink' set for world premiere at Toronto International Film Festival 2019 |publisher=Press Trust of India |work=Times of India |date=24 July 2019 |access-date=24 July 2019}}</ref> The only Asian film to be selected for \"Gala Presentation\", ''The Sky Is Pink'' premiered at the festival at the [[Roy Thomson Hall]] on 13 September 2019 and received a 15 minute long standing ovation.<ref name=\"tiffpremiere\">{{cite news|url=https://www.outlookindia.com/website/story/entertainment-news-the-sky-is-pink-gets-standing-ovation-at-its-world-premiere-at-tiff-2019/338836|title=\u2018The Sky Is Pink\u2019 Gets Standing Ovation At Its World Premiere At TIFF 2019|last=Roy|first=Lachmi Deb|work=Outlook|date=17 September 2019|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref> The premiere sold-out and was attended by 2000 people. This was followed by an another sold-out screening at the [[Elgin Theatre (Ottawa)|Elgin Theatre]].<ref name=\"tiffpremiere\"/> The Chaudhary family were in the attendance at the premiere along with the cast, director and the producers.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ndtv.com/entertainment/the-sky-is-pink-at-toronto-film-festival-priyanka-chopra-farhan-akhtar-shibani-dandekar-attend-world-2100748|title=The Sky Is Pink At Toronto Film Festival: Priyanka Chopra, Farhan Akhtar-Shibani Dandekar Attend World Premiere|last=Goyal|first=Divya|work=NDTV|date=14 September 2019|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref> The film also premiered at the [[24th Busan International Film Festival]] and the [[BFI London Film Festival|2019 BFI London Film Festival]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/bollywood/sky-pink-will-premiered-london-film-festival-busan-film-festival/|title=The Sky Is Pink will be premiered in the London Film Festival and Busan Film Festival|work=Bollywood Hungama|date=5 September 2019|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe promotions of the film started in the last week of September.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.news18.com/news/lifestyle/priyanka-chopra-takes-fans-behind-the-scenes-of-the-sky-is-pink-promotions-2323777.html|title=Priyanka Chopra Takes Fans Behind The Scenes of The Sky is Pink Promotions|last=Kashyap|first=Antara|work=|date=26 September 2019|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref> Chopra, Akhtar, Saraf and Bose took part in the promotions of the film.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.mid-day.com/photos/priyanka-chopra-farhan-akhtar-shonali-bose-rohit-saraf-promote-the-sky-is-pink/62863|title=Priyanka Chopra, Farhan Akhtar, Shonali Bose, Rohit Saraf promote The Sky Is Pink|work=[[Mid Day]]|date=29 September 2019|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref> On the other hand, Wasim, who had retired from acting due to her religious beliefs by the time of marketing, did not take part in the film's promotions.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/bollywood/story/after-quitting-films-zaira-wasim-opts-out-of-the-sky-is-pink-promotions-1560141-2019-07-02|title=Zaira Wasim opts out of The Sky Is Pink promotions after exiting films|work=India Today|date=2 July 2019|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/the-sky-is-pink-priyanka-chopra-shares-her-thoughts-on-zaira-wasims-decision-to-quit-bollywood/articleshow/71287080.cms|title='The Sky Is Pink': Priyanka Chopra shares her thoughts on Zaira Wasim\u2019s decision to quit Bollywood|work=The Times of India|date=25 September 2019|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref> After promoting the film in India, Chopra promoted the film in the United States by appearing on American prime time talk show ''[[The Tonight Show Starring Jimmy Fallon]]'' and the day time talk show [[The View (talk show)|The View]].<ref name=\"talkshow\">{{cite news|url=https://www.business-standard.com/article/news-ani/priyanka-chopra-to-promote-the-sky-is-pink-on-the-jimmy-fallon-talk-show-119101100239_1.html|title=Priyanka Chopra to promote 'The Sky is Pink' on the Jimmy Fallon talk show|publisher=[[Asian News International]]|work=[[Business Standard]]|date=11 October 2019|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.republicworld.com/entertainment-news/bollywood-news/the-sky-is-pink-priyanka-chopra-promotes-her-upcoming-film-in-usa.html|title=The Sky Is Pink: Priyanka Chopra Promotes Her Upcoming Film In The USA|last=Nair|first=Tarun|work=Republic World|date=11 October 2019|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref> ''The Sky Is Pink'' became the first Indian film to be promoted on American television.<ref name=\"talkshow\"/> The film was released on 11 October 2019. It received a [[Limited release|limited release]] in the United States.<ref name=\"rt\">{{cite news|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/the_sky_is_pink|title=The Sky Is Pink (2019)|work=Rotten Tomatoes|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n[[Netflix]] brought the worldwide streaming rights of the film, a first for an Indian film.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.outlookindia.com/website/story/entertainment-news-costs-already-covered-for-priyanka-chopra-jonas-and-farhan-akhtars-the-sky-is-pink/340286|title=Costs Already Covered For Priyanka Chopra Jonas And Farhan Akhtar\u2019s \u2018The Sky Is Pink\u2019|last=Roy|first=Lachmi Deb|work=Outlook|date=10 October 2019|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref> It became available on the platform on 11 December 2019.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.thequint.com/entertainment/hot-on-web/new-on-netflix-december-2019-the-sky-is-pink-you-season-2|title=New on Netflix This December:The Sky is Pink, Love Happens, You S2|work=[[The Quint]]|date=29 November 2019|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref> The film is also available on [[Apple TV Plus]].<ref name=\"rt\"/>\n\n== Reception ==\n=== Critical response ===\nThe film received generally positive reviews.<ref name=\"ibtimes.co.in\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.ibtimes.co.in/sky-pink-movie-review-rating-critics-cant-stop-praising-priyanka-chopra-farhan-akhtar-starrer-806940 |title=Sky Is Pink movie review and rating: Critics can't stop praising Priyanka Chopra-Farhan Akhtar starrer |last=Sarkar |first=Suparno |date=10 October 2019 |website=International Business Times, India Edition}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.ndtv.com/entertainment/the-sky-is-pink-box-office-collection-day-1-priyanka-chopra-and-farhan-akhtars-film-gets-a-slow-star-2115790 |title=The Sky Is Pink Box Office Collection Day 1: Priyanka Chopra And Farhan Akhtar's Film Gets A Slow Start |website=NDTV.com}}</ref> On the [[review aggregator]] website [[Rotten Tomatoes]], the film holds a rating of 71% based on 17 reviews, with an [[Weighted arithmetic mean|average rating]] of 6/10.<ref name=\"rotten:cr0\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/the_sky_is_pink |title=THE SKY IS PINK |website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]] |publisher=[[Fandango (company)|Fandango Media]] |access-date=17 October 2019}}</ref>\n\nDevesh Sharma of ''[[Filmfare]]'' rated the film four stars out of five, lauding the film's ability to make viewers laugh despite its tragic undertone. He concluded, writing \"this bitter-sweet film will make you laugh, will make you cry and will surely make you ruminate on the glorious uncertainty of life.\"<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.filmfare.com/reviews/bollywood-movies/movie-review-the-sky-is-pink-36641.html |title=Movie Review: The Sky Is Pink |website=filmfare.com}}</ref> Writing for ''[[Mid Day]]'', film critic [[Mayank Shekhar]] rated the film with three and half stars out of five, praising Bose for telling an \"astonishingly dark personal story with reasonable hope\" that never felt exploitative or manipulative. He complemented the \"smart\" screenplay which he felt was structured to dive viewers \"deeper and deeper\" into the characters and circumstances on screen.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.mid-day.com/articles/the-sky-is-pink-movie-review-cry-bucket-loads-cant-help/21877166 |title=The Sky is Pink Movie Review: Cry bucket-loads; can't help |date=10 October 2019 |website=mid-day}}</ref> Priyanka Sinha Jha of ''[[CNN-News18]]'', praising Chopra Jonas, Akhtar and Wasim for their performances, and wrote, \"The real hero in this instance, however, would have to be the zany uplifting story and to that effect, with ''The Sky is Pink'', Bose delivers a fitting salutation to life.\"<ref>{{Cite news |last=Sinha Jha |first=Priyanka |url=https://www.news18.com/news/movies/the-sky-is-pink-movie-review-priyanka-chopra-farhan-akhtar-film-is-all-shades-of-life-2340281.html |title=The Sky Is Pink Movie Review: Priyanka Chopra-Farhan Akhtar Film is All Shades of Life |date=10 October 2019 |work=CNN-News18 |access-date=10 October 2019}}</ref> Writing for ''[[NDTV]]'' [[Saibal Chatterjee]], rated the film with three and half stars out of five, and praised Bose for her direction and writing.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.ndtv.com/entertainment/the-sky-is-pink-movie-review-priyanka-chopra-lends-this-unmissable-film-a-starry-edge-3-5-stars-out-2114432 |title=The Sky Is Pink Movie Review: Priyanka Chopra Lends This Unmissable Film A Starry Edge |last=Chatterjee |first=Saibal |date=10 October 2019 |website=NDTV |access-date=10 October 2019}}</ref> Sreeparna Sengupta of ''[[The Times of India]]'' gave the film three and half stars out of five, praising the performances of Chopra Jonas, Akhtar and Wasim, she noted that the film scored high on the emotional quotient. She opined that though the film was lengthy and screenplay needed more focus, 'the emotional arc' and the 'stellar performances' kept the interest going. Concluding, she wrote, \"''The Sky is Pink'' is definitely a stirring watch.\"<ref>{{Cite news |last=Sengupta |first=Sreeparna |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/movie-reviews/the-sky-is-pink/movie-review/71509561.cms |title=The Sky Is Pink Movie Review: An emotional, stirring watch |date=10 October 2019 |work=The Times of India |access-date=10 October 2019}}</ref> Teo Bugbee of ''[[The New York Times]]'' lauded Bose for achieving a balanced tone in the film, writing \"The writer and director Shonali Bose bounces from tone to tone, livening the somber subject matter with bright hues, quippy dialogue and an ever-jubilant score.\"<ref name=\"nytimes.com\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/10/10/movies/the-sky-is-pink-review.html |title=\u2018The Sky Is Pink\u2019 Review: A Story Told From the Grave |last=Bugbee |first=Teo |date=10 October 2019 |via=NYTimes.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.indiewire.com/2019/10/the-sky-is-pink-review-1202178086/ |title=\u2018The Sky Is Pink\u2019 Review: An Unusual Grief Drama Obsessed With the Possibility of Life After Death |last=Erbland |first=Kate |last2=Erbland |first2=Kate |date=9 October 2019}}</ref>\n\n[[Rajeev Masand]] criticised the film's \"blatant manipulation\" but added that \"there are moments that left me with a heavy heart\".<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.rajeevmasand.com/reviews/our-films/pain-relief-2/ |title=Pain relief |last=Masand |first=Rajeev |date=11 October 2019 |website=RajeevMasand.com}}</ref> Dennis Harvey of ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'' too disliked the film and wrote that the \"somewhat bland polish on all levels doesn\u2019t much assist the raw pain that should be at this story\u2019s center\".<ref>{{Cite news |last=Harvey |first=Dennis |url=https://variety.com/2019/film/reviews/the-sky-is-pink-review-1203336082/ |title=Toronto Film Review: \u2018The Sky is Pink\u2019 |date=18 September 2019 |work=Variety}}</ref> Vinayak Chakraborty of ''[[Outlook (Indian magazine)|Outlook]]'' rated the film with three stars out of five, criticizing the \"flashback-driven storyline\" and its runtime which he felt was too long at nearly two and half hours. However, he opined that the film still works with all its flaws.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.outlookindia.com/newsscroll/the-sky-is-pink-sensitive-but-soppy-ians-review-rating-/1637218 |title=''The Sky Is Pink'': Sensitive but Soppy (IANS Review; Rating: ***) |website=[[Outlook (Indian magazine)|Outlook]]}}</ref> [[Anupama Chopra]] of ''[[Film Companion]]'' found the film to be \"sensitive\" but highly \"sanitized\". She wrote \"The Sky is Pink is sincere and heartfelt but it never gets raw or messy.\"<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.filmcompanion.in/the-sky-is-pink-movie-review-by-anupama-chopra-farhan-akhtar-priyanka-chopra-zaira-wasim |title=The Sky Is Pink Review By Anupama Chopra: A Sincere Yet Sanitised Look At Extreme Anguish |date=11 October 2019}}</ref> Shubhra Gupta of ''[[The Indian Express]]'' rated the film with two stars out of five. According to her, the film only occasionally worked. She opined the film felt \"both constructed and sentimental\", writing \"With the material at hand, you expect a legitimate heart-breaker but this one left me mostly unmoved.\"<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/movie-review/the-sky-is-pink-movie-review-rating-priyanka-chopra-6061269/ |title=The Sky Is Pink movie review: The colour barely seeps into the film |date=11 October 2019}}</ref>\n\n=== Box office ===\n''The Sky Is Pink'' collected {{INR}}2.50 crore on the opening day, {{INR}}4.00 crore on the second day, and {{INR}}4.20 on the third day, taking its opening weekend collection to {{INR}}10.70 crore in India. Film earned {{INR}}15.15 crore in its first week.\n\n{{As of|2019|10|24}}, with a gross of {{INR}}23.85 crore in India and {{INR}}10.56 crore overseas, the film has a worldwide gross collection of {{INR}}34.41 crore. It did not perform well at the box office.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Tuteja, Joginder |url=https://www.moneycontrol.com/news/trends/entertainment/priyanka-chopra-and-farhan-akhars-the-sky-is-pink-a-commercial-flop-that-deserves-better-4549841.html |title=Priyanka Chopra and Farhan Akhar\u2019s The Sky Is Pink \u2013 A commercial flop that deserves better |date=19 October 2019 |work=Money Control |access-date=19 October 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Accolades ==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\"\n|-\n!scope=\"col\"| Award\n\n!scope=\"col\"| Category\n!scope=\"col\"| Recipient(s) and nominee(s)\n!scope=\"col\"| Result\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\"| {{Abbr|Ref.|Reference(s)}}\n